Parameter name: New Radio PLMN Set for Adjacent Neighboring NSA NR Cell instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio PLMN Set for Adjacent Neighboring NSA NR Cell (ADJ_NRPLMNSET_NSA) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRADJNRCELL instance.    The ADJ_NRPLMNSET_NSA instance and its parent NRADJNRCELL instance can be created/updated by the gNB when Intra-NR ANR is activated (NRBTS.actNsaUeBasedAnrNr or NRBTS.actNsaUeBasedInterFreqAnrNr or NRBTS.actSaUeBasedAnrNr or NRBTS.actSaUeBasedInterFreqAnrNr is equal to TRUE). It may be deleted when NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval is equal to TRUE and the other criteria for autonomous removal of unused NR neighbor relations are met.
This parameter indicates whether or not the neighbor cell is reserved for operator use per PLMN.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: List of NRPLMN distinguished names of adjacent neighbor NSA New Radio cell
Description: This parameter defines the distinguished name of the NRPLMN instance(s) defining each operator for NR RAN Sharing assigned to the adjacent neighboring NSA cell. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1

Parameter name: New Radio PLMN Set for Adjacent Neighboring SA NR Cell instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio PLMN Set for Adjacent Neighboring SA NR Cell (ADJ_NRPLMNSET_SA) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRADJNRCELL instance.    A ADJ_NRPLMNSET_SA instance and its parent NRADJNRCELL instance can be created/updated by the gNB when Intra-NR ANR is activated (NRBTS.actNsaUeBasedAnrNr or NRBTS.actNsaUeBasedInterFreqAnrNr or NRBTS.actSaUeBasedAnrNr or NRBTS.actSaUeBasedInterFreqAnrNr is equal to TRUE). It may be deleted when NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval is equal to TRUE and the other criteria for autonomous removal of unused NR neighbor relations are met.
This parameter indicates whether or not the neighbor cell is reserved for operator use per PLMN.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: 5G extended tracking area code of adjacent neighbor New Radio cell
Description: This parameter identifies the NR extended Tracking Area Code (TAC) for an adjacent neighbor New Radio cell. For New Radio cells, TAC is extended from 2 octets to 3 octets.

Parameter name: List of NRPLMN distinguished names of adjacent neighbor SA New Radio cell
Description: This parameter defines the distinguished name of the NRPLMN instance(s) defining each operator for NR RAN Sharing assigned to the adjacent neighboring SA cell. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1
This parameter uniquely identifies the Bandwidth Part Profile (BWP_PROFILE) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance
This parameter indicates the type of the bandwidth part profile.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates the position and the size of the downlink BWP.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.

Parameter name: Downlink Common Resource Block size of the BWP
Description: This parameter indicates the number of Common Resource Block of the downlink BWP within the cell.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.

Parameter name: Downlink Common Resource Block start index of the BWP
Description: This parameter indicates the index of the first Common Resource Block of the downlink BWP within the cell.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.
This parameter indicates the position and the size of the uplink BWP.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.

Parameter name: Uplink Common Resource Block size of the BWP
Description: This parameter indicates the number of Common Resource Block of the uplink BWP within the cell.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.

Parameter name: Uplink Common Resource Block start index of the BWP
Description: This parameter indicates the index of the first Common Resource Block of the uplink BWP within the cell.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.

This parameter uniquely identifies the LTE eNB (LTEENB) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.    A LTEENB instance can be created/modified by the gNB during X2 link establishment or update. It may be deleted at the expiry of NRBTS.x2LinkReestabTmr, provided that this LTEENB instance is not locked (LTEENB.x2LinkLock) and that there is no SCTP association.
This parameter is part of the Global eNodeB-ID.  Global eNodeB-ID is used to identify eNBs globally which is composed of the concatenation of MCC, MNC and the eNodeBId (this parameter).
PLMN of the Global eNB Id received from LTE eNB in X2 SETUP message

Parameter name: MCC of PLMN ID in Global eNB ID
Description: Mobile Country Code of PLMN ID included in Global eNB ID received from LTE eNB in X2 SETUP message. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC of PLMN ID in Global eNB ID
Description: Mobile Network Code of PLMN ID included in Global eNB ID received from LTE eNB in X2 SETUP message. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC length of PLMN ID in Global eNB ID
Description: Length of Mobile Network Code of PLMN identity

This parameter holds the transport network IPv4/v6 address of the LTE eNB for X2 interface.  Both IP address formats can be used.  Format: IPv4 address parameter in dotted decimals or IPv6 address parameter according to RFC 4291.
This parameter indicates the local CU IPv4/v6 address
This parameter allows the customer to lock the X2-C link from a specific LTE eNB.
The parameter provides information whether the X2 link is successfully established.

Parameter name: New Radio Adjacent E-UTRAN Cell instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Adjacent E-UTRAN Cell (NRADJECELL) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.    A NRADJECELL instance can be created/updated by the gNB when Inter-RAT ANR is activated (NRBTS.actSaUeBasedAnrEutra). It may be deleted when NRANR.actAutoEutraNbRemoval is equal to TRUE and the other criteria in autonomous removal procedure are met.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates the Macro eNB identifier within the Global eNB Id of an adjacent eNB.

Parameter name: EPS tracking area code of adjacent E-UTRAN cell
Description: This parameter indicates the EPS Tracking Area Code of the adjacent E-UTRAN cell
This parameter indicates the additional frequency band indicators that an E-UTRAN cell belongs to.

Parameter name: EARFCN value of adjacent E-UTRAN cell
Description: This parameter indicates the carrier frequency used in an E-UTRAN cell for DL direction.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN ID of adjacent E-UTRAN cell in ECGI
Description: This parameter indicates the primary PLMN identity which is part of the E-UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (ECGI) of the adjacent E-UTRAN cell.

Parameter name: MCC of primary PLMN ID in adjacent E-UTRAN cell in ECGI
Description: This parameter indicates the Mobile Country Code of the primary PLMN ID included in ECGI of the adjacent E-UTRAN cell. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC of primary PLMN ID in adjacent E-UTRAN cell in ECGI
Description: This parameter indicates the Mobile Network Code of the primary PLMN ID included in ECGI of the adjacent E-UTRAN cell. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC length of primary PLMN in adjacent E-UTRAN cell in ECGI
Description: This parameter indicates the length of MNC in the primary PLMN identity.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN identity of adjacent eNB
Description: This parameter indicates the primary PLMN identity of the adjacent eNB.  The leftmost 20 bits of the eUtranCellIdentifier correspond to the value of the eNB ID. The eNB Id and primary PLMN form the globally unique eNB ID.

Parameter name: MCC of primary PLMN ID in adjacent eNB
Description: This parameter indicates the Mobile Country Code of the primary PLMN ID of adjacent eNB. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC of primary PLMN ID in adjacent eNB
Description: This parameter indicates the Mobile Network Code of the primary PLMN ID of the adjacent eNB. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC length of primary PLMN in adjacent eNB
Description: This parameter indicates the Length of MNC in the primary PLMN identity.

Parameter name: Data forwarding method for IRAT to LTE
Description: This parameter provides the data forwarding method to be used during IRAT handover to LTE.
This parameter indicates the E-UTRAN local cell resource identifier. The lcrId is unique within an eNB.

Parameter name: Physical cell ID of cell served by adjacent eNB
Description: This parameter indicates the physical cell ID of the adjacent E-UTRAN cell

Parameter name: Secondary PLMN ID list of adjacent E-UTRAN cell
Description: This parameter indicates the secondary PLMN list of the adjacent E-UTRAN cell.

Parameter name: MCC of secondary PLMN ID in adjacent E-UTRAN cell
Description: This parameter indicates the Mobile Country Code of the secondary PLMN ID of the adjacent E-UTRAN cell. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC of secondary PLMN ID in adjacent E-UTRAN cell
Description: This parameter indicates the Mobile Network Code of the secondary PLMN ID of the adjacent E-UTRAN cell. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC length of secondary PLMN in adjacent E-UTRAN cell
Description: This parameter indicates the length of MNC in the secondary PLMN identity.

Parameter name: New Radio Adjacent gNodeB instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Adjacent gNodeB (NRADJGNB) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.    A NRADJGNB instance can be created by the gNB during XN setup. It may be deleted in the following cases:  - upon expiry of the NRBTS.xnLinkReestabTmr timer, when an SCTP association is no longer available and NRADJGNB.gNodeBIdCtrl is equal to 'gnbControlled' and the NRADJGNB instance is not locked by the operator (NRADJGNB.administrativeState); or  - when autonomous removal of unused NR neighbor cells is activated (NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval is equal to TRUE) and the other criteria in autonomous removal procedure are met.

This parameter indicates the gNB Routing Id of the adjacent gNB. It is encoded in the gNB part of the I-RNTI. It is used to identify the adjacent gNB to which the XNAP: Retrieve UE Context Request is sent.
This parameter defines the administrative state of the NR Adjacent gNodeB.  It sets permission to use or prohibition against using the resource, imposed through the management services.
This parameter indicates the AMF region information of the gNB
The entire PLMN is divided into AMF regions, each of which is uniquely identified by an AMF region ID.

Parameter name: MCC of PLMN ID in AMF region information
Description: This parameter indicates the MCC part of the AMF's PLMN ID

Parameter name: MNC of PLMN ID in AMF region information
Description: This parameter indicates the MNC part of the AMF's PLMN ID

Parameter name: MNC length of PLMN ID in AMF region information
Description: This parameter indicates the MNC length of the AMF's PLMN ID

This parameter holds the C-Plane IPSec transport IPv4 or IPv6 address of the adjacent gNB based on information provided by ANR procedures.  Both IP address formats can be used.  Format: IPv4 address parameter in dotted decimals or IPv6 address parameter according to RFC 4291.    Note: This parameter is updated by the system automatically. If the parameter is modified by operator, it may affect the ANR functionality.

This parameter indicates if the NRADJGNB.gNodeBId parameter is controlled by the OAM or the remote gNB.
This parameter indicates the PLMN of the Global gNB Id received from gNB in Xn SETUP message

Parameter name: MCC of PLMN ID in Global gNB ID
Description: This parameter indicates the Mobile Country Code of PLMN ID included in Global eNB ID received from gNB in Xn SETUP message. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC of PLMN ID in Global gNB ID
Description: This parameter indicates the Mobile Network Code of PLMN ID included in Global eNB ID received from LTE eNB in Xn SETUP message. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Description: This parameter indicates the length of Mobile Network Code of PLMN identity
Pointer to the adjacency target NRBTS cell or external NRBTS cell (EXNRCE). Distinguished Name of the corresponding object. Parameter used and visible only in NetAct Advanced Configurator.

Parameter name: User Plane IP addresses of adjacent gNB
Description: This parameter indicates the list of Xn User Plane IP addresses of the adjacent gNB.
This parameter indicates the IPv4 address of the gNB Xn User Plane.  IPv4 address format: Dot-decimal notation (x.x.x.x).  Example: 10.10.10.10.

This parameter indicates the IPv6 address of the gNB Xn User Plane.  IPv6 address format compliant with RFC 4291 (long format recommended): x:x:x:x:x:x:x:x.  Example: ABCD:EF01:2345:6789:ABCD:EF01:2345:6789.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the New Radio PLMN instance representing the gNB Xn User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1

Parameter name: Weight factor for selecting SCells from an adjacent gNB
Description: This parameter indicates the weight factor applied to the cells of the adjacent gNB for inter-gNB CA secondary cell selection.  The higher the parameter value, the higher is the probability to select cell(s) from this adjacent gNB as secondary cell(s) for inter-gNB CA.  The parameter applies to all candidate SCells of this adjacent gNB on top of their cell specific weight factor NRCELL.weightForSCellSelection.  Note 1: adjacent gNB hosts only SCells for a UE context in inter-gNB CA and is named ext-gNB.  Note 2: if this parameter is not configured, the default value 1 is used by the system.
This parameter indicates the Xn Link (XNLINK) instance associated with the gNB Adjacent gNodeB (NRADJGNB) instance.

Parameter name: Second Xn link reference for adjacent gNB
Description: This parameter indicates the second Xn Link (XNLINK) instance associated with the Adjacent gNodeB (NRADJGNB) instance when the Adjacent gNodeB is a Cloud gNodeB with geo-redundancy enabled.    This parameter cannot be modified by the operator without locking the NRADJGNB object.  This parameter cannot be modified by the operator if XNLINK.xnLinkStatus is equal to 1 (corresponding to available)

Parameter name: New Radio Adjacent New Radio Cell instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Adjacent New Radio Cell (NRADJNRCELL) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.    A NRADJNRCELL instance and its child ADJ_NRPLMNSET_SA and ADJ_NRPLMNSET_NSA instances can be created/updated by the gNB when Intra-NR ANR is activated (NRBTS.actNsaUeBasedAnrNr or NRBTS.actNsaUeBasedInterFreqAnrNr or NRBTS.actSaUeBasedAnrNr or NRBTS.actSaUeBasedInterFreqAnrNr is equal to TRUE). It may be deleted when NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval is equal to TRUE and the other criteria for autonomous removal of unused NR neighbor relations are met.

This parameter indicates if a given adjacent neighbour cell supports access  - to NSA users only or  - to SA users only or  - to NR-DC-SN users only or  - to SA and NSA users or  - to NSA and NR-DC-SN users
This parameter indicates whether or not the neighbor cell is reserved for operator use per PLMN.

This parameter defines the downlink bandwidth for the gNB transmission in an adjacent cell.  This parameter is relevant only for adjacent cells in band 66 with asymmetric bandwidth; this allows the gNB to check the corresponding NR BW capabilities of the UE before HO in that case.

This parameter defines the uplink bandwidth for the gNB transmission in an adjacent cell.  This parameter is relevant only for adjacent cells in band 66 with asymmetric bandwidth; this allows the gNB to check the corresponding NR BW capabilities of the UE before HO in that case.

This parameter indicates the frequency of the SSB associated with the NRADJNRCELL instance.    In case of PCI re-use (the configuration contains multiple NRREL instances that refer to either NRCELL instances or NRADJNRCELL instances which have a matching physCellId value):  - It is important to configure NRADJNRCELL.ssbFrequency in order to allow handover to this target NR adjacent cell when reported.  - Depending on whether the respective ANR is disabled or enabled (using NRBTS.actSaUeBasedAnrNr for SA intra-frequency neighbour, NRBTS.actNsaUeBasedAnrNr for NSA intra-frequency neighbour,  NRBTS.actSaUeBasedInterFreqAnrNr for SA inter-frequency neighbour, NRBTS.actNsaUeBasedInterFreqAnrNr for NSA inter-frequency neighbour)  * If ANR is disabled: handover will be forbidden to this NRADJNRCELL instance even though NRADJNRCELL.physCellId is matching but NRADJNRCELL.ssbFrequency is not configured.  * If ANR is enabled and if NRADJNRCELL.ssbFrequency is not configured, ANR will populate this parameter before triggering handover.

Parameter name: New Radio Automatic Neighbor Relationship instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Automatic Neighbor Relationship (NRANR) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.    The NRANR instance defines the basic ANR configuration parameters which are not related to a dedicated carrier frequency.

Parameter name: Activate autonomous removal of unused E-UTRA neighbors
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates autonomous removal of unused E-UTRA neighbor cells.    It is recommended to activate autonomous removal (NRANR.actAutoEutraNbRemoval equal to TRUE) after or along with the creation of all the required ANR for E-UTRA profiles (NRANRPRE instances).    When this parameter is activated, gNB will start monitoring ANR removal in a periodic cycle. Deactivating this parameter will stop the monitoring of unused E-UTRA neighbors for ANR removal.

Parameter name: Activate autonomous removal of unused neighbors
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates autonomous removal of unused NR neighbor relations    It is recommended to activate autonomous removal (NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval equal to TRUE) after or along with the creation of all the required ANR profiles (NRANRPR instances).    In case of ANR profile changes (update/deletion of existing profiles, new profile creation) related to autonomous neighbour removal done at a later time i.e. after NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval changed to TRUE, those changes will be applied only for new neighbor relations. Existing neighbor relations which are part of the ongoing autonomous removal procedure will continue to use the previous ANR profile configuration.    If those ANR profile changes have to be applied for existing neighbor relations which are part of the ongoing autonomous removal procedure, autonomous removal shall be reset. i.e. it shall be deactivated (NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval set to FALSE) and activated (NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval set to TRUE) again via different delta plans.  ANR profile (NRANRPR) changes shall be part  - either of any previous delta plan or  - of the current delta plan in which autonomous removal gets activated (NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval = TRUE)

This parameter indicates the maximum number of automatic re-validation attempts within NRANR.autoRecheckInterval for neighbor relations via CGI measurement pointing at NRADJNRCELL with PLMN with cellReservedForOperatorUse set to 'reserved' in which cellReservedForOperatorUse is equal to ADJ_NRPLMNSET_SA.cellReservedForOperatorUse if configured, otherwise NRADJNRCELL.cellReservedForOperatorUse.

This parameter indicates the time interval between automatic triggers for re-validation via CGI measurement of neighbor relations pointing at NRADJNRCELL with PLMN with cellReservedForOperatorUse set to 'reserved' in which cellReservedForOperatorUse is equal to ADJ_NRPLMNSET_SA.cellReservedForOperatorUse if configured, otherwise NRADJNRCELL.cellReservedForOperatorUse.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Consecutive handover execution failure re-validation threshold
Description: This parameter indicates the number of consecutive handover execution failures observed for an NR Neighbor Relation causing the gNB to trigger a re-validation for this neighbor relation via CGI measurement (if CGI measurements are allowed).    If this parameter is equal to 0, then no re-validation is triggered.

Parameter name: Consecutive Inter-RAT handover failure threshold for E-UTRA neighbor
Description: This parameter indicates the number of consecutive inter-RAT handover execution failures observed for an EUTRA Neighbor Relation causing the gNB to trigger a re-validation for this neighbor relation via ECGI measurement (if ECGI measurements are allowed).    If this parameter is equal to 0, then no re-validation is triggered.

Parameter name: Consecutive Xn link resolution failure threshold
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of triggered consecutive Xn link resolution failures that might happen for a NR Neighbor Cell. Exceeding this threshold is causing the gNB to stop Xn link resolution retries for that NR Neighbor Cell.

This parameter gathers parameters to configure the length which will be used to extract the neighbor gNB Id from NCI received from the UE in the NRCGI measurement report during ANR procedure.  It is used only in case no information about neighbor gNB Id can be found in the existing configuration.    Different length may be defined per NCI ranges and PLMN.    NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig such that NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.nciStart, NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.nciEnd and NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.nrPlmnDN are configured are applicable to all NRCGI with NCI matching the defined NCI range (i.e. with NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.nciStart <= NCI <= NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.nciEnd) and first PLMN matching NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.nrPlmnDN.    NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig such that NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.nciStart and NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.nciEnd (defining the NCI range) are not configured are applicable to all NRCGI with first PLMN matching NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.nrPlmnDN.    NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig such that NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.nrPlmnDN is not configured are applicable to all NRCGI with NCI matching the defined NCI range (i.e. with NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.nciStart <= NCI <= NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.nciEnd).    NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig such that NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.nciStart, NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.nciEnd and NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.nrPlmnDN are not configured are applicable to all NRCGI (treated as default).    In case received NRCGI is not matched to any defined NRANR-gNbIdLengthConfig instance then NRBTS-gNbIdLength value will be used to extract the neighbor gNB Id.
This parameter indicates the length which will be used to extract the gNB Id from NCI
This parameter indicates the end (upper bound) of the NCI range.
This parameter indicates the start (lower bound) of the NCI range.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the New Radio PLMN (NRPLMN) instance defining the associated PLMN. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1

This parameter indicates the priority of the gNbId length configuration such that the received NRCGI is matched for the presence within the NCI range (defined by NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.nciStart and NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.nciEnd) in increasing order of NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig.priorityIndex value for a specific PLMN.    The first matched NRANR.gNbIdLengthConfig is taken into use by the ANR functionality (the other ones are ignored).

Parameter name: New Radio Automatic Neighbor Relationship Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Automatic Neighbor Relationship Profile (NRANRPR) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.    A NRANRPR instance defines carrier-frequency-specific settings for automatic detection of NR intra-frequency or inter-frequency neighbor NR Cells.    The NRANRPR instance with NRANRPR.nrAnrPrId equal to 1 defines the default NRANR profile (applicable only for intra-frequency).

Parameter name: ANR RSRP threshold for neighbor cells
Description: If RSRP of a strongest unknown neighbor cell among only unknown neighbor cells included in a A3/A4/A5 mobility measurement is greater than the value in this parameter, then this cell is accepted as 'candidate cell for ANR'.    The parameter is ignored if both NRBTS.actNsaUeBasedAnrNr and NRBTS.actSaUeBasedAnrNr are equal to FALSE  For A4 for mobility to higher priority NR frequency, PCI resolution is only done if the received A4 measurement report is related to the highest priority frequency configured in the UE.

Parameter name: ANR RSRQ threshold for neighbor cells
Description: If RSRQ of a best unknown neighbour cell among only unknown neighbour cells included in a A3/A4/A5 mobility measurement is greater than the value of this parameter, then this cell is accepted as 'candidate cell for ANR'.    The parameter is ignored if NRBTS.actNsaUeBasedAnrNr and NRBTS.actSaUeBasedAnrNr are equal to FALSE  For A4 for mobility to higher priority NR frequency, PCI resolution is only done if the received A4 measurement report is related to the highest priority frequency configured in the UE.

Parameter name: ANR threshold check selector for neighbour cells
Description: This parameter indicates which ANR quality threshold shall be compared against A3/A4/A5 measurement report to select a 'candidate cell' for ANR.    There can be criteria of RSRP, RSRQ or Combined (RSRP and RSRQ) to be fulfilled
This parameter indicates how the cell deployment type of the newly added adjacent neighbour cells (NRADJNRCELL.cellDepType) will be set.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Consecutive neighbor relation re-check removal number
Description: This parameter indicates the number of consecutive re-check of NR neighbor relations (without successful handover between them) causing the gNB to remove this neighbor relation.    The parameter is ignored if NRBTS.actAutoNrNbRemoval is equal to FALSE.    NOTE: re-check of NR neighbor relations is defined in NRANR.consecHoFailThres. Please check it for details

Parameter name: Idle time threshold for NR neighbor relations removal
Description: This parameter indicates the time up to which, if a NR neighbor relation is not selected for handover, the gNB may autonomously remove that NR neighbor relation (NRREL instance) provided NRREL.removeNotAllowed is equal to FALSE.    Note: If NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval is equal to TRUE before and during the modification of this parameter, the modified value shall be taken into use only for new neighbor relations. In case the modified value has to be applied for existing neighbor relations, autonomous removal shall be deactivated (NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval set to FALSE) and activated (NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval set to TRUE) again via different delta plans. These steps will trigger the reset of the autonomous removal procedure.  ANR profile (NRANRPR) changes related to this parameter shall be part  - either of any previous delta plan or  - of the current delta plan in which autonomous removal gets activated (NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval = TRUE)

Parameter name: Max number of allowed neighbor relations operating on a particular carrier for a given serving NR cell
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of neighbor relations (NRREL instances) operating on a particular carrier represented by NRANRPR.ssbFrequency for a given serving NR Cell.    Note: This parameter is used only by the ANR. It is not applicable while operator adds new NRREL instances.
This parameter indicates the New Radio Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number of the NR ANR frequency profile

This parameter indicates the SSB frequency of the NR target carrier for which this NRANR profile applies.    The profile applies for intra-frequency or inter-frequency ANR dependent on the carrier frequency of the NR Cell.    If a NRANRPR instance with a dedicated carrier frequency exists, this instance has a higher priority than the default NRANRPR profile.    The NRANRPR instance with NRANRPR.nrAnrPrId equal to 1 represents the Default ANR profile for which this parameter is not configured.    If this Default ANR profile is not configured, then Automated neighbor learning and neighbor removal will be supported only for the NR (adjacent) Cells operating on SSB frequencies equal to NRANRPR.ssbFrequency of one of NRANRPR instances (dedicated NRANRPR profiles).

Parameter name: New Radio Automatic Neighbor Relationship Profile for E-UTRA Inter-RAT instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Automatic Neighbor Relationship Profile for E-UTRA (NRANRPRE) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.    An NRANRPRE instance defines carrier frequency-specific settings for automatic detection of E-UTRA neighbor cells.    The NRANRPRE instance with identifier (NRANRPRE.nrAnrPrEId) equal to 1 defines the ANR Inter-RAT for E-UTRA's default profile. If there is no carrier frequency-specific profile defined, this default profile configuration is used for ANR Inter-RAT procedures in any E-UTRA frequency.

Parameter name: ANR RSRP threshold for E-UTRA neighbor cells
Description: This parameter indicates the RSRP threshold for detection of unknown E-UTRA neighbor cell that is reported in a B2 mobility measurement.    If the RSRP of a strongest unknown E-UTRA neighbor cell among only unknown neighbor cells included in a B2 mobility measurement is greater than the value of this parameter, then this cell is accepted as 'candidate cell' for Inter-RAT ANR.    The parameter is relevant only if NRBTS.actSaUeBasedAnrEutra is equal to TRUE.

Parameter name: ANR RSRQ threshold for E-UTRA neighbor cells
Description: This parameter indicates the RSRQ threshold for detection of unknown E-UTRA neighbor cell that is reported in a B2 mobility measurement.    If the RSRP of a strongest unknown E-UTRA neighbor cell among only unknown neighbor cells included in a B2 mobility measurement is greater than the value of this parameter, then this cell is accepted as 'candidate cell' for Inter-RAT ANR.    The parameter is relevant only if NRBTS.actSaUeBasedAnrEutra is equal to TRUE.

Parameter name: ANR threshold check selector for E-UTRA neighbor cells
Description: This parameter indicates which ANR quality threshold shall be compared against B2 measurement report to select a 'candidate cell' for Inter-RAT ANR.    There can be criteria of RSRP, RSRQ or Combined (RSRP and RSRQ) to be fulfilled.
This parameter indicates the E-UTRA target carrier frequency for which this ANR Inter-RAT profile (NRANRPRE) instance applies.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Consecutive neighbor relation re-check for E-UTRA neighbor cells
Description: This parameter indicates the number of consecutive re-check of E-UTRA neighbor relations (without successful handover between them) causing the gNB to remove this neighbor relation.    The parameter is relevant only if NRBTS.actAutoEutraNbRemoval is equal to TRUE.    NOTE: Re-check of E-UTRA neighbor relations is defined in NRANR.consecHoFailThresEutra.

Parameter name: Data forwarding method for IRAT to LTE
Description: This parameter provides the data forwarding method to be used during IRAT handover to LTE.

Parameter name: Idle time threshold for E-UTRA neighbor relations removal
Description: This parameter indicates the time up to which, if an E-UTRA neighbor relation is not selected for handover, the gNB may autonomously remove that E-UTRA neighbor relation (NRRELE instance) provided NRRELE.removeNotAllowed is equal to FALSE.

Parameter name: Max number of allowed E-UTRA neighbor relations operating on a particular carrier for a given serving NR cell
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of E-UTRA neighbor relations (NRRELE instances) operating on a particular carrier frequency (represented by NRANRPRE.carrierFreq) for a given serving NR Cell.    Note: This parameter is used only by the Inter-RAT ANR. It is not applicable while operator adds new NRRELE instances.

Parameter name: New Radio Beam Mapping instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Beam Mapping (NRBEAMMAP) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRCELL instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter indicates the list of beam group identifiers associated with a given beam within the Distributed Unit (DU).  The first entry in the list indicates the initial beam group identifier used during the RACH access procedure.

Parameter name: DU beam group list for NR-DC calls
Description: This parameter indicates the list of beam group identifiers associated with a given beam within the Distributed Unit (DU). This parameter shall be specifically used only for NR-DC calls.  The first entry in the list indicates the initial beam group identifier used during the RACH access procedure.

This parameter indicates the Distributed Unit (DU) beam identifier.  In order to map and calculate the DU and O-RAN Radio Unit (O-RU) beams correctly, the DU beam identifiers need to be configured in continuous order from value 0 to N-1, where N is the maximum number of beams.
This parameter indicates the O-RAN Radio Unit (O-RU) beam identifier

Parameter name: New Radio beam instance identifier for EMF test mode
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio EMF beam profile (NRBEAM_EMF) instance within the same containing NRCELL instance.

Parameter name: Beam pattern id for EMF test mode
Description: This parameter indicates the beam pattern id for EMF test mode.

Parameter name: Beam type for EMF test mode
Description: This parameter indicates the beam type for EMF test mode.

Parameter name: Gain in configured direction for EMF test mode
Description: This parameter indicates the gain in configured direction (based on NRCELL.emfAzimuth and NRCELL.emfElevation) for EMF test mode.

Parameter name: Maximum gain and direction for EMF test mode
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum gain and corresponding direction within the configured azimuth range and elevation range for EMF test mode.

Parameter name: Minimum gain and direction for EMF test mode
Description: This parameter indicates the minimum gain and corresponding direction within the configured azimuth and elevation range for EMF test mode.
This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Basestation (NRBTS) instance within the same containing MRBTS instance.  It is also used as a telecom parameter of the 3GPP Global gNB ID.

Parameter name: Activate 3GPP standard baseline for gNB 22R2 release
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the functional changes to support the 3GPP standard baseline for the gNB 22R2 release.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to TRUE.

Parameter name: Activate 3GPP standard baseline for gNB 22R3 release
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the functional changes to support the 3GPP standard baseline for the gNB 22R3 release.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to TRUE.

Parameter name: Activate 3GPP standard baseline for gNB 22R4 release
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the functional changes to support the 3GPP standard baseline for the gNB 22R4 release.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to TRUE.

Parameter name: Activate 3GPP standard baseline for gNB 23R1 release
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the functional changes to support the 3GPP standard baseline for the gNB 23R1 release.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to TRUE.
This parameter activates/deactivates Real-time Performance Monitoring (RTPM) in 5G

Parameter name: Activate 5G user layer TCP MSS clamping
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates 5G User Plane Configurable TCP MSS Clamping.  If activated, the MSS in end-user TCP SYN packets is reduced to a value avoiding IP fragmentation in the transport layer.

Parameter name: Activate modification of 5QI for nonGBR QoS flows and UPF endpoint for NG-U transport bearers
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the modification of 5QI value for nonGBR QoS flows and UPF endpoint for the NG-U transport bearers.    This parameter is applicable only for SA NR Cells.

Parameter name: Activate A1 based traffic steering to preferred NR layer
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates A1 based traffic steering to preferred NR layer
This parameter activates/deactivates A2 based SgNB release

Parameter name: Activate A3/A5 measurement report handling during DRX setup
Description: This parameter enables/disables enhanced concurrency handling of A3/A5 measurement reports during DRX setup during incoming intra-gNB handover and incoming inter-gNB handover via Xn.

Parameter name: Activate adaptive scheduler budget overload control
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the dynamic allocation of the processing time provided to all the schedulers such that there is still enough processing resources available to process asynchronous messages.    Note: This parameter is not applicable for TDD FR2 (NRCELL-cellTechnology equal to TDD and NRCELL.nrarfcn is greater than or equal to 2016667) and also for the cells with FDD FR1( NRBTS/NRCELL-cellTechnology equal to 'FDD' and NRBTS/NRCELL-nrarfcn less than or equal to 800000) that's are linked to BBMOD instance with HW variant ABIL/ABILL.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter activates/deactivates additional standard slice support.  More precisely, it activates/deactivates DRB inactivity timer per slice and per DRB profile. It also allows to use the full range of SNSSAI.sst.

Parameter name: Activate prioritization of band combinations based on allowedBC-ListMRDC order applied by MeNB
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates prioritization of band combinations according to their order in the allowedBC-ListMRDC IE received from the MeNB during EN-DC setup or modification.    Prioritization is applied in the gNB-DU if there is more than one band combination offering the same highest DL and UL 5G throughput. It is assumed that the entries in allowedBC-ListMRDC IE are sorted with descending priority by the MeNB.    This parameter is applicable for FR1 NSA and FR2 NSA calls only.    If this parameter is equal to TRUE the best results can be achieved if NRDCDPR.actSortBcListEnDc on LTE side is also equal to TRUE (which activates sorting of the allowedBC-ListMRDC IE entries per maximum LTE throughput in descending order). If NRDCDPR.actSortBcListEnDc is equal to FALSE, only 5G DL and UL throughput can be maximized.
This parameter activates/deactivates AMF planned removal.
This parameter activates/deactivates ARP based QoS scaling.  It introduces the possibility to configure scaling factors per each ARP priority level for non-GBR bearers (non-GBR QoS flows).

This parameter activates/deactivates the assumption of Voice over New Radio (VoNR) capability in User Equipment (UE) by the gNB.  If NRBTS.actAssumeVoNRCapability is set to True and the UE Capability information related to VoNR is missing, the gNB will assume that the UE is VoNR. If the UE Capability information related to VoNR is present, the gNB will use this information to evaluate the UE's VoNR capability.  If NRBTS.actAssumeVoNRCapability is set to False, the gNB determines the UE's support for VoNR based on the UE capability information.

Parameter name: Activate automated PRACH configuration index assignment in FDD FR1
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates automated PRACH configuration Index assignment in FDD FR1.  Updating this parameter requires a restart of all the NRCELL instances with NRCELL.cellTechnology equal to 'FDD'.

Parameter name: Activate enhanced automated PRACH configuration Index assignment
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates enhanced automated PRACH configuration Index assignment.  If it is activated, automatic PRACH Configuration Index assignment is possible also when cells with different bandwidths are combined in resource allocation.  This allows a more efficient use of HW resources in the case where same Baseband Unit handles cells that have different bandwidths.

Parameter name: Activate baseband resource pooling FR1 TDD extension
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates FR1 TDD baseband resource pooling extension  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate baseband resource pooling FR1 TDD
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates FR1 TDD baseband resource pooling.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart when Airscale System Core Units are not installed

Parameter name: Activate enhanced algorithm of baseband resource pooling FR1 TDD
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the enhanced algorithm of FR1 TDD baseband resource pooling.

Parameter name: Activate baseband resource pooling FR1 TDD enhancements
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates baseband resource pooling FR1 TDD enhancements  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart when Airscale System Core Units are not installed

This parameter activates/deactivates Bandwidth Combination Set (BCS) checks in carrier aggregation or NR-DC.  The gNB performs a BCS check during FR1 CA secondary cell selection to ensure the bandwidth combination of the selected gNB serving cells is compatible with the UE capabilities. The gNB also performs a BCS check during allowed NR-DC band combination selection for NR-DC establishment to ensure the bandwidth of FR1 PCell is compatible with the UE capabilities.    The possible values are the following:  - 'disabled' meaning the BCS checks are disabled in all cells.  - 'enabled_FR1' meaning the BCS checks are enabled during the FR1 CA secondary cell selection in all cells.  - 'enabled_NRDC' meaning the BCS checks are enabled in PCell during the allowed band combination selection for NR-DC establishment.  - 'enabled_FR1+NRDC' meaning the BCS checks are enabled both during the FR1 CA secondary cell selection in all cells and in PCell during the allowed band combination selection for NR-DC establishment.    This parameter is ignored if NRDU.carrierAggregationSupportList has an element equal to 'none' and the NRCELL instance corresponding to the UE's PCell has NRCELL.actNrDualConnectivity equal to 'disabled'.

This parameter activates/deactivates the TCI state indication while beam toggling.    The value of this parameter is used on all the cells that satisfy the following conditions:  - NRCELL.actBeamforming is equal to TRUE  - NRCELL.cellTechnology is equal to 1 (corresponding to TDD)  - NRCELL.nrarfcn <= 800000 (FR1)  For the cells that do not satisfy the above conditions, this parameter is ignored.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to TRUE.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter activates/deactivates the reduction of the UL beam re-probing rate, especially for the 4Rx receivers.    The value of this parameter is used on all the cells that satisfy the following conditions:  - NRCELL.actBeamforming is equal to TRUE  - NRCELL.cellTechnology is equal to 1 (corresponding to TDD)  - NRCELL.nrarfcn <= 800000 (FR1)  For the cells that do not satisfy the above conditions, this parameter is ignored.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to TRUE.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter enables the buffer-based SCell addition. Possible values are:  - disabled: Functionality is disabled.  - oneShot_Dl_Fr1: Activates one-shot buffer based SCell Addition. The gNB may trigger one-shot SCell Addition only when the UE is not in CA.  - oneShot_stepWise_Dl_Fr1: Activates one-shot buffer based SCell Addition and step-wise SCell Addition. The gNB may trigger one-shot SCell Addition only when the UE is not configured with an SCell. The gNB may trigger step-wise SCell Addition when the UE is configured with at least one SCell.    Note: Currently, this parameter is applicable for FR1 only.
This parameter activates/deactivates CMAS broadcasting

Parameter name: Activate calculation of carriers contiguity checks using maximum allowed subcarrier spacing for FR1 CA
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the gNB and UE configuration independent contiguity check calculation of nominal channel spacing between two intra-band carriers using the maximum allowed subcarrier spacing for those carriers.    If this parameter is equal to FALSE, the gNB uses for calculation the subcarrier spacing that will be configured to the UE.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE, the gNB uses for calculation the maximum subcarrier spacing that is allowed by 3GPP 38.101-1 Table 5.3.5-1 for the band and UE channel bandwidths of the carriers.    This parameter is applicable for FR1 carriers only.

This parameter activates/deactivates DL data bundling at RLC entity when carrier aggregation is configured.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to TRUE.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter controls the activation/deactivation of the functionalities for CA overload control enhancement. This parameter is applicable to FR1 cells only, not applicable to FR2 cells.

Parameter name: Activate carrier aggregation performance measurement counters
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the carrier aggregation related performance measurement counters
This parameter activates/deactivates the 5G carrier aggregation feature.  This parameter is applicable only for aggregation of FR2/TDD NSA and NR-DC NR Cells.

Parameter name: Activate carrier aggregation for FR2 TDD SA
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the 5G intra-band carrier aggregation feature.  This parameter is applicable only for aggregation of FR2 TDD SA NR Cells.
This parameter activates/deactivates CBRS (Citizens Broadband Radio Service) enhanced measurement.
This parameter activates/deactivates CBRS (Citizens Broadband Radio Service) mobility enhancement.

Parameter name: Activate cell switch on for online configuration management update
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates cell switch on for online configuration management update.    If this parameter is not configured or is configured and equal to FALSE, then cell switch on for online configuration management update is deactivated.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE, then cell switch on for online configuration management update is activated.
This parameter activates/deactivates cell trace report at gNB level.

This parameter activates/deactivates channel object mapping validation checks to match the NR cell type.    The possible values are:  - Disabled: the checks are deactivated and any wrong configuration may result in cell operation failures  - ShowAsWarning: the checks are activated and the failures are shown as warnings  - ShowAsError: the checks are activated and the failures are shown as errors

Parameter name: Activate chipset and RAN information exchange
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates chipset and RAN information exchange. gNB will provide information about the RAN manufacturer and running version, while the UE will provide an identification of the chipset vendor, as well as the SW version.
This parameter activates/deactivates the management of conflicting configuration of incoming Xn links.

Parameter name: Activate baseband pooling of RRC connected users
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates baseband pooling of RRC connected users.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate coordinated EN DSS power saving for 5G
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates coordinated EN DSS power saving for 5G.
This parameter activates/deactivates coordinated 4G-5G power saving, 5G.
This parameter activates/deactivates the coverage based handling of non-coherent MIMO UEs

Parameter name: Activate reduction factor for overload control
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the algorithm of maximum CS2 list size reduction and controlling the maximum number of FDM UEs with respect to maximum number of CS1 list size during high load for scheduling fairness consideration functionality and overload control. It is considered only when NRBTS.actFdmScheduling is equal to TRUE. If NRBTS.actFdmScheduling is equal to FALSE, then this parameter is ignored and the reduction factor for overload control is deactivated. The reduction factor for overload control is applicable only for FR1 TDD and FDD cells with NRCELL.pucchModeSelect equal to 'longPucch'.  Additionally, the reduction factor for overload control is considered in UL when NRBTS.actSchedFairnessUlOlc is equal to TRUE. If NRBTS.actSchedFairnessUlOlc is equal to FALSE, then this parameter is ignored in UL and the reduction factor for overload control in UL is deactivated.

Parameter name: Activate PUCCH multiplexing of CSI reports
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the 5G PUCCH multiplexing of CSI reports feature.  It is applicable only for TDD NR cells. Activating this feature significantly reduces the PUCCH F2 coverage (e.g. by up to -5 dBm pathloss).

Parameter name: Activate CSI and TCI release during PSCell change
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates a workaround for some legacy UEs' problems during PSCell change by adjusting the TCI relations and explicitly releasing the SCell's CSI and TCI configurations that were configured in the source PSCell.
This parameter activates/deactivates custom beam set realization in the gNB.

This parameter activates/deactivates DDDS period optimization.    If NRCELLs with high loads are expected in configuration the recommended value for this parameter is TRUE.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter activates/deactivates data duplication for mobility. It defines whether the gNB is allowed to send duplicate PDCP PDU when mobility is ongoing to improve PDCP PDU delivery reliability.

Parameter name: Activate data duplication for SA mobility
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates data duplication for SA mobility. It defines whether the gNB is allowed to send duplicate PDCP PDU when mobility is ongoing to improve PDCP PDU delivery reliability.

Parameter name: Activate special DRX profiles for NR ANR functionality
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the special DRX profiles for NR ANR functionality.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to TRUE.

Parameter name: Activate direct SN terminated split bearer establishment by SgNB modification procedure for NSA
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates SN terminated split bearer establishment directly without PDCP anchor change by MeNB initiated SgNB modification procedure.

Parameter name: Activate disabling of NR remote interference management RS at gNB level
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the disabling of remote interference management RS at gNB level.  When equal to TRUE, it is not allowed to support RIM framework-0 nor framework-1 at gNB level.  When equal to FALSE, it is allowed to support RIM framework-0 and framework-1 at gNB level.

Parameter name: Activate disabling user plane integrity protection for 64kbpsPreferred
Description: Activation Flag to Disable the UPIP for a PDU session of the UE having the max supported data rate per UE for integrity protection 64kbps for "Preferred" case.

Parameter name: Activate disabling of UL proactive grant for NR ANR functionality
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the disabling of UL proactive grant for NR ANR functionality.
This parameter activates/deactivates the DL UE AMBR limitation for SA non-GBR DRBs.

Parameter name: Activate DL data forwarding over X2
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates DL data forwarding over X2

Parameter name: Activate DL data forwarding limitation over X2
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates DL data forwarding limitation over X2 towards the MeNB to protect LTE's PDCP buffer overrun.    If set to true, the amount of data to be forwarded to the MeNB will be limited based on calculation done in the gNB (applicable only with Nokia LTE interworking)    If set to false, all the buffered data will be forwarded to the MeNB (applicable during interworking with other vendors).
This parameter activates/deactivates the extension of DRX profiles which allows operator to improve UE battery consumption by optimizing DRX for each specific service 5QI and/or QCI.
This parameter activates/deactivates DRB preemption.

Parameter name: Activate DRB profile for cell aggregation level
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates DRB profile for cell aggregation level.
This parameter activates/deactivates 5G dual sector/dual band RU.  It is applicable only for FR2/TDD NR sectors in an AirScale mmWave Radio (ASMR) RU.
This parameter activates/deactivates the dynamic firewall configuration on the S1, X2, Xn, NG and Xg interfaces.

Parameter name: Activate dynamic target share calculation for RG
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the usage of dynamic target share calculation for a resource group when NRBTS.actSliceAwareScheduler is equal to TRUE. If NRBTS.actSliceAwareScheduler is equal to FALSE then this parameter is ignored.

This parameter activates/deactivates E2 based carrier aggregation by adapting the A1 threshold for secondary cell addition, secondary cell selection weight and A2 threshold for secondary cell release with RIC (RAN Intelligent Controller) generated offset according to machine learning.

Parameter name: Activate E2 based idle mode load balancing
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates E2 based idle mode load balancing with adaption of the cell re-selection priority with RIC (RAN Intelligent Controller) generated offset according to machine learning.

This parameter activates/deactivates the E2 interface between the E2 Node (gNB-CU-CP) and the Near-RT RIC.  Note that, in the Cloud vCU deployment, if this parameter is equal to TRUE then the optional CPE2 Pod shall exist.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter activates/deactivates ETWS broadcasting
This parameter activates/deactivates the eCPRI phase 2  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter activates/deactivates the eCPRI phase 3  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate eCPRI RU PTP only synchronization
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the eCPRI RU PTP only synchronization mode over the ethernet interface.    Updating this parameter may provoke a RU reset, depending on the RU capability. In case RU reset is not required, the parameter will be updated on-line.

Parameter name: Activate emergency services fallback to LTE
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates emergency services fallback to LTE
This parameter activates/deactivates the Periodic retries of EN-DC Configuration Update to MeNB from SgNB.

Parameter name: Activate Enhanced RRC Reconfiguration UL PRB Randomization
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the UL PRB Randomization during RRC Reconfiguration.

Parameter name: Activate enhancements on intra-NR intra-frequency ANR
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the enhancements on intra-NR intra-frequency ANR concerning the maintenance of neighbor relations.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to TRUE.

Parameter name: Activate the enhanced link adaptation procedures
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the enhanced link adaptation procedure
This parameter activates/deactivates the NG enhancements for multi-vendor AMF support.
This parameter activates/deactivates enhanced X2 link supervision
This parameter activates/deactivates the capability request filter when UE-Capability is requested to the UE for E-UTRAN.

Parameter name: Activate E-UTRAN frequency band NR MRDC filtering
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the usage of the requestedFreqBandsNR-MRDC IE in the 3GPP 36.331 UE capability Enquiry message. requestedFreqBandsNR-MRDC ensures that the UE includes all necessary feature sets (i.e. E-UTRA and NR) needed for subsequently requested eutra-nr capabilities.
This parameter activates / deactivates the exclusion of E-UTRAN band check when interRAT-Parameters is not present in the UE-NR-Capability.
This parameter activates/deactivates the exclusion of E-UTRAN cells.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to FALSE.

Parameter name: Activate explicit TRS CSI-RS pooling solution
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates explicit baseband pooling extension TRS and cell specific CSI-RS resources pooling solution in the gNB.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE, then  In that case pooling support 40/80/160 and 320 slots for CSI-RS periodicity and NRCELL.actCellCsiRsImTddNonBf or NRCELL.actCellCsirsTddOnSsbBf can be activated  If this parameter is equal to FALSE, then  In that case pooling support 160 and 320 slots for CSI-RS periodicity and NRCELL.actCellCsiRsImTddNonBf or NRCELL.actCellCsirsTddOnSsbBf cannot be activated  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter activates/deactivates the extended n77 band support 2 (3650- 3980 MHz) in the gNB in countries where usage of the n77 band might be restricted otherwise.    Note: The gNB does not check the PLMN ID to determine whether the gNB is located in a country where the n77 band usage is restricted or not. Thus, it is the operator's responsibility to determine whether this functionality shall be activated in their network or not.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter activates/deactivates the extended n77 band support (3450-3550 MHz) in the gNB in countries where usage of the n77 band might be restricted otherwise.    Note: The gNB does not check the PLMN ID to determine whether the gNB is located in a country where the n77 band usage is restricted or not. Thus, it is the operator's responsibility to determine whether this functionality shall be activated in their network or not.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate extended schedulWeight and pref WRR algorithm
Description: This Parameter activates/deactivates the enhanced weighted round robin (WRR) algorithm and extends the range of the scheduling weight which is used for frequency domain resource allocation.  - disabled: The feature is disabled. Legacy algorithm WRR and legacy scheduling weight range i.e. 1...100.  - ExtendedRange_LegacyWrr: Legacy WRR algorithm with extended scheduling weight range i.e. 1...1000 (Only if CB008709 feature parameter actSliceAwareSchedulerUlAndEnh is disabled)  - ExtendedRange_EnhancedWrr: Enhanced WRR algorithm with extended scheduling weight range i.e. 1...1000.

This parameter activates/deactivates enhanced frequency domain (FDM) scheduling.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to TRUE.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter activates/deactivates frequency domain scheduling.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to TRUE.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate FDM UE skipping overload control
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates FDM UE skipping overload control  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate a fix for non-3GPP compliant random access response window in specific vendor UEs for FDD DSS cells
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates a fix for non-3GPP compliant random access response window in specific vendor UEs for FDD DSS cells. This allows such UEs to correctly receive msg2 in cells with prachConfigurationIndex 13 and 40.

Parameter name: Activate flexible SCell selection for FR1
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates more flexible SCell selection for carrier aggregation (CA) for frequency range 1 (FR1).    If this parameter is equal to TRUE, then the following limits apply for CA for FR1:  - The maximum number of SCell candidates per PCell is limited to 21.  - The maximum number of PCells per SCell is limited to 21.  - The maximum number of SCell frequency layers is limited to 7.  - The maximum number of SCell candidates per frequency layer for a PCell is 21 (all max. SCell candidates can be configured to the same frequency layer).    If this parameter is equal to FALSE (legacy behavior), then the following limits apply for CA for FDD / FR1 TDD:  - The maximum number of SCell candidates per PCell is limited to 12 / 10.  - The maximum number of PCells per SCell, is limited to 12 / 10.  - The maximum number of SCell frequency layers is limited to 6 / 5.  - The maximum number of SCell candidates per frequency layer for a PCell is limited to 2.    If this parameter is changed from TRUE to FALSE and there is a need to reconfigure the CA configuration for FR1 to return to legacy limits, this may require the deletion of managed object instances and as a result, a 5G RAT restart of the SBTS (see parameter NRREL.sCellAdditionMethod) might be triggered.    Note: At least one FR1 CA feature should be activated, but this is not enforced.

This parameter indicates if DL ICMP traffic is directed to the UE preferred UL path or the NR path.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE, DL ICMP traffic is directed to the UE preferred UL path.  If this parameter is equal to FALSE, DL ICMP traffic is directed to the NR path.
This parameter activates/deactivates the flow control load balance.

Parameter name: Activate force full RRC configuration for SA HO
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates enforcement of full RRC configuration for SA Inter-gNB handover.    The possible values are:-  -'disabled' meaning full RRC configuration for SA HO is not enforced and only basic full configuration triggers are applicable as per NRBTS.actFullRRCConfigurationSaHo  - 'enabled' meaning full RRC configuration for SA HO is always enforced during incoming Inter-gNB handover.  - 'onlyXnHo' meaning full RRC configuration for Xn HO is always enforced during Xn handover. For NG handover only basic full configuration triggers are applicable as per NRBTS.actFullRRCConfigurationSaHo.  - 'onlyNgHo' meaning full RRC configuration for NG HO is always enforced during NG handover. For Xn handover only basic full configuration triggers are applicable as per NRBTS.actFullRRCConfigurationSaHo.    This parameter brings an additional possibility to trigger full RRC configuration regardless of source configuration and does not change full RRC configuration triggers defined by NRBTS.actFullRRCConfigurationSaHo.

Parameter name: Activate admitting HO with insufficient UE capability
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates admitting incoming handover in case of insufficient supportBandCombination capabilities received during Handover.  This parameter is also used to activates/deactivates succeeding the Initial Context Setup in case supportedBandCombinationList IE not present in the UE-NR-Capability.
This parameter activates/deactivates the New Radio forced cell switch off.    Note: There is no coordination between the technologies that are configured for RF Sharing.

Parameter name: Activate L2 DL pre-calculation of TD metric for FR2 8CC
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates TD metric parallelization for TDD FR2 8CC deployment by updating TD metric independently of TD user selection.
This parameter activates/deactivates FR2 standalone (SA) mode in the gNB.
This parameter activates/deactivates reading full PLMN list during Xn setup

Parameter name: Activate full RRC configuration for SA HO
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates full RRC configuration for SA HO.    The possible values are:  - 'disabled' meaning full RRC configuration for SA HO is deactivated.  - 'enabled' meaning full RRC configuration for SA HO is activated.  - 'DrbToQosMappingOnly' meaning full RRC configuration for SA HO is activated for inter-vendor interoperability issues of DRB to QoS flows mapping mismatch.  - 'extended' meaning full RRC configuration for SA HO is extended for additional triggers in case of mismatched configuration for RLC mode, RLC SN size, PDCP SN size , Disabled cipher, Integrity protection, Out-of-order delivery, DL SDAP header.

Parameter name: Activate full RRC configuration for NSA PSCell change
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates full RRC configuration for NSA PSCell change.    The possible values are:  - 'disabled' meaning full RRC configuration for NSA PSCell change is deactivated.  - 'enabled' meaning full RRC configuration for NSA PSCell change is activated.  - 'enforced' meaning full RRC configuration for NSA PSCell change is always enforced to trigger full RRC configuration regardless of source configuration.
This parameter activates/deactivates the gNB initiated RLF feature  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter activates/deactivates graceful cell shutdown.  This feature allows a less service impacting cell locking.

Parameter name: Activate GTP-U Sequence Numbers for PM Counters Calculation
Description: This parameter enables filling the GTP-U Sequence numbers for PM Counters Calculation.    Note: GTP-U Sequence numbers are used for monitoring the downlink packet loss rate on the 5G side.

This parameter activates/deactivates high slice weight factor. When activated, the high value of slice weight factor is applied for slice resource control algorithm to address issue of resource share deviation from configured slice minimum quota target share in the presence of relatively high numbers of small traffic DRBs/users per slice.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate mobility to higher priority NR frequency
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates mobility to higher priority NR frequency

Parameter name: Activate mobility to higher priority NR frequency for CA UEs
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates mobility to higher priority NR frequency for CA UEs.    If this parameter is set to 'disabled' or is not configured, then inter-frequency A4 measurements will not be configured for the UEs which support NR Carrier Aggregation and for which at least one of the SgNB/gNB available configurations for CA matches one of the UE supported CA combinations.  If this parameter is set to 'NSA', then inter-frequency A4 measurements will be configured for all UEs (non-CA capable UEs, CA capable UEs with CA configured on SgNB, CA capable UEs with CA not configured on SgNB) on the NSA call.  If this parameter is set to 'SA', then inter-frequency A4 measurements will be configured for all UEs (non-CA capable UEs, CA capable UEs with CA configured on gNB, CA capable UEs with CA not configured on gNB) on the SA call.  If this parameter is set to 'SA+NSA', then inter-frequency A4 measurements will be configured for all UEs (non-CA capable UEs, CA capable UEs with CA configured on the SgNB/gNB, CA capable UEs with CA not configured on SgNB/gNB) on the NSA/SA call.

Parameter name: Activate band combination selection based on highest estimated NR throughput
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates band combination selection based on the highest estimated NR throughput calculated using both the gNB configuration of P(S)Cell and SCell(s) and UE Capabilities.    If this parameter is set to TRUE then  - If SCell(s) are selected for FR1 Carrier Aggregation, gNB-CU will send to gNB-DU all matching band combinations with all valid feature set entry indices  - gNB-DU will select the band combination and feature set entry index offering the highest estimated NR throughput calculated using both the gNB configuration of P(S)Cell and SCell(s) and UE Capabilities for the band combination. The selection is done among the band combinations and feature set entry indices either received from gNB-CU or taken from UE Capabilities, depending on the UE connection type (NSA or SA) and whether SCell(s) are configured for the UE.    If this parameter is set to FALSE then  - If SCell(s) are selected for Carrier Aggregation, gNB-CU will send to gNB-DU at most one matching band combination and one corresponding feature set entry index  - gNB-DU will select the band combination and feature set entry index offering the highest theoretical NR throughput calculated using UE Capabilities for the band combination only. The selection is done among the band combinations and feature set entry indices either received from gNB-CU or taken from UE Capabilities, depending on the UE connection type (NSA or SA) and whether SCell(s) are configured for the UE.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to TRUE.

Parameter name: Activate handover optimization for carrier aggregation
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates handover related optimizations for carrier aggregation.  It activates/deactivates secondary cell addition based on the UE measurement results for the target primary cell provided by the source primary cell during an incoming handover procedure or primary cell change without performing A1 measurement at the UE

Parameter name: Activate idle mode traffic steering from NR SA to LTE EN-DC carrier
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates idle mode traffic steering from NR SA to LTE EN-DC carrier.    There are two options to define/configure the idle mode mobility EN-DC aware steering functionality towards a target SSB frequency:  - Without mobility profile by configuring NRCELL.idleMMEnDcSteeringSsbFrequency and the related parameters for the NRCELL instances  - With mobility profile by configuring NRMOIMP_SA.idleMMEnDcSteeringSsbFrequency and the related parameters for the NRMOIMP_SA instance).
This parameter activates/deactivates idle mode mobility steering.

Parameter name: Activate inactivity detection for NSA UE
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the UE inactivity handling feature for non standalone UE in mode 3x.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to TRUE.
This parameter activates/deactivates the management of incoming Xn links

Parameter name: Activate inter-frequency handover for the Standalone mode
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the inter-frequency handover for the Standalone mode.
This parameter activates/deactivates the inter-frequency inter-gNB mobility NSA 3X.
This parameter activates/deactivates the inter-frequency intra-gNB mobility NSA 3X.

Parameter name: Activate RRC connection re-establishment under a prepared gNB during inter-gNB handover via Xn or NG
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the RRC connection re-establishment under a prepared gNB during Inter-gNB handover via Xn or NG (SA).
This parameter activates/deactivates inter MeNB Mobility in the gNB.

Parameter name: Activate direct data forwarding for IRAT to LTE
Description: This parameter activates / deactivates the possibility to have direct data forwarding during IRAT HO to LTE  If this parameter is set to 'IRATDirectDataFwdOnXn', it indicates that direct data forwarding is done on Xn interface.  If this parameter is set to 'IRATDirectDataFwdOnNg', it indicates that direct data forwarding is done on Ng interface.  If this parameter is set to 'IRATDirectDataFwdOnX2', it indicates that direct data forwarding is done on X2 interface.

Parameter name: Activate inter-RAT handover from E-UTRA to NR-SA UE
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the inter-RAT handover from E-UTRA to SA UE.

Parameter name: Activate inter-RAT handover for SA UE
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the inter-RAT handover to E-UTRA for SA UE

Parameter name: Activate DL data forwarding for inter-RAT handover for SA UE
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates DL data forwarding for inter-RAT handover for SA UE

Parameter name: Activate intra-frequency handover for the Standalone mode
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the intra-frequency handover for the Standalone mode.
This parameter activates/deactivates the intra-frequency inter-gNB mobility NSA 3x.
This parameter activates/deactivates the intra-frequency intra-gNB mobility NSA, which covers both intra-DU and inter-DU case.
This parameter activates/deactivates intra MeNB Mobility in the gNB.
This parameter activates Intra-NR Mobility Robustness Optimization

This parameter activates/deactivates intra-NR NG based handover for the Standalone mode.    The supported values are:  - disabled meaning that intra-NR NG based handover is deactivated  - sourceAndTarget meaning that intra-NR NG based handover is activated for the source gNB and the target gNB  - targetOnly meaning that intra-NR NG based handover is activated for the target gNB and deactivated for the source gNB  - basicTargetOnly meaning that basic intra-NR NG based handover is activated for the target gNB and deactivated for the source gNB

Parameter name: Activate reporting of DL PDCP cell level and DL/UL RLC cell level throughput PM counters
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates reporting of DL PDCP cell level and DL/UL RLC cell level for throughput PM counters and PDCP and RLC level PCMD throughput reports.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate traffic shaping at gNB L2 with DL data over X2-U
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates traffic shaping at gNB L2 with DL data over X2-U  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter activates/deactivates the feature activation of the L4S support.

Parameter name: Activate large baseband resource pooling FR1 TDD
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates FR1 TDD baseband resource pooling on full baseband board deployment.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate refinement of large BB resource pooling FR1 TDD
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the refinement function of large baseband resource pooling on full board with single L1 pool deployment, this function is applicable on ABIP/ABIQ/ASOG/ASOH/RINLINE2 and TDD FR1. Updating this parameter will reset all TDD cells deployed on that board and might provoke RU reset.

This parameter activates/deactivates the overload control (OLC) enhancements for the last scheduler in a slot.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to TRUE.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate reporting of NR latency PM counters
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates reporting of NR latency PM counters.  This parameter controls both PMQAP and non PMQAP NR latency PM counters.

Parameter name: Activate load-based PS control logic enhancement
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the cell switch off and power saving control logic enhancement.
This parameter activates/deactivates NRCGI information to be sent by the SgNB during each SgNB addition or SgNB modification procedure.
This parameter activates/deactivates location reporting in SA.

This parameter activates/deactivates LTE-NR dynamic spectrum sharing.  If activated, sharing mode must be defined in each cell.    Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset if NRBTS.actSlowPrbPooling is equal to TRUE.  The gNB reset is not required and this parameter will be updated online If NRBTS.actSlowPrbPooling is equal to FALSE.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter activates/deactivates Minimization of Drive Test (MDT) trace report at gNB level.
This parameter activates/deactivates the multiple frequency band indicator (MFBI) for E-UTRA

Parameter name: Activate reporting of DL MAC SDU user throughput PM counters per NR P(S) cell
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates reporting of DL MAC SDU user throughput PM counters per NR P(S) cell

Parameter name: Activate IE maximum number of CC limit per FR gap
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the capability IE 'independentGapConfig-maxCC-r17' for UE to indicate to the gNB the maximum amount of configured CC serving cells that the UE can perform measurements for without the scheduling of dedicated measurement gaps by the gNB.

Parameter name: Activate measurement based secondary cell addition for NSA
