Description: This parameter activates/deactivates secondary cell addition for carrier aggregation based on UE measurement for NSA 3x.  Note: This parameter is applicable for A1-based secondary cell addition only.

Parameter name: Activate measurement based secondary cell addition for SA
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates secondary cell addition for carrier aggregation based on UE measurements for FR1 SA (Option 2). Measurements can be from event A1 or from event A4 or from both.

Parameter name: Activate power class determination based on MeNB power coordination for NSA cells
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates power class determination based on MeNB power coordination for NSA cells.    By default or if value 'deactivated' is configured, measurement profile selection procedure does not consider MeNB power coordination.

Parameter name: Activate measurement profile for CA-capable UEs
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the possibility to define dedicated measurement profiles for Carrier Aggregation capable UEs

Parameter name: Activate measurement profile reselection for CA
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates measurement profile reselection for carrier aggregation of SA cells.    By default or if value 'deactivated' is configured, measurement profile selection procedure does not consider if UE is in Carrier Aggregation or not.    If value 'pcInSaUlCaNotSupported' is configured, then NRMEASPR_MA_SA instances with configured NRMEASPR_MA_SA.pcCapabilityList.uePowerClass criterion are ignored if a measurement profile is selected when a SCell is used for uplink and downlink. Note that when the last SCell is released in uplink and downlink, and if NRMEASPR_MA_SA.pcCapabilityList.uePowerClass is configured for the cell, it is taken into account for the measurement profile reselection.    For UL CA only  If pcInSaUlCaSupported is set, then Power Class criterion is supported in DL+UL Carrier Aggregation and power class for the band combination is determined according to the effective power limitation calculated by Power Control.    For UL and DL CA  If pcInSaUlAndDlCaSupported is set, then Power Class criterion is supported in DL+UL and DL only Carrier Aggregation and power class for the band combination is determined according to the effective power limitation calculated by Power Control with consideration of the feature set.

This parameter activates/deactivates measurement profiles. If this feature is activated and there is no measurement profile mapping configured with NRCELL.measPrMaSAList for SA cells or NRCELL.measPrMaNSAList for NSA cells, or measurement profile mapping configuration has no matching criterion, or measurement profile has not been configured in the measurement profile mapping selected for the UE, then the legacy configuration from NRCELL is used for Intra-Frequency, NRHOIF for Inter-Frequency and NRHOIR for Inter-RAT Frequency measurements values.    Measurement profile configuration:  - New Radio Measurement Profile parameters in NRMEAS_PROFILE  - New Radio Measurement Profile for Intra-Frequency parameters in NRMEASPR_IAF  - New Radio Measurement Profile for Inter-Frequency parameters in NRMEASPR_IEF  - New Radio Measurement Profile for Inter-RAT Frequency parameters in NRMEASPR_IRF  - NRCELL measurement profile mapping parameters in NRCELL.measPrMaSAList  - NRCELL measurement profile mapping parameters in NRCELL.measPrMaNSAList    Measurement profile mapping configuration:  - New Radio Measurement Profile Mapping for SA parameters in NRMEASPR_MA_SA  - New Radio Measurement Profile Mapping for NSA parameters in NRMEASPR_MA_NSA

Parameter name: Activate measurement prioritization in coverage-based mobility
Description: This parameter activates / deactivates the measurement prioritization in coverage based mobility

Parameter name: Activate resolving MFBI DL CA measurement config conflicts
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the resolution of measurement configuration conflicts between SCell and potential target cells for inter-frequency mobility.

Parameter name: Activate multi-frequency band support for FR1 CA
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the multi-frequency band support for carrier aggregation for NR FR1.

Parameter name: Activate multi-frequency band support for FR2 DL CA
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the multi-frequency band support for carrier aggregation for NR FR2.    Note: For time being, this parameter is applicable in NSA mode only. In SA mode, this parameter is ignored.
This parameter activates/deactivates the mobility profiles
This parameter activates/deactivates the mobility profile reselection

Parameter name: Activate mobility retry to second best cell
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates one mobility retry to second best cell
This parameter activates/deactivates the Multiple VLAN interfaces feature.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate multi DRBs per NSA UE
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates multi DRBs per NSA UE in the gNB.
This parameter activates/deactivates the multi-frequency band feature.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter activates/deactivates multiple dedicated bandwidth parts (BWPs).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activation flag for extending the ngSetupRespTmr
Description: This Parameter is used to extend the ngSetupRespTmr to be used also for the case the NG Setup failure message does not include a Time to Wait indication.
This parameter activates/deactivates the NG-C flex (SA mode).
This parameter activates/deactivates non-GBR service differentiation according to the scheduling weight configuration.

Parameter name: Activate normal voice call fallback to LTE
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates normal voice fallback to LTE

Parameter name: Activate normal voice call fallback to LTE enhancement
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates EPS fallback enhancement for normal voice call which sends NAS PDU to the UE and NGAP: Initial Context Setup Response to the AMF.  If an NGAP: Initial Context Setup Request for normal voice call is received and the gNB decides to trigger EPS fallback, then:  - If this parameter is equal to TRUE, then NAS PDU is sent to the UE and NGAP: Initial Context Setup Response is sent to the AMF including the 'PDU Session Resource Setup Unsuccessful Transfer' with the cause 'IMS voice EPS fallback or RAT fallback triggered'.  - If this parameter is equal to FALSE, then NAS PDU is not sent to the UE and NGAP: Initial Context Setup Failure is sent to the AMF.

This parameter activates/deactivates New Radio CBRS (Citizens Broadband Radio Service).    A New Radio cell (NRCELL instance) is considered to be a CBRS cell if NRCELL.freqBandIndicatorNR is equal to 48.

This parameter activates/deactivates the handling of external alarm for energy-efficient emergency activation for the NR cells listed in NRPSGRP_EEEA.eeeaCellList.    If this parameter is equal to TRUE, then energy-efficient emergency activation is activated for all the NR cells listed in NRPSGRP_EEEA.eeeaCellList. This means that, if an external alarm is raised, it can wake up cells from this list from power saving state.

Parameter name: Activate NR cell-level extended configurations for MIMO muting and cell switch off
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates New Radio cell-level extended configurations for MIMO muting and cell switch off.

This parameter activates/deactivates NR load-based power saving feature.  When it is equal to TRUE, intra-gNB NR cells that provide service to the same coverage area may be automatically switched off/on according to the aggregate load across the set of NR cells (Power Saving Group).    Note:  There is no coordination between load-based power saving and the technologies that are configured for RF Sharing.

Parameter name: Activate NR load-based reduced TX power saving
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the NR load-based MIMO muting feature. When the feature is activated, intra-gNB NR cells that provide service to the same coverage area may have TX-Paths automatically switched off/on according to the aggregate load across the set of NR cells (Power Group).

Parameter name: Activate NR load-based mMIMO TX power saving
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates NR load-based mMIMO TX power saving.  If this parameter is equal to FALSE, then updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE, then updating this parameter will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter from false to true will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate mixed mode load-based power saving
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates mixed mode load-based power saving.

Parameter name: Activate NR UL Received Interference Power including thermal Noise measurement
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the NR UL Received Interference Power including thermal Noise measurement.    The possible values are the following:  - disabled means no NR UL Received Interference Power including thermal Noise measurement is reported;  - enabledWithPRACH_PUCCH_F1 means PRACH and PUCCH F1 channels are also included during the measurement;  - enabledWithoutPRACH means PRACH channels are excluded during the measurement;  - enabledWithoutPUCCH_F1 means PUCCH F1 channels are excluded during the measurement;  - enabledWithoutPRACH_PUCCH_F1 means both PRACH and PUCCH F1 channels are excluded during the measurement.    Note(s):  - PUSCH and PUCCH (except F1) are always included in the measurement when reported.  - This measurement is not supported by the BTS having BBMOD hardware variant ABIL or ABILL
This parameter activates/deactivates the NRPMQAP profiles.

Parameter name: Activate NSA PSCell load balancing in FR1
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the PSCell load balancing in FR1 during NSA initial access
This parameter activates/deactivates NSA network slicing support

Parameter name: Activate ANR for EN-DC with resolution of unknown cells
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates ANR for EN-DC with resolution of unknown cells (NR-reportCGI).    Note: A separate activation parameter is used to enable automatic removal of unused NR neighbor relations (NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval)

Parameter name: Activate ANR for EN-DC with resolution of unknown cells based on inter frequency UE measurements
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates ANR for EN-DC with resolution of unknown cells based on inter frequency UE measurements (NR-reportCGI).    Note: A separate activation parameter is used to enable automatic removal of unused NR neighbor relations (NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval)

Parameter name: Activate ignoring of Old AMF IE in specific NGAP procedures
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the handling or ignoring of Old AMF IE in specific NGAP procedures - Initial Context Setup Request and Downlink NAS Transport messages:  - If this parameter is equal to FALSE, the Old AMF IE is checked  - If this parameter is equal to TRUE, the Old AMF IE is ignored

This parameter activates/deactivates O-RAN CU-Plane phase 1, which introduces the O-RAN compliant eCPRI C-Plane and U-Plane for NR TDD FR1 on ABIO/ABIOL/ABIP/ASOH (Nokia's O-DU), according to DCM TP 3D705 Interoperable O-RAN LLS interface and profile specification (Profile Categorization).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter activates/deactivates UE overheating assistance handling which consists in deactivating, or keeping inactive, UE configured SCells according to the UE indication via the field reducedCCsDL in the Overheating Assistance Information IE of the RRC: UE Assistance Information message.
This parameter activates/deactivates the overload protection due to L2 scheduling overload.
This parameter activates/deactivates the overload protection due to L2 signalling overload.
This parameter activates/deactivates PCMD report at gNB level.
This parameter activates/deactivates paging.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to TRUE.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter activates/deactivates paging enhancements. The possible values are the following:  - 'disabled' means paging enhancements are deactivated.  - 'postponedPaging' means that if paging record cannot fit the Paging Record List (maximum size is reached) in the first Paging Frame (PF) / Paging Occasion (PO), then the next one, if applicable, will be used until the paging record lifetime expires which is equal to default paging DRX cycle duration. This gives the opportunity not to discard such paging requests during paging overload.  - 'pagingStratForRrcInact' means that, if enabled, paging strategy for RAN Paging of UE in RRC_INACTIVE State is applied. RAN Paging prioritization and/or RAN Paging repetitions are supported based on DRB profile. Postponed Paging is also enabled.

Parameter name: Activate partial slot UL CCE count for DSS cells
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates partial slot UL CCE count for DSS cells.  More precisely, for EN DSS NR load reporting to CRM,  - if this parameter is equal to TRUE, then the PRBs in slots that can be scheduled from slots 5/9 are considered as available only when there are enough CCEs to schedule UL traffic.  - if this parameter is equal to FALSE, then the PRBs in slots reachable from slots 5/9 are considered as available.  Note. To take the parameter value change into use, it is required to lock and unlock the corresponding DSS cells.

Parameter name: Activate PDCP HFN desynchronization detection algorithm
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the HFN/SN desynchronization detection and recovery action functionality.  When activated, this functionality enables to recover frozen bearers  faster due to HFN issues or corruption of PDCP SN at UE for the packets sent in UL direction.

This parameter activates/deactivates a PDCP/RLC buffer congestion mechanism.  Buffer congestion is detected via the NRBTS.pdcpBufUsageThreshold/NRBTS.rlcBufUsageThreshold parameters.    The possible values are the following:  - disabled meaning PDCP/RLC buffer congestion is disabled  - gbrOnly meaning that the gNB will start discarding non-GBR packet when buffer congestion is detected for a GBR bearer  - gbrNonGbr meaning that the gNB will start discarding non-GBR packet when buffer congestion is detected for the GBR or non-GBR bearers  - rrcInactive meaning that the gNB will start discarding non-GBR packet when buffer congestion is detected for the RRC Inactive bearer  - gbrAndRrcInactive meaning that the gNB will start discarding non-GBR packet when buffer congestion is detected for the GBR or RRC Inactive bearer  - gbrNonGbrAndRrcInactive meaning that the gNB will start discarding non-GBR packet when buffer congestion is detected for the GBR bearer or the non-GBR bearer or RRC Inactive bearer  - bufferOverflowProtection meaning that the gNB will activate 5G-L2-HI buffer overflow protection.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
Range and step: disabled (0), gbrOnly (1), gbrNonGbr (2), rrcInactive (3), gbrAndRrcInactive (4), gbrNonGbrAndRrcInactive (5), bufferOverflowProtection (6)

Parameter name: Activate reporting of DL MAC SDU nonGBR user throughput PM counters for each Carrier Combination
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates reporting of DL MAC SDU nonGBR user throughput PM counters for each Carrier Combination

Parameter name: Activate reporting of UL RLC SDU nonGBR user throughput PM counters for each Carrier Combination
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates reporting of UL RLC SDU nonGBR user throughput PM counters for each Carrier Combination

Parameter name: Activate reporting of DL MAC SDU user throughput PM counters per NR serving cell
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates reporting of DL MAC SDU user throughput PM counters per NR serving cell.

Parameter name: Activate persistent storage of system-set managed object instance(s)
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the persistent storage of set-by-the-system managed object instance(s) during system upgrade.  This parameter is only applicable to LTEENB managed object instances.

Parameter name: Activate PLMN based cell reserved for operator use
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates cell reserved for operator use functionality per PLMN group.

Parameter name: Activate handling of higher priority procedures during ANR
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the handling of higher priority procedures during ANR

This parameter activates/deactivates the gNB prioritisation of redirection to LTE in SA calls for setup of VoNR bearers if the inter-RAT parameters are available in UE capability.  Only If redirection is not possible, then VoNR call will be admitted into gNB.

Parameter name: Activate proactive re-sending of RLC PDUs
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the proactive re-sending of RLC PDUs.

Parameter name: Activate time alignment UL grant reduction based on PUCCH format 3
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates time alignment UL grant reduction based on PUCCH format 3.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE and NRBTS.actTimeAlignExtension is equal to TRUE and NRCELL.pucchModeSelect is equal to 'longPucch', the gNB reduces UL grant for time alignment based on PUCCH format 3 to improve the UL grant congestion caused by NRBTS.actTimeAlignExtension equal to TRUE.  This parameter is ignored if NRBTS.actTimeAlignExtension is equal to FALSE or NRCELL.pucchModeSelect is equal to 'shortPucch'.
This parameter activates/deactivates per band, IE capability for pusch-RepetitionTypeA-v16c0.

This parameter activates/deactivates 5G RAN sharing.  If equal to TRUE, then at least one NRPLMNSET_NSA or NRPLMNSET_SA instance shall be configured for each NR cell. In this case, the Primary PLMN (defined by NRBTS.mcc, NRBTS.mnc and NRBTS.mncLength) is not assigned to each cell automatically.  If equal to FALSE, then each NR cell is automatically assigned to the gNB Master PLMN defined by NRBTS.mcc, NRBTS.mnc and NRBTS.mncLength, regardless of the NRPLMNSET_NSA and NRPLMNSET_SA settings.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter activates/deactivates the enhancements to support RAN sharing for up to 10 PLMNs per gNB and transport separation for up to 10 operators.

Parameter name: Activation of Reduced Periodic CSI Processing
Description: This parameter enables reduced periodic CSI processing.    When activated, reduced periodic CSI processing functionality shall be enabled in FR1 TDD and FR1 FDD cells with:  - NRCELL-actHighSpeedCell set to false  - The number of RRC connected UEs in the cell is beyond a certain level.

This parameter activates/deactivates reduced periodic SRS processing.    When activated, reduced periodic SRS processing can be enabled in FR1 TDD cells having:  - NRCELL.actDlSrsBm equal to TRUE or NRCELL.actUlSrsBm equal to TRUE, and  - NRCELL.actHighSpeedCell equal to FALSE, and  - NRCELL.actEcpri72e equal to FALSE, and  - The number of UEs that have p-SRS configured larger than 20 within the cell.    Note: If the functionality is enabled and the number of UEs that have p-SRS configured in the cell is reduced to less than 10, the functionality is disabled.

Parameter name: Activate RRC Connection Release with redirection
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates RRC Connection Release with redirection

This parameter activates/deactivates special handling of A2 Measurement report for redirection with RSRP value 0 for the "PCell": UE context release request to AMF with cause value "user-inactivity" and releasing the UE without redirection when gNB receives an A2 Measurement Report with RSRP value 0 for the "PCell"
This parameter activates/deactivates RAT/Frequency Selection Priority (RFSP) index
This parameter activates/deactivates robust header compression for SA option 2 only.

Parameter name: Activate RRC Inactive state transitions under same gNB (SA mode)
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the RRC Inactive state transitions under same gNB (SA mode).

Parameter name: Activate RRC inactive state transitions under same gNB (SA mode) for RedCap
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the RedCap UEs transitions from the RRC_CONNECTED state to the RRC_INACTIVE state under the same gNB (SA mode)

Parameter name: Activate UE Assistance Information to report preference on the RRC state
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates UE Assistance Information to report preference on the RRC state in a capable 5G-UE
This parameter activates/deactivates the NR RTWP measurement.

Parameter name: Activate state transition and call processing (Option 2) for DU
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates RRC state transition and call processing for the gNB-DU  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate SCell release on bad SCell radio link quality
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the SCell release on bad SCell radio link quality (RLQ).  When this is activated, the gNB immediately releases SCells that are deactivated due to bad SCell RLQ or reported with CQI=0  Note: Currently, this parameter is applicable for FR1 only.

Parameter name: Activate SCell release for inactive SCells
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the release for inactive SCells after no data activity for longer than the SCell inactivity release timer (NRCELL.sCellInactivityReleaseTimer).  Note: Currently, this parameter is applicable for FR1 only.

Parameter name: Activate SCell swap for FR1 CA
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates SCell swap functionality for NR FR1 carrier aggregation.    Supported functionality:  a6BasedSa: A6 measurement based SCell swap for SA users
This parameter activates/deactivates the subscriber profile ID (SPID) for RAT/frequency priority

Parameter name: Activate enhanced HO delta configuration for multi-vendor inter-operability testing for SA
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates enhancements to HO delta configuration for multi-vendor inter-operability testing for SA deployment.

Parameter name: Activate special DRX profile for intra-frequency ANR for SA
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the special DRX profile for intra-frequency ANR for SA.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to TRUE.

Parameter name: Activate ANR for SA with resolution of unknown E-UTRA cells
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates ANR for SA with resolution of unknown E-UTRA Inter-RAT cells (ECGI report).    Note: A separate activation parameter is used to enable automatic removal of unused EUTRA neighbor relations (NRANR.actAutoEutraNbRemoval)

Parameter name: Activate ANR for SA with resolution of unknown cells
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates ANR for 5G SA with resolution of unknown cells (NR-reportCGI).    Note: A separate activation parameter is used to enable automatic removal of unused NR neighbor relations (NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval)

Parameter name: Activate ANR for SA with resolution of unknown cells based on inter frequency UE measurements
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates ANR for SA with resolution of unknown cells based on inter frequency UE measurements (NR-reportCGI).    Note: A separate activation parameter is used to enable automatic removal of unused NR neighbor relations (NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval)

Parameter name: Activate scheduled UE per TTI pooling
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates scheduled UE per TTI pooling.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate scheduling fairness enhancement in L2 UL overload control
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates scheduling fairness enhancement in L2 UL overload control  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter activates/deactivates secondary data usage report service.  The secondary data usage report service consists in event and periodical reporting. If this service is activated then event reporting is activated by default. Periodical reporting could be activated on top of event reporting by the parameter NRBTS.periodicalDataUsageReportTimer.

Parameter name: Activate segmentation of UE capability information in UL
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates segmentation of UE capability information in UL

Parameter name: Activate separate IP address for NSA3x NR X2-U PDCP data split traffic
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the support of separate local IP addresses for NSA3x NR X2-U PDCP data split traffic and X2-U PDCP data forwarding traffic.    If equal to TRUE, separate local IP addresses shall be used for X2-U PDCP data split traffic and X2-U PDCP data forwarding traffic.  If equal to FALSE, X2-U PDCP data split traffic and X2-U PDCP data forwarding traffic will use single local IP address.

Parameter name: Activate separate PDU session release due to GTP error
Description: This parameter activates / deactivates the PDU session release instead of UE context release due to NG-U GTP error.

Parameter name: Activate separate PDU session release due to RLC error
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the PDU session release instead of UE context release due to RLC error.
This parameter activates/deactivates service-aware PDCP configuration per DRB profile, including PDCP discard timer for uplink, and out-of-order delivery for downlink and uplink.
This parameter activates/deactivates the slice aware admission control in the gNB.

Parameter name: Activate slice aware scheduler in DL
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the slice aware scheduler in downlink in the gNB.

Parameter name: Activate slice aware scheduler in UL and enhancements
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the slice aware scheduler in uplink in the gNB.  This parameter also activates/deactivates the enhanced Slice Volume Control (SVC) algorithm and mixed resource groups for SA and NSA to be used for slice aware scheduler both in downlink and uplink.
This parameter activates/deactivates extension of number of slices.

Parameter name: Activate PDU session setup for a non-configured slice
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the possibility to accept a PDU session setup even if the related slice is not configured in the gNB by fallback to a default slice instead of rejecting the PDU setup entirely
This parameter activates/deactivates slow PRB pooling.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate slow PRB pooling enhancements in FDD FR1
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates slow PRB pooling enhancements in FDD FR1
This parameter activates/deactivates SMTC centering while configuring A3/A5 measurements in asynchronous networks
This parameter activates/deactivates spatial stream pooling.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate SPID based network slicing for NSA
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the Subscriber Profile ID (SPID) based network slicing for NSA in the gNB.

Parameter name: Activate SPID or RFSP based inactivity detection for UE
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the SPID or RFSP based UE inactivity handling feature for UE

Parameter name: Activate split of UE capability enquiry message for NR and E-UTRA
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the possibility to split the request of UE Capability for NR and E-UTRA.  If this parameter is enabled, NR is requested during ICS and EUTRA (if needed) after ICS. If this parameter is disabled, both are requested during ICS.
This parameter activates/deactivates subscriber trace report at gNB level.

Parameter name: Activate switch radio link monitoring configuration
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the releasing and adding back of the RadioLinkMonitoringConfig IE, when source configuration includes failureDetectionResources in the RadioLinkMonitoringConfig message.
This parameter activates/deactivates TDD CSI-IM rate matching.
This parameter activates/deactivates the CSI-RS allocation optimization for FR1 TDD. This parameter indicates whether sub-band TRS will be enabled.

This parameter activates/deactivates TDD pre-pooling.  It shall be equal to TRUE for certain baseband configurations with:  - at least one NRCELL instance allocated on an ABIL board with NRCELL.cellTechnology is equal to 1 (corresponding to TDD) and  - for all the NRCELL instances which are mapped to the same ABIL board, the total UL streams (referring to NRCELL.nrCellType) is greater than 4.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate time domain resource allocation fallback
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates time domain resource (TDRA) allocation fallback.    When it is equal to TRUE, the use of dedicated PUSCH TDRA list is abandoned supporting UEs with older SW versions (which do not manage properly the release or the addition of the dedicated PUSCH TDRA list) avoiding HO failures between gNBs on 20B/5G21A SW level and newer SW release versions or vice versa. However, as a consequence, features requiring the support of dedicated TDRA list such as 5GC000545, 5GC001817 and CB007220 should not be activated.

Parameter name: Activate reporting of DL PDCP and UL RLC throughput distribution PM counters
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates reporting of DL PDCP and UL RLC throughput PM counters.  This parameter controls both PMQAP and Non PMQAP throughput distribution PM counters
This parameter activates/deactivates the time alignment extensions

This parameter activates/deactivates the overload protection mechanism due to debug trace streaming.  More precisely, if this parameter is equal to TRUE, this activates the mechanism to automatically stop the ongoing streaming of debug logs in case of overload detection from:  - NR UP logs (L2Hi-CU and L2Hi-DU)  - NR CP trace streaming  - NR L1 logs

Parameter name: Activate non-random PRB allocation for transient phase UEs
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the allocation of PRBs to a transient phase UE (UE undergoing an RRC reconfiguration) at the start of the UE's dedicated bandwidth part (BWP).  When this parameter is equal to FALSE, the PRBs allocated to the transient phase UE will be allocated at a random location in the UE's active BWP.  Note that PRB randomization for transient phase UEs only occurs for UEs in FDD cells when their active BWP has the same size as the initial BWP.

Parameter name: Activate transport separation for NSA RAN sharing
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates 5G transport separation for NSA RAN sharing.    If its value is equal to TRUE, different S1-U IP addresses can be configured in one system module/gNB-CU for each operator sharing the gNB. The operators can use shared or dedicated X2-C/X2-U IP addresses in one system module/gNB-CU depending on whether the connected eNBs are shared or dedicated. In cloud gNB, different F1-U IP addresses can be configured for each operator sharing the gNB-CU/gNB-vDU.    If its value is equal to FALSE, the first S1-U IP address, first X2-C and first X2-U IP address of the system module/gNB-CU for the gNB will be used. In cloud gNB, the first F1-U IP address of the gNB-CU/gNB-vDU will be used.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate transport separation for SA RAN sharing
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates 5G transport separation for SA RAN sharing.    If its value is equal to TRUE, different Xn-U, Xn-C, NG-C, NG-U and Xg-U IP addresses can be configured in one system module/gNB-CU for each operator sharing the gNB. In cloud gNB, different F1-U IP addresses can be configured for each operator sharing the gNB-CU/gNB-vDU.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate user plane integrity protection for user plane integrity protection set to 'Preferred'
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the user plane integrity protection when the User Plane Security Enforcement information is provided by the SMF to the NG-RAN with user plane security policies for a PDU session having user plane integrity protection set to 'Preferred', for SA mode DRBs.    NRBTS.upipSupportForPreferredNrDcFlag may disable this setting for NR-DC eligible PDU session on MN side. This parameter is not applicable to NR-DC user on SN side.
This parameter activates/deactivates automatic unified access control.  When activated, access attempts may be barred for certain access categories and access identities during high load or overload.

This parameter activates/deactivates UAC barring per PLMN.  When activated, it causes the broadcast of uac-BarringPerPLMN-List and individualPLMNList for uac-AccessCategory1-SelectionAssistanceInfo in SIB1.

Parameter name: Activate UE capability enquiry after Xn based handover
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates triggering of the UE capability enquiry procedure for the purpose of carrier aggregation after incoming Xn based inter-gNB handover for SA mode, if band combinations in the UE capability do not match the bands in the gNB
This parameter activates/deactivates UE delta configuration optimization.
This parameter activates/deactivates the UE initiated RLF feature  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter activates/deactivates the UL UE AMBR limitation for SA non-GBR DRBs.

This parameter activates/deactivates the method for the calculation of UL CA UE PM counters.    If equal to TRUE, the number of CA UEs in the current cell configured as a SCell, which have x number of configured SCell is incremented  If equal to FALSE, the number of CA UEs in the current cell configured as a UL SCell, which have x number of configured SCell is incremented.

Parameter name: Activate UL CA aware idle mode mobility steering
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates UL CA aware IMM steering.

Parameter name: Activate unlimited data rate in downlink
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates unlimited data rate in downlink.  When set to TRUE, this deactivates the restriction on the maximum data rate in downlink supported by the UE calculated as defined at 3GPP 38.306 section 4.1.2 if UE supported Scaling Factor is 1. More precisely, in that case, the gNB will not limit the data rate in downlink scheduled for the UE if the UE omits the Scaling Factor IE in the signaled UE capability for the selected band combination.
This parameter activates/deactivates unsupported IEs handling

Parameter name: Activate unsupported IEs handling in release 23R4
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates unsupported IEs handling in release 23R4
This parameter activates/deactivates user plane integrity protection for SA mode DRBs  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate use cause to identify SN initiated
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the identification of whether the SgNB Modification Request is received due to SN initiated reason or due to MN initiated reasons.  This parameter is ignored if both NRBTS.actInterFreqIntraGnbMobilityNSA and NRBTS.actInterFreqInterGnbMobilityNSA are equal to FALSE.
This parameter activates/deactivates UE context preemption.  Updating this parameter might provoke reset of cells under this gNB-- gNB takes decision of reset necessity.

Parameter name: Activate voice fallback to LTE for B1 meas-based redirection
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the voice fallback to LTE for B1 measurement-based redirection

Parameter name: Activate VoNR prioritization during handover preparation
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates VoNR prioritization during handover preparation

Parameter name: Activate voice fallback to LTE during handover preparation
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates voice fallback to LTE via call setup prioritization during handover preparation
This parameter activates/deactivates the VoNR related PM counters
This parameter activates/deactivates X2 configuration transfer

Parameter name: Activate XnAP UE security capabilities new mode
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the new mode of gNB encoding/decoding XnAP UE security capabilities (introduced by 3GPP CR R3-214322).  If the new mode is activated, these capabilities start from the second bit (Bit 1), else (old mode) these capabilities start from the first bit (Bit 0).

This parameter indicates the activity notification level for SA and NR-DC-SN UE. Regardless its value, in NR-DC SN gNB, the XNAP Activity Notification procedure concerns  data traffic activity for the UE.

Parameter name: Allow slow static NDM-SRS PRB pooling
Description: This parameter indicates if slow static NDM-SRS PRB pooling is allowed or not.  If NRBTS.actBbPoolTddFr1 is equal to TRUE, more NR cells can be deployed in the half board of BBMOD or SMOD, if there are more than 3 NR cells with SRS enabled deployed in the half board of BBMOD or SMOD, such as 4 NR cells with SRS enabled deployed in half ASOE or 6 NR cells with SRS enabled deployed in half ABIP, then it is required to set NRBTS.allowSlowPrbPoolingStatNdmSrs to TRUE. For NRBTS with ABIP and eCPRI 7-2a fronthaul interface, NRBTS.allowSlowPrbPoolingStatNdmSrs can be set to FALSE regardless of the number of NR cells with SRS enabled deployed in half ABIP.    Note 1:  For Max 6 cells/half ABIP or 12 cells/ABIP configuration,  If allowSlowPrbPoolingStatNdmSrs is equal to FALSE and below conditions are fulfilled:    - MRBTS/NRBTS/NRCELL/tddFrameStructure.frameStructureType is equal to 'semiStatic'  - MRBTS/NRBTS/NRCELL/tddFrameStructure.ulDlDataSlotRatio is equal to '1/4'(for 5GC001208) or MRBTS/NRBTS/NRCELL/tddFrameStructure.ulDlDataSlotRatio is equal to '3/7'(for 5GC001070)  - NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm.srsUePeriodicityInput is set to 20(slots20)  - NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm-maxNumUeSrs is equal to 1 or 2    then NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm-srsUePeriodicityOutput will be set by system to 20(slots20)  Otherwise, NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm-srsUePeriodicityOutput will be set by system to greater than 20(slots20).    Note 2: NR cells with SRS enabled means that (NRCELL.actDlSrsBm is equal to TRUE and/or NRCELL.actUlSrsBm is equal to TRUE) or NRCELL.actHPPosMethodOptList doesn't contain element equal to 'disabled'.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This timer indicates the time period (delay) used when the timer approach for GUAMI removal is employed.  This timer is optionally started when a NGAP: AMF Status Indication Message is received from the AMF.

This parameter indicates which priority access calls (High Priority Access or Multimedia Priority Service or both) may use the dedicated radio resource pools defined by NRCELL-numOfRadioResReservForPa and NRDU-numOfDrbsReservForPa.  Configuring/Updating/Removing this parameter might provoke reset of cells under this gNB-- gNB takes decision of reset necessity.  Note: All priority access calls may use emergency radio resource pools, regardless of this parameter settings.

This parameter indicates the time to wait for B1 measurement report from redirection to E-UTRAN.    After voice fallback or emergency fallback is triggered for redirection to a E-UTRAN carrier, a timer is started with duration defined by this parameter. This timer is stopped after B1 measurement report with valid target E-UTRAN carrier(s) is received.
This parameter indicates the list of BSR packages installed in the gNB.  It contains the list of BSR package names that are downloaded and available for use in the BTS.
This parameter indicates the blocking state of the New Radio BTS

Parameter name: Discard initial number of dropped PDCP SDUs
Description: This parameter indicates the initial number of PDCP SDUs packets discarded in the event of a buffer overflow threat.

Parameter name: Discard initial number of dropped RLC SDUs
Description: This parameter indicates the initial number of RLC SDUs packets discarded in the event of a buffer overflow threat.
This parameter indicates the threshold which the buffer will start to be protected by limiting incoming traffic.

This parameter defines the differentiated services code point (DSCP) value assigned to the gNB-CU and gNB-DU Control Plane traffic for all interfaces including F1-C, NG-C, X2-C and Xn-C.  DSCP marking must be the same on gNB-CU and all associated gNB-DUs.

Parameter name: CA configuration backoff timer for UE overheating
Description: This parameter indicates the time during which the gNB does not attempt CA after releasing all of the SCells for a UE and at least one SCell was inactive due to UE overheating.    If this parameter is set to 0, the timer is not started and the UE is not prohibited from SCell Addition after last SCell release of inactive SCell due to UE overheating.  Note: Currently this parameter is applicable for FR1 carrier aggregation only.

This parameter indicates the specific maximum CA configuration support that is activated in the gNB.  In particular, this parameter limits the maximum number of carrier components in UL and DL that can be aggregated in the gNB.  This parameter is ignored if NRBTS.actCarrierAggregation is equal to FALSE.  This parameter is applicable only for aggregation of FR2/TDD NSA or NR-DC NR Cells.

Parameter name: CA configuration support for FR2 SA
Description: This parameter indicates the specific maximum CA configuration support that is activated in the gNB.  In particular, this parameter limits the maximum number of carrier components in UL and DL that can be aggregated in the gNB.  This parameter is ignored if NRBTS.actCarrierAggregationFr2SA is equal to FALSE.  This parameter is applicable only for aggregation of FR2 TDD SA NR Cells.
This parameter indicates the DL data bundling interval at RLC entity when carrier aggregation is configured (NRBTS.actCaDlDataBundling is equal to TRUE)

Parameter name: UL CA BC power limit rule
Description: This parameter indicates the power limit rule for uplink inter-band carrier aggregation band combinations.  The possible values are:  - 'disabled': PPowerClass, CA is defined by maximum UE power specified in TS38.101-1 Table 6.2A.1.3-1 UE Power Class for uplink inter-band CA  - 'enabled': PPowerClass, CA is replaced by 10 log10 SUM (pPowerClass, c) presented in TS 38.101-1 chapter 6.2A.4.1.3. This enables a higher power for uplink band combination for uplink inter-band CA.  - 'p-NR-FR1 not signaled': Power class of cell group not limited.
This parameter indicates the list of supported AS ciphering algorithms. Each algorithm is identified by the parameter name, and the assigned value determines the algorithm preference
This parameter indicates the preference for the Null ciphering algorithm. A lower value represents a lower preference and 0 does not admit the algorithm.
This parameter indicates the preference for the SNOW 3G-based algorithm for ciphering. A lower value represents a lower preference and 0 does not admit the algorithm.
This parameter indicates the preference for the AES-based algorithm for ciphering. A lower value represents a lower preference and 0 does not admit the algorithm.
This parameter indicates the preference for the ZUC-based algorithm for ciphering. A lower value represents a lower preference and 0 does not admit the algorithm.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This structure configures the load balancing parameters for CPUE
This parameter defines an override flag to allow for new UE context allocation to happen even after CPUE resiliency threshold has been reached

Parameter name: CSI resource overlap with measurement gaps
Description: This parameter indicates whether overlap between CSI resources and measurement gaps is checked.  The gNB shall accept the measurement gap setup with or without checking for CSI resources overlap based on the configured value.
This parameter gathers parameters for 5G C-plane counter measures handling

Parameter name: Reject beam switch due to overload
Description: This parameter enables/disables the counter measure of rejecting beam switch or port switch for NSA / NR-DC-SN UEs and non-emergency and non-priority access SA UEs during overload.

Parameter name: Discard A4 timer expiry for NSA due to overload
Description: This parameter enables/disables the counter measure of discarding A4 timer expiry for NSA during overload

Parameter name: Reject NSA addition blocking due to overload
Description: This parameter enables/disables the counter measure of rejecting SgNB Addition Request messages from MeNB or SNode Addition Request from MN gNB during overload.

Parameter name: Reject NSA E-RAB addition blocking due to overload
Description: This parameter enables/disables the counter measure of rejecting SgNB Modification Request messages from MeNB for E-RAB additions during overload

Parameter name: Reject NSA mobility blocking due to overload
Description: This parameter enables/disables the counter measure of rejecting intra/inter MeNB mobility and Intra-gNB PSCell during overload.

Parameter name: Reject NSA intra/inter MeNB mobility blocking due to overload
Description: This parameter enables/disables the counter measure of rejecting intra/inter MeNB mobility during overload

Parameter name: Discard measurements for NSA due to overload
Description: This parameter enables/disables the counter measure of discarding measurements for NSA during overload

Parameter name: Reject SN initiated modification due to overload
Description: This parameter enables/disables the counter measure of rejecting SNode Modification Required from secondary node (SN) during overload.

Parameter name: Discard A4 timer expiry for SA due to overload
Description: This parameter enables/disables the counter measure of discarding A4 timer expiry for SA during overload

Parameter name: Reject incoming HO due to overload
Description: This parameter enables/disables the counter measure of rejecting incoming handover of non-emergency and non-priority access UEs during overload.

Parameter name: Discard measurements for SA due to overload
Description: This parameter enables/disables the counter measure of discarding measurements for SA during overload

Parameter name: Reject PDU session resource setup for SA due to overload
Description: This parameter enables/disables the counter measure of rejecting PDU Session Resource Setup and RRC Resume for non-emergency and non-priority access SA UEs during overload.

Parameter name: Reject RRC connection request for SA due to overload
Description: This parameter enables/disables the counter measure of rejecting of non-emergency and non-priority access RRC Connection Request and RRC Resume Request1 messages from UE during overload.

Parameter name: CU UE ID to link mapping update delay
Description: This parameter indicates how often the gNB-CU UE ID to link mapping should be updated in the SDL database.  The gNB-CU entity, responsible for storing this information, shall wait this specified time after the last SDL update of the information mentioned above before sending next update.  In between SDL updates, the gNB-CU entity will aggregate pending updates for all UEs.    There might be multiple instances of gNB-CU entities updating this information.    The value 'never' shall be used only in deployments with single baseband card or single card deployments like ASOE. Using this value for configuration with multiple baseband cards or cloud deployments will result in disabling of cleaning up of peer NE resources during gNB-CU internal failures handling.

Parameter name: Deactivate enhanced PRB pooling UL MU-MIMo
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the usage of enhanced PRB pooling algorithm introduced in UL for optimal PRB distribution between cells when UL MU-MIMO is enabled. The introduced enhancement includes consideration of PRB utilization of secondary subcells as additional factor for the PRB distribution by the PRB pooling algorithm.

This parameter indicates the maximum allowed offset (delta, unit: dB) in RSRP value of FR1 cell to be selected for SgNB addition.    The FR1 cell is allowed to be selected for initial access during the SgNB addition procedure if at least one of the two following conditions is met:  - RSRP of the cell to be selected >= (highest RSRP among the candidate cells + NRBTS.deltaRsrpFromBestCell)  - RSRQ of the cell to be selected >= (highest RSRQ among the candidate cells + NRBTS.deltaRsrqFromBestCell).

This parameter indicates the maximum allowed offset (delta, unit: dB) in RSRQ value of FR1 cell to be selected for SgNB addition.    The FR1 cell is allowed to be selected for initial access during the SgNB addition procedure if at least one of the two following conditions is met:  - RSRP of the cell to be selected >= (highest RSRP among the candidate cells + NRBTS.deltaRsrpFromBestCell)  - RSRQ of the cell to be selected >= (highest RSRQ among the candidate cells + NRBTS.deltaRsrqFromBestCell).
This parameter indicates the list of distinguished names representing the gNB E2 node IP addresses.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV4 instance representing the primary IPv4 address of the gNB-CU-CP E2 node.  Example: MRBTS-1/NRBTS1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV6 instance representing the primary IPv6 address of the gNB-CU-CP E2 node.  Example: MRBTS-1/NRBTS1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1
This parameter defines the monitoring period for non-GBR DRBs to update the DL UE AMBR limit.
This parameter defines the frequency of averaging for the incoming DL data rate for the non-GBR DRBs to update the DL UE AMBR limit.

Parameter name: Zero rate monitoring duration for DL AMBR
Description: This parameter defines the duration of monitoring the zero input data rate to reduce the DL AMBR for the non-GBR DRBs.

Parameter name: Stand alone UE DRB inactivity timer
Description: This timer indicates the time period for the indication of the DRB inactivity in both DL and UL directions for SA UE.  If this parameter is equal to 0, then this timer is off.  Note: NRBTS.drbRrcInactInactivityTimerSA is used for RRC Inactive state.

Parameter name: Stand alone UE 5QI1 DRB inactivity timer
Description: This parameter indicates the time period for the indication of the DRB inactivity in both DL and UL directions for 5QI1 DRB of SA UE and taken into account only when NRBTS.activityNotificationLevelSA is equal to 'drb'.    If this parameter is equal to 0, then this timer is off.    The recommended value for this parameter is 7200 (s)

Parameter name: Stand alone UE 5QI5 DRB inactivity timer
Description: This parameter indicates the time period for the indication of the DRB inactivity in both DL and UL directions for 5QI5 DRB of SA UE and taken into account only when NRBTS.activityNotificationLevelSA is equal to 'drb'.    If this parameter is equal to 0, then this timer is off.    The recommended value for this parameter is 7200 (s)

Parameter name: Stand alone UE DRB inactivity timer for RedCap
Description: This timer indicates the time period for the indication of the DRB inactivity in both DL and UL directions for RedCap SA UEs.    It is recommended to use a value lower than drbInactivityTimerSA for the non RedCap UEs, which is:  - NRDRB.drbInactivityTimerSA if configured and NRBTS.actAdditionalSliceSupport is equal to TRUE, or  - SNSSAI.drbInactivityTimerSA if configured and NRBTS.actAdditionalSliceSupport is equal to TRUE and NRDRB.drbInactivityTimerSA is not configured, or  - NRBTS.drbInactivityTimerSA if configured and NRBTS.actAdditionalSliceSupport is equal to FALSE.    If this parameter is not configured, then the value of drbInactivityTimerSA for the non RedCap UEs is applicable.  If this parameter is equal to 0, then the timer is off.

Parameter name: RRC Inactive UE DRB inactivity timer for SA
Description: This timer defines the time period for the indication of the DRB inactivity in both DL and UL directions for RRC Inactive capable SA UEs.  If this parameter is equal to 0, then this timer is off.

Parameter name: RRC inactive UE DRB inactivity timer for RedCap SA
Description: This timer indicates the time period for the indication of the DRB inactivity in both DL and UL directions for RRC inactive capable RedCap SA UEs.    It is recommended to use a value lower than drbRrcInactInactivityTimerSA for the non RedCap UEs, which is:  - NRDRB.drbRrcInactInactivityTimerSA if configured and NRBTS.actAdditionalSliceSupport is equal to TRUE, or  - SNSSAI.drbRrcInactInactivityTimerSA if configured and NRBTS.actAdditionalSliceSupport is equal to TRUE and NRDRB.drbRrcInactInactivityTimerSA is not configured, or  - NRBTS.drbRrcInactInactivityTimerSA if configured and NRBTS.actAdditionalSliceSupport is equal to FALSE.    If this parameter is not configured, then the value of drbRrcInactInactivityTimerSA for the non RedCap UEs is applicable.  If this parameter is equal to 0, then the timer is off.

Parameter name: Default DRX paging cycle value for the gNB
Description: This parameter indicates the default value for the DRX paging cycle to be shared with AMF and the UE.  Value v32 corresponds to 32 radio frames, v64 to 64 radio frames, v128 to 128 radio frames and v256 to 256 radio frames respectively.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter gathers parameters for DU side countermeasures handling.
This parameter indicates a delay for the application of gNB-DU RRC overload countermeasures.

Parameter name: Reject RRC connection request for SA due to overload
Description: This parameter enables/disables the counter measure of rejecting non-emergency and non-priority access RRC Setup Request and RRC Resume Request 1 messages from UE during overload. This parameter also controls DU overload monitoring.
This parameter indicates the list of distinguished names representing the gNB E2 node IP addresses    If NRBTS.actE2Interface is equal to FALSE, then this parameter is ignored.

Parameter name: E2 node transport network layer identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the gNB-CU-CP E2 node transport network Layer.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV4 instance representing the primary IPv4 address of the gNB-CU-CP E2 node. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1    Updating this parameter without changing the referenced instance will be performed on-line.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV6 instance representing the primary IPv6 address of the gNB-CU-CP E2 node. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1    Updating this parameter without changing the referenced instance will be performed on-line.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Wait time for receiving E2 setup response
Description: This parameter indicates the amount of time a gNB should wait for an E2 SETUP RESPONSE message after it had sent an E2 SETUP REQUEST message

Parameter name: Discarding Paging records during paging overload
Description: This parameter indicates the way how paging records (w/ or w/o eDRX) are discarded during paging overload if there's no enough room on 'pagingRecordList' in RRC Paging message.  If it is not configured or set to 'false' then gNB-DU shall discard paging records using time based algorithm (the oldest record is discarded first).  If this parameter is configured to 'true' then gNB-DU shall discard paging records using eDRX/non-eDRX distinction algorithm (eDRX paging records are discarded first and then normal paging records).
This parameter defines the length of the reattempt timer.

Parameter name: Waiting timer for EN-DC X2 setup request
Description: This timer specifies the amount of time a gNB should wait for an X2AP:EN-DC X2 SETUP REQUEST message after the SCTP association is established.

Parameter name: Exclude Inter-gNB NG based HO selected causes
Description: This parameter enables/disables excluding from counting selected cause codes related to the Inter-gNB NG based handover scenario, when the NGAP: UE Context Release Command is received by the source gNB from the AMF (for completion phase of the handover procedure).    It affects the following list of PM counters for Inter-gNB NG based HO:  - NG_HO_EXEC_SUCC_SRC_IEF - cell level  - NG_HO_EXEC_SUCC_SRC_IAF - cell level  - IEF_NG_HO_EX_SUC_SRC_VONR - cell level  - IAF_NG_HO_EX_SUC_SRC_VONR - cell level  - NG_HO_EXEC_SUCC_SRC_IAF_PLMN - slice level  - NG_HO_EXEC_SUCC_SRC_IEF_PLMN - slice level  - NG_HO_EXEC_SUCC_SRC_NRREL - neighbor relation level  - A4_IEF_NG_HO_EXEC_SUC_SRC_PR - PMQAP level  - IEF_NG_HO_EX_SUC_SRC_PMQAP - PMQAP level  - IAF_NG_HO_EX_SUC_SRC_PMQAP - PMQAP level  - NG_FLOW_REL_IANR_SUC_HO - Cell level  - NG_FLOW_REL_IANR_SUC_HO_5QI1 - Cell level  - NG_FLOW_REL_IANR_SUC_HO_PMQAP - Cell level
This parameter indicates the period to consider that the E-UTRAN cell is excluded
This parameter indicates the threshold of handover failures in the sliding window to consider that the E-UTRAN cell will be excluded
This parameter indicates the time of the sliding window over which exclusion control is applied
This parameter indicates the applicable EUTRA frequency band indicator

This parameter defines a name for the gNB-CU. It is configured at the gNB-CU. The parameter value is initially set in the F1AP: F1 Setup Response message sent by the gNB-CU to the gNB-DU over the F1 interface but it can be updated with the F1AP: GNB-CU Configuration Update message. This value is also used as RAN Node name at the NG-C interface in messages sent to the AMF.    It is strongly recommended to set a new value of this parameter only when NRBTS.actEnhancedNgRanSupport is equal to TRUE in order to notify the AMF about the change and have the Core network aligned.

This parameter indicates the RRC version for the gNB-CU.  It is configured at the gNB-CU. The parameter value is set in the F1AP: F1 Setup Response message sent by the gNB-CU to the gNB-DU over the F1 interface.

This parameter indicates if a given gNB-CU supports NSA cells or SA cells or both SA and NSA cells or NR-DC-SN cells or combination of any of these.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
Range and step: NSA (0), SA (1), NR-DC-SN (3), SA+NSA (10), NR-DC-SN+NSA (30), NR-DC-SN+SA (31), NR-DC-SN+SA+NSA (310)

Description: This parameter indicates the length chosen by the operator for NRBTS.nrBtsId. It corresponds to the left most bits of NRCELL.nrCellIdentity.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter indicates the 5G overload protection mode for the gNB.

This parameter defines the differentiated services code point (DSCP) value assigned to the GTP-U management traffic for all interfaces including F1-U, NG-U, S1-U, X2-U, Xn-U and Xg-U.    Note: Xg-U is the interface used for inter-gNB carrier aggregation.

Parameter name: Handover for PLMNs reserved for operator use enabled
Description: This parameter enables/disables the handover procedure to a target cell whose PLMN(s) have Cell Reserved For Operator Use equal to 'reserved'.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE, then the source shall allow Handover to Target cell even if its PLMN(s) have Cell Reserved For Operator Use equal to Reserved.  If this parameter is equal to FALSE, then the source shall not allow Handover to Target cell if its PLMN(s) have Cell Reserved For Operator Use equal to Reserved.    'Cell Reserved For Operator Use' is represented by ADJ_NRPLMNSET_SA.cellReservedForOperatorUse and ADJ_NRPLMNSET_NSA.cellReservedForOperatorUse

Parameter name: Handover to cells that are in barred state enabled
Description: This parameter enables/disables handover to cells that are barred.

Parameter name: Handover to cells that are reserved for operator use enabled
Description: This parameter enables/disables the handover procedure to target cell whose PLMN(s) have Cell Reserved For Operator Use equal to 'reserved'. This parameter is evaluated at the target cell.    If this parameter is equal to TRUE, then the target cell shall allow handover even if the UEs selected PLMN have Cell Reserved For Operator Use equal to 'reserved'.  If this parameter is equal to FALSE, then the target cell shall not allow handover if the UEs selected PLMN have Cell Reserved For Operator Use equal to 'reserved'.

Parameter name: Inter-gNB CA Xn configuration update back-off timer
Description: Consecutive Inter-gNB CA Configuration Update Indication procedures, serving to update served NR cells' configuration/status in adjacent gNB, are separated by at least the time given by this parameter.    This parameter serves to limit the maximum rate of Inter-gNB CA Configuration Update Indications due to cell changes and allows the gNB to accumulate and transmit all changes occurring during back-off time in one XnAP:IGNB CA CONFIGURATION UPDATE INDICATION message.    If this parameter is set to 0, then no back-off time is applied by the gNB.

Parameter name: Waiting timer for inter-gNB CA Xn removal
Description: This timer indicates the amount of time a gNB should wait for a response message after XnAP:IGNB CA REMOVAL REQUEST message is sent.

Parameter name: Waiting timer for Xn inter-gNB CA setup request
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum amount of time a gNB should wait before sending to an adjacent gNB the XnAP:IGNB CA SETUP REQUEST message, after successful completion of the Xn Setup procedure with that adjacent gNB. The actual waiting time is a dynamically generated random value between 0 and the value of this parameter.

Parameter name: Waiting timer for inter-gNB CA Xn setup response
Description: This timer indicates the amount of time a gNB should wait for a XnAP:IGNB CA SETUP RESPONSE message after the XnAP:IGNB CA SETUP REQUEST message is sent.
This parameter allows providing 'Index to RAT/Frequency Selection Priority' (as defined in 3GPP TS 38.413 and 38.423) that is considered as the identification of FWA (Fixed Wireless Access) UEs

Parameter name: Include all logical channel IDs corresponding to DRBs in RLC-BearerToReleaseList
Description: This parameter enables/disables including all logical channel IDs corresponding to DRBs in RLC-BearerToReleaseList

Parameter name: Include SRB to add mod list
Description: This parameter indicates if srb-ToAddModList is included in sourceConfig sent in the Xn: Handover Request and the NG: Handover Required messages.

This parameter indicates the time interval during which an inter-gNB SCell will be not considered as candidate SCell for a specific PCell after a Xg-U link failure between PCell and this inter-gNB SCell has been detected.
This parameter indicates the list of supported AS integrity protection algorithms. Each algorithm is identified by the parameter name, and the assigned value determines the algorithm preference

This parameter indicates the preference for the Null integrity protection algorithm. A lower value represents a lower preference and 0 does not admit the algorithm.  For customer deployment, this parameter shall be set to 0 as per 3GPP R2-1815965 since this is mandatory for NSA 3x SRB3 deployment.  For emergency call in limited service mode, this parameter can be set to a value different from 0.
This parameter indicates the preference for the SNOW 3G-based algorithm for integrity protection. A lower value represents a lower preference and 0 does not admit the algorithm.
This parameter indicates the preference for the AES-based algorithm for integrity protection. A lower value represents a lower preference and 0 does not admit the algorithm.
This parameter indicates the preference for the ZUC-based algorithm for integrity protection. A lower value represents a lower preference and 0 does not admit the algorithm.
This parameter defines a threshold for PDCP COUNT supervision. If the remaining COUNT space becomes less than this threshold, the gNB key hierarchy should be refreshed.

Parameter name: Absolute allowed maximum time error for BTS
Description: This parameter configures the maximum allowed absolute time error of the BTS required for supporting features depending on Loose H-SFN Sync in NR.

Parameter name: Maximum time for cell disabling when NMS connection lost
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum time for cell disabling since the last NMS communication.    Note: Modification of this parameter will cause NMS disconnection timer restart.
This parameter defines the maximum allowed number of reattempts for not successfully completed EN-DC Configuration Update procedure.
This parameter defines the maximum number of F1-links supported by the gNB

Parameter name: Max number of allowed neighbour relation managed object instances
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of neighbor relations (NRREL and NRRELE instances) configured in the gNB's site configuration plan. It includes intra-frequency, inter-frequency, and inter-RAT neighbor relations that the gNB can support.    Note: This parameter is used only by the ANR. It is not applicable while the operator adds new NRREL and NRRELE instances.

Parameter name: Maximum number of NG RAN configuration update retries
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of NG RAN configuration update retries by the gNB

Parameter name: Maximum number of NG setup request retries
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of NG Setup Request retries by the gNB.

Parameter name: Maximum number of UE context preemptions
Description: This parameter defines the maximum number of UE context preemptions (including UE context preemption candidate related to UE context resource shortage) that can be initiated by a single higher priority request. If this number is exceeded, then admission control will fail.

Parameter name: Maximum number of secondary cells for DL carrier aggregation
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of FR2 secondary cells (SCells) a gNB can configure in the 5G UE for DL carrier aggregation in addition to the primary cell (PCell).  This parameter is applicable only for aggregation of FR2/TDD NSA or NR-DC NR Cells.

Parameter name: Maximum number of secondary cells for FR2 SA DL CA
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of FR2 SA secondary cells (SCells) that gNB can configure in the 5G UE for DL carrier aggregation in addition to the primary cell (PCell).

Parameter name: Maximum number of secondary cells for UL carrier aggregation
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of secondary cells (SCells) a gNB can configure in the 5G UE for UL carrier aggregation in addition to the primary cell (PCell).  This parameter is applicable only for aggregation of FR2/TDD NSA or NR-DC NR Cells.

Parameter name: Maximum number of secondary cells for FR2 SA UL CA
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of FR2 SA secondary cells (SCells) that gNB can configure in the 5G UE for UL carrier aggregation in addition to the primary cell (PCell).
This parameter defines the maximum number of X2-links supported by the gNB
This parameter indicates the maximum number of Xn links supported by the gNB

Parameter name: Maximum number of Xn setup retry
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of consecutive unsuccessful Xn Setup retries done by gNB-CU to report a Fault to M-Plane.

Parameter name: Max parallel incoming X2 Setup handling
Description: This parameter defines the maximum number of parallel handling of incoming EN-DC X2 Setup requests supported by one CP-IF instance.  In case of classical gNB, there is only one CP-IF instance, so this maximum number is applicable to the whole gNB.  In case of Cloud gNB, there may be several CP-IF instances.

This parameter indicates the maximum number of parallel handling of Xn Setup request supported by one CP-IF instance.  In case of classical gNB, there is only one CP-IF instance, so this maximum number is applicable to the whole gNB.  In case of Cloud gNB, there may be several CP-IF instances.

Parameter name: Maximum percentage of DRB over F1-U during overload
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum percentage of DRB for which downlink data is sent over F1-U during to overload

Parameter name: Maximum size of RRC container for NGAP messages
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum size of the RRC container including UE capabilities within NGAP messages.    For handover to LTE (NGAP: HandoverRequired):  If this parameter is configured, then the lowest value of NRBTS.maxSizeRrcContainerNgap and 51,200 bytes (50 Kilobytes) is used by the gNB, otherwise only 51,200 bytes (50 Kilobytes) is used by the gNB during the RRC container size check.    For intra-NR NGAP Handover (NGAP: HandoverRequired):  If this parameter is configured, then this value is used by the gNB during the RRC container size check, otherwise no size check is performed.    For UE Radio Capability Info Indication (NGAP: UERadioCapabilityInfoIndication):  If this parameter is configured, then its value is used by the gNB during the UE Radio Capability IE size check, otherwise no size check is performed.
The parameter indicates the maximal source UDP port value.

Parameter name: Maximum time for the UE in RRC Inactive state
Description: This parameter sets the maximum time for the UE RRC Inactive state in the gNB. If suspended UE context stays without sending user data for this time, then Inactive UE Context is silently removed from the gNB.    Note: It is recommended to configure NRBTS.t380 to a value lower than NRBTS.maxUeRrcInactTime.

Parameter name: Max X2 EN-DC Configuration Update retries
Description: This parameter defines the maximum number of times the gNB shall retry the X2 EN-DC Configuration Update attempts.

Parameter name: Max X2 Partial Reset Required retries
Description: This parameter defines the maximum number of times the gNB shall retry the X2 Partial Reset Required attempts.

Parameter name: Max Xn NG-RAN Node Configuration Update retries
Description: This parameter defines the maximum number of times the gNB shall retry the Xn NG-RAN Node Configuration Update attempts / Xn partial reset attempts / inter-gNB CA Xn Removal attempts.
This parameter indicates the Primary Mobile Country Code of the gNB.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
When the 5G carrier aggregation feature is activated and NRBTS.sCellActivationMethod is set to 'bufferAndRLQualityBased', this parameter indicates the DL MCS value for SCell deactivation.
When the 5G carrier aggregation feature is activated and NRBTS.sCellActivationMethod is set to 'bufferAndRLQualityBased', this parameter indicates the UL MCS value for SCell deactivation.
The parameter indicates the minimal source UDP port value.
This parameter indicates the Primary Mobile Network Code of the gNB.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: MNC length of PLMN ID in primary PLMN of gNB
Description: This parameter indicates the length of the Mobile Network Code of the primary PLMN identity, in digits.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: ARP based QoS parameters for multiple ARP values
Description: This structure gathers the ARP based QoS parameters for multiple ARP values.

This parameter indicates the ARP priority level.  The range of the ARP priority level is 1 to 15 with 1 as the highest level of priority. NRBTS.multiArpBasedParam.nbrUlDlSF and/or NRBTS.multiArpBasedParam.schedulingWeightSF for the same NRBTS.multiArpBasedParam element will be applied as scaling factor to the ARP priority level indicated by this parameter.

Parameter name: Scaling factor for nominal bitrates for UL and DL
Description: This parameter indicates the scaling factor for nominal bitrates for uplink and downlink.
This parameter indicates the scaling factor for scheduling weight for uplink and downlink.
This parameter indicates the maximum number of consecutive 'out-of-sync' indications for the PSCell received from lower layers
This parameter indicates the maximum number of consecutive 'in-sync' indications for the PSCell received from lower layers
The name of the managed object.
This parameter enables/disables the neutral PLMN functionality.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE, the NRPLMN instance with NRPLMN.nrPlmnId equal to 1 is the neutral PLMN.
This parameter indicates the list of distinguished names representing the gNB NG Control Plane IP addresses.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV4 instance representing the primary IPv4 address of the gNB NG Control Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV4 instance representing the secondary IPv4 address of the gNB NG Control Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV6 instance representing the primary IPv6 address of the gNB NG Control Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV6 instance representing the secondary IPv6 address of the gNB NG Control Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

Parameter name: NG Control Plane transport Network Layer identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the NG Control Plane transport network Layer.

Parameter name: NG induced cell deactivation delay timer
Description: This timer defines the time period to wait for NG link recovery after a SA NR cell is barred due to the unavailability of the last NG link.  If, for a SA NR cell, all the NG links/configured PLMN IDs are unavailable on the NG interface for the duration given by this parameter, then that NR cell is deactivated.

Parameter name: Wait time for receiving NG Setup Response
Description: This parameter indicates the amount of time a gNB should wait for an NG SETUP RESPONSE message after it had sent an NG SETUP REQUEST message
This parameter enables or disables the UE retention functionality in the gNB at NG Setup.  It is applicable to only those deployments that have an NG interface (not applicable to NSA-3x for example)

This parameter indicates the amount of time a gNB should retain its UE contexts before releasing them.  It is applicable to only those deployments that have an NG interface (not applicable to NSA-3x for example)

This parameter indicates the list of distinguished names representing the gNB NG User Plane IP addresses.  Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV4 instance representing the primary IPv4 address of the gNB NG User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV4 instance representing the secondary IPv4 address of the gNB NG User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1    Note: The modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV6 instance representing the primary IPv6 address of the gNB NG User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.
