Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV6 instance representing the secondary IPv6 address of the gNB NG User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1    Note: The modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the New Radio PLMN instance representing the gNB NG User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1

Parameter name: Non-contention based RACH access for incoming handover with full configuration
Description: This parameter indicates if non-contention based RACH access shall be applied during Inter-RAT handover from LTE and during Intra-NR Inter-gNB handover with full configuration triggered by target gNB-CU. If it is equal to TRUE, the gNB shall try to allocate a dedicated RACH preamble for the UE. If inter-RAT handover from LTE and full RRC configuration are deactivated (i.e. NRBTS.actInterRatHoFromEutraToSA is equal to FALSE and NRBTS.actFullRRCConfigurationSaHo is equal to 'disabled'), then this parameter is ignored.
This timer indicates the time period for which gNB-CU waits for NR-DC cell activation after receiving the served cell information over F1.

Parameter name: Supervision timer for NR E-CID measurement report
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum time to wait for measurement report from the UE for the UL NR Enhanced Cell Id (UL NR E-CID) positioning method.  This timer is started each time the NRPPa: E-CIDMeasurementInitiationRequest message is received from the LMF with measurement quantities that requires configuration towards the UE. When this timer expires and no measurement report is received from the UE, the NRPPa: E-CIDMeasurementInitiationFailure message is sent to the LMF.    Note: an additional 500 ms buffer is recommended with respect to NRBTS.timerRRCGuard.

Parameter name: SYNC Template distinguished name for NR-LTE DSS
Description: This parameter defines the distinguished name of the SYNC Template to be used for NR-LTE Dynamic Spectrum Sharing DSS. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/MNL-1/MNLENT-1/SYNCSVC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1  SYNCSVC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1  SYNCTEMPLATE-1    Updating this parameter without changing the referenced instance will be performed on-line.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: SYNC Template distinguished name for 5G TDD
Description: This parameter defines the distinguished name of the SYNC Template to be used for 5G TDD. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/MNL-1/MNLENT-1/SYNCSVC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1  SYNCSVC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1  SYNCTEMPLATE-1    Updating this parameter without changing the referenced instance will be performed on-line.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Non Stand Alone Activity Notification Level
Description: This parameter indicates the activity notification level for NSA UE in mode 3x.

This timer defines the time period for which gNB-CU waits for NSA cell activation after receiving the served cell information over F1. After the timer expiry, gNB-CU shall raise the alarm 'CELL SERVICE PROBLEM'

This timer defines the time period for the indication of the bearer inactivity in both DL and UL directions for NSA UE in mode 3x.  It is ignored if UE inactivity for non standalone UE in mode 3x is deactivated (NRBTS.actInactDetNSAUe is equal to 0 corresponding to FALSE)  If this parameter is equal to 0, then this timer is off.
This parameter determines whether a fallback to null ciphering caused by gNB limitations should be accepted (true) or not (false).

Parameter name: Number of non GBR PDCP SDU to be discarded
Description: This parameter indicates the number of PDCP SDU for non GBR DRB which need to be discarded when PDCP buffer usage threshold is exceeded.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Number of non GBR RLC SDU to be discarded
Description: This parameter indicates the number of RLC SDU for non GBR DRB which need to be discarded when RLC buffer usage threshold is exceeded.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Number of consecutive packet validation failures
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of validation failures for consecutive numbers of non-VoNR (GBR/nonGBR) packets after which the HFN/SN desynchronization detection and recovery action is triggered.  It is used to compare consecutive failures which occur due to deciphering issues caused by HFN desynchronization between the UE and the gNB.

Parameter name: Number of consecutive VoNR packet check failures
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of check failures for consecutive numbers of VoNR packets.  These check failures are:  - RoHC decompression failures in case RoHC is enabled  - failures due to deciphering issues caused by the HFN desynchronization between the UE and the gNB in case RoHC is disabled.

Parameter name: Reserved DRB number per emergency call
Description: This parameter indicates the number of DRBs reserved per emergency call.  Note: The reserved number of DRBs per emergency call for one cell is equal to NRBTS.numOfDRBReservedPerEmergency * NRCELL.numOfRadioResReservForEmergency.    Only one QoS flow with Guaranteed Flow Bit Rate (GFBR) is assumed to be part of the number of DRBs reserved per emergency call.
This parameter defines the operational state of the New Radio Basestation.  It shows if the resource is physically installed and working.
Range and step: initializing (0), commissioned (1), configured (3), integrated to RAN (4), onAir (5), test (6), notCommissioned (7), disabled (10), enabled (11)

Parameter name: UE Assistance Information out of connected preference flag
Description: This parameter configures preference on the RRC state change when the gNB receives UE Assistance Information with release preference set to 'out of connected'.    The possible values are the following:  - 'idle' means preference on the RRC state change to RRC Idle  - 'inactive' means preference on the RRC state change to RRC Inactive
This parameter gathers 3GPP protocol version parameters to be used for chipset and RAN information exchange.

Parameter name: CA bandwidth class EUTRA DL 3GPP version
Description: This parameter indicates the 3GPP protocol version supported by the gNB to be used for chipset and RAN information exchange for CA bandwidth class EUTRA in downlink.

Parameter name: CA bandwidth class EUTRA UL 3GPP version
Description: This parameter indicates the 3GPP protocol version supported by the gNB to be used for chipset and RAN information exchange for CA bandwidth class EUTRA in uplink.
This parameter gathers gNB version parameters to be used for chipset and RAN information exchange.

Parameter name: CA bandwidth class EUTRA DL gNB version
Description: This parameter indicates the gNB version to be used for chipset and RAN information exchange for CA bandwidth class EUTRA in downlink.

Parameter name: CA bandwidth class EUTRA UL gNB version
Description: This parameter indicates the gNB version to be used for chipset and RAN information exchange for CA bandwidth class EUTRA in uplink.
This parameter indicates the list of interfaces for which GTP-U path supervision is supported.

Parameter name: Pathloss delta for SCell activation due to DL trigger
Description: When the 5G carrier aggregation feature is activated and NRBTS.sCellActivationMethod is set to 'bufferAndRLQualityBased', this parameter indicates the value of the pathloss delta for SCell activation.

Parameter name: Pathloss delta for SCell activation due to UL trigger
Description: When the 5G carrier aggregation feature is activated and NRBTS.sCellActivationMethod is set to 'bufferAndRLQualityBased', this parameter indicates the value of the pathloss delta for SCell activation.

Parameter name: Configuration for updating PDCP and RLC Counters
Description: This parameter decides if PDCP and RLC counters shall be generated at QoS level or NRPMQAP level.    This parameter controls only counters handled in feature CB013554.
This parameter indicates the percentage of PDCP buffer usage threshold after which discarding of PDCP SDU(s) is started.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: PDU session guard timer for End Marker reception
Description: This timer guards the target gNB against missing DL End Marker from the source gNB over the forwarding tunnel associated with the PDU session during the Inter-gNB mobility procedure (SA).  Value 0 indicates this timer is disabled.
This parameter indicates the periodicity of the buffer status reporting that is expected from the UE

Parameter name: Timer for periodical data usage report
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the periodical secondary data usage report service and defines the report periodicity.  If this parameter is equal to 0, periodical reporting is deactivated. If this parameter is not equal to 0 and NRBTS.actSecDataUsageRep is equal to TRUE, periodical reporting is activated with the specified periodicity.

Parameter name: Probability False Alarm Target for PRACH
Description: This parameter indicates the probability False Alarm Target for PRACH.  It is needed to determine the DTX threshold for PRACH  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This table specifies Power headroom parameters
This parameter specifies Downlink pathloss change
This parameter specifies UE configuration for sending periodic power headroom reports
This parameter specifies minimum of intermediate time between two consecutive power headroom reports.

Parameter name: Power saving avoidance options for priority access calls
Description: This parameter indicates the methods for excluding cells serving priority access calls by the power saving algorithm.  The possible values are:  - 'PA avoidance disabled' meaning to not exclude cells serving priority access calls by the power saving algorithm  - 'PA avoidance PCell enabled' meaning to exclude cells serving priority access calls by the power saving algorithm for cells that are recognized as primary cell  - 'PA avoidance P(S)Cell(s) enabled' meaning to exclude cells serving priority access calls by the power saving algorithm for cells that are recognized as primary cell or secondary cell
Range and step: PA avoidance disabled (0), PA avoidance PCell enabled (1), PA avoidance P(S)Cell(s) enabled (2)

Parameter name: Power saving bandwidth part switching parameters
Description: This structure gathers the parameters used to determine if and how the UEs are switched between the cell full bandwidth part and the cell power saving bandwidth part.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart

Parameter name: Downlink buffer empty ratio for switching from power saving bandwidth part
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold under which it is sufficient to be for the percentage of DL 'buffer empty' occurrences over the measurement period averaged by L2-PS based on its slot measurements, in order to switch a UE from the power saving bandwidth part to the cell full bandwidth part.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Downlink buffer empty ratio for switching to power saving bandwidth part
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold above which the percentage of DL 'buffer empty' occurrences over the measurement period averaged by L2-PS based on its slot measurements must be, in order to switch a UE to the power saving bandwidth part from the cell full bandwidth part.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Downlink data rate threshold for switching from power saving bandwidth part
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold above which it is sufficient to be for the DL rate averaged by L2-PS based on its slot measurements, in order to switch a UE to the cell full bandwidth part from the power saving bandwidth part.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Downlink data rate threshold for switching to power saving bandwidth part
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold under which the DL rate averaged by L2-PS based on its slot measurements must be in order to switch a UE to the power saving bandwidth part from the cell full bandwidth part.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Duration of the measurements used for switching from power saving bandwidth part
Description: This parameter indicates the duration during which the L2-PS measurements are averaged in order to decide whether to switch a UE from the power saving bandwidth part to the cell full bandwidth part.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Duration of the measurements used for switching to power saving bandwidth part
Description: This parameter indicates the duration during which the L2-PS measurements are averaged in order to decide whether to switch a UE from the cell full bandwidth part to the power saving bandwidth part.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: UL buffer empty ratio for switching from PS BWP
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold under which it is sufficient to be for the percentage of UL 'buffer empty' occurrences over the measurement period averaged by L2-PS based on its slot measurements, in order to switch a UE from the power saving bandwidth part to the cell full bandwidth part.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: UL buffer empty ratio for switching to PS BWP
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold above which the percentage of UL 'buffer empty' occurrences over the measurement period averaged by L2-PS based on its slot measurements must be, in order to switch a UE to the power saving bandwidth part from the cell full bandwidth part.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: UL rate threshold for switching noVoNR UEs from PS BWP
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold above which it is sufficient to be for the UL rate averaged by L2-PS based on its slot measurements, in order to switch a UE to the cell full bandwidth part from the power saving bandwidth part.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: UL rate threshold for switching noVoNR UEs to PS BWP
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold under which the UL rate averaged by L2-PS based on its slot measurements must be in order to switch a UE to the power saving bandwidth part from the cell full bandwidth part.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: UL rate threshold for switching VoNR UEs from PS BWP
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold above which it is sufficient to be for the UL rate averaged by L2-PS based on its slot measurements, in order to switch a UE to the cell full bandwidth part from the power saving bandwidth part.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: UL rate threshold for switching VoNR UEs to PS BWP
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold under which the UL rate averaged by L2-PS based on its slot measurements must be in order to switch a UE to the power saving bandwidth part from the cell full bandwidth part.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter enables/disables PWS (Public Warning Message) restart indication for the CMAS and the ETWS

Parameter name: RAN eDRX Paging Cycle for UE in RRC Inactive state
Description: This parameter indicates the eDRX Paging Cycle for UE in RRC Inactive state. RAN eDRX is configured by gNB in RRC Release suspendConfig IE ran-ExtendedPagingCycle IE. Parameter may be not configured and then RRC Release suspendConfig IE ran-ExtendedPagingCycle IE is not sent to UE which means that UE is not configured by RRC with the eDRX for RAN Paging.  - Value v256 corresponds to 256 radio frames, v512 to 512 radio frames, v1024 to 1024 radio frames respectively.  If Core Network TeDRX Cycle value received in Core Network Assistance Information:  - <= 'hf1' then UE in RRC Inactive is configured with min(TeDRX, CN; NRBTS.ranEdrxPagingCycle) eDRX Cycle value.  - > 'hf1' then UE in RRC Inactive is configured with NRBTS.ranEdrxPagingCycle eDRX Cycle value.

Parameter name: DRX Paging Cycle for UE in RRC Inactive state
Description: This parameter indicates the DRX paging cycle for UE in RRC Inactive state. If NRBTS.ranPagingCycle is not configured, then NRBTS.drxDefaultPaging parameter is used or UE Specific DRX from CNAI, if received.    Value v32 corresponds to 32 radio frames, v64 to 64 radio frames, v128 to 128 radio frames and v256 to 256 radio frames respectively.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Reject BCS4 or BCS5 support during Bandwidth Combination Set (BCS) checks
Description: This parameter accepts/rejects the support of BCS4 or BCS5 during Bandwidth Combination Set (BCS) checks in FR1 carrier aggregation or BCS4 during BCS checks in NR-DC. The gNB performs a BCS check during FR1 CA secondary cell selection to ensure the bandwidth combination of the selected gNB serving cells is compatible with the UE capabilities. During NR-DC establishment, the gNB performs a BCS check on FR1 PCell to ensure the bandwidth of PCell is compatible with the UE capabilities.    The gNB considers BCS4 if BCS check is enabled (NRBTS.actBcsCheck contains at least one element not equal to 'disabled') and BCS4 is known by the gNB (as specified in 3GPP).  The gNB considers BCS5 if BCS check is enabled (NRBTS.actBcsCheck contains at least one element not equal to 'disabled') and BCS5 is known by the gNB (as specified in 3GPP).    The possible values are the following:  - 'none' meaning BCS4 or BCS5 are accepted by the BCS check in all cells.  - 'BCS4' meaning the BCS4 is rejected by the BCS checks during the FR1 CA secondary cell selection in all cells or during allowed band combination selection for NR-DC establishment.  - 'BCS5' meaning the BCS5 is rejected by the BCS checks during the FR1 CA secondary cell selection in all cells.    This parameter is ignored if NRDU.carrierAggregationSupportList has an element equal to 'none' and NRCELL.actNrDualConnectivity is set to 'disabled' in the concerned PCell. This parameter is ignored if NRBTS.actBcsCheck is equal to 'disabled'.

Parameter name: Waiting timer for next Xn setup procedure
Description: This timer indicates the amount of time a gNB should wait for the next XNAP:XN SETUP procedure
This parameter indicates the percentage of RLC buffer usage threshold after which discarding of RLC SDU(s) is started.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: CA/non CA aware IMM steering preference flag for RRC Inactive
Description: This parameter enables/disables UL and DL CA/UL CA/CA/non CA aware idle mode mobility steering during transition of UE in RRC Connected state to RRC Inactive state.  Note: CA aware means DL CA aware algorithm.

Parameter name: Location reporting preference flag for RRC Inactive
Description: This parameter enables/disables location reporting in SA for RRC Inactive state.

Parameter name: UE Assistance Information preferred state for RRC Inactive
Description: This parameter enables/disables UE Assistance Information preferred state for RRC Inactive state.
This parameter indicates the RRC reestablishment type in SA.  It is used to deactivate RRC reestablishment as a whole or activate it either under the same gNB or via RRC Setup.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name representing the S1 User Plane IP address.  Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV4 instance representing the primary IPv4 address of the gNB S1 User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV4 instance representing the secondary IPv4 address of the gNB S1 User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1    Note: The modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV6 instance representing the primary IPv6 address of the gNB-CU S1 User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV6 instance representing the secondary IPv6 address of the gNB S1 User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1    Note: The modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the New Radio PLMN instance representing the gNB S1 User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1

When the 5G carrier aggregation feature is activated, this parameter indicates if secondary cells (SCells) are  - 'blind': blindly activated at UE connection setup or  - 'bufferBased': stepwise activated/deactivated based on buffer size or  - 'bufferAndRLQualityBased': stepwise activated/deactivated based on a combination of buffer size and RL quality    Note: For FR1 CA, 'bufferAndRLQualityBased' will be considered as equivalent to 'bufferBased'.

Parameter name: Number of continuous bad radio quality report to trigger secondary cell deactivation
Description: The parameter indicates the number of continuous bad radio quality reports to trigger secondary cell deactivation during which the gNB will monitor the secondary cell radio quality after the secondary cell is activated.    If this parameter is equal to 0 (meaning infinity), the secondary cell will not be deactivated due to bad radio link quality and only scheduling will be suspended during the time bad radio link quality is detected on the secondary cell.

Parameter name: SCell exclude-list timer due to A2 based SCell release
Description: This parameter indicates the time during which the gNB does not consider the FR1 SCell for SCell selection in SCell Addition or SCell Change after the SCell has been released due to A2 measurement report from UE, when there are multiple candidate SCells on the same frequency carrier.    If this parameter is set to 0 or is not configured, an SCell released due to A2 measurement report from UE is immediately available for SCell Addition or SCell Change for the UE.  This timer is ignored for A4 based SCell Addition and A6 based SCell Swap.

Parameter name: SCell exclude-list timer due to bad radio link quality
Description: This parameter indicates the time during which the gNB does not consider the SCell for SCell selection in SCell Addition, SCell Change, or SCell Swap after the SCell has been released due to bad SCell radio link quality (RLQ).    If this parameter is set to 0, a SCell released due to bad SCell radio link quality is immediately available for SCell Addition, SCell Change and SCell Swap for the UE.

Parameter name: Measurement cycle on configured secondary cells
Description: This parameter indicates the measurement period of a deactivated secondary cell.  It is used by UE only when performing measurements on a secondary cell, which is in deactivated state.

This timer indicates the time period for which gNB-CU waits for SA cell activation after receiving the served cell information over F1. After the timer expiry, gNB-CU shall raise the alarm 'CELL SERVICE PROBLEM'

Parameter name: Profile 1 of CU flow control parameters for SCG F1-U for NR-DC split bearer
Description: This structure gathers the profile for the SCG F1-U flow control parameters

Parameter name: Periodicity of SCG F1-U downlink data delivery status indication message
Description: This parameter indicates the periodicity of polling for the SCG F1-U downlink data delivery status indication message

Parameter name: Max RLC queuing delay for SCG F1-U
Description: This parameter defines the value of max RLC queuing delay to be used for flow control algorithm specifically for SCG F1-U of NR DC bearers

Parameter name: Max transfer delay for SCG F1-U
Description: This parameter indicates the value of the max queuing delay including the SCG F1-U interface delay to be used for the flow control algorithm

Parameter name: Minimum throughput for flow control for SCG F1U
Description: This parameter indicates the value of the minimum throughput to be used for the SCG F1-U in flow control algorithm
This parameter indicates the IPv4 or IPv6 address of the secondary security gateway of the CU. It is used to indicate a connection point for the CU from the DU

Parameter name: SgNB release due to no possibility of handover enabled
Description: This parameter enables/disables SN (gNB) initiated SgNB release in the case where all the NR cells reported by the UE have no associated NRREL instance.

Parameter name: Waiting timer for SCTP link shutdown due to no traffic
Description: This timer is managed per X2 link.  This timer is started when there is no more traffic on the X2 link (no gNB UE X2AP ID allocated and no X2-C message).  The link state is checked periodically every 15 minutes. This timer will be started at the end of the period if following conditions are met: There is no UE setups over this link and no message has been sent in the last 15 minutes period over this link.    When the timer expires, the SCTP association is shutdown  Value 0 means no shutdown

Parameter name: Waiting timer for SCTP link shutdown due to no traffic per Xn link
Description: This timer is managed per Xn link.  This timer is started when timer NRBTS.xnSetupReqTmr expires and after sending Xn setup failure.  This timer shall be stopped when Xn Setup Request is received from the neighboring gNB.  SCTP association is shutdown when the timer expires  Value 0 means 'no shutdown'.

Parameter name: Waiting timer for SCTP link shutdown due to no gNB cell
Description: This timer is managed per X2 link.  This timer is started when there is no more gNB cell available.    When the timer expires, the SCTP association is shut down.  Value 0 means 'no delay before to shut down the SCTP association'
This parameter indicates the number of power reduction steps during the graceful cell shutdown operation.
This parameter indicates the duration of the power reduction phase of cell shutdown operation in case of graceful cell shutdown. The overall shutdown might take at least 10 seconds longer.

The parameter defines the description of the site template that is assigned for the base station. Site template description can be used for searching the Site template name, which is needed when generating the complete BTS configuration.
The parameter defines the name of the site template assigned for the base station. Site template can be used for generating the complete BTS configuration during the planning phase.
This structure gathers parameters that define the slice for which the UE has PS BWP deactivated.
This parameter indicates the slice differentiator.
This parameter indicates the slice service type which identifies the slice type.

Parameter name: Slow PRB pooling FDD FR1 enhancement compatibility mode
Description: This parameter defines compatibility mode for enhanced slow PRB pooling in FDD FR1.    - Value 0 corresponding to 'disabled' means compatibility mode for enhanced slow PRB pooling FDD FR1 is deactivated.  - Value 1 corresponding to 'mute_slot_3_6_8' means PDSCH last symbol muting in slot 3 and 6 in even SFNs and slot 8 in odd SFNs is enabled.  - Value 2 corresponding to 'mute_slot_0_3_6_8' means PDSCH last symbol muting in slot 0, 3 and 6 in even SFNs and slot 8 in odd SFNs is enabled.    Updating this parameter requires restart of all FDD NR cells.
This parameter indicates whether to use 3gpp defaults or nokia defaults for the SRB1 configuration.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter indicates the RLC AM profile for SRB1.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter specifies the maximum number of downlink ARQ retransmissions allowed on the downlink. When the retransmission counter of a PDU exceeds this threshold, the gNB-DU user plane triggers a notification for radio failure towards the gNB-DU control plane. This parameter is applicable to the DL transmitter side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the downlink value of pollByte parameter as per 3GPP TS 38.322. This parameter represents the interval between polls in terms of number of transmitted bytes. This parameter is applicable to the DL transmitter side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the downlink value of pollPDU parameter as per 3GPP TS 38.322. This parameter represents the interval between polls, in PDU. This parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. It is applicable to the DL transmitter side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the downlink value of timer T-PollRetransmit as per 3GPP TS 38.322. The parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. This parameter is applicable to the DL transmitter side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the downlink value of timer t-StatusProhibit. This timer is used to prohibit the receiving side of an AM RLC entity from sending consecutive acknowledgement status reports. The parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. This parameter is applicable to the DL receiver side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the downlink value of timer for reassembly in TS 38.322, in milliseconds. Value ms0 means 0ms, ms5 means 5ms and so on. This parameter is applicable to the DL receiver side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter specifies the maximum number of uplink ARQ retransmissions allowed on the uplink. When the retransmission counter of a PDU exceeds this threshold, the UE triggers a request for RLC reestablishment procedure, as per TS 38.322. This parameter is applicable to the UL transmitter side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the uplink value of pollByte parameter as per 3GPP TS 38.322. This parameter represents the interval between polls in terms of number of transmitted bytes. Note that in the uplink this function cannot be disabled in the UE, as per 3GPP. This parameter is applicable to the UL transmitter side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the uplink value of pollPDU parameter as per 3GPP TS 38.322. This parameter represents the interval between polls, in PDU. The parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. This parameter is applicable to the UL transmitter side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the uplink value of timer T-PollRetransmit as per 3GPP TS 38.322. The parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. This parameter is applicable to the UL transmitter side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the uplink value of timer t-StatusProhibit. This timer is used to prohibit the receiving side of an AM RLC entity from sending consecutive acknowledgement status reports. The parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. This parameter is applicable to the UL receiver side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the uplink value of timer for reassembly in TS 38.322, in milliseconds. Value ms0 means 0ms, ms5 means 5ms and so on. This parameter is applicable to the UL receiver side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter indicates the RLC AM profile for SRB2.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter specifies the maximum number of downlink ARQ retransmissions allowed on the downlink. When the retransmission counter of a PDU exceeds this threshold, the gNB-DU user plane triggers a notification for radio failure towards the gNB-DU control plane. This parameter is applicable to the DL transmitter side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the downlink value of pollByte parameter as per 3GPP TS 38.322. This parameter represents the interval between polls in terms of number of transmitted bytes. This parameter is applicable to the DL transmitter side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the downlink value of pollPDU parameter as per 3GPP TS 38.322. This parameter represents the interval between polls, in PDU. This parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. It is applicable to the DL transmitter side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the downlink value of timer T-PollRetransmit as per 3GPP TS 38.322. The parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. This parameter is applicable to the DL transmitter side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the downlink value of timer t-StatusProhibit. This timer is used to prohibit the receiving side of an AM RLC entity from sending consecutive acknowledgement status reports. The parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. This parameter is applicable to the DL receiver side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the downlink value of timer for reassembly in TS 38.322, in milliseconds.  This parameter is applicable to the DL receiver side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter specifies the maximum number of uplink ARQ retransmissions allowed on the uplink. When the retransmission counter of a PDU exceeds this threshold, the UE triggers a request for RLC reestablishment procedure, as per TS 38.322. This parameter is applicable to the UL transmitter side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the uplink value of pollByte parameter as per 3GPP TS 38.322. This parameter represents the interval between polls in terms of number of transmitted bytes. Note that in the uplink this function cannot be disabled in the UE, as per 3GPP. This parameter is applicable to the UL transmitter side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the uplink value of pollPDU parameter as per 3GPP TS 38.322. This parameter represents the interval between polls, in PDU. The parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. This parameter is applicable to the UL transmitter side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the uplink value of timer T-PollRetransmit as per 3GPP TS 38.322. The parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. This parameter is applicable to the UL transmitter side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the uplink value of timer t-StatusProhibit. This timer is used to prohibit the receiving side of an AM RLC entity from sending consecutive acknowledgement status reports. The parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. This parameter is applicable to the UL receiver side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the uplink value of timer for reassembly in TS 38.322, in milliseconds. Value ms0 means 0ms, ms5 means 5ms and so on. This parameter is applicable to the UL receiver side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter indicates the RLC AM profile for SRB3.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter specifies the maximum number of downlink ARQ retransmissions allowed on the downlink. When the retransmission counter of a PDU exceeds this threshold, the gNB-DU user plane triggers a notification for radio failure towards the gNB-DU control plane.This parameter is applicable to the DL transmitter side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the downlink value of pollByte parameter as per 3GPP TS 38.322. This parameter represents the interval between polls in terms of number of transmitted bytes. This parameter is applicable to the DL transmitter side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the downlink value of pollPDU parameter as per 3GPP TS 38.322. This parameter represents the interval between polls, in PDU. This parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. It is applicable to the DL transmitter side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the downlink value of timer T-PollRetransmit as per 3GPP TS 38.322. The parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. This parameter is applicable to the DL transmitter side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the downlink value of timer t-StatusProhibit. This timer is used to prohibit the receiving side of an AM RLC entity from sending consecutive acknowledgement status reports. The parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. This parameter is applicable to the DL receiver side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the downlink value of timer for reassembly in TS 38.322, in milliseconds. Value ms0 means 0ms, ms5 means 5ms and so on. This parameter is applicable to the DL receiver side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter specifies the maximum number of uplink ARQ retransmissions allowed on the uplink. When the retransmission counter of a PDU exceeds this threshold, the UE triggers a request for RLC reestablishment procedure, as per TS 38.322. This parameter is applicable to the UL transmitter side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the uplink value of pollByte parameter as per 3GPP TS 38.322. This parameter represents the interval between polls in terms of number of transmitted bytes. Note that in the uplink this function cannot be disabled in the UE, as per 3GPP. This parameter is applicable to the UL transmitter side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the uplink value of pollPDU parameter as per 3GPP TS 38.322. This parameter represents the interval between polls, in PDU. The parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. This parameter is applicable to the UL transmitter side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the uplink value of timer T-PollRetransmit as per 3GPP TS 38.322. The parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. This parameter is applicable to the UL transmitter side (UE).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the uplink value of timer t-StatusProhibit. This timer is used to prohibit the receiving side of an AM RLC entity from sending consecutive acknowledgement status reports. The parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. This parameter is applicable to the UL receiver side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter configures the uplink value of timer for reassembly in TS 38.322, in milliseconds. Value ms0 means 0ms, ms5 means 5ms and so on. This parameter is applicable to the UL receiver side (gNB-DU).  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter enables or disables the support of SRB3 for a direct RRC signaling for non standalone (NSA) mode 3x operation.

Parameter name: Stand alone UE SRB inactivity timer
Description: This timer indicates the time period for the indication of the SRB inactivity in both DL and UL directions for SA UE  This timer is started when an NGAP: Initial UE Message is sent to the AMF.

Parameter name: Stand alone RedCap UE SRB inactivity timer
Description: This timer indicates the time period for the indication of the SRB inactivity in both DL and UL directions for RedCap SA UEs.  This timer is started when an NGAP: Initial UE Message is sent to the AMF.    It is recommended to use a value lower than NRBTS.srbInactivityTimerSA.    If this parameter is not configured, then the value of NRBTS.srbInactivityTimerSA is applicable.

This parameter indicates the duration, in seconds, for which a client instance waits to get a response for a service request, before it concludes that the service is unavailable.  This timer is used for a client instance to confirm that Control Plane service unavailability is not transient.  This parameter is ignored if NRBTS. actSrvcAvaReporting is equal to FALSE

Parameter name: Support CN partial admission during intra-NR HO via NG
Description: This parameter indicates if core network partial admission on target gNB during intra-NR handover via NG is supported or not.
This parameter defines the timer value to be configured in the UE for successful completion of random access on the corresponding SpCell.
This timer is used for detecting physical layer problems for the PSCell, i.e. upon receiving N310 consecutive 'out-of-sync' indications from lower layers
This timer is used to supervise the RRC connection reestablishment.

This parameter indicates the periodic RAN Area Update timer for the gNB. It is used in the RRC Inactive state to trigger the periodic RAN Area update procedure. It is also sent to the UE in RRC release suspend configuration.    Note 1: As per 3GPP 23.501 it is recommended that NRBTS.t380 is configured to the lower value than T3512 (Periodic Registration Update Timer).    Note 2: In order to avoid racing condition between UE and gNB when t380 expires, gNB should wait longer than configured t380 in SuspendConfig IE. Additional fixed margin of 5 seconds is added to t380 on gNB side.
This timer guards the SgNB against missing confirmation from the MeNB during the SgNB Addition procedure or the SgNB Change procedure.
This parameter is used by the gNB to calculate the amount of data to be forwarded to the MeNB during the SgNB Release procedure.

This parameter defines the value of the RAN eDRX Paging guard timer in gNB.  The timer is started when F1AP:Paging is sent for UE with configured eDRX and during its time the paged UE in RRC Inactive state should respond to the RRC Paging message with RRC Resume Request1 and UE Context should be found and verified. Timer is stopped and RAN eDRX Paging is treated as successful when UE Context is found and resumeMAC-I verified. Paging Failure is detected when this timer expires.    Note: This timer is used when loose H-SFN synchronization is available. Otherwise, tRanPagingGuard is used in RRC Inactive state.

Parameter name: HO cancel procedure timer for intra-NR NG based HO
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum time for handover cancel procedure during intra-NR NG based handover at the source gNB.

Parameter name: Delta to Ng handover execution procedure timer for E-UTRA
Description: This parameter indicates the delta for supervision timer for the handover execution phase of handover from E-UTRA to NR-SA at the target gNB.  The supervision timer tNgRelocExec is the sum of NRBTS.t304 and this parameter.  If inter-RAT handover from E-UTRA to SA UE is deactivated (i.e. NRBTS.actInterRatHoFromEutraToSA is equal to FALSE), then this parameter is ignored.

Parameter name: Delta to intra-NR NG HO execution procedure timer
Description: This parameter indicates the delta for the supervision timer for the Handover Execution Phase of intra-NR NG based handover at the target gNB.
This parameter indicates the maximum time for the protection of the overall handover procedure in the source gNB for inter-RAT handover.

Parameter name: Overall timer for intra-NR NG based HO
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum time for the protection of overall intra-NR NG based handover procedure at the source gNB.

This parameter indicates the maximum time for the handover preparation procedure in the source gNB for inter-RAT handover.  It is started in the source gNB when the NGAP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message is sent to the AMF and is stopped when the NGAP: HANDOVER COMMAND or NGAP: HANDOVER PREPARATION FAILURE message is received in response. If the timer expires, the handover is aborted or cancelled.

Parameter name: Preparation procedure timer of intra-NR NG based HO
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum time for the preparation phase of intra-NR NG based handover at the source gNB.

This parameter defines the maximum time interval which may elapse from when a UE has left a cell by handover till when it returns to that cell by another handover in order to consider such event as a PingPong
This timer is started in DU when RLF status message is sent from Packet Scheduler. When it expires, DU sends RLF indication to CU.  It is for users other than SA users.

Parameter name: RLF indication timer for DU and for SA
Description: This timer is started in DU for SA users when RLF status message is sent from Packet Scheduler. When it expires, DU sends RLF indication to CU.

Parameter name: RLF indication timer for DU for VoNR
Description: This timer is started in DU for VoNR service when RLF status message is sent from Packet Scheduler.  When it expires, DU sends RLF indication to CU.

This parameter defines the value of the RAN Paging guard timer in gNB.    The timer is started when F1AP:Paging is sent and during its time the paged UE in RRC Inactive state should respond to the RRC Paging message with RRC Resume Request1 and UE Context should be found and verified. Timer is stopped and RAN Paging is treated as successful when UE Context is found and resumeMAC-I verified. Paging Failure is detected when this timer expires.
This timer defines the period in which the handover problems can be detected and evaluated at the target cell. Possibile values are 100...100000, in units of 100 ms.
This timer is started in CU to wait the RL recovery after Radio Link Failure is identified. When it expires, UE Context release procedure will happen.  It is for users other than SA users.

Parameter name: Waiting RL Recovery timer for SA
Description: This timer is started in CU for SA users to wait the RL recovery after Radio Link Failure is identified. When it expires, UE Context release procedure will happen.  This timer also prolongs the value of the handover target gNB supervision timer (Xn and NG handover), to wait for RRC Reestablishment Request received at handover target gNB.  In case of NG handover the prolongation depends on NRBTS.actInterGnbRREPreparedCell set to TRUE.

This parameter indicates the range of the highest BIN for DL throughput distribution PM counters.  Its value is the estimated maximum value of the highest BIN, i.e. BIN 20 for DL throughput distribution.  Note: This is an estimated maximum, thus if during calculation, the DL throughput for a certain measurement period exceeds this value, it is still reported under the maximum BIN, i.e. BIN 20.    Its value is used to define the range of all BINs

This parameter indicates the range of the lowest BIN for DL throughput distribution PM counters.  Its value is the highest value of the lowest BIN, i.e. BIN 01 for DL throughput.    Note: In case 0 is selected, value 1 is taken as parameter value to avoid division by 0 issue when calculating BIN ranges.

Parameter name: Throughput histogram scale type for both UL and DL throughput distribution counters
Description: This parameter indicates if the histogram scale type is linear or logarithmic for both the DL PDCP and UL RLC throughput histogram.

This parameter indicates the range of the highest BIN for UL throughput distribution PM counters.  Its value is the estimated maximum value of the highest BIN, i.e. BIN 20 for UL throughput distribution.  Note: This is an estimated maximum, thus if during calculation, the UL throughput for a certain measurement period exceeds this value, it is still reported under the maximum BIN i.e. BIN 20.

This parameter indicates the range of the lowest BIN for UL throughput distribution PM counters.  Its value is the highest value of the lowest BIN, i.e. BIN 01 for the UL throughput.    Note: In case 0 is selected, value 1 is taken as parameter value to avoid division by 0 issue when calculating BIN ranges.

This parameter enables/disables the method for the calculation mechanism of DL PDCP cell level and UL RLC cell level throughput time calculation PM counters and PDCP and RLC level PCMD throughput reports.    The possible values are the following:  - 'enabled': The throughput time modifications are taken into consideration and F1 delay+DU buffer delay is added to the time calculation for DL PDCP throughput calculation.  The UL burst time calculation is also modified such that BSR reports are distinguished between PCell and SCell in the PDCP for UL throughput time calculation.  - 'disabled': The throughput time calculation modifications are not taken into account.

Parameter name: Handover guard timer radio bearer management
Description: This timer is started when an RRC Reconfiguration is sent to the UE for handover and gNB is waiting for RRC Reconfiguration complete. When the timer expires, the UE is released.

Parameter name: Guard timer for the establishment of NGAP Signaling Connection
Description: This timer is started when:  - NGAP:UE CONTEXT RELEASE REQUEST is sent to the AMF. When the timer expires without receiving NGAP: UE CONTEXT RELEASE COMMAND, the gNB shall trigger the release.  - NGAP: PATH SWITCH REQUEST is sent to the AMF. The timer guards the receipt of NGAP: PATH SWITCH REQUEST ACKNOWLEDGE.  - NGAP: PDU SESSION RESOURCE MODIFY INDICATION is sent to the AMF. The timer guards reception of NGAP: PDU SESSION RESOURCE MODIFY CONFIRM

Parameter name: Random access guard timer for NSA
Description: This parameter defines the guard timer for Random Access at SgNB (NSA) or SN (NR-DC) during Initial Access.  This timer is started when SgNB/SN receives X2AP: SgNBReconfigurationComplete/XnAP: SNodeReconfigurationComplete and stopped when Random Access complete or getting SCGFailureInformation via X2AP: SgNBModificationRequest or SgNB/SN Release is initiated.  Upon this timer expiry, the UE context will be released in SgNB/SN.

This timer, used by the UE, defines the minimum time interval that should elapse between two consecutive RRC: UE Assistance Information messages with Overheating Assistance Information content.  The UE starts this timer, if not already running, when it sends an RRC: UE Assistance Information message with Overheating Assistance Information.  While this timer is running, the UE should not send an RRC: UE Assistance Information message with Overheating Assistance Information content.  The gNB does not validate whether two consecutive RRC: UE Assistance Information messages are received with a time delay according to this timer value.

This timer, handled by the gNB, defines the minimum time interval that should elapse between the deactivation of (all or a sub-set of) UE's configured SCells for overheating and their (full or partial) re-activation for data activity when the UE is no more or less overheated.  This timer is started by the gNB when the UE indicates that it can be served by more SCells than currently allowed to be active for overheating or when the UE indicates that it is no more overheated.  The purpose of this timer is to avoid SCell activation and deactivation ping-pongs during overheating.

Parameter name: RRC guard timer radio bearer management
Description: This timer is used to guard RRC transactions over NR.  This timer is started when gNB sends out a RRC message and stopped when gNB receives the response of this RRC message.  When this timer expires, the corresponding procedure is aborted.

This timer defines the time in seconds the UE has to wait before sending a subsequent RRC Setup Request or RRC Resume Request1.    The timer value is sent as waitTime IE in RRC Reject message or, in case of preemption procedure, RRC Release message.

Parameter name: Prohibit timer for release preference assistance information reporting
Description: Prohibit timer for release preference assistance information reporting. Value in seconds. Value s0 means prohibit timer is set to 0 seconds, value s0dot5 means prohibit timer is set to 0.5 seconds, value s1 means prohibit timer is set to 1 second and so on. Value infinity means that once a UE has reported a release preference, the UE cannot report a release preference again during the RRC connection.
This parameter is used by the gNB during UE Context Release X2 procedure to allow completion of X2 data forwarding towards MeNB.

Parameter name: Guard timer for X2-C UE related signaling
Description: This timer guards X2-C UE related signaling.

This parameter is used by the gNB during:  - UE Context Release Xn procedure to allow completion of Xn data forwarding towards target gNB, or  - inter-gNB NR-DC SNode Addition (with data forwarding) procedure, to allow completion of Xn data forwarding towards Secondary Node gNB, or  - inter-gNB NR-DC SNode Release (with data forwarding) procedure, to allow completion of Xn data forwarding towards Master Node gNB.

Parameter name: Xn DC guard timer used by secondary node
Description: This parameter indicates the guard timer for XN-C related UE signaling initiated by the secondary node.
This parameter indicates the guard timer for the SN Addition Preparation or MN initiated SN Modification Preparation procedure
This parameter is a Guard Timer for the UE Associated Procedures over Xn. It applies to gNB-CU Initiated Class 1 procedures.
This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.  It is used to enable dedicated functionality in the gNB.

This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.  It is used to enable dedicated functionality in the gNB.    In 24R3 and 25R1 Bit 22 of this temporary parameter is used to change the CPU overload value for a L2Hi DU instance and for an Up UE VM from 90% to 100%. Bit 22 of this temporary parameter anticipates the 25R2 final solution which by default set 100% of the CPU overload value for a L2Hi DU instance and for an Up UE VM.  If NRBTS.tmpActFeat2 not exist or Bit 22 of NRBTS.tmpActFeat2 is equal to '0' means that the legacy algorithm is used and set 90% of the CPU overload value for a L2Hi DU instance and for an Up UE VM.  If Bit 22 of NRBTS.tmpActFeat2 is equal to '1' means that the updated algorithm is used and set 100% of the CPU overload value for a L2Hi DU instance and for an Up UE VM.    Modification of Bit 22 can be done online. This parameter is used in SBTS, DU and CU products.
This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.  It is used to enable dedicated functionality in the gNB.
This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.
This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.
This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.

This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.
This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.
This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.
This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.
This parameter indicates the time period for which NRBTS.trsBurstSize is applicable.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter indicates the maximum burst size for the configured NRBTS.trsBurstPeriod.    The recommended configuration is to set NRBTS.trsBurstSize to 'b6440000' and set NRBTS.trsBurstPeriod to 5 (ms). If NRBTS.trsBurstSize is set to 'b6440000' and NRBTS.trsBurstPeriod is set to a value less than 5 (ms), then there will be packet losses.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter indicates whether or not IPv6 addresses support is enabled.  It is equal to true if at least one of the ipV6AddressDN1 parameter is configured.

This parameter indicates the mode to handle the TX path failures.    The possible values are:  - 'keepCellInService' meaning a cell remains enabled as long as the minimum required number of TX paths are operating as defined in the dedicated features.  - 'disableCell' meaning a cell is disabled if at least one TX path is not operable.

This parameter indicates the duration range for UP data interruption during HO for PM counters.  The value configured in this parameter is considered as max limit of moderate interruption duration.    All UP HO interruption duration higher than this parameter shall be updated to high range PM counter

This parameter indicates the duration range for UP data interruption during HO for PM counters.  The value configured in this parameter is considered as max limit of target interruption duration.    All UP HO interruption duration higher than this parameter shall be updated to moderate range PM counter  All UP HO interruption duration lower than this parameter shall be updated to target range PM counter

This parameter defines the maximum number of octets of a UDP datagram excluding the UDP and IPSec header in the transport layer. This value is used to determine the MSS for clamping of end user TCP traffic. The maximum segment size due to clamping is udpMaxDatagramSize - 20 (GTP-U) - 20/40 (IPv4/v6) - 20 (TCP) - 3 (PDCP HEADER 18bit) - 4 (MAC-I if integrity protection configured) - 1 (if SDAP header configured).  Note: If this value is configured more than minimum(all U-Plane IP Interface IpMtu for which MSS Clamping is desired), Egress IP Fragmentation may occur in gNB.
This parameter indicates whether special algorithms for some special UE are enabled or not
This parameter indicates the UE specific CSI-RS slot ratio.

Parameter name: UL TX switching boost for aggregated channel bandwidth
Description: This parameter indicates the boosting used for calculating the aggregated channel bandwidth for UL TX switching capable band combination.

Parameter name: Uplink VoIP packet aggregation SINR threshold
Description: This parameter indicates the minimum uplink SINR that a UE must have before VoIP packet aggregation will be applied to that UE.

This parameter indicates the size of a voice packet that is sent over the air when the Adaptive Voice TBS function is disabled (i.e. when NRCELL.actAdaptVoipTbs is equal to FALSE).  This includes all applicable headers, MAC CEs, and VoIP payload. The value of this parameter will be used by the scheduler to determine the TBS to be sent in response to a scheduling request from a VoNR UE, and for the TBS used for VoNR proactive grants.
The parameter is a flag to enable variable source UDP port for all interfaces.

Parameter name: VoNR tunneling delay during HO moderate range
Description: This parameter indicates the duration range for VoNR tunneling delay during HO for PM counters.  The range configured in this parameter is considered as max limit of moderate tunneling delay duration.    All VoNR packet delay interruption duration higher than this parameter shall be updated to high range PM counter

Parameter name: VoNR tunneling delay during HO target range
Description: This parameter indicates the duration range for VoNR tunneling delay during HO for PM counters.  The range configured in this parameter is considered as max of target tunneling delay duration.    All VoNR interruption duration higher than this parameter shall be updated to moderate range PM counter  All VoNR interruption duration lower than this parameter shall be updated to target range PM counter
This parameter indicates the threshold for the VoNR mute period duration to be used in related PM counter calculation.
This parameter indicates the threshold for the VoNR silent period duration to be used in related PM counter calculation.

The parameter provides the factoring value for the VoNR mute period duration threshold and VoNR silent period duration threshold parameters.  The value of parameters vonrMuteDurThresh and vonrSilentDurThresh is divided by this value to set the threshold for DL FH mute calculation.

Parameter name: Wait time for E1 or NG interface to recover before cells are barred
Description: This parameter indicates the amount of time a gNB should wait for NG/E1 interface to recover before gNB initiates cell barring

Parameter name: Weight factor for selecting SCells from the gNB
Description: This parameter indicates the weight factor applied to all candidate SCells of this gNB when inter-gNB CA is enabled.  The higher the parameter value, the higher is the probability to select SCell(s) of this gNB.  The parameter applies to all candidate SCells of this gNB on top of their cell specific weight factor NRCELL.weightForSCellSelection.  Note: gNB hosts the P(S)Cell for a UE context in inter-gNB CA and is named prime-gNB.

This parameter indicates the list of distinguished names representing the X2-C Control Plane IP addresses.  Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPSECTEMPLATE instance representing the IPSec template for the gNB X2-C Control Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/IPSECTEMPLATE-1  TNLSVC-1/IPSECTEMPLATE-1

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV4 instance representing the primary IPv4 address of the gNB X2-C Control Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV6 instance representing the primary IPv6 address of the gNB X2-C Control Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the New Radio PLMN instance representing the gNB X2 Control Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element. configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1

Parameter name: X2 EN-DC ConfigUpdate neighbor info back-off timer
Description: Consecutive X2 EN-DC Configuration Update procedures, serving to update served NR cells in neighbor eNB, are separated by at least the time given by this parameter.  The back-off timer serves to limit the maximum rate of EN-DC Configuration Updates due to cell changes and allows the gNB to accumulate and transmit all changes occurring during back-off time in one EN-DC Configuration Update message.  If this parameter is set to 0, then no back-off time is applied by the gNB.  If this parameter is not set to 0, then NR cell activation can be delayed.

Parameter name: X2 EN-DC configuration update random delay timer
Description: After detecting that X2 EN-DC Configuration Update has to be sent, the gNB applies a random delay time from the interval from 0 to the value of this parameter before starting the X2 EN-DC Configuration Update procedure.    If this parameter is set to 0, then no random delay is applied.    The random delay serves to avoid bursts of X2 EN-DC Configuration Update procedures within the network.

Parameter name: Waiting timer for EN-DC Configuration Update response
Description: This timer specifies the amount of time the gNB should wait for X2AP EN-DC CONFIGURATION UPDATE ACKNOWLEDGE before assuming that the procedure has failed.

Parameter name: Guard timer for X2-U DL End Marker reception
Description: This timer guards the SgNB against missing DL End Marker from the MeNB during the SgNB Addition procedure.  Value 0 indicates this timer is disabled.

Parameter name: Waiting timer for X2 link reestablishment by LTE eNB
Description: This timer specifies the amount of time the gNB should wait for X2 link reestablishment before removing the LTEENB instance.

Parameter name: Supervision timer to indicate no X2 link are available
Description: This timer specifies the amount of time the gNB should wait before sending an alarm indicating there is no X2-C link available

Parameter name: Waiting timer for X2 Partial Reset Confirm
Description: This timer specifies the amount of time the gNB should wait for X2AP PARTIAL RESET CONFIRM before assuming that the procedure has failed.

Parameter name: Waiting timer for X2 Reset response
Description: This timer specifies the amount of time the gNB should wait for X2AP RESET RESPONSE before assuming that the procedure has failed.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name representing the X2-U User Plane IP address.  Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

Parameter name: Data split IPv4 address 1 distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV4 instance representing the primary IPv4 address of the gNB X2-U User Plane for PDCP data split traffic. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1    Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

Parameter name: Data split IPv6 address 1 distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV6 instance representing the primary IPv6 address of the gNB X2-U User Plane for PDCP data split traffic. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1    Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPSECTEMPLATE instance representing the IPSec template for the gNB X2-U User Plane.
