Parameter name: Xn Control Plane transport Network Layer identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the Xn Control Plane transport network Layer.

Parameter name: Waiting timer for removing unused Xn link
Description: This timer specifies the amount of time the gNB should wait for Xn link reestablishment before removing the XNLINK instance.

Parameter name: Xn NG-RAN Node ConfigUpdate neighbor info back-off timer
Description: Consecutive Xn NG-RAN Node Configuration Update procedures, serving to update served NR cells in neighbor eNB, are separated by at least the time given by this parameter.  This parameter serves to limit the maximum rate of Xn NG-RAN Node Configuration Updates due to cell changes and allows the gNB to accumulate and transmit all changes occurring during back-off time in one Xn NG-RAN Node Configuration Update message.  If this parameter is set to 0, then no back-off time is applied by the gNB.

Parameter name: Xn NG-RAN Node configuration update random delay timer
Description: After detecting that Xn NG-RAN Node Configuration Update has to be sent, the gNB applies a random delay time from the interval from 0 to the value of this parameter before starting the Xn NG-RAN Node Configuration Update procedure.  This parameter serves to avoid bursts of Xn NG-RAN Node Configuration Update procedures within the network.    If this parameter is set to 0, then no random delay is applied.

Parameter name: Waiting timer for Xn NG-RAN Node Configuration Update response
Description: This timer specifies the amount of time the gNB should wait for Xn NG-RAN NODE CONFIGURATION UPDATE ACKNOWLEDGE before assuming that the procedure has failed.

Parameter name: NG-RAN Node configuration update Time To Wait
Description: This parameter defines the value of the 'Time to Wait' IE set by the gNB-CU-CP in the NG-RAN Node Configuration Update Failure message.

Parameter name: Waiting timer for Xn reset response
Description: This timer indicates the amount of time a gNB should wait for a XNAP:XN RESET RESPONSE message after the XN RESET REQUEST is sent.

Parameter name: Waiting timer for Xn setup request
Description: This timer indicates the amount of time a gNB should wait for a XNAP:XN SETUP REQUEST message after the SCTP association is established.

Parameter name: Waiting timer for Xn setup response
Description: This timer indicates the amount of time a gNB should wait for a XNAP:XN SETUP RESPONSE message after the XN SETUP REQUEST is sent.
This parameter defines the value of the 'Time to Wait' IE set by the gNB-CU-CP in the Xn Setup Failure message.

This parameter indicates the list of distinguished names representing the Xn User Plane IP addresses.  Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPSECTEMPLATE instance representing the IPSec template for the gNB Xn-U User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/IPSECTEMPLATE-1  TNLSVC-1/IPSECTEMPLATE-1    Note:  In a 5G SA RAN sharing configuration, the operator shall configure a common IPSec template for the gNB Xn-C Control Plane and the gNB Xn-U User Plane based on the configured SERVEDAMF.ngTnlId and PLMN supported by served AMF.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV4 instance representing the primary IPv4 address of the gNB Xn User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV6 instance representing the primary IPv6 address of the gNB Xn User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  Note: In SBTS, the modification of this parameter requires a BTS restart if MNL.resetNeededForIpChange is equal to TRUE, otherwise modification is online

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the New Radio PLMN instance representing the gNB Xn User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1

Parameter name: X2-U/Xn-U flow control profile for CU
Description: This structure gathers profile of CU flow control parameters for SN Terminated MCG X2-U for EN-DC and SN Terminated MCG Xn-U for Inter-gNB NR-DC
This parameter indicates the periodicity of the X2-U/Xn-U Downlink Data Delivery Status Indication message
This parameter indicates the value of maximum queuing delay including the X2-U/Xn-U interface delay to be used for the flow control algorithm

Parameter name: X2-U/Xn-U minimum throughput for flow control
Description: This parameter indicates the value of minimum throughput to be used for the flow control algorithm for the X2-U/Xn-U link.

Parameter name: UE Carrier Aggregation Capability Class instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the UE Carrier Aggregation Capability Class (NRCACLASS) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRMEAS_PROFILE instance.
This parameter indicates the list of frequency bands which needs to be supported by UE for CA capable criterion

Parameter name: Second list of CA frequency bands
Description: This parameter indicates the second list of frequency bands which needs to be supported by UE for CA capable criterion
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates the list of frequency bands which shall not be supported by the UE

This parameter indicates the list of frequency bands to be supported as PCell band with both DL and UL directions in UE supported band combination which fulfills CA capable criterion defined by NRCACLASS.caBandList

Parameter name: Second list of PCell frequency bands
Description: This parameter indicates the list of frequency bands to be supported as PCell band with both DL and UL directions in UE supported band combination which fulfills CA capable criterion defined by NRCACLASS.caBandList2

Parameter name: New Radio Carrier Aggregation Aware Idle Mode Configuration for Primary Cells instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Carrier Aggregation Aware Idle Mode Configuration for Primary Cells (NRCAIMP) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Primary cell configuration for idle mode mobility steering
Description: This structure indicates the primary cell configuration used in the CA aware algorithm for idle mode mobility steering.

Parameter name: NR carrier frequency of a primary cell
Description: This parameter indicates the center frequency of the SS block of the NR carrier of a primary cell in a primary cell/secondary cell combination used for idle mode mobility steering, where the frequency corresponds to a GSCN value as specified in TS 38.101

Parameter name: New Radio Carrier Aggregation Aware Idle Mode Configuration for Secondary Cells instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Carrier Aggregation Aware Idle Mode Configuration for Secondary Cells (NRCAIMS) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRCAIMP instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Secondary cell configuration for idle mode mobility steering
Description: This structure indicates the secondary cell configuration used in the CA aware algorithm for idle mode mobility steering.

Parameter name: NR carrier frequency of a secondary cell
Description: This parameter indicates the center frequency of the SS block of the NR carrier of a secondary cell in a primary cell/secondary cell combination used for idle mode mobility steering, where the frequency corresponds to a GSCN value as specified in TS 38.101

Parameter name: New Radio CBRS Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio CBRS Profile (NRCBRSPR) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.    A NRCBRSPR instance cannot be deleted if a NRCBSD instance exists such that NRCBSD.nrCbrsPrId is equal to NRCBRSPR.nrCbrsPrId.

Parameter name: Activate PAL and GAA channels bonding
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates bonding of the PAL and GAA channels into one single grant in gNB CBSD side.

Parameter name: Channel spacing between two cells with their channel bandwidths
Description: This parameter indicates the channel spacing between two CBSD cells with their channel bandwidths.
This parameter indicates the channel bandwidth of cell 1.
This parameter indicates the channel bandwidth of cell 2.
This parameter indicates the channel spacing between two CBSD cells.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates the connection mode of the BTS to the SAS server
Range and step: direct connect to SAS server (0), connect through https proxy (1), connect through domain proxy (3)

Description: This structure indicates the desired values of parameters to configure the TDD frame structure for a CBSD cell.
This parameter indicates the desired type of the frame structure
This parameter indicates the desired length in the OFDM symbols of the guard period

Parameter name: Desired LTE to NR frame shift
Description: This parameter indicates the desired LTE to NR frame shift in ms
This parameter indicates the desired TD LTE uplink and downlink configuration.  Refer to TS 36.211 section 4.2 for information.
This structure indicates the fallback values of the parameters to configure the TDD frame structure.
This parameter indicates the fallback type of the frame structure
This parameter indicates the fallback length in the OFDM symbols of the guard period.

Parameter name: Fallback LTE to NR frame shift
Description: This parameter indicates the fallback LTE to NR frame shift in ms.
This parameter indicates the fallback TD LTE uplink and downlink configuration.  Refer to TS 36.211 section 4.2 for information.

Parameter name: Max power difference allowed between PAL and GAA channels
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum power lower allowed by the GAA channel from the adjacent PAL channel.    Note this parameter set to -1 means there is no need to check the power difference between PAL and GAA channels, As long as the GAA channel does not violate the HW limitation or does not violate the desidedPmax-maxGrantPwrRed, it can be used.
This parameter indicates the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) or IP Address (IPv4 or IPv6)/port or Hostname/port of the primary domain proxy server.
This parameter indicates the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) or IP Address (IPv4 or IPv6)/port or Hostname/port of the primary HTTPS proxy server.
This parameter indicates the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) or IP Address (IPv4 or IPv6)/port or Hostname/port of the primary Spectrum Access System (SAS) server.
This parameter indicates a unique name to the CBRS profile.  This parameter has no operation impact on the system.
This parameter indicates the period to query the SAS server in order to check if a better spectrum grant is available.
This parameter indicates the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) or IP Address (IPv4 or IPv6)/port or Hostname/port of the secondary domain proxy server.
This parameter indicates the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) or IP Address (IPv4 or IPv6)/port or Hostname/port of the secondary HTTPS proxy server.
This parameter indicates the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) of the secondary Spectrum Access System (SAS) server.

This parameter indicates the supported channel bandwidth of a grant.  This parameter is encoded as a bitmap, where bit N is equal to 0 if the corresponding channel bandwidth is not supported, and is equal to 1 if the corresponding channel bandwidth is supported.  The channel bandwidth is in 5 MHz block increments, from right to left, the right most bit 0 corresponds to 5MHz, bit 1 corresponds to 10MHz, ... , bit 19 corresponds to 100 MHz.
Range and step: bits mask: 5 MHz channel bandwidth (0), 10 MHz channel bandwidth (1), 15 MHz channel bandwidth (2), 20 MHz channel bandwidth (3), 25 MHz channel bandwidth (4), 30 MHz channel bandwidth (5), 35 MHz channel bandwidth (6), 40 MHz channel bandwidth (7), 45 MHz channel bandwidth (8), 50 MHz channel bandwidth (9), 55 MHz channel bandwidth (10), 60 MHz channel bandwidth (11), 65 MHz channel bandwidth (12), 70 MHz channel bandwidth (13), 75 MHz channel bandwidth (14), 80 MHz channel bandwidth (15), 85 MHz channel bandwidth (16), 90 MHz channel bandwidth (17), 95 MHz channel bandwidth (18), 100 MHz channel bandwidth (19)

Description: This parameter indicates the version of the WINNF SAS-CBSD interface technical specification used by BTS.

Parameter name: New Radio CBRS Device instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio CBRS Device (NRCBSD) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.

This parameter indicates the boresight direction of the horizontal plane of the antenna in degrees with respect to true north.  It is optional for a Category A CBSD and required for a Category B CBSD.  A value of 0 (degrees) means true north; a value of 90 (degrees) means east.

This parameter indicates the 3 dB antenna horizontal-plane beamwidth in degrees.  It is optional for a Category A CBSD and required for a category B CBSD.  A value of 360 (degrees) means the antenna has an omnidirectional radiation pattern in the horizontal plane.

This parameter indicates the antenna downtilt in degrees.  It is optional for a Category A CBSD and required for a Category B CBSD.  A negative value means the antenna is tilted up (above horizontal).
This parameter indicates the peak antenna gain in dBi.  It is optional for a Category A CBSD and required for a Category B CBSD.
This parameter indicates (optionally) the antenna model if an external antenna is used.

Parameter name: List of Antenna Line distinguished names
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the ANTL instance(s) associated with this NRCBSD instance. These distinguished names can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/EQM-1/APEQM-1/RMOD-1/ANTL-1  ANTL-1    This parameter shall only be configured when multiple sector antennas are attached to the radio or when radio resiliency with cross-sectors connectivity is in use
This parameter indicates the CBSD ID assigned by the SAS server.  When this parameter has no value, it means no valid CBSD ID information from SAS server is available.
This parameter indicates a device identifier provided by the Federal Communications Commission (FCC).
This parameter indicates whether the CBSD should operate in the Priority Access License (PAL) or in the General Authorized Access (GAA) mode.

Parameter name: CBRSA group identifier of common channel group
Description: This parameter indicates the CBRSA group identifier of the common channel group for this CBSD.    The range represents the number of bytes to store all the characters of the string. If the string is UTF-8 encoded, each character occupies between 1 to 4 bytes, depending upon the language. If ASCII encoded, each character occupies a single byte. The numbers of characters supported in case of UTF-8 encoding is 32.

Parameter name: CBRSA group ID of interference coordination group
Description: This parameter indicates the CBRSA group identifier of the interference coordination group for this CBSD.    The range represents the number of bytes to store all the characters of the string. If the string is UTF-8 encoded, each character occupies between 1 to 4 bytes, depending upon the language. If ASCII encoded, each character occupies a single byte. The numbers of characters supported in case of UTF-8 encoding is 32.
This parameter indicates the device category of a CBSD cell.
This parameter indicates the current registration state of the CBSD.
This parameter indicates the serial number of the CBSD.  It is same as the RRH serial number.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter indicates the Federal Communications Commission (FCC) certification identifier of the CBSD.    FCC ID = Grantee Code(G) + Product Code(P)  Current Grantee Code Process:  - Grantee code = 3 characters  - Product code = maximum of 14 characters  - AGGPPPPPPPPPPPPPP, where A = grantee code character limited to alphabetic character only    New Grantee Code Process:  - Grantee code = 5 characters  - Product code = maximum of 14 characters  - #GGGGPPPPPPPPPPPPPP, where # = grantee code character limited to numeric value only (no zeros or ones)
This parameter indicates the CBSD antenna height in meters
This parameter indicates the height type.  AGL height means the height is measured relatively to the ground level. AMSL height means the height is measured relatively to the mean sea level.
This parameter indicates the accuracy (as a positive number in meters) of the CBSD antenna horizontal location if it is smaller than the FCC requirement (50 meters).
This parameter indicates whether the CBSD antenna is installed indoor or not.

This parameter indicates the latitude of the CBSD antenna location in degrees relatively to the NAD 83 datum.  Positive values represent latitudes north of the equator; negative values south of the equator.

This parameter indicates the longitude of the CBSD antenna location in degrees relatively to the NAD 83 datum.  Positive values represent longitudes east of the prime meridian; negative values west of the prime meridian.
This parameter indicates the New Radio CBRS profile instance ID associated with the CBSD.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the Radio Module (RMOD) instance representing the radio module assigned to the CBSD instance. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/EQM-1/APEQM-1/RMOD-1  EQM-1/APEQM-1/RMOD-1  RMOD-1
This parameter indicates the list of SAS user group(s) this CBSD belongs to

This parameter indicates the frequency range, in 5 MHz block increments, within the 3.5GHz spectrum (3550 - 3700 MHz) in which CBSD seeks information.  This parameter is encoded as a bitmap, where bit N is equal to 0 if the corresponding frequency is not in selection list, and is equal to 1 if the corresponding frequency is within the selection list.
Range and step: bits mask: frequency range 3550 - 3555 (0), frequency range 3555 - 3560 (1), frequency range 3560 - 3565 (2), frequency range 3565 - 3570 (3), frequency range 3570 - 3575 (4), frequency range 3575 - 3580 (5), frequency range 3580 - 3585 (6), frequency range 3585 - 3590 (7), frequency range 3590 - 3595 (8), frequency range 3595 - 3600 (9), frequency range 3600 - 3605 (10), frequency range 3605 - 3610 (11), frequency range 3610 - 3615 (12), frequency range 3615 - 3620 (13), frequency range 3620 - 3625 (14), frequency range 3625 - 3630 (15), frequency range 3630 - 3635 (16), frequency range 3635 - 3640 (17), frequency range 3640 - 3645 (18), frequency range 3645 - 3650 (19), frequency range 3650 - 3655 (20), frequency range 3655 - 3660 (21), frequency range 3660 - 3665 (22), frequency range 3665 - 3670 (23), frequency range 3670 - 3675 (24), frequency range 3675 - 3680 (25), frequency range 3680 - 3685 (26), frequency range 3685 - 3690 (27), frequency range 3690 - 3695 (28), frequency range 3695 - 3700 (29)

Description: This parameter indicates the identifier of a CBSD user.    The range represents the number of bytes to store all the characters of the string. If the string is UTF-8 encoded, each character occupies between 1 to 4 bytes, depending upon the language. If ASCII encoded, each character occupies a single byte. The numbers of characters supported in case of UTF-8 encoding is 32.
This parameter indicates the accuracy (as a positive number in meters) of the CBSD antenna vertical location if it is smaller than the FCC requirement (3 meters).

Parameter name: New Radio CBSD Cell Configuration instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio CBSD Cell Configuration (NRCBSDCELL) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRCELL instance.

Parameter name: NRCELL id of the other CBSD cell in the carrier pair requiring contiguous carrier aggregation
Description: This parameter indicates the NRCELL id of the other CBSD cell in the carrier pair requiring contiguous carrier aggregation.

Parameter name: CBRS cell priority for spectrum assignment
Description: This parameter indicates the priority of the channel allocation for the CBRS cell per Cell level.
Range and step: top priority (1), 2nd priority (2), 3rd priority (3), 4th priority (4), 5th priority (5), 6th priority (6), 7th priority (7), 8th priority (8)

Parameter name: Configuration set for various channel bandwidths
Description: This structure gathers the configuration set for various channel bandwidths that the CBSD cell could be using.
This parameter selects the aggregation level in number of control channel elements (CCEs) configured within the parent NRCELL instance for the corresponding channel bandwidth.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the BWP_PROFILE instances configured within the parent NRCELL instance for the corresponding channel bandwidth. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/BWP_PROFILE-1  BWP_PROFILE-1

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the BWP_PROFILE instances configured within the parent NRCELL instance for the corresponding channel bandwidth. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/BWP_PROFILE-1  BWP_PROFILE-1

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the BWP_PROFILE instances configured within the parent NRCELL instance for the corresponding channel bandwidth. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/BWP_PROFILE-1  BWP_PROFILE-1

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the BWP_PROFILE instances configured within the parent NRCELL instance for the corresponding channel bandwidth. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/BWP_PROFILE-1  BWP_PROFILE-1

This parameter indicates the SRS bandwidth configuration (corresponding to CSRS in table 6.4.1.4.3-1 of 3GPP TS38.211) configured within the parent NRCELL instance for the corresponding channel bandwidth.
This parameter indicates the channel bandwidth that the CBSD cell could be using for transmission.
This parameter defines the period with which CSI-RS for tracking are transmitted configured within the parent NRCELL instance for the corresponding channel bandwidth.
This parameter defines the RB range allocated for CSI-RS for tracking.
This parameter indicates the desired maximum output power of the CBSD cell for the corresponding channel bandwidth.
This parameter indicates the maximum power reduction from the desired Pmax for the corresponding channel bandwidth that the operator is willing to accept.
This parameter defines the PRACH Frequency start configured within the parent NRCELL instance for the corresponding channel bandwidth.

Parameter name: Number of transmitted Synchronization Signal Blocks
Description: This parameter indicates the number of transmitted Synchronization Signal Blocks configured within the NRCELLGRP instance that the parent NRCELL instance is associated with for the corresponding channel bandwidth for CBRS beamforming radios.
Range and step: 0 beam (0), 1 beam (1), 2 beams (2), 3 beams (3), 4 beams (4), 5 beams (5), 6 beams (6), 8 beams (8), 9 beams (9), 12 beams (12), 15 beams (15), 18 beams (18), 21 beams (21), 24 beams (24), 32 beams (32), 56 beams (56)

Parameter name: Requested minimum number of PUSCH PRBs
Description: This parameter indicates the requested minimum number of PUSCH PRBs in the UL spectrum in case the long PUCCH is selected, configured within the parent NRCELL instance for the corresponding channel bandwidth.
This parameter defines the RB number, on which allocation for CSI-RS for tracking starts, configured within the parent NRCELL instance for the corresponding channel bandwidth.
This parameter indicates the control resource set zero (CORESET(0)) configuration configured within the parent NRCELL instance for the corresponding channel bandwidth.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates the desired CBSD Cell bandwidth.

This parameter indicates whether the SAS grant channel type is Priority Access License (PAL) or General Authorized Access (GAA) or Mixed with PAL and GAA (MIX=PAL+GAA)  When this parameter has no value, it means no valid grant channel type information from SAS server is available.

This parameter indicates the maximum Effective Isotropic Radiated Power (EIRP) granted by the SAS server.  When this parameter has no value, it means no valid max EIRP information from SAS server is available.

This parameter indicates the grant spectrum high frequency assigned by the SAS server.  When this parameter has no value, it means no valid spectrum frequency information from SAS server is available.
This parameter indicates the grant spectrum low frequency assigned by the SAS server.  When this parameter has no value, it means no valid spectrum frequency information from SAS server is available.

This parameter indicates the maximum bandwidth reduction in MHz from NRCBSDCELL.desiredChBw in grant for the CBSD Cell.  In case there is no available spectrum that its bandwidth is greater than or equal to the configured CBSD Cell bandwidth (NRCELL.chBw), if this parameter is greater than 0, the CBSD attempts to acquire grant with the reduced bandwidth (NRCBSDCELL.desiredChBw - NRCBSDCELL.maxGrantChBwRed) from the SAS server.

This structure gathers parameters  for a subset of Grant Information (grant ID, current operation state of the grant and NRCBSD instance identifier).  In case of a supercell, the NRCBSD instance Id can be used to associate the grant to a subcell.
This parameter indicates the grant ID from SAS server for the CBSD cell.  When this parameter has no value, it means no valid grant ID information from SAS server is available.
This parameter indicates the current operation state of the grant from the SAS server for the CBSD cell.

Parameter name: New Radio CBRS Device instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio CBRS Device (NRCBSD) identifier within the same containing NRBTS.
This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Cell (NRCELL) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.

Parameter name: A1 measurement configuration for primary cell switch enabled
Description: This parameter indicates the measurement configuration on secondary cell that is enabled on event A1 for primary cell switch.  This can be the RSRP measurement or the RSRQ measurement or both or a combined criteria.    More precisely, this configuration can be the following ones:  - rsrp: Single UE measurement is configured with RSRP event criteria. Parameter name: A2 measurement configuration for secondary cell release enabled
Description: This parameter indicates the measurement configuration on secondary cell that is enabled on event A2 for secondary cell release.  This can be the RSRP measurement or the RSRQ measurement or both or a combined criteria.  It also activates/deactivates secondary cell release based on UE measurement.    More precisely, this configuration can be the following ones:  - rsrp: Single UE measurement is configured with RSRP event criteria. The secondary cell is released immediately after the measurement report is received.  - rsrq: Single UE measurement is configured with RSRQ event criteria. The secondary cell is released immediately after the measurement report is received.  - rsrpAndRsrq: Two UE measurements are configured, one with RSRP and one with RSRQ event criteria. The secondary cell is released immediately after the first measurement report is received for either of them.  - rsrpCombined: Single UE measurement is configured with RSRP event criteria. The secondary cell is released immediately after the measurement report is received, if the additional RSRQ criteria are also met (RSRQ criteria checked by the gNB).  - rsrqCombined: Single UE measurement is configured with RSRQ event criteria. The secondary cell is released immediately after the measurement report is received, if the additional RSRP criteria are also met (RSRP criteria checked by the gNB).
Range and step: none (0), rsrp (1), rsrq (2), rsrpAndRsrq (3), rsrpCombined (4), rsrqCombined (5)

Description: This parameter gathers all associated parameters used to characterize the set of A2 measurement for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP for secondary cell release.

Description: This parameter defines the hysteresis value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A2 for secondary cell release.

Parameter name: Delta to A2 threshold SSB RSRP for MPR intra-band contiguous secondary cell release
Description: This parameter defines the delta value applied to A2 RSRP threshold (a2ThresholdSCellRelSsbRsrp) for secondary cell release in order to compensate the high maximum power reduction (MPR) value applied by the UEs configured with FR1 UL CA intra-band contiguous.  When this parameter is configured, the A2 RSRP threshold value configured at the UE is equal to (NRCELL.a2MeasSCellRelSsbRsrp.a2ThresholdSCellRelSsbRsrp + NRCELL.a2MeasSCellRelSsbRsrp.a2ThresholdMPRIntraContDelta).  When this parameter is not configured, then no delta is applied.

Description: This parameter defines the delta applied to the threshold value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A2 for secondary cell release for UL TX switching UEs with FDD PCell + TDD SCell.  This parameter is only used for UL TX switching UEs with FDD PCell + TDD SCell, and only when NRBTS.actBufferBasedSCellAddition is equal to 'disabled'.

This parameter indicates the measurement configuration that is enabled on event A3.  This can be the RSRP measurement or the RSRQ measurement or both or a combined criteria.
Range and step: none (0), rsrp (1), rsrq (2), rsrpAndRsrq (3), rsrpCombined (4), rsrqCombined (5)

Description: This parameter gathers all the associated parameters used to characterize the set of A3 measurement for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP.
This parameter indicates the hysteresis value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3.

This parameter defines the offset value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3.    The offset value configured in this parameter is not the actual value used in the measurement quantity RSRP applied at the UE side in NR measurement report triggering.    The UE derives the actual a3-Offset in dB to be applied as follows:  actual a3-Offset = value configured in this parameter * 0.5 dB.    Examples:  - If this parameter is equal to 3, then the actual a3-Offset derived by the UE is equal to 3 * 0.5 dB = 1.5 dB  - If this parameter is equal to 6, then the actual a3-Offset derived by the UE is equal to 6 * 0.5 dB = 3 dB

Parameter name: A3 time to trigger SSB RSRP
Description: This parameter defines the time during which specific criteria for the event needs to be met in order to trigger a measurement report for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3.
This parameter gathers all the associated parameters used to characterize the set of A3 measurement for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ.
This parameter indicates the hysteresis value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3.

This parameter defines the offset value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3.    The offset value configured in this parameter is not the actual value used in the measurement quantity RSRQ applied at the UE side in NR measurement report triggering.    The UE derives the actual a3-Offset in dB to be applied as follows:  actual a3-Offset = value configured in this parameter * 0.5 dB.    Examples:  - If this parameter is equal to 3, then the actual a3-Offset derived by the UE is equal to 3 * 0.5 dB = 1.5 dB  - If this parameter is equal to 6, then the actual a3-Offset derived by the UE is equal to 6 * 0.5 dB = 3 dB

Parameter name: A3 time to trigger SSB RSRQ
Description: This parameter defines the time during which specific criteria for the event needs to be met in order to trigger a measurement report for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3.

Parameter name: Maximum number of times A4 measurement for mobility to higher priority NR frequency can be reactivated for NSA UE.
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of times A4 measurement for mobility to higher priority NR frequency can be reactivated for NSA UE.  When A1 measurement report for steering UE to preferred NR layer is received, inter-frequency A4 measurements for mobility to higher priority NR frequency can be reactivated if the number of times inter-freq A4 configured in the UE has reached the maximum value (NRCELL.a4PeriodicMeasControlNSA.a4MeasMaxNumber) and the number of reactivation completed is less than the limit defined by this parameter (NRCELL.a4MeasHigherPrioFreqMaxReact).

Parameter name: Maximum number of times A4 measurement for mobility to higher priority NR frequency can be reactivated for SA UE.
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of times A4 measurement for mobility to higher priority NR frequency can be reactivated for SA UE.  When A1 measurement report for steering UE to preferred NR layer is received, inter-frequency A4 measurements for mobility to higher priority NR frequency can be reactivated if the number of times inter-freq A4 configured in the UE has reached the maximum value (NRCELL.a4PeriodicMeasControlSA.a4MeasMaxNumber) and the number of reactivation completed is less than the limit defined by this parameter (NRCELL.a4MeasHigherPrioFreqMaxReactSA).

Parameter name: Periodic A4 measurement control for NSA
Description: This parameter gathers all the associated parameters used to configure A4 measurement for NSA

Parameter name: Supervision timer for A4 FR1 measurement for NSA
Description: This supervision timer indicates the time to wait for A4 FR1 measurement report from the UE for NSA mobility to higher priority NR layer.  When it expires, if an A4 measurement for a frequency not having the highest priority was saved during supervision period, then PSCell change is triggered else A4 deactivation is triggered.  This timer is started each time A4 measurement is activated at the UE.  If FR1 and FR2 inter-frequencies are configured for A4 measurement, max value between (NRCELL.a4PeriodicMeasControlNSA.a4Fr1SupervisionTimer and NRCELL.a4PeriodicMeasControlNSA.a4Fr2SupervisionTimer) is used

Parameter name: Supervision timer for A4 FR2 measurement for NSA
Description: This supervision timer indicates the time to wait for A4 FR2 measurement report from the UE for NSA mobility to higher priority NR layer.  When it expires, if an A4 measurement for a frequency not having the highest priority was saved during supervision period, then PSCell change is triggered else A4 deactivation is triggered.  This timer is started each time A4 measurement is activated at the UE.  If FR1 and FR2 inter-frequencies are configured for A4 measurement, max value between (NRCELL.a4PeriodicMeasControlNSA.a4Fr1SupervisionTimer and NRCELL.a4PeriodicMeasControlNSA.a4Fr2SupervisionTimer) is used

Parameter name: Block timer for activating A4 measurements for NSA
Description: This parameter indicates the duration of inter-frequency A4 measurement activation block timer for mobility to higher priority NR frequency for NSA.    If this parameter is set to value greater than 0, the periodical inter-frequency A4 measurement activation will be blocked for the duration of this timer after NRCELL-a4PeriodicMeasControlSA/a4MeasMaxNumber consecutive retries of A4 measurement activation. After expiration of this timer, the periodical inter-frequency A4 measurement activation is resumed.

Parameter name: Maximum number of times A4 measurement will be activated for NSA UE
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of times A4 measurement will be activated for NSA UE.

Parameter name: Retry timer for A4 measurement for NSA
Description: This timer indicates the time to wait before A4 measurement activation for NSA when the UE enters the cell and between the deactivation of A4 due to the expiry of the supervision timer (NRCELL.a4PeriodicMeasControlNSA.a4Fr1SupervisionTimer or NRCELL.a4PeriodicMeasControlNSA.a4Fr2SupervisionTimer) and the subsequent activation of the A4 measurement for NSA.    When it expires, A4 measurement is configured in the UE if A4 measurement was not already done else A4 measurement reactivation is triggered.    This timer is started at deactivation of the A4 measurement.

Parameter name: Periodic A4 measurement control for SA
Description: This parameter gathers all the associated parameters used to configure A4 measurement for SA

Parameter name: Supervision timer for A4 FR1 measurement for SA
Description: This supervision timer indicates the maximum time to wait for A4 FR1 measurement report from the UE in the following 2 cases:  1) for SA mobility to higher priority NR layer or  2) for A4-based FR1 CA SCell Addition.  When it expires, if an A4 measurement for a frequency not having the highest priority was saved during supervision period, then handover is triggered (applicable only to case 1) else A4 deactivation is triggered (applicable to cases 1 and 2).  This timer is started each time A4 measurement is activated at the UE.  If FR1 and FR2 inter-frequencies are configured for A4 measurement, the maximum value between (NRCELL.a4PeriodicMeasControlSA.a4Fr1SupervisionTimer and NRCELL.a4PeriodicMeasControlSA.a4Fr2SupervisionTimer) is used.

Parameter name: Supervision timer for A4 FR2 measurement for SA
Description: This supervision timer indicates the maximum time to wait for A4 FR2 measurement report from the UE:  1) for SA mobility to higher priority NR layer, or  2) for NR-DC PSCell addition  When it expires, if an A4 measurement for a frequency not having the highest priority was saved during supervision period, then handover is triggered (applicable only to point 1) else A4 deactivation is triggered (applicable to points 1 and 2).    This timer is started each time A4 measurement is activated at the UE.  If FR1 and FR2 inter-frequencies are configured for A4 measurement, max value between (NRCELL.a4PeriodicMeasControlSA.a4Fr1SupervisionTimer and NRCELL.a4PeriodicMeasControlSA.a4Fr2SupervisionTimer) is used

This parameter indicates the duration of A4 measurement activation block timer.    If this parameter is set to value greater than 0, the periodical A4 measurement activation will be blocked for the duration of this timer after NRCELL-a4PeriodicMeasControlSA.a4MeasMaxNumber consecutive retries of A4 measurement activation. After expiration of this timer, the periodical A4 measurement activation is resumed.    This parameter is applicable to A4 inter-frequency measurements for NR-DC or for mobility to higher priority NR frequency.

Parameter name: Maximum number of times A4 measurement will be activated for SA UE
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of times A4 measurements will be activated for SA UE.

Parameter name: Retry timer for A4 measurement for SA
Description: This timer indicates the time to wait before A4 measurement activation for SA when the UE enters the cell and between the deactivation of A4 due to the expiry of the supervision timer (NRCELL.a4PeriodicMeasControlSA.a4Fr1SupervisionTimer or NRCELL.a4PeriodicMeasControlSA.a4Fr2SupervisionTimer) and the subsequent activation of the A4 measurement for SA.    When it expires, A4 measurement is configured in the UE if A4 measurement was not already done else A4 measurement reactivation is triggered.    This timer is started at deactivation of the A4 measurement.

Parameter name: A4 measurement report timer for EN-DC
Description: This parameter indicates the timer for the A4 measurement report in EN-DC aware idle mode traffic steering.
This parameter indicates the measurement configuration that is enabled on event A5.  This can be the RSRP measurement or the RSRQ measurement or both or a combined criteria.
Range and step: none (0), rsrp (1), rsrq (2), rsrpAndRsrq (3), rsrpCombined (4), rsrqCombined (5)

Description: This parameter gathers all the associated parameters used to characterize the set of A5 measurement for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP.
This parameter specifies the hysteresis value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A5
This parameter defines the threshold1 value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A5.
This parameter defines the threshold2 value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A5.

Parameter name: A5 time to trigger SSB RSRP
Description: This parameter defines the time during which specific criteria for the event needs to be met in order to trigger a measurement report for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A5
This parameter gathers all the associated parameters used to characterize the set of A5 measurement for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ.
This parameter specifies the hysteresis value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A5
This parameter defines the threshold1 value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A5.
This parameter defines the threshold2 value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A5.

Parameter name: A5 Time To Trigger SSB RSRQ
Description: This parameter defines the time during which specific criteria for the event needs to be met in order to trigger a measurement report for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A5

Parameter name: A6 measurement configuration for secondary cell swap enabled
Description: This parameter indicates the measurement configuration on secondary cell that is enabled on event A6 for secondary cell swap.  This can be the RSRP measurement or the RSRQ measurement or both or a combined criteria.  It also activates/deactivates secondary cell swap based on UE measurement. This parameter is configured on the secondary cell.    More precisely, this configuration can be the following ones:  - rsrp: Single UE measurement is configured with RSRP event criteria. The secondary cell is swapped immediately after the measurement report is received.  - rsrq: Single UE measurement is configured with RSRQ event criteria. The secondary cell is swapped immediately after the measurement report is received.  - rsrpAndRsrq: Two UE measurements are configured, one with RSRP and one with RSRQ event criteria. The secondary cell is swapped immediately after the first measurement report is received for either of them.  - rsrpCombined: Single UE measurement is configured with RSRP event criteria. The secondary cell is swapped immediately after the measurement report is received, if the additional RSRQ criteria are also met (RSRQ criteria checked by the gNB).  - rsrqCombined: Single UE measurement is configured with RSRQ event criteria. The secondary cell is swapped immediately after the measurement report is received, if the additional RSRP criteria are also met (RSRP criteria checked by the gNB).
Range and step: none (0), rsrp (1), rsrq (2), rsrpAndRsrq (3), rsrpCombined (4), rsrqCombined (5)

Parameter name: A6 measurement SSB RSRP for secondary cell swap
Description: This parameter gathers all associated parameters used to characterize the set of A6 measurement for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP for secondary cell swap.  This parameter is configured on the secondary cell.

Parameter name: A6 hysteresis SSB RSRP for secondary cell swap
Description: This parameter defines the hysteresis value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A6 for secondary cell swap.  This parameter is configured on the secondary cell.

Parameter name: A6 offset SSB RSRP for secondary cell swap
Description: This parameter defines the offset value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A6 for secondary cell swap.  This parameter is configured on the secondary cell.

Parameter name: A6 time to trigger SSB RSRP for secondary cell swap
Description: This parameter specifies the time during which specific criteria for the event needs to be met in order to trigger a measurement report for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A6 for secondary cell swap.  This parameter is configured on the secondary cell.

Parameter name: Use allowed cell list A6 SCell swap SSB RSRP
Description: This parameter indicates whether only the cells included in the allow-list of the associated measObjectNR are applicable for A6 measurement for SCell swap when NRCELL.a6MeasSCellSwapEnabled is equal to 'rsrp' or 'rsrpAndRsrq' or 'rsrpCombined'.  This parameter is configured on the secondary cell.

Parameter name: A6 measurement SSB RSRQ for secondary cell swap
Description: This parameter gathers all associated parameters used to characterize the set of A6 measurement for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ for secondary cell swap.  This parameter is configured on the secondary cell.

Parameter name: A6 hysteresis SSB RSRQ for secondary cell swap
Description: This parameter defines the hysteresis value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A6 for secondary cell swap.  This parameter is configured on the secondary cell.

Parameter name: A6 offset SSB RSRQ for secondary cell swap
Description: This parameter defines the offset value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A6 for secondary cell swap.  This parameter is configured on the secondary cell.

Parameter name: A6 time to trigger SSB RSRQ for secondary cell swap
Description: This parameter specifies the time during which specific criteria for the event needs to be met in order to trigger a measurement report for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A6 for secondary cell swap.  This parameter is configured on the secondary cell.

Parameter name: Use allowed cell list A6 SCell swap SSB RSRQ
Description: This parameter indicates whether only the cells included in the allow-list of the associated measObjectNR are applicable for A6 measurement for SCell swap when NRCELL.a6MeasSCellSwapEnabled is equal to 'rsrq' or 'rsrpAndRsrq' or 'rsrqCombined'.  This parameter is configured on the secondary cell.
This parameter defines the absolute RSRP threshold for the consolidation of measurement results per SS/PBCH block(s) from L1 filter(s).
This parameter defines the absolute RSRQ threshold for the consolidation of measurement results per SS/PBCH block(s) from L1 filter(s).

This parameter activates/deactivates ARP based admission control.  The possible values are the following:  - value off: ARP based admission control is deactivated  - value on: ARP based admission control is activated for all possible cases  - value handovers: ARP based admission control is activated only for handovers

This parameter activates/deactivates uplink adaptive VoIP TBS.  With this function, the gNB will initially set the uplink VoIP TBS based on the 5QI1 GBR value provided by the AMF when the 5QI1 bearer is established. As the VoIP data is transmitted by the UE over the 5QI1 bearer, the gNB will measure the VoIP data and adjust the VoIP TBS to match the amount of VoIP data that is being transmitted by the UE.  If this function is disabled, NRBTS.ulsVoipPacketSize will be used to set the uplink VoIP TBS.

Parameter name: Activate adaptive retransmission based on reserved MCS
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates adaptive retransmission based on reserved MCS in DL and UL    This parameter is ignored for UL data transmission processed by DSP based BB modules like e.g. ABIO if UL MU-MIMO is activated (NRCELL.actUlMuMimo is equal to TRUE).    Note: This parameter is ignored for UL data transmission processed by FPGA based BB modules like e.g. ABIL

Parameter name: Activate adaptive retransmission with reserved MCS enhancements for ABIL and interworking with UL MU MIMO
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the adaptive retransmission for ABIL in UL and interworking of adaptive retransmission with UL MU-MIMO. The adaptive retransmission allows the use of reserved MCS in retransmission.
This parameter activates/deactivates load based adaptive UL scheduling request (SR)

Parameter name: Activate adjustment of PRACH DTX threshold option
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the adjustment of PRACH DTX threshold option.  It is recommended to keep the default value (FALSE), as changing the value will affect network performance.
This parameter activates/deactivates the user-configurable mapping between logical and physical antenna ports in DL direction.
This parameter activates/deactivates the aperiodic CSI reporting in the NR cell.

Parameter name: Activate priority boost for SRB anticipatory UL grant
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates priority boosting anticipatory UL grant for SRB higher than SR priority.

Parameter name: Activate averaging algorithm for UL CLPC receive power
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the averaging algorithm for receive power in UL closed loop power control.    Note: This parameter is ignored if NRCELL.actUlClosedLoopPwrCtrl is not equal to 'puschSrs' or to 'pucchPuschSrs'.

Parameter name: Activate bad UL radio based redirection
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates bad uplink radio based redirection and indicates the algorithm to be used by gNB for detection of bad uplink radio.    The possible values are:  - 'highUlBlerBased', meaning that the gNB-DU considers the uplink radio for the UE context is in bad radio condition if 'high uplink BLER' is observed for the UE context.  - 'highUlBlerOrUlNackFloodBased', meaning that the gNB-DU considers the uplink radio for the UE context is in bad radio condition if either 'high uplink BLER' or 'uplink Nack flooding' is observed for the UE context.  - 'rIEventAndHighUlBlerOrUlNackFloodBased', meaning that the gNB-DU considers the uplink radio for the UE context is in bad radio condition if either 'high uplink BLER' or 'uplink Nack flooding' is observed for the UE context and at the same time RIM alarm is present.  - 'dataRimAndHubOrUnf_voNrHubOrUnf', meaning that the gNB-DU considers the uplink radio for the UE context is in bad radio condition if for:  * data only calls 'remote interference' and either 'high uplink BLER' or 'uplink Nack flooding' is observed for the UE context.  * VoNR calls either 'high uplink BLER' or 'uplink Nack flooding' is observed for the UE context.  - 'voNrRimAndHubOrUnf_dataHubOrUnf', meaning that the gNB-DU considers the uplink radio for the UE context is in bad radio condition if for:  * VoNR calls 'remote interference' and either 'high uplink BLER' or 'uplink Nack flooding' is observed for the UE context.  * data only calls either 'high uplink BLER' or 'uplink Nack flooding' is observed for the UE context.
Range and step: disabled (0), highUlBlerBased (10), highUlBlerOrUlNackFloodBased (20), rIEventAndHighUlBlerOrUlNackFloodBased (30), dataRimAndHubOrUnf_voNrHubOrUnf (40), voNrRimAndHubOrUnf_dataHubOrUnf (50)

Description: This parameter activates/deactivates beamforming.

Parameter name: Activate blanking of DL symbols for border coordination
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates blanking the DL symbol at the local slot, if it interferes with the guard symbol of a remote slot.

This parameter activates/deactivates IMEI based management of UE bandwidth capabilities.  The possible values are:  - 'disabled' meaning these capabilities are disabled  - 'NRUEBWLIM_PROFILE-1' meaning these capabilities are enabled and the NRUEBWLIM_PROFILE instance with identifier equal to 1 is used as limitation profile  - 'NRUEBWLIM_PROFILE-2' meaning these capabilities are enabled and the NRUEBWLIM_PROFILE instance with identifier equal to 2 is used as limitation profile
This parameter activates/deactivates the connected DRX function in the cell. Connected DRX will be configured for the UEs in the cell if this parameter is equal to true.

This parameter activates/deactivates connected DRX VoNR in the NR Cell.  Connected DRX VoNR will be configured for the UEs in the NR Cell if this parameter is equal to TRUE.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to TRUE.

Parameter name: Activate the addition of NR CGI-Info during inter-gNB PSCell change
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the addition of CGI-Info of NR target cells in candidateCellInfoListSN.measResultNeighCellListNR during inter-gNB PSCell change

Parameter name: Activate CA aware PSCell selection for FR1 cells
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the FR1 cell prioritization as a PSCell candidate over other FR1 cells provided from MeNB during PSCell selection for NSA call.    Prioritization takes effect only during SgNB addition if the UE can be configured with FR1 CA in the cell.  If the UE can be configured with FR1 CA in two or more FR1 cells with this parameter set to TRUE, then those cells shall be prioritized in the highest frequency order.

This parameter activates/deactivates having no inter PLMN carrier aggregation (CA) check between P(S)Cell and SCell.  It is configured on P(S)Cell and applies to FR1 only.  If it has a value other than 'disabled', the gNB shall allow FR1 CA between P(S)Cell and SCell of different PLMNs.    The possible values are:  - 'disabled' meaning inter PLMNs CA between P(S)Cell and SCell is not allowed.  - 'enabled_SA' meaning inter PLMN CA is allowed only for SA calls.  - 'enabled_NSA' meaning inter PLMN CA is allowed only for NSA calls.  - 'enabled_SA_NSA' meaning inter PLMN CA is allowed for both SA and NSA calls.

This parameter activates/deactivates the Wimax Interference Avoidance for Canada.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Activate Use DCI 0_0 for CBRA Contention Resolution
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates usage of DCI 0_0 for CBRA Contention Resolution.
This parameter activates/deactivates CCE split, i.e. the capability to share a PDCCH occasion between uplink and downlink grants.

Parameter name: Activate cell CSI-RS/IM for TDD non beamforming
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates cell specific NZP-CSI-RS-Resource and csi-IM-Resource for channel acquisition for TDD non beamforming cells.

Parameter name: Activate cell specific CSI-RS for FR1 TDD cell based on SSB beamforming
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates cell specific NZP-CSI-RS-Resource for TDD FR1 cells based on SSB beamforming

This parameter activates/deactivates the configurable DL interference generation.    This parameter indicates also the type of DL artificial load to generate in the cell:  - 'none' means deactivated  - 'PDSCH' means generating artificial load on PDSCH, excluding PDSCH symbols on TRS and SSB slots  - 'PDSCH+PDCCH' means generating artificial load on PDSCH and PDCCH, excluding PDSCH and PDCCH symbols on TRS and SSB slots  - 'PDSCH+PDCCH+TRS+SSB' means generating artificial load on PDSCH and PDCCH, including PDSCH and PDCCH symbols on TRS and SSB slots

Parameter name: Activate CSI-IM randomization for FDD non DSS
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates CSI-IM randomization for a NR Cell FDD non DSS. Slots and symbols that can be used for PDSCH will be used for CSI-IM with first priority if this parameter is equal to TRUE, so DL throughput may be impacted.

Parameter name: Activate CSI measurement based throughput estimation for flow control
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the CSI measurement based throughput estimation for flow control.    The supported values are:  - 'PastTputBased' meaning the CSI measurement based throughput estimation for flow control is deactivated and the past throughput based throughput estimate is used for flow control;  - 'CSIMeasBasedCaUe' meaning the CSI measurement based throughput estimation for flow control is activated for the CA UEs only;  - 'CSIMeasBasedAllUe' meaning the CSI measurement based throughput estimation for flow control is activated for all the UEs;  - 'PastTputBasedMuMimoCSIMeasBasedNonMuMimo' meaning the CSI measurement based throughput estimation for flow control is activated for all UEs with one exception: in cells with MU-MIMO enabled, only the past throughput based throughput estimation is used for flow control for both the CA and non-CA UEs;  - 'PastTputBasedMuMimoCSIMeasBasedNonMuMimoEnh' meaning the enhancement of CSI measurement based throughput estimation for flow control is activated for all UEs with the same exception as above.  - 'Spare1' is intended for future enhancements.    For all NRCELLs utilizing MU-MIMO (i.e. (NRCELL.actDlMuMimo is equal to TRUE) OR (NRCELL.actDlMuMimoEnh is equal to TRUE)) and all NRCELLs that have CA relation with those NRCELLs:  - the recommended value for this parameter is 'PastTputBased' if enhanced flow control based throughput estimation is activated, i.e. NRCELL.actEnhancedFlowControlETh is equal to TRUE.

Parameter name: Activate option for SCell CSI resource allocation
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the options for SCell CSI resource allocation.  It shall be configured for a NRCELL instance representing a PCell and applies to the FR1 SCell(s) of that P-Cell.    The possible values are the following:  - 'disabled' meaning the optimization algorithms are deactivated.  - 'csiRepAllCcHighCsiRs' meaning the simultaneousCSI-ReportsAllCC limit (see 3GPP TS 38.306 chapter 4.2.7.4) is followed and the highest number of CSI-RS resources assigned to the SCells is prioritized. This optimization algorithm will be effective when allocating periodic PUCCH resource for SCell and will never be effective for non CA UE.  - 'sCellCsiAllocAlgoOpt' meaning the use of the unified CSI resource allocation algorithm for FR1 TDD SCells with cell-specific CSI-RS is activated. For SCells that are not FR1 TDD SCells, this value is not supported.    Default value 2 (sCellCsiAllocAlgoOpt) always needs to be configured and as a consequence the value 0 (disabled) can not be configured. The value 2 will be removed in future releases.

This parameter activates/deactivates PDSCH scheduling on the CSI-RS symbols from the neighbour cells.  More precisely,  - If this parameter is equal to FALSE, then PDSCH could be scheduled on the CSI-RS symbols from the neighbour cells.  - If this parameter is equal to TRUE, then PDSCH shall not be scheduled on the CSI-RS symbols from the neighbour cells.
This parameter activates/deactivates beam power balancing between 2 SRS based DFT beams for UE specific CSI-RS.

Parameter name: Activate multiple CSI-RS resources multiplexing in slot
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates multiple CSI-RS resources multiplexing in slot for both UE and cell specific CSI-RS.  This parameter can only be equal to TRUE for cells connected to CPRI (non beamforming) or eCPRI (non beamforming or beamforming) capable radio modules.    Note: If NRCELL.actCsirsMultiplexing is equal to TRUE, ScramblingId (see 3GPP TS 38.331) for the 2nd CSI-RS that will be multiplexed together refers to NRCELL.periodicCsiAcquisition.scramblingIdStep.

This parameter activates/deactivates DL data forwarding for Voice over New Radio (VoNR) in order to prevent DL packet loss during HO while also minimizing interruption time. This feature can be activated for Xn or NG or both Xn and NG based inter-gNB handovers. For intra-gNB handovers, packet loss will be prevented by re-sending the unacknowledged packets of source node over the target node when this feature is activated.

Parameter name: Activate demotion of UL proactive scheduling
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the demotion of UL proactive scheduling.
This parameter activates/deactivates the disabling of Frequency Offset Estimation (FOE) protection.  Note: This parameter is used for FR1 cells only and its value is ignored in the other cases.

Parameter name: Activate disabling the update of the minimum number of allowed PRBS for PUSCH with UCI
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates disabling the update of the minimum number of allowed PRBs for PUSCH with UCI for the QPSK and pi/2-BPSK cases.
This parameter activates/deactivates the support of 256QAM in DL

Parameter name: Activates UE reported CQI Increment Restriction
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates UE reported CQI increment restriction.

This parameter activates/deactivates the 'dynamicswitch' resource allocation for downlink DCI 1_1 PDSCH grants instead of resource allocation type1(RAT1), provided the UE supports this allocation (UE capability: dynamicSwitchRA-Type0-1-PDSCH). This parameter is enabled only if Downlink RAT1 allocation is enabled (NRCELL.actRat1Alloc ) If the parameter is enabled and the UE capability supports this allocation, the gNB shall substitute the Downlink RAT1 allocation by the dynamic switch allocation and at slot level, the gNB will grants PDSCH with a DCI 1_1 where the Frequency Domain Resource Assignment field is set to a 'dynamicswitch' RAT1 or 'dynamicswitch' RAT0 under certain conditions.
This parameter activates/deactivates downlink inter-cell interference avoidance feature.
This parameter activates/deactivates dynamic BLER target for OLLA improvement for 256 QAM FR1

Parameter name: Activate enhanced DL link adaptation CQI to MCS  tables
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the enhanced CQI to MCS mapping tables in DL link adaptation.

Parameter name: Activate downlink low PAPR optimized precoding
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates downlink optimized low PAPR (peak-to-average power ratio) precoding.
This parameter activates/deactivates DL MU-MIMO  Note: In SBTS, this parameter is applicable for TDD only

This parameter activates/deactivates downlink MU MIMO enhancement. When downlink SRS based sub-band beam management is enabled (NRCELL.actDlSrsSubbandBm is equal to TRUE), the gNB will decide whether a UE be configured with periodic SRS for sub-band beamforming and this UE with valid sub-band beams will not be paired for downlink MU MIMO.
This parameter activates/deactivates DL MCS Selection Optimization in Mapping table.  This CNI is only for FR1 (FR1 TDD and FR1 FDD).
This parameter activates/deactivates the power amplifier (PA) warm-up for adequate PDSCH EVM for FR1 TDD cells in DL.
Activation flag for power boost for DL HARQ retransmissions with VoNR and/or SRB1/2 data.

Parameter name: Activate downlink rank adaptation and SRB1 MCS limitation during handover
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates downlink rank adaptation in bad radio condition and downlink MCS limitation and rank degradation for SRB1 transmission during handover.

This parameter activates/deactivates downlink rank 4 probing for sounding based beamforming. If NRBTS/NRCELL-actDlMuMimoEnh is enabled and DL MU eligible UEs is difficult to meet rank4 probing criteria due to MU scheduling. If scheduling frequency is not enough for a UE, the rank 4 probing criteria cannot be met.

This parameter activates/deactivates downlink RBG randomization of the dedicated BWP. When this feature is enabled the scheduler will allocate downlink RBGs to the UEs in random locations throughout the bandwidth.    There are two modes that can be activated: Basic (enabled) and Enhanced (enhanced). The Basic mode only supports downlink RBG randomization for initial transmissions in FDD with one dedicated BWP. The Enhanced mode supports downlink RBG randomization for FDD and TDD, initial transmissions and retransmissions, multiple dedicated BWPs, and inter-working with the DL Interference Avoidance feature.    When this feature is enabled the recommended value is enhanced.

Parameter name: Activate downlink scheduler low buffer optimization
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the low buffer optimization for the downlink scheduler.

Parameter name: Activate downlink SRS based beam management
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates downlink SRS based beam management.    Updating this parameter will provoke a cell reset.

Parameter name: Activate SRS based downlink beamforming for intra-band TDD CA
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates SRS based downlink beamforming for intra-band TDD carrier aggregation

Parameter name: Activate downlink SRS based sub-band beam management
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates downlink SRS based sub-band beam management.  If it is equal to TRUE, the number of RRC reconfigurations of a cell will increase because the gNB will select UEs to be configured or released with periodic SRS for sub-band beamforming.  If NRCELL.srsForBeamMgmt is configured with NRCELL.srsForBeamMgmt.srsTypeAllocForDlBm equal to 'antenna switching' and there is no antenna switching SRS resource available for this UE, then the UE will not be selected as sub-band BF candidate.  Only UEs with valid DL SRS based wideband BF can be selected as sub-band BF candidate.

Parameter name: Activate DL VoNR limitation of maximum MCS and layer
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the limitation of the DL voice over NR (VoNR) maximum MCS and number of layers to 1 to reduce DL VoNR BLER.    If this parameter equal to TRUE:  - All DL transmissions with VoNR packet are forced to rank 1 and the appropriate rank-dependent MCS translation and PMI translation for the forced rank 1 transmission is performed.  - The maximum MCS is limited for DL VoNR packet transmission  - Excessively large increases of CQI during rank drop on a call with established VoNR bearer are compensated so that the MCS does not have a huge jump at rank change  note.  If VoNR bearer is not activated, then this parameter has no effect. Restriction of rank and MCS is not applied to DL transmissions without 5QI1 allocation. The parameter has no effect on uplink.

This parameter activates/deactivates down sampling of a NR Cell.    Updating this parameter will provoke cell reset.  In case timing setting (such as CABLINK.iqCompression) needs adjustment due to DS activation/deactivation, other cells on the same timing group may also need to be reset.

Parameter name: Activate service aware Data Radio Bearer specific BLER Target for Basic Reliability
Description: Activate service aware Data Radio Bearer specific BLER Target for Basic Reliability

This parameter activates/deactivates the DRX retransmission timer support. It provides the flexibility to configure the following parameters, as described:  - NRDRX.drxHarqRttTimerDl to allow non-zero values  - NRDRX.drxHarqRttTimerUl to allow non-zero values  - NRDRX.drxRetransTimerDl to allow '1slot', '2slot', '4slot', '6slot' and '8slot' values  - NRDRX.drxRetransTimerUl to allow '1slot', '2slot', '4slot', '6slot' and '8slot' values

This parameter activates/deactivates DRX special functionality to force UE to remain active i.e. not go into DRX sleep mode.    The value 'Disabled' does not enforce DRX sleep off for a UE with VoNR DRB while in PUSCH slot aggregation mode and DRX is activated.  The value 'Enabled_VoNr_SAg' enforces DRX sleep off for a UE with VoNR DRB while in PUSCH slot aggregation mode and DRX is activated.    Note: When NRCELL.actUlSlotAgg is set to 'Enabled_VoNr' it is recommended to set NRCELL.actDrxSleepOff to 'Enabled_VoNr_SAg'.

This parameter activates/deactivates the use of the micro DTX optimized scheduler.  If this parameter is equal to FALSE, the scheduler shall not apply the micro DTX specific optimizations.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE, the scheduler will try to aggregate DL data in order to minimize PDSCH symbols and thus reduce gNB power consumption. To do so, the gNB will buffer, for a maximum time defined by the max retention delay (NRCELL.dtxOptimizedScheduler.dtxMaxRetentionDelay), DL non-GBR DRB data (except 5QI5) to increase co scheduling opportunities.  The micro DTX optimized scheduler aims at improving power saving performances on low loaded cells. To improve power saving gains, it shall be used jointly with micro DTX for energy efficiency.

Parameter name: Active dynamic PDCCH time domain mode
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the dynamic PDCCH size management in time domain mode.  The supported values are  - 'disabled' meaning the dynamic PDCCH in time domain mode is disabled  - 'largestBWP' meaning the dynamic PDCCH in time domain mode is active based on the large BWP.  - 'perBWP' meaning the dynamic PDCCH in time domain is active based on each BWPs

Parameter name: Activate dynamic UL data split mode
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the dynamic UL data split mode function for this cell.  This feature dynamically reconfigures the UL data split mode for SCG split bearer based on NR UL radio quality.
This parameter activates/deactivates dynamic UL resource allocation
The parameter activates/deactivates the dynamic power back-off of the 256QAM algorithm.
Range and step: off (0), on, precoding independent (1), on, precoding dependent (2)

Parameter name: Activate support of in-vehicle emergency call service called NG eCall (eCall over IMS).
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the support of eCall, the Pan-European in-vehicle emergency call service defined under the eSafety initiative of the European Commission, supplemented with a minimum set of emergency related data (MSD). gNB indicates NG eCall support in SIB1.

This parameter activates/deactivates the eCPRI 7-2e UL and DL fronthaul interface.  If this parameter is set to TRUE, the supported fronthaul interface is eCPRI 7-2e.  If this parameter is set to FALSE, the supported fronthaul interface is other FH protocols than eCPRI 7-2e.

Parameter to activate or deactivate extended DRX in idle or inactive state in a cell. This feature is effectively working only when parameter is not set to 'None' and loose H-SFN synchronization is available.

This parameter activates/deactivates EIRP control over the cell segment grid. The grid covers the front half sphere centered at the antenna position and is composed of (numOfSegmentElevationEdges + 1) x (numOfSegmentAzimuthEdges + 1) cell segments.
This parameter activates/deactivates emergency calls handling.  Updating this parameter might provoke cell reset-- gNB takes decision of reset necessity.

This parameter activates/deactivates the emergency calls handling extensions of support multiple emergency ARP values per PLMN. If this flag is enabled, then NRCELL.arpPrioEmergencyCall is not used. NRBTS/NREMERGARP_PROFILE.emergArpList is used instead of NRCELL.arpPrioEmergencyCall.
This parameter activates/deactivates the test mode for electromagnetic field (EMF) validation.

Parameter name: Activate enhancements to micro DTX optimized scheduler
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the enhancements to micro DTX optimized scheduler.

Parameter name: Activate enhanced multiple dedicated bandwidth parts (BWPs)
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates enhanced multiple dedicated bandwidth parts (BWPs) concerning the use for secondary cells configured to CA UEs connected to the cell

Parameter name: Activate enhanced flow control based throughput estimation
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the enhanced flow control based throughput estimation.    The recommended value for this parameter is TRUE in case of FDD NRCELL or FR1 TDD NRCELL.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE then the recommended values for below parameters are:  - for NRCELL.primaryPathMaxQueueingDelay is 15ms.  - for NRCELL.secondaryPathMaxQueueingDelay is 15ms.  - for corresponding DRB Profile (NRDRB) instance NRDRB.actOptDataFlowRateEst is TRUE.

Parameter name: Activate enhanced PDSCH scheduling on special slot
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates enhanced PDSCH scheduling at special slot.

Parameter name: Activate enhanced voice over NR call support in the NR cell
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates enhanced voice over NR (SA option 2) call support in the NR cell.
This parameter activates/deactivates external antenna beamforming.

Parameter name: Activate multiplexing of UEs scheduled in initial bandwidth part and dedicated bandwidth part
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the multiplexing of messages from UEs in initial bandwidth part with messages/data from UEs in dedicated bandwidth part.

Parameter name: Activate multiplexing of multiple UEs in initial BWP
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates multiplexing of multiple UEs in initial BWP.

This parameter activates/deactivates the flexible measurement gap offset to prevent a conflict of long PUCCH for SR and/or DRX ON duration and/or allocated CSI-RS with the measurement gap. This parameter is applicable only for SA and when measurement gaps are configured after SR/DRX/CSI-RS has been allocated.    The possible values are:  - 'none': meaning the flexible gap offset is deactivated  - 'SR': meaning the flexible gap offset to prevent a conflict of long PUCCH for SR with the measurement gap is activated  - 'SR_and_DRX': meaning the flexible gap offset to prevent a conflict of long PUCCH for SR and/or DRX ON duration with the measurement gap is activated  - 'SR_and_DRX_and_CSIRS': meaning the flexible gap offset to prevent a conflict of long PUCCH for SR and/or DRX ON duration and/or allocated CSI-RS with the measurement gap is activated.

Parameter name: Activate full TX power mode in uplink
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates full TX power mode in uplink transmission.

Parameter name: Activation of radio admission control for GBR data radio bearers
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates radio admission control for GBR data radio bearers.    If it is equal to 1, the GBR admission control is applicable only for VoNR GBR.  If it is equal to 2, the GBR admission control is applicable for VoNR and non-VoNR GBR.

Parameter name: Activate GBR load reporting for DSS
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates GBR load reporting by NR Cells with DSS phase greater than 1, i.e. by NRCELL instances with NRCELL.lteNrDssMode equal to a value different from 0 (corresponding to none) and 1 (corresponding to DSS_Phase_1).  For GBR Load reporting to occur, the common resource manager (CRM) must also have activated GBR Load reporting.

Parameter name: Activate enhanced RAC for GBR on TD resource Priority
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the enhancement of radio admission control for GBR data based on the estimate of Time Domain resources used for priority higher than VoNR.

Parameter name: Activate option for high precision positioning method
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the options for high precision positioning method.  If there's at least one NRPOSCELL associated to this NRCELL, then updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset  Otherwise, updating this parameter will provoke cell reset  Note: NRPOSCELL associated to this NRCELL means: NRCELL.nrCellId equal to NRPOSCELL.nrCellId
This parameter activates/deactivates high speed cell.  If it is equal to TRUE, gNB supports UE speed up to 350 km/h, otherwise gNB supports UE speed up to 120 km/h.
