Parameter name: Activate increased frequency domain multiplexed users per slot
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates increased number of frequency domain multiplexed (FDM) scheduled UEs per slot.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition or cell removal will not provoke a gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke a gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter activates/deactivates interfering TDD frame muting    Note: when NRCELL.tddFrameStructure-frameStructureType is equal to 'semiStatic' and NRCELL.tddFrameStructure-ulDlDataSlotRatio is equal to '3/7', then  NRCELL.actInfTddFrameMuting shall be equal to FALSE

Parameter name: Activate flexible setting of initial bandwidth part
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the bandwidth part flexibility for the initial bandwidth part with respect to the power saving bandwidth part.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE, then it could be possible to have initial bandwidth part in higher frequencies than the power saving bandwidth part.
This parameter activates/deactivates inter rank switch block for TDD FR1 only.
This parameter activates Irc Rdd Debiasing

Parameter name: Activate K1 optimization for distributed PUCCH algorithm (DPA)
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates K1 optimization for the distributed PUCCH algorithm (DPA).

Parameter name: Activate link adaptation for high reliability DRB
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates link adaptation for high reliability DRB.

Parameter name: Activate legacy Canadian n77 with extended Canadian n77 coexistence in NR cell
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the coexistence of the legacy Canadian n77 with the extended Canadian n77 in NR cell. The legacy Canadian n77 and extended Canadian n77 UEs can attach to NR cell concurrently.

Parameter name: Activate extension type 6 on long PUCCH F1F3 beamforming
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates beamforming on long PUCCH Format1 and Format 3 over eCPRI with extension type 6.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition might provoke gNB reset. Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset, Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter activates/deactivates the long PUCCH improvements for FR1 (TDD/FDD) on ABIO and vDU (phase 2) and ABIP and RINLINE2 and ABIQ.

Parameter name: Activate long PUCCH resources optimization for FR1 TDD cells
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the long PUCCH Format 1/Format 3 HARQ feedback PRBs and long PUCCH Format 1 scheduling request (SR) PRBs optimization for FR1 TDD cells.

Parameter name: Activate low gbr number handling enhancement
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the low gbr number handling enhancement

Parameter name: Activate MAC BSR Index alignment to 3GPP
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the alignment of the MAC BSR index received from UE to the values provided by 3GPP TS 38.321 6.1.3.1-2 table.

Parameter name: Activate maximum initial delta CQI clamp for VoNR UEs
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the clamp of maximum initial delta CQI for VoNR UEs.  When equal to TRUE, a maximum initial Delta CQI value (corresponding to NRCELL.maxInitDeltaCqiClampVoNR) for VoNR UEs which is conservative in nature is considered to ensure that DLLA calculates conservative MCS values during the early phase of handover. It should ensure that BLER remains low while OLLA adjusts to the actual channel conditions. When the cell average delta CQI value is higher than NRCELL.maxInitDeltaCqiClampVoNR, the gNB will use NRCELL.maxInitDeltaCqiClampVoNR as initial Delta CQI value for VoNR UEs.

Parameter name: Activate UL MCS downgrading and PRB reduction for FDM
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the UL MCS downgrading and the UL PRB reduction for transmissions after Msg5 if the available user data is not able to fill the transport block completely.  This only concerns the UL scheduling of the FDM scheduler (FDD and TDD FR1) when activated.

Parameter name: Activate scheduling of Msg3 on slots containing PRACH
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the scheduling of Msg3 on slots containing PRACH.  It is ignored if NRCELL.pucchModeSelect is equal to 'shortPucch'.

Parameter name: Activate nominal bitrate for non-GBR bearers
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates nominal bitrate for non-GBR bearers in the NR cell

Parameter name: Activate GBR services support in the NR cell
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates GBR services support in the NR cell (SA mode)

Parameter name: Activate GBR services support in NR cell enhancements
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates GBR services support enhancements in the NR cell (SA mode).

This parameter activates/deactivates NR-DC on the cell.    The possible value is the following:  'disabled': NR-DC on the cell is deactivated  'inter-gNB_FR1-FR2': allows FR1 cell to be PCell in inter-gNB NR-DC (FR1 PCell and FR2 PSCell are located on different gNBs).

This parameter activates/deactivates remote interference management.    Note:  The value 'framework-0' of this parameter is used to activate the support of RIM framework-0 (which includes remote interference avoidance).  The value 'framework-1' of this parameter is used to activate the support of RIM framework-1 (which includes remote interference avoidance).
Range and step: disabled (0), RI detection only (1), RI detection and mitigation (2), framework-0 (3), framework-1 (4)

Description: This parameter activates/deactivates beamforming for O-RAN compliant RUs.

Parameter name: Activate flexible beam group mapping for O-RU
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates flexible mapping of beam group identifiers for O-RAN compliant RUs

Parameter name: Activate flexible beamId mapping for O-RU
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates flexible mapping of beam identifiers for O-RAN compliant RUs

This parameter activates/deactivates optimized internal reporting of measurements for flow control.  The supported values are  - 'nonOptimized' meaning the optimization is deactivated.  - 'optimizedAllUe' meaning the optimization is activated for all UE.
This parameter activates/deactivates consistency check of Other System Information (SIB3/SIB4/SIB5) between gNB-CU and gNB-DU for the cell which support SA.
This parameter activates/deactivates PRB blanking in the NR cell.

This parameter activates/deactivates the paging Optimization (the closest position with respect to SSB). Applies only for FR1.    Note:  offset (the closest position with respect to SSB),  twoBeamsPerSlot (the closest position with respect to SSB and 2 PMOs/slot for paging)

Parameter name: Activate pathloss radio link problem detection
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the usage of path loss for radio link problem detection.

Parameter name: Activate CSI-IM randomization based on PCI
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates CSI-IM/CSI-RS randomization for a NR Cell based on PCI. Slots and symbols that can be used for PDSCH will be used for CSI-RS/CSI-IM with first priority if this parameter is equal to TRUE so DL throughput may be impacted.  When NRCELL.dlMimoMode is equal to '8x4 Closed Loop Spatial Multiplexing', a different randomization method for cell specific CSI-RS and CSI-IM is triggered via setting this parameter to FALSE or TRUE. For both methods, the possibility of UE drop due to measurement gap and the number of supported DRX UEs might be impacted in some PCI configurations. Shortening the periodicity of CSI-RS/CSI-IM that is set via NRCELL.periodicCsiAcquisition.csirsNumberWithinReportPeriod_Set1 will improve the problem of DRX and measurement gap but peak throughput of PDSCH will be impacted.
This parameter activates/deactivates Periodic CSI FDM in the NR cell.

This parameter activates/deactivates the PDCCH power boosting.    Value 'disabled' means PDCCH power boosting is disabled.  Value 'enabledNonDTX' means PDCCH power boost is enabled except retransmissions for DTX.  Value 'enabled' means PDCCH power boost is enabled for all transmissions.
The parameter activates/deactivates the sharing of PDCCH symbol(s) with PDSCH.    Modification of this parameter will not provoke a gNB/5G RAT reset.

Parameter name: Activate PDSCH allocation around SSB PRBs
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the PDSCH allocation around SSB PRBs.    If this parameter is FALSE, then the PDSCH allocation around SSB is blocked (default).  If this parameter is TRUE, then the PDSCH allocation around SSB is NOT blocked.
This parameter activates/deactivates PDSCH at SSB slots
This parameter activates/deactivates power balance between 2 SRS based DFT beams for PDSCH with rank 3 and rank 4 under cell specific CSI-RS and UE specific CSI-RS scenario.

Parameter name: Activate CSI-RS for tracking rate matching for PDSCH
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates CSI-RS for tracking rate matching for PDSCH in SSB and TRS slots

Parameter name: Activate periodic CSI report bundling TDD FR1
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the periodic CSI report bundling TDD FR1

Parameter name: Activate proportional fair metric reinitialization based on scheduled UEs
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the proportional fair metric reinitialization based on scheduled UEs.
This parameter activates/deactivates the usage of the power saving bandwidth part

Parameter name: Activate PRACH format C2 with SCS 15kHz in TDD FR1
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the subcarrier spacing 15kHz for PRACH short format C2 in TDD FR1

Parameter name: Activate PRACH slot uplink channel multiplexing
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates PRACH slot uplink channel multiplexing    Configuring this parameter during cell addition or cell removal will not provoke a gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke a gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter activates/deactivates the PRACH multiplexing Level.  The possible values are:  - 'disabled' meaning these 2 PRBs of guard band is presented between PRACH and PUSCH and those 2 PRBs are not used for PUSCH  - 'enabled_Level1' meaning that L1 PRACH algorithm improvement is activated and:  - if NRCELL.pucchModeSelect is equal to 'shortPucch' - these 2 PRBs of guard band is still presented between PRACH and PUSCH.  - if NRCELL.pucchModeSelect is equal to 'longPucch' - these 2 PRBs of guard band is not presented between PRACH and PUSCH and those 2 PRBs can be used for PUSCH scheduling when the multiplexing is supported  It is strongly recommended to set this parameter value to 'enabled_Level1'

Parameter name: Activate PRACH noise power estimate when no preamble
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates PRACH noise power estimate report when no preamble detected.  This parameter is ignored if the NRCELL instance is served by a RMOD instance which is connected to a BBMOD instance that is an ABIL or ABILL one.
This parameter activates/deactivates the support for (high) priority access.  Updating this parameter might provoke cell reset-- gNB takes decision of reset necessity.

Parameter name: Proactive scheduling in NR when UL switches to LTE only
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the proactive UL scheduling in NR while UE UL work in "LTE Only" mode, connected DRX is configured for UE and Proactive UL grant feature is activated.
This parameter activates/deactivates the UL proactive scheduling
This parameter activates/deactivates PUCCH F3 additional DMRS.

Parameter name: Activate the enhanced method for PUCCH format3 DTX
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the enhanced method DTX for PUCCH format 3 when the number of UCI bits ranges from 3 to 19.  This parameter is also ignored if the NRCELL instance is served by a RMOD instance which is connected to a BBMOD instance that is an ABIL or ABILL one

Parameter name: Activate pusch12 symbols in 10MHz FDD long PUCCH
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates pusch12 symbols in 10MHz FDD long PUCCH

Parameter name: Activate threshold adjustment for PUSCH A-CSI CSI part2
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates threshold adjustment for PUSCH A-CSI CSI part2.  This parameter is ignored if the NRCELL instance is served by a RMOD instance which is connected to a BBMOD instance that is an ABIL or ABILL one.
This parameter activates/deactivates prevention of RACH access based on Timing Advance (TA) limit.

This parameter activates/deactivates the FD resource allocation type1 (RAT1) for downlink DCI 1_1 PDSCH grants per NR cell. If actRat1Alloc is set to TRUE, gNB will replace the current RAT0 allocation by the RAT1 allocation for the DL DCI 1_1 scheduled. Otherwise the DCI 1_1 allocation remains in RAT0. Note: If NRCELL.actDlDynSwitchAlloc is set to true too, gNB will replace the DL RAT1 allocation by the 'dynamicswitch' allocation (dynamicswitch RAT1 or dynamicswitch RAT0 at slot level) for the DL DCI 1_1 scheduled for the UE with dynamic switch capability.
This parameter activates/deactivates the support for reduced capability UEs.
This parameter activates/deactivates reduced frequency offset.

Parameter name: Activate Rel-16 low-PAPR DMRS for PUCCH F3
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the low-PAPR DMRS sequence type 2 as per Rel-16 3GPP TS38.211 for PUCCH F3 modulated with use of Pi/2-BPSK.

Parameter name: Activate Rel-16 low-PAPR DMRS for PUSCH
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the low-PAPR DMRS sequence type 2 as per Rel-16 3GPP TS38.211 for PUSCH with DFT-s-OFDM (Transform Precoding is used) and modulated with use of Pi/2-BPSK.

Parameter name: Activate the scheduling of UEs with an initial PUSCH transmission if the UE's retransmission is blocked
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the scheduling of UEs with an initial PUSCH transmission if the UE's retransmission cannot be scheduled due to lack of physical resources

Parameter name: Activate RRC reconfiguration at each beam switch
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates RRC reconfiguration with each beam switch.  This parameter is applicable only if NRCELL.actBeamforming is equal to TRUE; otherwise, it will be ignored.    This parameter is strongly recommended to be equal to FALSE if NRCELL.cellDepType is equal to 'SA' and NRCELL.nrarfcn >= 2016667 (FR2)
This parameter activates/deactivates service-aware configuration per DRB profile, including scheduling request, the maximum number of H-ARQ retransmissions for downlink and uplink.
This parameter activates/deactivates scheduler operation with shared PUCCH scheduling request resource.
This parameter activates/deactivates the short BSR (buffer status report) limit adaptation.

Parameter name: Activate SIB1 propagation for NR NSA or partially activated SA+NSA cells
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates SIB1 propagation for ANR purposes concerning NR NSA or SA+NSA cells when only the NSA mode is activated.  Note that this parameter does not control SIB1 propagation for SA+NSA cell when the cell is activated for both (SA and NSA) modes or when cell is activated for only the SA mode.

Parameter name: Activate slice based UL power control
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the slice-based UL power control.    Note: If NRCELL.actUlClosedLoopPwrCtrl is equal to 'puschSrs' or to 'pucchPuschSrs' and NRSULPC_PROFILE.clpcPuschTargetSinrAddOffset is not configured, then for NRSULPC_PROFILE.clpcPuschTargetSinrAddOffset the value 0 is applied by the system.

Parameter name: Activate RRC establishment with smallest RRCSetup
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the solution in which, during the RRC connection establishment procedure, the gNB sends the RRCSetup message with the smallest size.    This parameter is recommended to be equal to TRUE if NRCELL.cellDepType is equal to 'SA' and NRCELL.nrarfcn >= 2016667 (FR2)

Parameter name: Activate smart rounding in Fd UE skipping
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates smart rounding in Fd UE skipping

This parameter activates/deactivates specific BWP size in the NR cell.    Note: If this parameter is set to TRUE, then the multiple dedicated BWPs function will be disabled in this cell even if NRBTS.actMultipleDedicatedBWPs is equal to TRUE.

This parameter activates/deactivates the speculative DTX algorithm.  This algorithm will treat DTX in HARQ feedback as ACK (MAC CE are excluded) under good RF condition.    The supported values are:  - disabled meaning the speculative DTX algorithm is disabled;  - shortPUCCHMode meaning the speculative DTX algorithm is enabled for the short PUCCH mode only;  - enabled meaning the speculative DTX algorithm is enabled for both the short and long PUCCH modes.

Parameter name: Activate SRS DL beams fallback by retransmission
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates SRS DL beams fallback to PMI beams triggered by HARQ retransmission.

Parameter name: Activate SRS UL beams fallback by retransmission
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates SRS UL beams fallback to SSB/refined beams triggered by HARQ retransmission.

Parameter name: Activate stationary RedCap UE RRM measurement relaxation
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates RedCap UE relaxed RRM stationary measurement in RRC IDLE and RRC INACTIVE state for UE Power Saving in NR.

This parameter activates/deactivates the sub-band TRS rate matching.  More precisely,  - If this parameter is equal to FALSE, then sub-band TRS rate matching is disabled.  - If this parameter is equal to TRUE, then sub-band TRS rate matching is enabled.
This parameter activates/deactivates super cell
This parameter activates/deactivates super cell single SSB for NR FDD  This functionality Super Cell Single SSB is supported only in ABIL/ABILL

Parameter name: Activate TA-based disconnect - RRC connection release
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates disconnecting UE (RRC connection release) based on Timing Advance (TA) limit.

Parameter name: Activate specific initial DL and UL BLER target for VoNR DRBs
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the use of specific initial DL and UL BLER target for VoNR DRBs.

Parameter name: Activate TCP boost proactive uplink grants
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the TCP proactive UL grants (PUGs) to be sent to the UE to retrieve TCP ACKs more quickly. This feature can be activated for all UEs or only for UEs that support skippable UL grants.    TCP boost PUGs profile must be defined and referenced by a NRDRB profile before the feature will take effect.

Parameter name: Activate transport PDSCH average CQI ratio
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the reduction factor to the reported CQI for the selection of the MCS of PDSCH rate matched around TRS resource elements.

Parameter name: Activate UL scheduling for inactive BWP
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the procedure to prevent SR trans max failure by triggering UL scheduling in the assumed inactive BWP of a UE configured with a power saving BWP in case gNB detects PUSCH DTX in the assumed active BWP

This parameter activates/deactivates UCA antenna with 8T8R    When this parameter is set to TRUE, it is used for uncalibrated antenna when no external calibration is used. The value shall be the same in all cells connected to the same radio unit, that means in all LNCEL and NRCELL instances.  If this parameter is configured to TRUE,  NRCELL.beamSet.customBeamSetName shall be configured with a UCA specified beam set realization package name. Please refer to the Customer Documentation regarding valid/allowed beam set realization package names.

Parameter name: Activate UE and cell specific CSI-RS coexist
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates UE specific CSI-RS coexisted with cell specific CSI-RS in case NRCELL.actDlSrsBm is equal to TRUE and NRCELL.dlMimoMode is equal to '8x4 Closed Loop Spatial Multiplexing'.  FALSE means no UE specific CSI-RS resources are allocated by the gNB. TRUE means the gNB will firstly allocate UE specific CSI-RS resources.

Parameter name: Activate UE RRM measurement relaxation in idle
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates UE relaxed RRM measurement in RRC IDLE and RRC INACTIVE status for UE Power Saving in NR.
This parameter activates/deactivates the support of 256QAM in UL

Parameter name: Activate uplink AoA in LCS format
Description: This parameter activation or deactivation the usage of uplink AoA in LCS format.
This parameter activates/deactivates additional uplink proactive grants for VoNR UEs (with/without slot aggregation mode enabled) if there is a detected gap of no 5QI-1 data.
This parameter activates/deactivates UL configured grants type 2

Parameter name: Activate UL closed loop power control
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates uplink closed loop power control for the NR cell. It offers various combinations for PUCCH and PUSCH/SRS closed-loop power control.  When downlink SRS based sub-band beam management is enabled (NRCELL.actDlSrsSubbandBm is equal to TRUE), the gNB will decide whether a UE be configured with periodic SRS for sub-band beamforming and in this case closed loop power control will be disabled for all SRS resource sets on the large BWP, for this UE with the value in this parameter ignored. When UE is configured with pSRS for high precision positioning, then CLPC function for pSRS is not working for the UE.    Available options:  - 'disabled': Deactivate closed loop power control for PUCCH, PUSCH and SRS;  - 'pucch': Activate closed loop power control for PUCCH;  - 'puschSrs': Activate closed loop power control for PUSCH and SRS  - 'pucchPuschSrs': Activate closed loop power control for PUCCH, PUSCH and SRS
This parameter activates/deactivates the use of DFT-s-OFDM in PUSCH

Parameter name: Activate UL OLLA calculation for Re-transmissions in TDD and DFT-s-OFDM
Description: This parameter activates UL LA OLLA calculation for Re-transmissions for UEs configured with DFT-s-OFDM in TDD.

Parameter name: Activate UL minimum TBS for VoNR UEs
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates UL minimum TBS for voice packets of VoNR UEs with 5QI1 DRB configured.  It introduces the use of specific minimum MCS/PRB combination pair for cell-edge VoNR UEs to arrive at a minimum TBS in the UL direction, to avoid end-to-end packet loss due to too much segmentation. Segmentation involves lesser SINR requirements due to smaller TB sizes, but also causes additional overhead while transmission which corresponds to a considerable percentage of the TBS considering the usually small data packets in VoNR UEs. More HARQs used would mean more transmissions, and if there are segment losses in between, the entire packet is lost as there is no RLC level retransmissions.
This parameter activates/deactivates UL MU MIMO

Parameter name: Activate uplink AoA NR enhanced cell ID measurement
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates providing UL Angle of Arrival (UL AoA) measurement report for E-CID measurement result.

Parameter name: Activate uplink NR E-CID NG RAN access point position
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates providing NG RAN access point position for E-CID measurement result.

Parameter name: Activate uplink NR Enhanced Cell ID based on NR measurements
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates uplink NR Enhanced Cell ID (UL NR E-CID) based on NR measurements.

Parameter name: Activate timing advance for UL NR E-CID
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates additional measurements NR timing advance reporting using the uplink NR E-CID positioning methods.
This parameter activates/deactivates UL MCS Selection Optimization in Mapping table.  This CNI is only for FR1 (FR1 TDD and FR1 FDD).
This parameter activates/deactivates PUSCH slot aggregation to improve UE's PUSCH cell edge performance for VoNR.

Parameter name: Activate uplink SRS based beam management
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates uplink SRS based beam management    Updating this parameter will provoke a cell reset.

Parameter name: Activate PUSCH transform precoder for HO
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the UE configuration for PUSCH Transform Precoder at target cell as part of a HO procedure.

Parameter name: Activate UL transport precoder enhanced interworking with rank switching
Description: This parameter activates/ deactivates UL transport precoder enhanced interworking with rank switching.

Parameter name: Activate UL Transform Precoder Enhanced SINR Metric
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the UL Transform Precoder Enhancements SINR Metric
This parameter activates/deactivates skipping UL transmission for UL proactive scheduling.  It can only be equal to TRUE for UEs that support the skipping UL transmission capability.

Parameter name: Activate voice over NR call support in the NR cell.
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates voice over NR (SA option 2) call support in the NR cell.

Parameter name: Activate increased coding gain for DL HARQ for VoNR UEs
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the increased coding gain functionality for DL HARQ retransmissions for the VoNR UEs (with 5Q1 bearer(s)).  For a VoNR UE, when the DL HARQ transmission attempts (where transmission attempts include the initial transmission which is not successful and following retransmission attempts) are greater than NRCELL.numTxPrbVoNRIncCodingGain during a VoNR TBS scheduled in DL HARQ transmissions, in this DL HARQ process PRB increment will be used based on the number of PRBs used during the initial transmission and the availability of PRBs/RBGs. As a result, more coded bits are added to increase coding gain and making the DL HARQ retransmission attempts more robust. It improves the situation with VoNR packet loss by decreasing DL HARQ failure.

Parameter name: Activate VoNR fallback from measurement profiles
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates VoNR fallback from measurement profiles when NRBTS.actMeasurementProfile is equal to 'SA' or 'SA+NSA' and NRCELL.actVoNrMobilityThresholds is equal to 'VoNrMobilityThresholds'. Otherwise, this parameter is ignored by the system.

Parameter name: Activation of mobility thresholds for VoNr UEs
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates different mobility thresholds for VoNr UEs

This parameter activates/deactivates VoIP packet aggregation in the uplink and downlink.  Two VoIP packets will be aggregated and sent in the same transmission if the PDCCH usage in the cell is high. If there are unused PDCCH resources the VoIP packets will be sent one at a time.    When gNB is performing PUSCH slot aggregation, VoIP packets will not be aggregated in uplink.

This parameter indicates the policy used to minimize the effect of a blocking SR pool during load based adaptive UL scheduling request (SR).  Blocking of SR pools can happen when SR resources from a pool of a longer SR period are being blocked by the occupied resources from a pool of some shorter SR period and, at the same time, reallocation to a longer SR period is not fast enough to make room in a pool of a longer SR period for new incoming UEs.    There are three policies defined depending on the value of the parameter:  - 0: minimization of SR pool blocking is based only on the load thresholds  - 1: static minimization of SR pool blocking - during transition time (while UEs are being reallocated to different SR pool) SR period from the longest configured pool is being used for new UEs and for those that are undergoing reallocation procedure.  - 2...1000: dynamic minimization of SR pool blocking - moving average of absolute arrival rate of incoming UEs measured over sliding time window length defined by this parameter [in seconds]. During a transition time, the SR period for new UEs and for those that are undergoing a reallocation procedure is being allocated from the pool selected depending on the arrival rate.

This parameter indicates the lower threshold for load based adaptive UL scheduling request (SR).  It is used to determine the load when new incoming UEs should use the pool with a shorter SR period and when to trigger reallocation from the pool with a longer SR period to the pool with a shorter SR period.

This parameter indicates the upper threshold for load based adaptive UL scheduling request (SR).  It is used to determine the load when new incoming UEs should use the pool with a longer SR period and when to trigger reallocation from the pool with a shorter SR period to the pool with a longer SR period.

This parameter indicates the additional external delay compensation (Round Trip Time (RTT) in microseconds) that has to be compensated by the gNB.  The default value (0.0 microseconds) indicates that this delay compensation is deactivated.    Depending on the scenario, this parameter may refer to:  - 3rd party delay compensation - delay of the 3rd party system between the gNB (BBU + RU) and the UE - i.e. Distributed Antenna System (DAS)  - ring cell deployment - delay to the start of the cell (corresponds to the ring cell hole radius)  - 3rd party delay compensation with ring cell deployment - delay of the 3rd party system between the gNB (BBU + RU) and the UE plus the delay to the start of the cell. This kind of scenario is experimental one and not officially supported.    Refers to the value of the required shift of the PRACH reception window.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition might provoke gNB reset (the gNB takes the decision whether gNB reset is needed or not).  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion might provoke gNB reset (the gNB takes the decision whether gNB reset is needed or not).

Parameter name: Additional GBR traffic resources for handovers
Description: This parameter indicates the additional percentage of radio resources that can used for GBR traffic in uplink and downlink from total available radio resources available for both non-GBR and GBR.  It corresponds to the percentage of radio resources that are available for GBR transmissions from the PDSCH and PUSCH resources. PDCCH, PUCCH and PRACH resources are not controlled by this parameter.  It is used by the radio admission control in the gNB-DU.

Parameter name: Additional number of GBR DRB resources for handovers
Description: This parameter indicates the additional number of GBR 5QI resources.  It allows additional number of GBR DRBs to be configured for GBR 5QI and also reserves needed GBR resource buffer from radio resources.  It is used by the radio admission control in the gNB-CU and the gNB-DU.

This parameter indicates the power control adjustment offset.    More precisely, the value of powerControlOffset that is sent to the UE is computed based on the PDSCH and the CSI-RS power. This parameter increases or decreases this computed value in steps of 0.1 dB to optimize performance.
This parameter indicates the PRACH DTX threshold adjustment offset

This parameter defines the administrative state of the New Radio Cell.  It sets permission to use or prohibition against using the resource, imposed through the management services.    Notes:  - The value 'Shutting Down' is only taken into account in the DU functional entity.  - If, for a NR Cell, the operator sets NRCELL.administrativeState to 'Shutting Down' and NRBTS.actGrflShdn is equal to TRUE, the power level in that NR Cell will be gradually reduced (by steps) and NRCELL.administrativeState will then be tuned to 'Locked' by the gNB. Once triggered, the shutting down procedure cannot be stopped (it is not possible for the operator to set NRCELL.administrativeState to 'Unlocked', after this parameter was set to 'Shutting Down' and before this parameter is tuned to 'Locked' by the gNB).
This parameter selects the aggregation level in number of control channel elements (CCEs).  Specification is detailed in 3GPP 38.211 chapter 7.3.2.1

Parameter name: allow CSI-RS outside of DRX On-duration
Description: This parameter defines whether CS-RS for channel measurement or CSI-IM for interference measurement is allowed to drop outside of DRX on-duration. By default behavior is not allowed. It can be configured only for FR1 TDD cells.

Parameter name: Allow emergency radio resources for temporary use during preemption
Description: This parameter indicates, if radio resources reserved for emergency calls could be temporarily used by regular UEs during preemption.

Parameter name: Allow unsupported band combination or BCS
Description: This parameter indicates the list of bandwidth combination set (BCS) check options that are allowed.  The gNB performs a BCS check during FR1 CA secondary cell selection to ensure the bandwidth combination of the selected gNB serving cells is compatible with the UE capabilities. During NR-DC establishment, the gNB performs a BCS check on FR1 PCell to ensure the bandwidth of PCell is compatible with the UE capabilities.    The possible values are the following:  - 'complete BCS check' meaning the gNB performs a complete BCS check on the band combinations considered for secondary cell selection or for NR-DC establishment;  - 'accept unknown band combinations' meaning the following modification is made to the BCS check: if the gNB internal BCS table does not support a UE reported band combination then, during secondary cell selection or NR-DC establishment, the gNB may accept the bandwidth combination;  - 'accept unknown BCSs' meaning the following modification is made to the BCS check: if the gNB supports a UE reported band combination in its internal BCS table and the UE reports an unsupported BCS, then, during secondary cell selection or NR-DC establishment, the gNB may accept the band combination with the unknown BCS.
Range and step: complete BCS check (0), accept unknown band combinations (1), accept unknown BCSs (2)

Description: Antenna element electrical tilt angle.
This parameter indicates the mechanical downtilt applied to the antenna used for the computation of EIRP, including remote electrical tilt (RET).

Parameter name: Absolute radio frequency channel number of SSB PBCH
Description: This parameter indicates the Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number of SSB PBCH if the gNB DU is able to compute it; otherwise this parameter is equal to -1.

This parameter indicates the allocation and retention priority used to prioritize an emergency call over a normal call.  The range of the ARP priority level is 1 to 15 with 1 as the highest level of priority. For emergency sessions, only ARP priority levels 1-8 may be applied (3GPP TS23.501).
This parameter defines the availability status of the NR Cell.  It shows if any specific conditions are present for the resource.
Range and step: in test (0), failed (1), power off (2), off line (3), off duty (4), dependency (5), degraded (6), not installed (7), log full (8)

Parameter name: Average data rate re-initialization prohibit period
Description: This parameter allows flexibility in configuration for the UE PF metric re-initialization prohibit periodicity depending on the traffic pattern.  If this parameter is not configured, then it will take the default value (10 msec).

Parameter name: List of parameters for B1 measurement redirection
Description: This parameter contains the list of parameters needed for the B1 measurement redirection
This parameter indicates the priority of the B1 measurement ID.  The higher value of the parameter means the lower priority.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the NRHOIR instance to be used for redirection.  This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRHOIR-1  NRHOIR-1

This parameter indicates the period for which either the current carrier frequency or NR is deprioritized as per 3GPP parameter deprioritisationTimer in TS38.331.  Value '0min' means that deprioritisationTimer will not present in the RRCRelease message.

Parameter name: Barring status due to unavailability of NG links or slices
Description: This parameter indicates the barring status of a NR SA cell.    When a NR SA cell is barred (due to unavailability of any NG links or slice support or other reasons), this parameter is set to the corresponding value and this is notified to the operator.  Note: NRCELL.cellBarred is not concerned by this parameter.

This parameter indicates the threshold of the beam power offset.  If the 2 SRS based DFT beam power offset is more than the value of this parameter, then power balancing will be performed with the value of this parameter.
This parameter indicates the horizontal beam sequence direction for O-RAN compliant RUs
This parameter indicates the vertical beam sequence direction for O-RAN compliant RUs
This parameter collects beamforming related settings for a single cell.

This parameter defines the basic set of beams consisting of SS/PBCH beams and refined beams on gNB side.    For digital beamforming with FR1, beam property follows nomenclature beamSet_?#k_#l_#m? where,  - the number of columns in a row is given by the respective integer, preceded by the character '#'  - rows are counted from top to bottom, i.e. the first row is the one with the highest pointing beams, the last row is the one with the lowest pointing beams    For analog beamforming with FR2, the beam property follows nomenclature beamSetFR2_?#1_#2_#3?_?Number of Panels?P" where  - ?#1_#2_#3? indicates the SSB beams per row based on the number of rows of the beamSet  - ?Number of Panels? refers to the number of RRU panel(s) for the beamSet with 1, 2, 3 or 4 panel support. 2 panels will support 180-degree of azimuth opening angle, 3 and 4 panels will support 360-degree of azimuth opening angle.
Range and step: beamSet_1 (1), beamSet_2 (2), beamSet_4 (3), beamSet_8 (4), beamSet_4_4 (5), beamSet_5_3 (6), beamSet_6_2 (7), beamSet_2_2_2_2 (9), beamSet_3_3_2_square (10), beamSet_3_3_2_azimuth (11), beamSet_6 (16), beamSet_2_2 (22), beamSet_2SS (24), beamSet_4SS (25), beamSet_3_1 (31), beamSet_3_3 (33), beamSet_4_2 (42), beamSet_5_1 (51), beamSetAbf_1A (100), beamSetAbf_32A (101), beamSetAbf_32B (102), beamSetAbf_32C (103), beamSetFR2_16_8_8_1P (104), beamSetFR2_8_8_8_8_1P (105), beamSetFR2_6_6_6_6_6_2_1P (106), beamSetFR2_6_6_4_2P (201), beamSetFR2_6_2_4P (301), beamSetFR2_4_4_2_3P (401)

Description: This parameter indicates the beam set that is applied and in use.
This parameter indicates the beams which are muted in the beamSet.
Range and step: bits mask: Beam ID 0 (0), Beam ID 1 (1), Beam ID 2 (2), Beam ID 3 (3), Beam ID 4 (4), Beam ID 5 (5), Beam ID 6 (6), Beam ID 7 (7), Beam ID 8 (8), Beam ID 9 (9), Beam ID 10 (10), Beam ID 11 (11), Beam ID 12 (12), Beam ID 13 (13), Beam ID 14 (14), Beam ID 15 (15), Beam ID 16 (16), Beam ID 17 (17), Beam ID 18 (18), Beam ID 19 (19), Beam ID 20 (20), Beam ID 21 (21), Beam ID 22 (22), Beam ID 23 (23), Beam ID 24 (24), Beam ID 25 (25), Beam ID 26 (26), Beam ID 27 (27), Beam ID 28 (28), Beam ID 29 (29), Beam ID 30 (30), Beam ID 31 (31), Beam ID 32 (32), Beam ID 33 (33), Beam ID 34 (34), Beam ID 35 (35), Beam ID 36 (36), Beam ID 37 (37), Beam ID 38 (38), Beam ID 39 (39), Beam ID 40 (40), Beam ID 41 (41), Beam ID 42 (42), Beam ID 43 (43), Beam ID 44 (44), Beam ID 45 (45), Beam ID 46 (46), Beam ID 47 (47), Beam ID 48 (48), Beam ID 49 (49), Beam ID 50 (50), Beam ID 51 (51), Beam ID 52 (52), Beam ID 53 (53), Beam ID 54 (54), Beam ID 55 (55)

Description: This parameter indicates the customized beam set realization package name without file extension.  When this parameter contains a valid package name, the corresponding package is downloaded to the gNB or the gNB will try to download this package from its northbound interface.

This parameter indicates the external antenna type that impacts the beam set at gNB side. Please refer to Customer Documentation regarding valid/allowed antenna names of specific supported model.    This parameter is ignored if NRCELL.actExternalAntennaBF is equal to FALSE.

This parameter defines the angle limiting cell on left side with respect to bore sight.    For mmWave radio, the service area of azimuth can be up to 90, 120, 180 or 360 degrees based on the hardware installed with one, two, three or four panels in use respectively.
This parameter defines the angle limiting cell on lower side with respect to bore sight.  The parameter is applicable for analog beamforming and SRS based digital beamforming.

This parameter indicates whether beam refinement on gNB side (P2) is enabled or disabled.  Beam refinement on gNB side (P2) requires transmission of CSI-RS and respective reporting. It is applicable only for digital beamforming below 6GHz and if beamforming is enabled.  If the frequency setting is not applicable, this parameter can be undefined or shall be equal to FALSE.

This parameter defines the angle limiting cell on right side with respect to bore sight.    For mmWave radio, the service area of azimuth can be up to 90, 120, 180 or 360 degrees based on the hardware installed with one, two, three or four panels in use respectively.

This parameter indicates the tilt offset that can be applied to 32/64TRX cmWave (FR1) or RF7.1 mmWave (FR2) Radios with beamforming capability connected to the system.    In panel split mode (h-cut) with horizontal cut, a 32 TRX Radio becomes 2 times 16 TRX and a 64 TRX Radio 2 times 32 TRX. In case of the 32 TRX Radio in split mode (h-cut), the tilt offset will only be supported in case the Radio has an inbuilt VET (vertical electrical tilt).  For Radios which do not support the tilt offset, a value different from the Default Value for this parameter will be rejected by the Radio and an alarm with fault ID 1900 will be raised.    The range of the tilt offset is HW specific and within the range defined for this parameter. For values outside the steering range of the particular Radio, an alarm will be raised indicating an out of range error (warning).    Note: Before configuring this parameter, please check if tilt configuration is supported by the radio unit.
This parameter defines the angle limiting cell on upper side with respect to bore sight.  It is applicable for analog beamforming and SRS based digital beamforming.

Parameter name: Timer for strategy based on cell quality without mobility profile
Description: This parameter indicates the time during which the handover preparation will be delayed for strategy based on cell quality.

Parameter name: BI slot PDSCH average CQI ratio
Description: This parameter indicates the percentage used to reduce the corrected average WB-CQI (rrmCorrAvgCqi) in BI slot during MCS calculation for the BI slot.  More precisely, the corrected average WB-CQI is reduced by 100 - NRCELL.biSlotPdschAvgCqiRatio%.    The value of this parameter is ignored if NRBTS.actEnhancedPDSCHSchSplSlot is equal to FALSE.

Parameter name: Timer for blocking a cell for handover
Description: This parameter indicates the time for which a cell has to be marked as unavailable for Handover after a Handover to the cell failed.

Parameter name: Block handover to SCell based on A3/A5 measurement report
Description: This parameter blocks or allows handover to SCell based on A3/A5 measurement report
This parameter indicates the blocking state of the New Radio Cell
The parameter defines the MCS value to select a region amongst 2 possible regions in 2-region algorithm.

Parameter name: Buffer threshold for secondary cell deprioritization
Description: This parameter indicates the buffer threshold at DU such that, when the buffer level goes below this threshold, it is checked if the data split could be done over less number of secondary cells.

Parameter name: Load level for carrier aggregation setup blocking
Description: This parameter indicates the cell load level in % starting from which the setup of SCells in carrier aggregation will be blocked from P(S)Cell perspective.    Setting the value to X% means that carrier aggregation setup blocking will start when less than (100-X)% of PUCCH cell capacity is left for UE context establishment. Note that emergency reserved pool is not part of the above defined cell capacity. Setting the value to 100% shall disable the carrier aggregation setup blocking.    The parameter is not applicable to cells operating at frequency range 2 (FR2).
This parameter defines the number of CBRA preambles per SSB per RACH transmission occasion
This parameter indicates the component carrier (CC) load threshold to start the load balancing in the CU.

The parameter defines whether the cell is barred. A barred cell is a cell on which a UE is not allowed to camp. When the cell status is 'barred', the UE is not permitted to select/reselect the cell, not even for emergency calls.  Supplemental DL cells are always barred.
This parameter indicates whether the cell is barred for reduced capability UEs.
This parameter indicates the list of bandwidth parts in the cell.

This parameter activates/deactivates the CCE fragment management during PDCCH congestion. If activated, the free fragment CCE resources will not be considered as free resources on load measurement when PDCCH starvation is detected.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters. If NRCELL.actDynPdcchTdMode is set to 'disabled', the value of this parameter will be ignored by gNB.

This parameter activates/deactivates the upper ACK/NACK filtering threshold for basic reliability DRB. It controls the capability to filter the HARQ feedbacks until the highest threshold for the Aggregation Level (AL) selected for a UE on the PDCCH, and which corresponds to the less robust AL allowed in PDCCH.dynamicAggregationLevelSet.aggregationLevelList when PDCCH.alSelection is equal to 'dynamic'.

Parameter name: Activate upper ACK/NACK filtering threshold for high reliability DRB
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the upper ACK/NACK filtering threshold for high reliability DRB. It controls the capability to filter the HARQ feedbacks until the highest threshold for the Aggregation Level (AL) selected for a UE on the PDCCH, and which corresponds to the less robust AL allowed in PDCCH.dynamicAggregationLevelHRSet.aggregationLevelListHR when PDCCH.alSelection is equal to 'dynamic'.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the BWP_PROFILE instances configured within the NRCELL instance. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/BWP_PROFILE-1  BWP_PROFILE-1    Updating this parameter without changing any of the referenced instances will be performed on-line.
This parameter indicates the identifier of the BWP_PROFILE instance within the NRCELL instance.

Parameter name: PDCCH blocking resource threshold in DL
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for the lack of PDCCH resource to increase the PDCCH resources in time domain DL.  Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters

Parameter name: PDCCH blocking resource threshold in UL
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for the lack of PDCCH resource to increase the PDCCH resources in time domain UL.  Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.
This parameter indicates the threshold for free resource to decrease the PDCCH resources in time domain DL  Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.
This parameter indicates the threshold for free resource to decrease the PDCCH resources in time domain UL  Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.

This parameter indicates if decreasing PDCCH symbol (for higher peak rate) or increasing PDCCH symbol (for higher capacity) shall be evaluated firstly for dynamic PDCCH management in time domain.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters. If NRCELL.actDynPdcchTdMode is set to 'disabled', the value of this parameter will be ignored by gNB.
This structure defines the list of configuration for cell specific csi-IM-Resource location

Parameter name: Resource id for Cell CSI-IM location
Description: This parameter identifies the csi-IM-Resource within the CSI-IM-ResourceSet.  This is not the csi-IM-ResourceId in TS38.331 but just an identifier to distinguish resources within the set for the configuration.

Parameter name: Set id for cell CSI-IM location list
Description: This parameter identifies the CSI-IM-ResourceSet for the cell.  Its value indicates the number of CSI-IM resources within the set. This is not the csi-IM-ResourceSetId in TS38.331 but just an identifier to distinguish sets of the cell for the configuration.

This parameter indicates the subcarrier location of the csi-IM-Resource.  Only subcarrierLocation-p1 in TS38.331 is supported. symbolLocation-p1 is the same as relevant NZP-CSI-RS. This parameter is a 12 bits mask with Bit 0 (LSB) corresponding to the first subcarrier within one RB, each bit refers to one subcarrier, if Bit x is equal to 1, subcarrier x is used.
Range and step: bits mask: subcarrier 0 (0), subcarrier 1 (1), subcarrier 2 (2), subcarrier 3 (3), subcarrier 4 (4), subcarrier 5 (5), subcarrier 6 (6), subcarrier 7 (7), subcarrier 8 (8), subcarrier 9 (9), subcarrier 10 (10), subcarrier 11 (11)

Description: This parameter indicates the configuration mode for cell specific NZP-CSI-RS-Resource and csi-IM-Resource for channel acquisition.  The configuration of NRCELL.cellCsiImLocationList and NRCELL.cellCsiRsLocationList will take effect if this parameter is equal to 'manual'.    It is recommended to use the 'automatic' mode, otherwise the NZP-CSI-RS-Resource and the csi-IM-Resource must be carefully configured to avoid the collision with SSB/TRS/SIB1/PDCCH and PDSCH in SSB/TRS slots. Please refer to Customer Documentation to configure them properly.
This parameter defines the list of configuration for cell specific NZP-CSI-RS-Resources location

Parameter name: First OFDM symbol in time domain
Description: This parameter indicates the first OFDM symbol in time domain for the NZP-CSI-RS-Resource.    Note: This parameter shall not be equal to 13 when NRCELL.dlMimoMode is equal to '8x4 Closed Loop Spatial Multiplexing'

This parameter indicates the frequency domain allocation for the NZP-CSI-RS-Resource, which is different from the original field frequencyDomainAllocation TS38.331 for simplicity.  This parameter is a 12 bits mask with Bit 0 (LSB) corresponding to the first subcarrier within one RB, each bit refers to one subcarrier, if Bit x is equal to 1, subcarrier x is used.
Range and step: bits mask: subcarrier 0 (0), subcarrier 1 (1), subcarrier 2 (2), subcarrier 3 (3), subcarrier 4 (4), subcarrier 5 (5), subcarrier 6 (6), subcarrier 7 (7), subcarrier 8 (8), subcarrier 9 (9), subcarrier 10 (10), subcarrier 11 (11)

Description: This parameter indicates the offset of periodicityAndOffset which is defined in 3GPP TS38.331 for each NZP-CSI-RS-Resource.  The periodicity is configured from NRCELL.periodicCsiAcquisition.csiReportPeriodicity and NRCELL.periodicCsiAcquisition.csirsNumberWithinReportPeriod_Set1.

Parameter name: Resource id for Cell CSI-RS location
Description: This parameter identifies the NZP-CSI-RS-Resource within the NZP-CSI-RS-ResourceSet.  This is not nzp-CSI-RS-ResourceId in TS38.331 but just an identifier to distinguish resources within the set for the configuration.

Parameter name: Set id for cell CSI-RS location list
Description: This parameter identifies the NZP-CSI-RS-ResourceSet for the cell.  Its value indicates the number of NZP-CSI-RS resources within the set. This is not the nzp-CSI-ResourceSetId in TS38.331 but just an identifier to distinguish sets of the cell for the configuration.

This parameter indicates if a given cell supports access  - to NSA PSCell users only or  - to SA PCell users only or  - to NR-DC-SN PSCell users only (New Radio Dual Connectivity Secondary Node users of the NR-DC connection, where the PCell is in a SA cell and the PSCell is in an NR-DC-SN cell) or  - to SA and NSA P(S)Cell users or  - to NR-DC-SN and NSA PSCell users  Please note, that SCell allocation is NRCELL.cellDepType agnostic, so e.g. SCell for NSA PSCell user can be established in a NR-DC-SN cell.

Parameter name: Cell disabled due to NMS connection loss
Description: This parameter indicates cell disabling due to connection toward NMS lost.
This parameter defines the cell individual SSB RSRP offset applicable to a specific cell
This parameter defines the cell individual SSB RSRQ offset applicable to a specific cell

This parameter allows the operator to give a cell a unique name.    The range represents the number of bytes to store all the characters of the string. If the string is UTF-8 encoded, each character occupies between 1 to 4 bytes, depending upon the language. If ASCII encoded, each character occupies a single byte. The numbers of characters supported in case of UTF-8 encoding is at least 20.
This parameter indicates the absolute priority for the concerned NR frequency.  Value 0 means the lowest priority.

This parameter indicates the fractional priority value to be added to the NRCELL cellReselectionPriority value to obtain the absolute priority of the concerned carrier frequency for NR.  oDot2 corresponds to 0.2, oDot4 corresponds to 0.4 and so on.
This parameter indicates whether or not the cell is reserved for operator use (per PLMN).
This parameter indicates whether or not the cell is reserved. The field is applicable to all PLMNs

This parameter indicates if the NRCELL instance shall be used as a FDD or TDD cell. Dependent on the configuration of the technology, instances of the associated child MOC under NRCELL, if any, have to be configured.

Channel bandwidth defines the bandwidth for the gNB transmission in a cell. It is used (together with NRCELLGRP.scs) to compute the maximum number of Physical Resource Blocks according to 3GPP specification in 38.104.    This parameter affects real center frequency and channel bandwidth which is not validated against radio module capabilities and misconfiguration can cause cell setup failures with fault '1900: RF Module configuring failed' raised.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition might provoke gNB reset - gNB takes decision of reset necessity.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates the configured EPS tracking area code (TAC) for a given New Radio cell. It enables to apply Roaming and Access Restrictions for EN-DC.
This parameter indicates the congestion detection period for NBR.  If it is equal to 'off', the congestion detection is disabled.

This parameter indicates the algorithm to prioritize bearers for MAC scheduling until the NBR congestion situation is resolved. Two different algorithms are possible:  - 'priorityLevel': Bearers are prioritized in order of their NRDRB.priorityLevel.  - 'arpPrioPerVul': First the bearers with ARP vulnerability 'preemptable' are prioritized in order of the ARP priority, then the bearers with ARP vulnerability 'not preemptable' also in order of ARP priority.

Parameter name: Number of times that the UE detects T300 expiry
Description: This parameter indicates the number of times the UE detects T300 expiry on the same cell before applying connEstFailOffset .
This parameter indicates the temporary offset to be taken into account in the 'SrxLev' evaluation by the UE.

Parameter name: Amount of time that the UE applies connEstFailOffset
Description: This parameter indicates the amount of time the UE applies connEstFailOffset before removing the offset from evaluation of the cell.
This parameter indicates the threshold for the number of times that UL radio link outage criteria needs to be met consecutively in order to trigger UL RL outage
This parameter indicates the threshold for the number of times that UL radio link outage criteria needs to be met consecutively in order to trigger UL RL Resume
This parameter collects settings for CSI-RS configuration for Beam Management. It comprises currently CSI-RS for L1 RSRP measurement, other aspects could be added later on.
This parameter defines the density of CSI-RS allocation for L1 RSRP Measurement
This parameter defines the first RE to be allocated for CSI-RS for L1-RSRP. Different RE allocation can mitigate inter-cell interference of these signals.
This parameter defines whether the subband below or above the SS/PBCH block allocation shall be used for transmission of CSI-RS for L1 RSRP measurement.
This parameter collects settings for CSI-RS for tracking.
This parameter defines the period with which CSI-RS for tracking are transmitted.
This parameter defines the RE allocation within a RB for CSI-RS for tracking.
This parameter defines the RB range allocated for CSI-RS for tracking.
This parameter defines the RB number on which allocation for CSI-RS for tracking starts.

This structure gathers the settings for the CSI-RS resource subpanel split.    The gNB SW default operation for 1/2/4 CSI-RS applies if:  - either this structure is not configured  - or the three parameters within it (namely NRCELL.csirsResourceSet.csirsResourceSetConfig1CRI, NRCELL.csirsResourceSet.csirsResourceSetConfig2CRI and NRCELL.csirsResourceSet.csirsResourceSetConfig4CRI) are equal to 0 (corresponding to gNB SW default operation).

This parameter indicates the CSI-RS resource subpanel split, location vertically and horizontally for one CSI-RS resource.    The possible values are:  - 0 meaning the gNB SW default operation applies (for 1 CSI-RS)  - 4x1-1e meaning full 120 degree coverage for PMI beams is provided  - 4x1-1n meaning around 90 degree coverage for PMI beams is provided  - 4x1-1 meaning around 60 degree coverage for PMI beams with maximum gain beams is provided  - 4x1-1w meaning around 90 degree coverage for PMI beams with maximum gain beams is provided  - 4x1-1wT is similar to 4x1-1w but wider because beams are tapered.

This parameter indicates the CSI-RS resource subpanel split, location vertically and horizontally of the two CSI-RS resources relatively to the SSB top row.    The possible values are:  - 0 meaning the gNB SW default operation applies (for 2 CSI-RS)  - values using the notation ixj-a-b_d_e in which:  * ixj is equal to 2x2 or 4x1  * a-b defines how many CSI-RS resources are having the same vertical tilt in the same row. Horizontally, the CSI-RS resources are evenly distributed to cover sector width. See NRCELL.csirsResourceSet.csirsResourceSetConfig1CRI for more information about single CSI-RS resource  * d_e defines the relative vertical tilts for the rows. d is up tilt versus the SSB, e is down tilt versus the SSB.

This parameter indicates the CSI-RS resource subpanel split, location vertically and horizontally of the four CSI-RS resources relatively to the SSB top row.    The possible values are:  - 0 meaning the gNB SW default operation applies (for 4 CSI-RS)  - values using the notation ixj-a-b-c_d_e_f in which:  * ixj is equal to 2x2 or 4x1  * a-b-c defines how many CSI-RS resources are having same vertical tilt in same row. Horizontally, the CSI-RS resources are evenly distributed to cover sector width. See NRCELL.csirsResourceSet.csirsResourceSetConfig1CRI for more information about single CSI-RS resource  * d_e_f defines the relative vertical tilts for the rows. d is up tilt versus the SSB, e&f are down tilt versus the SSB. Orth means bottom row beams are vertically orthogonal to top row beams
This parameter indicates whether or not the gNB should include the SIB1 in RRC Reconfiguration while sending the Handover Command

Parameter name: Delivery delay threshold with data split
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for the delivery delay for data buffered at DU when the data is split over multiple cells
This parameter indicates whether the parameter deriveSSB-IndexFromCell in intra-frequency A3/A5 measurement configuration should be equal to TRUE or FALSE

Parameter name: Power threshold between two horizontal DFT beams
Description: This parameter indicates the power threshold between two horizontal DFT beams which are candidate for beam selection.

Parameter name: Power threshold between two vertical DFT beams
Description: This parameter indicates the power threshold between two vertical DFT beams which are candidate for beam selection.

Parameter name: DFT beams muted in vertical side
Description: This parameter indicates which DFT beams in vertical side are used or muted. One bit corresponds to one DFT beam in vertical.  If the value for the corresponding bit is 1, it means the beam is in use. Otherwise, it means the corresponding beam is muted. If all the bits are set to 0 or this parameter is not configured, it means the beam set in vertical side is controlled by NRCELL.beamSet.upperEdgeAngle and NRCELL.beamSet.LowerEdgeAngle.    This parameter settings shall be applicable to both uplink and downlink SRS based beamforming since both uplink and downlink use the same DFT beam set.    Please refer to the documentation which provides details on beam muting on vertical direction.
Range and step: bits mask: Beam 0 (0), Beam 1 (1), Beam 2 (2), Beam 3 (3), Beam 4 (4), Beam 5 (5), Beam 6 (6), Beam 7 (7), Beam 8 (8), Beam 9 (9), Beam 10 (10), Beam 11 (11), Beam 12 (12), Beam 13 (13), Beam 14 (14), Beam 15 (15)

Parameter name: Disabling cell when NMS connection lost
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates cell disabling when M-Plane connection toward NMS is lost.
This parameter disables early RAR transmission if equal to TRUE.

This parameter activates/deactivates to have a reduced amount of reRachs due to beam failure recovery.  When this parameter is equal to TRUE means gNB is not instructing the UE to ReRach after a defined count of Beam Failures Detected within a time window

This parameter indicates the minimum time a UE must meet the CQI threshold defined by NRCELL.dlCaMinPCellCqi or NRCELL.dlCaMinPCellCqi5qi1 on PCell before it can be considered a candidate for adding a SCell.
This parameter indicates the minimum PCell CQI for a UE with no established 5QI1 bearer to be considered a candidate for adding a SCell.

Parameter name: Downlink CA minimum PCell CQI for 5QI1
Description: This parameter indicates the minimum PCell CQI for a UE with an established 5QI1 bearer to be considered a candidate for adding a SCell.
This structure contains parameter related to DL CQI Restriction.

Parameter name: Additional CQI Increment For Rank Reduction
Description: This Parameter defines additional allowed increment in CQI, when UE reports lesser rank indication (RI) in CQI with respect to previously reported RI.
This Parameter defines the allowed increment when UE reports high CQI with respect to previously reported CQI in order to stabilize the DL BLER.

This parameter indicates the DMRS additional position for PDSCH.    The supported values are:  - 0 (No additional DMRS) meaning the PDSCH DMRS additional position equals to 0 whether the UE has the DL PTRS capability or not,  - 1 (One additional DMRS) meaning the PDSCH DMRS additional position equals to 1 whether the UE has the DL PTRS capability or not,  - 2 (Two additional DMRS) meaning the PDSCH DMRS additional position equals to 2 whether the UE has the DL PTRS capability or not,  - 255 (Automatic) meaning the PDSCH DMRS additional position is controlled by the gNB based on the UE capability: the PDSCH DMRS additional position is equal to 0 if the UE has the DL PTRS capability, otherwise it is equal to 1.    Notes:  - 255 (Automatic) is not allowed for FR1 TDD and FDD.  - Setting the PDSCH DMRS additional position to 0 (No additional DMRS) might highly decrease the performance for high frequency offset scenario for UE without PTRS capability. Higher frequency offset is expected with higher UE mobility velocity.
Range and step: No additional DMRS (0), One additional DMRS (1), Two additional DMRS (2), Automatic (255)

Description: This parameter gathers parameters for downlink data and DMRS FDM (frequency domain multiplexing).

Parameter name: Activate downlink data and DMRS FDM
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates downlink data and DMRS FDM. It does not apply to RedCap 1X UEs.

Parameter name: Downlink data and DMRS FDM threshold 256QAM MCS
Description: This parameter indicates the MCS threshold for 256QAM MCS table to enable downlink data and DMRS FDM in runtime packet scheduling.  Downlink data and DMRS FDM could be enabled if the MCS used in PDSCH is higher or equal to this parameter. It does not apply to RedCap 1X UEs.  Note: The threshold is only a precondition to use data and DMRS FDM. It just makes sure no data and DMRS FDM for MCS lower than this parameter. It does not mean data and DMRS FDM must be used when MCS is higher or equal to the threshold.  The gNB has the flexibility to decide whether data and DMRS FDM need to be used when MCS is higher or equal to the threshold.

Parameter name: Downlink data and DMRS FDM MCS threshold for 64QAM low SE MCS table
Description: This parameter indicates the MCS threshold for 64QAM low SE MCS table to enable downlink data and DMRS FDM in runtime packet scheduling.

Parameter name: Downlink data and DMRS FDM threshold 64QAM MCS
Description: This parameter indicates the MCS threshold for 64QAM MCS table to enable downlink data and DMRS FDM in runtime packet scheduling.  Downlink data and DMRS FDM could be enabled if the MCS used in PDSCH is higher or equal to this parameter.  Note: The threshold is only a precondition to use data and DMRS FDM. It just makes sure no data and DMRS FDM for MCS lower than this parameter. It does not mean data and DMRS FDM must be used when MCS is higher or equal to the threshold. The gNB has the flexibility to decide whether data and DMRS FDM need to be used when MCS is higher or equal to the threshold.

Parameter name: Enable downlink data and DMRS FDM for RedCap 1RX UEs
Description: This parameter enables/disables downlink data and DMRS FDM for RedCap 1RX UEs.

This parameter indicates the MCS threshold for 256QAM MCS table to enable downlink data and DMRS FDM in runtime packet scheduling for RedCap 1RX UEs.  Downlink data and DMRS FDM could be enabled if the MCS used in PDSCH is higher or equal to this parameter.  Note: The threshold is only a precondition to use data and DMRS FDM. It just makes sure no data and DMRS FDM for MCS lower than this parameter. It does not mean data and DMRS FDM must be used when MCS is higher or equal to the threshold.  The gNB has the flexibility to decide whether data and DMRS FDM need to be used when MCS is higher or equal to the threshold.

This parameter indicates the DL DMRS type for PDSCH.  The supported values are:  - 'Type1': PDSCH shall use DMRS configuration type 1 for all the UEs in the NR cell.  - 'Type2': PDSCH shall use DMRS configuration type 2 or type 1, depending on the UE capability and call type.

This parameter indicates the downlink gain per TX array carrier element.  The DL gain of a TX array carrier element is defined by mapping 0dBFs carried over any subcarrier (of the carrier) on the digital interface to the maximum RMS power the TX array carrier element is supposed to output at the assumed-lossless antenna connector port. In single-carrier operation, the configured DL gain applies to the carrier. In multiple-carrier operation, the configured DL gain should be lower accommodating the number of multiple carriers and their bandwidths.  Configured DL gain [in dB] <= maximum TX power per array element [in dBm], valid for each individual spatial stream served under this TX array carrier element.    Note 1: The configured DL gain of a TX array carrier is equivalent to mapping 0dBFs carried over any subcarrier (of the carrier) on the digital interface to the maximum RMS power the TX array carrier element is supposed to output + 10 log10 (the number of array elements).  Note 2: For a category A O-RAN compliant RU, the TX array output RMS power is measured over 1 polarization  Note 3: For a category B O-RAN compliant RU, the TX array output RMS power shall be measured over all polarizations addressed by the respective precoding operations.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition might provoke gNB reset  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

- If NRCELL.actRat1Alloc = False, This parameter indicates the percentage of RBGs that will be reserved for high performance UEs when Downlink Interference Avoidance is enabled and Downlink RBG Randomization is in the enhanced mode.  - If NRCELL.actRat1Alloc = True, this parameter indicates the corresponding number of PRBs to be reserved for high performing UEs when Downlink Interference Avoidance is enabled, no matter what Downlink RBG Randomization setting is.    Note: NRCELL.dlHpReservedRbgs with a value greater than 0% is needed for proper interworking between randomization of DL frequency resources (RBGs or PRBs) and Downlink Interference Avoidance. Parameter NRCELL.dlHpReservedRbgs should not be configured with a value greater than 0% when Downlink Interference Avoidance is not enabled, as it would needlessly degrade the benefit of DL frequency resource randomization.
This structure contains parameter related to downlink inter-cell interference avoidance functionality.

This parameter indicates minimal amount of data in buffer for high performing UEs. UE data buffer must be higher than this value in order to fulfill data buffer threshold for classifying a UE as high performing.

This parameter indicates maximal MCS index for high performing UEs. UE MCS index must be less than or equal to this value, but greater than or equal to NRCELL.dlInterferenceAvoidance.startMcs in order to fulfill MCS limitation for classifying a UE as high performing.

This parameter indicates allocation order for UEs classified as high performing. For RAT1 high-performance, UE is always allocated from high2low. UEs are always allocated in highPerforming_High2low order in DL slots, which do not contain paired UEs.
This parameter indicates minimal rank for high performing UEs. UE rank must be higher or equal to this value in order to fulfill rank limitation for classifying a UE as high performing.
This parameter indicates number of RBGs not available for scheduling for high performing UEs.

This parameter indicates minimal MCS index for high performing UEs. UE MCS index must be higher greater than or equal to this value, but lower less than or equal to NRCELL.dlInterferenceAvoidance.endMcs in order to fulfill MCS limitation for classifying a UE as high performing.

Parameter name: Enable DL buffer based MCS downgrade or enhanced DL LA for buffer based MCS downgrade for high reliability
Description: This parameter enables/disables DL buffer based MCS downgrade or enhanced DL link adaptation for buffer based MCS downgrade for high reliability.    The possible values are:  - 'disabled' meaning the DL buffer based MCS downgrade for high reliability is disabled.  - 'enabled' meaning the DL buffer based MCS downgrade for high reliability is enabled.  - 'enhanced' meaning the DL buffer based MCS downgrade and the enhanced DL link adaptation for buffer based MCS downgrade for high reliability are enabled.

Parameter name: Activate limit for DL MCS downgrade for VoNR DRBs
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the limit for the MCS downgrade for VoNR DRBs. Value 0 means the MCS downgrade is disabled, value 28 means unlimited MCS downgrade is allowed.  It is used for improved control of delta CQI/BLER for VoNR DRBs. Rationale is that, for VoNR DRBs, the TBS is usually smaller and when MCS downgrade is applied for these smaller TBSs with this function deactivated (corresponding to NRCELL.dlMcsDropLimitForVoNR equal to 28), this results in OLLA skipping the step-up adjustments for delta CQI leading to downward drift of delta CQI and lower MCS selection and downgraded PDSCH transmission and higher RB utilization over time. This causes significant MCS/TBS fluctuations as OLLA is unable to adjust to the actual channel conditions.
NRCELL.dlMimoMode is set to '2x2 Closed Loop Spatial Multiplexing' by default because it is mandatory for PDSCH early implementation stages.
Range and step: 1x1 Single Antenna Transmission (12), 2x2 Closed Loop Spatial Multiplexing (30), 4x4 or 4x2 Closed Loop Spatial Multiplexing (40), 2x2 Open Loop Spatial Multiplexing (50), 4x4 or 4x2 Open Loop Spatial Multiplexing (60), 8x4 Closed Loop Spatial Multiplexing (70)

Parameter name: DL MU-MIMO pairing low SINR threshold
Description: The downlink pairing algorithm for the feature DL MU-MIMO shall only pair UEs which have a SINR value derived from the reported CQI that is bigger than this threshold.

Parameter name: DL MU-MIMO maximum number of paired UEs
Description: The downlink pairing algorithm for the feature DL MU-MIMO shall only pair a maximum number of UEs that is given by this parameter.

Parameter name: DL MU-MIMO pairing threshold for neighbor UEs
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold used to decide whether UEs are neighbors for DL MU-MIMO pairing

Parameter name: DL MU-MIMO pairing intra-cell interference threshold
Description: The downlink pairing algorithm for the feature DL MU-MIMO shall only pair UEs which shall ensure estimated interferences of all paired UEs are lower than this threshold.
This parameter gathers parameters for downlink PTRS.

This parameter activates/deactivates downlink PTRS.  When this parameter is equal to FALSE, downlink PTRS is not configured to the UE.  When this parameter is equal to TRUE, downlink PTRS is configured to the UE which has downlink PTRS capability.

Parameter name: Downlink PTRS frequency density threshold NRB0
Description: This parameter indicates the downlink PTRS frequency density threshold NRB0 (see 3GPP TS 38.214 chap 5.1.6.3 and 3GPP TS 38.331) in order to set the value for the frequency density Kpt-rs.  - Values in the range 1...276 correspond to the configured number of PRBs for NRB0.  - 277 means frequency density Kpt-rs is not configured in PTRS-DownlinkConfig.  - 278 means the gNB selected downlink PTRS frequency density values (both NRB0 and NBR1) are used for downlink PTRS frequency density configuration.  - 279 means the UE recommended downlink PTRS frequency density values (both NRB0 and NRB1) included in the UE capability report are used for downlink PTRS frequency density configuration. If the UE does not report recommended downlink PTRS frequency density values, then the gNB selected downlink PTRS frequency density values are used instead, i.e. same behavior as if this parameter is equal to 278.

Parameter name: Downlink PTRS frequency density threshold NRB1
Description: This parameter indicates the downlink PTRS frequency density threshold NRB1 (see 3GPP TS 38.214 chapter 5.1.6.3 and 3GPP TS 38.331) in order to set the value for the frequency density Kpt-rs.  Values in the range 1...276 correspond to the configured number of PRBs for NRB1.
This parameter defines the power backoff applied for UEs supporting the 256QAM scheme in DL bands above 6GHz
This parameter defines the power backoff applied for UEs supporting the 256QAM scheme in DL bands of below 6GHz
This structure gathers parameters for downlink retransmission power boost control.

Parameter name: Maximum number of PRBs during power boost
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of PRBs that can be allocated to the UE with retransmission during power boost of PDSCH transmission with VoNR data (with 5QI1 bearer(s)) or SRB1/2 data, if NRCELL.actDlPowerBoost is not equal to 'disabled'.This limit is applied per UE in any slot.        If NRCELL.cellTechnology is equal to 'TDD' and NRCELL.chBw is equal to '10MHz', it is recommended to set this parameter to 18.  If NRCELL.cellTechnology is equal to 'TDD' and NRCELL.chBw is equal to '15MHz', it is recommended to set this parameter to 18.  If NRCELL.cellTechnology is equal to 'FDD' and NRCELL_FDD.chBwDl is equal to '5MHz', it is recommended to set this parameter to 18

Parameter name: Number of transmission attempts for power boost
Description: This parameter indicates the DL HARQ transmission attempts (where transmission attempts include the initial transmission which is not successful and following retransmission attempts) threshold for power boost, if NRCELL.actDlPowerBoost is not equal to 'disabled'.

This parameter indicates the scaling (multiplying) factor to increase the allocated PRB that can be used to power boost the PDSCH transmissions with VoNR or SRB1/2 data, if NRCELL.actDlPowerBoost is not equal to 'disabled'.
This parameter defines the minimum number of TTIs required to empty the UE's DL non-GBR data buffer in order to trigger SCell addition.  Note: Currently, this parameter is applicable for FR1 only.

Parameter name: Number of consecutive DL buffer checks for DL SCell config. level
Description: This parameter defines the number of sampled subframes that would require CA configuration for serving all the UE non-GBR DL data traffic.  Note: Currently, this parameter is applicable for FR1 only.
This parameter defines the target Block Error Ratio (BLER) of initial downlink transmissions for DL Outer Loop Link Adaptation in percent

Parameter name: Delta CQI maximum of DL OLLA
Description: This parameter defines the maximum value of the CQI offset

Parameter name: Delta CQI minimum of DL OLLA
Description: This parameter defines the minimum value of the CQI offset

Parameter name: Delta CQI stepdown of DL OLLA
Description: This parameter defines the size of the delta CQI step down in OLLA for a NACK.
This parameter defines the default MCS for DL transmissions.  The default MCS is applied as long as CQI reports are missing or when the CQI reports are outdated.

Parameter name: Specific initial DL BLER target for VoNR DRBs
Description: This parameter indicates the specific initial DL BLER target value for VoNR DRBs.

This parameter indicates the position of the first Orthogonal Frequency Division Multiplex (OFDM) symbol handling the Physical Downlink Shared Channel (PDSCH) and Physical Uplink Shared Channel (PUSCH) Demodulation Reference Signals (DM-RS)

Parameter name: Special DRX profiles for NR ANR solutions
Description: This parameter defines the DRX profile for UEs that needs to receive ReportCGI measurement report from unknown neighbour cells.    All the parameters in this structure are used for one of Automatic Neighbor Relations functionality solution.
