Parameter name: Number of rightmost DFT beams muted
Description: This parameter indicates the number of rightmost DFT beams in horizontal which are muted. The number of beams muted is relative to the full DFT beam set. Value 0 means the full DFT beam set in right side is in use. The full DFT beam set is wider than the configured sector via NRCELL.beamSet.leftEdgeAngle/NRCELL.beamSet.rightEdgeAngle and can cause increased interference. Value 1 means 1 beam relative to the full DFT beam set in right side is muted. And so on...    If this parameter is not configured, then the DFT beams in right side are internally determined by the gNB according to the open angle setting.

Parameter name: Number of deprioritized RBGs in DL transmission.
Description: Parameter defines the number of PRBs corresponding to RBGs, that are deprioritized for the largest bandwidth part in the high part of the spectrum which are assigned for DL transmission. It is applicable when actRat1Alloc flag is activated.  Note:  The RBG size varies with different BW size, and accordingly the deprioritized PRBs changes as per the RBG size and the parameter value that is set.

Parameter name: Number of paging frames in a DRX cycle
Description: This parameter indicates the number of paging frames in one DRX cycle of the UE.    If the cell has NRCELL.dlMimoMode equal to 70 (corresponding to 8x4 Closed Loop Spatial Multiplexing), better lock and unlock the cell to modify paging related configuration instead of online modification. Otherwise the cell CSI-RS resources that have been previously configured to UEs may conflict with the new paging slots.

Parameter name: Number of radio resources reserved for emergency calls
Description: This parameter indicates the number of radio resources (RRC users, PUCCH, GBR DRBs) reserved for emergency calls needed per emergency UE at NR cell level.  Admission control shall reserve specific amount of resources for emergency calls at a cell. If NRBTS.actConnRrcPooling is equal to TRUE, the number of radio resources reserved for emergency calls at pool level is equal to the sum of NRBTS.numOfRadioResReservForEmergency of all NR cells belonging to the same pool.  Configuring/Updating/Removing this parameter might provoke cell reset-- gNB takes decision of reset necessity.

Parameter name: Number of radio resources reserved for priority access
Description: This parameter indicates the number of radio resources reserved for Priority Access calls as defined by NRBTS-applyPriorityAccess at NRCELL level.    Admission control shall reserve a specific amount of resources for priority access calls at cell level. If NRBTS-actConnRrcPooling is equal to TRUE, the number of radio resources reserved for priority access calls at pool level is equal to the sum of NRCELL-numOfRadioResReservForPa of all NR cells belonging to the same pool.  Configuring/Updating/Removing this parameter might provoke cell reset-- gNB takes decision of reset necessity.  Note: The number of reserved DRBs for priority access calls is calculated in the same way as for emergency reserve, i.e., based on the NRBTS-numOfDRBReservedPerEmergency.

Parameter name: Number of radio resources reserved for temporary use
Description: This parameter indicates the number of radio resources (RRC users, PUCCH, DRBs) reserved for temporary use during preemption or RRC setup until UE resource group is established.  Admission control shall reserve a specific amount of resources for temporary use during preemption at cell level. If NRBTS-actConnRrcPooling is equal to TRUE, the number of radio resources reserved for temporary use at pool level is equal to the sum of NRCELL-numOfRadioResReservForTempUse of all NR cells belonging to the same pool.  Configuring/Updating/Removing this parameter might provoke cell reset-- gNB takes decision of reset necessity.  Note: The number of reserved DRBs for temporary use is calculated in the same way as for emergency reserve, i.e., based on the NRBTS-numOfDRBReservedPerEmergency.

This parameter indicates the number of sub-sectors of a New Radio cell.    This parameter is used when all the available antennas are split into independent groups of antennas which are used to form independent sub-sectors.  In that case, groups of antennas correspond to sub-sectors. This parameter is the number of such groups.  Each sub-sector is then composed of either 4 antennas (if this parameter is equal to 2sub-sectors), or 2 antennas (if this parameter is equal to 4sub-sectors).    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke a gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke a gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke a gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Number of subcells for super cell
Description: This parameter indicates the number of subcells for super cell

Parameter name: Number of paging occasions in a paging frame
Description: This parameter indicates the number of paging occasions in a paging frame.    If the cell has NRCELL.dlMimoMode equal to 70 (corresponding to 8x4 Closed Loop Spatial Multiplexing), better lock and unlock the cell to modify paging related configuration instead of online modification. Otherwise the cell CSI-RS resources that have been previously configured to UEs may conflict with the new paging slots.

Parameter name: Number of PUSCH PRBs for VoNR UEs
Description: This parameter indicates the number of PUSCH PRBs for a minimum MCS/PRB combination to realize a minimum UL TBS for VoNR UEs.  If NRCELL.actUlMinTbsForVoNR is equal to TRUE, then while allocating the PUSCH PRBs to a VoNR UE, the gNB shall try to adhere to assign number of PRBs not exceeding this parameter except in certain conditions. This is to avoid end-to-end packet loss due to too much of segmentation. Segmentation involves lesser SINR requirements due to smaller TB sizes, but also causes additional overhead while transmission which corresponds to a considerable percentage of the TBS considering the usually small data packets in VoNR UEs. More HARQs used would mean more transmissions, and if there are segment losses in between, the entire packet is lost as there is no RLC level retransmissions.

Parameter name: Transmission attempts threshold for PRB increment for a VoNR TBS
Description: This parameter indicates the DL HARQ transmission attempts (where transmission attempts include the initial transmission which is not successful and following retransmission attempts) threshold for PRB increment to be used during a VoNR TBS scheduled in DL HARQ transmissions when NRCELL.actVoNRIncCodingGain is equal to TRUE.

This parameter indicates the number of Rx spatial streams/(e)AxCs for a New Radio beamforming cell.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke a gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke a (gNB or cell) reset - the gNB decides if (gNB or cell) reset is needed.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke a gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter indicates the number of reception streams for both PUCCH F1 and F3 when NRCELL.numberOfRxBeamforming is equal to '8Rx' or '16Rx'.  If it is equal to '4Rx', PUCCH F1 and F3 are received with 4Rx MRC.  If it is equal to '8Rx', PUCCH F1 is received with 8Rx plus noise whitening and PUCCH F3 is received with 8Rx IRC.    When NRCELL.numberOfRxBeamforming is not equal to '8Rx', this parameter is ignored.

Parameter name: RU supported beam identifier list for O-RU
Description: This parameter indicates the list of beam identifiers supported by the O-RAN compliant RUs
The parameter specifies the old distinguished name of the managed object before a configuration change like rehosting. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates if p-Max is omitted in the broadcast SIB1 (value TRUE).  This overrides the NRCELL.pMaxNROwnCell setting.

This parameter indicates the precoding applied when NRCELL.dlMimoMode corresponds to Open Loop.    Automatic means that:  - SCDD (Small Cyclic Delay Diversity) is used if the value of NRCELL.dlMimoMode corresponds to 4x4 or 4x2 Open Loop Spatial Multiplexing and  - LCDD (Large Cyclic Delay Diversity) is used if the value of NRCELL.dlMimoMode corresponds to 2x2 Open Loop Spatial Multiplexing.    Dynamic means that a rank/MCS dependent selection of the precoding scheme is chosen.    This parameter is ignored if NRCELL.dlMimoMode corresponds to Closed Loop.
Range and step: Disabled (0), NoPrecoding (1), SCDD (2), LCDD (3), Automatic (4), Dynamic (5)

Description: This parameter defines the operational state of the NR Cell.  It shows if the resource is physically installed and working.

This parameter defines the maximum output power of the cell per TX in dBm (Pmax). Pmax is the maximum value for the linear sum of the power of all downlink physical channels and physical signals that is allowed to be used in a cell per TX. The maximum output per cell is the maximum value for the linear sum of the power of all TXs in a radio unit serving the cell, i.e., Pmax + 10*log10(Number of TX).  Note: The maximum output power supported by particular Radio Units might vary and shall be checked in the latest Customer Documentation file: 'SBTS Supported Configurations'.    The setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide '5G DL Power Calculator'.    Note1: NRCELL.ssPbchBlockPower is not directly link to Pmax. Each time NRCELL.pMax (Pmax) is updated, NRCELL.ssPbchBlockPower shall be updated to keep the same ratio between SSB EPRE and PDSCH/PDCCH EPRE.    Note2: To have PBCH channel and PDSCH channel equalized, NRCELL.ssPbchBlockPower (dB) = Pmax + 10*log10(Nb TX per Polar) - 10*log10(Nb Beam simultaneous) - 10*log10(NB PRB within the bandwidth * 12 RE) - 256QamPowerBackOff in which 256QamPowerBackOff denotes NRCELL.dlQam256PowerBackoffAbove6 for DL bands above 6GHz or NRCELL.dlQam256PowerBackoffSub6 for DL bands below 6GHz    Note3: The supported output power range (minimum and maximum value for Pmax) might vary depending on the particular Radio Unit and shall be checked in the latest Customer Documentation file: 'SBTS Supported Configurations'.

Parameter name: Maximum UL transmit power on own cell
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum UL transmission power for a UE on a carrier frequency.

This parameter indicates the paging offset used for paging frame determination.    If the cell has NRCELL.dlMimoMode equal to 70 (corresponding to 8x4 Closed Loop Spatial Multiplexing), better lock and unlock the cell to modify paging related configuration instead of online modification. Otherwise the cell CSI-RS resources that have been previously configured to UEs may conflict with the new paging slots.

Parameter name: Maximum priority level for PA paging
Description: This parameter together with parameter NRCELL-pagingPrioLevelPaMin indicate the range of paging message priority levels that allow the gNB to treat subsequent mobile terminated RRC connection (with the same 5G-S-TMSI) as Priority Access service. Paging requests with PrioLevels within the given Priority Access range are regarded as Priority Access calls which can use NRCELL-numOfRadioResReservForPa reserved resources. Paging requests with PrioLevels outside of the given Priority Access range are regarded as allowed to use emergency reserved resources from NRCELL-numOfRadioResReservForEmergency.    Note: 3GPP 38.413 defines PrioLevel1, PrioLevel2, ... , PrioLevel8 to indicate the priority paging. Lower value codepoint indicates higher priority.

Parameter name: Minimum priority level for PA paging
Description: This parameter together with parameter NRCELL-pagingPrioLevelPaMax indicate the range of paging message priority levels that allow the gNB to treat subsequent mobile terminated RRC connection (with the same 5G-S-TMSI) as Priority Access service. Paging requests with PrioLevels within the given Priority Access range are regarded as Priority Access calls which can use NRCELL-numOfRadioResReservForPa reserved resources. Paging requests with PrioLevels outside of the given Priority Access range are regarded as allowed to use emergency reserved resources from NRCELL-numOfRadioResReservForEmergency.    Note: 3GPP 38.413 defines PrioLevel1, PrioLevel2, ... , PrioLevel8 to indicate the priority paging. Lower value codepoint indicates higher priority.

This parameter indicates the paging target rate for Link Adaptation (LA).  If equal to 0 (corresponding to pagingDciAggregation), the target rate for LA is the one associated with the Aggregation Level (AL) selected for paging.  Otherwise, the target rate for LA is the one corresponding to the selected value.
Range and step: pagingDciAggregation (0), MCS0_SF2 (1), MCS1_SF2 (2), MCS2_SF2 (3), MCS0_SF1 (4), MCS3_SF2 (5), MCS4_SF2 (6), MCS1_SF1 (7), MCS5_SF2 (8), MCS2_SF1 (9), MCS6_SF2 (10), MCS0_SF0 (11), MCS3_SF1 (12), MCS7_SF2 (13), MCS8_SF2 (14), MCS4_SF1 (15), MCS1_SF0 (16), MCS9_SF2 (17), MCS5_SF1 (18), MCS2_SF0 (19), MCS6_SF1 (20), MCS3_SF0 (21), MCS7_SF1 (22), MCS8_SF1 (23), MCS4_SF0 (24), MCS9_SF1 (25), MCS5_SF0 (26), MCS6_SF0 (27), MCS7_SF0 (28), MCS8_SF0 (29), MCS9_SF0 (30)

Parameter name: Payload size for UL proactive grant for DRX UEs
Description: This parameter indicates the payload size that is scheduled and granted in UL proactive scheduling for UEs that are configured with DRX.    It is expected that the size of the grant includes the size of possible UL MAC CEs and higher level protocol headers. This parameter is used for UEs that are not configured for skipping UL transmission.

Parameter name: Payload size for UL proactive grant for non-DRX UEs
Description: This parameter indicates the payload size that is scheduled and granted in UL proactive scheduling for UEs that are not configured with DRX.    It is expected that the size of the grant includes the size of possible UL MAC CEs and higher level protocol headers. This parameter is used for UEs that are not configured for skipping UL transmission.

Parameter name: Payload size for skippable UL proactive grant
Description: This parameter indicates the payload size that is scheduled and granted in UL proactive scheduling for UEs that are configured for skipping UL transmission.    It is expected that the size of the grant includes the size of possible UL MAC CEs and higher level protocol headers. This parameter is used for UEs regardless if they are configured with DRX or not.

Parameter name: List of PCI values for excluded cells
Description: This structure gathers the list of PCI values that are excluded in each serving cell
This parameter indicates if the current PCI range entry is applicable  - to NSA users only or  - to SA users only or  - to both SA and NSA users.
This parameter indicates the first physical layer cell identity in a list of PCI values to be statically excluded in the serving cell

This parameter indicates the number of physical cell identifiers in the range (including NRCELL.pciExcludeList.physCellId).  The UE shall apply value 1 in case the field is absent, in which case only the physical cell identity value indicated by NRCELL.pciExcludeList.physCellId applies
This structure gathers parameters for automatic PDCCH configuration

Parameter name: BWP channel bandwidth for second dedicated type
Description: This parameter indicates to the feature configuration tool the desired channel bandwidth of the second BWP_PROFILE instance with BWP_PROFILE.bwpType equal to 'dedicated'.

Parameter name: BWP channel bandwidth for third dedicated type
Description: This parameter indicates to the feature configuration tool the desired channel bandwidth of the third BWP_PROFILE instance with BWP_PROFILE.bwpType = 'dedicated'.

Parameter name: BWP channel bandwidth for power saving type
Description: This parameter indicates to the feature configuration tool the desired channel bandwidth of the BWP_PROFILE instance with BWP_PROFILE.bwpType equal to 'powerSaving'.

This parameter indicates the cell coverage expected by the PDCCH control channel.    The possible values are the following:  - verySmall: cell coverage by PDCCH Aggregation Level with 1 CCE (control channel element).  - small: cell coverage by PDCCH Aggregation Level with 2 CCEs (control channel element).  - normal: cell coverage by PDCCH Aggregation Level with 4 CCEs (control channel element).  - large: cell coverage by PDCCH Aggregation Level with 8 CCEs (control channel element).  - enhLarge: cell coverage by PDCCH Aggregation Level with 8 CCEs (control channel element) for all common channels.  - veryLarge: cell coverage by PDCCH Aggregation Level with 16 CCEs (control channel element).  - enhVeryLarge: cell coverage by PDCCH Aggregation Level with 16 CCEs (control channel element) for all common channels.
Range and step: verySmall (1), small (2), normal (4), large (8), veryLarge (16), enhLarge (108), enhVeryLarge (116)

Parameter name: Fine tune mode for PDCCH automatic configuration
Description: This parameter indicates the fine tune mode to be used by the PDCCH automatic configuration.
Range and step: disabled (0), mode1 (1), mode2 (2), mode3 (3), mode4 (4), mode5 (5), mode6 (6), mode7 (7), mode8 (8), mode9 (9)

Description: This parameter indicates the initial Uplink bandwidth part profile (BWP) configuration (only for TDD).    The possible values are the following:  - sameAsCoreset0: The CORESET0 is used for initial uplink BWP, allowing more capacity for traffic  - widerInitBWP: The wider bandwidth will be used for initial uplink BWP, allowing PRACH to be configured adjacent PUCCH for single UE peak rate.

Parameter name: PUCCH size in PRB for long PUCCH
Description: This parameter indicates the size of PUCCH PRB resources for long PUCCH.

Parameter name: PUCCH size of LTE in PRB for DSS
Description: This parameter indicates the size of LTE PUCCH PRB resources for DSS

This parameter indicates the size of the specific BWP.  Its possible values depend on the FDD/TDD FR1 channel bandwidth:  - 'n45' or 'n50' for 10 MHz FDD  - 'n70' for 15 MHz FDD  - 'n41' for 20 MHz TDD FR1  - 'n75' for 30 MHz TDD FR1  - 'n100' for 40 MHz TDD FR1  - 'n122' or 'n131' for 50 MHz TDD FR1  - 'n148' or 'n155' for 60 MHz TDD FR1  - 'n203' for 80 MHz TDD FR1  - 'n239' for 90 MHz TDD FR1  - 'n256' for 100 MHz TDD FR1

Parameter name: The start CRB index of the specific BWP
Description: This parameter indicates the start CRB index of the specific BWP
This parameter indicates the start CRB index of CORESET0 which depends on GSCN and Point A (see 3GPP TS 38.211 Section 4.4).

Parameter name: BLER target for PDCCH outer loop link adaptation
Description: This parameter indicates the Block Error Ratio (BLER) target of PDCCH and HARQ response for downlink transmissions for PDCCH Outer Loop Link Adaptation.  If it is not configured, default value 1% will be used.  Changing this parameter may also impact the BLER of downlink and uplink transmissions.

Parameter name: BLER target for PDCCH high reliability outer loop link adaptation
Description: This parameter indicates the Block Error Ratio (BLER) target of PDCCH and HARQ response for downlink transmissions for PDCCH High Reliability Outer Loop Link Adaptation.  If it is not configured, default value 0.1% will be used.  Changing this parameter may also impact the BLER of downlink and uplink transmissions.
This parameter indicates the index in the NOKIA PDCCH configuration table introduced to help with the dynamic PDCCH configuration

Parameter name: PDSCH configuration for high reliability link adaptation
Description: This structure gathers the PDSCH configuration for high reliability link adaptation.

Parameter name: CQI offset to corrected CQI calculation of ILLA for high reliability
Description: This parameter defines the CQI offset to corrected CQI calculation of ILLA for high reliability.

Parameter name: Delta CQI maximum of DL OLLA for high reliability
Description: This parameter defines the maximum value of the CQI offset for DL transmission of high reliability.

Parameter name: Delta CQI minimum of DL OLLA for high reliability
Description: This parameter defines the minimum value of the CQI offset for DL transmission of high reliability.

Parameter name: Delta CQI stepdown of DL OLLA for high reliability
Description: This parameter defines the size of the delta CQI step down in OLLA for a NACK for high reliability.

Parameter name: Initial Delta CQI of DL OLLA for high reliability
Description: This parameter defines the initial Delta CQI of DL OLLA for high reliability.

Parameter name: Initial MCS for DL transmission of high reliability
Description: This parameter defines the default MCS for DL transmission of high reliability.  The default MCS is applied as long as CQI reports are missing or when the CQI reports are outdated.

Parameter name: Maximum MCS of 64QAM low SE MCS table for DL of HR for RANK1
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed MCS for DL transmission when the UE works in high reliability mode and uses the 64QAM low SE MCS table for RANK1.

Parameter name: Maximum MCS of 64QAM low SE MCS table for DL of HR for RANK2
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed MCS for DL transmission when the UE works in high reliability mode and uses the 64QAM low SE MCS table for RANK2.

Parameter name: Maximum MCS of 64QAM low SE MCS table for DL of HR for RANK3
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed MCS for DL transmission when the UE works in high reliability mode and uses the 64QAM low SE MCS table for RANK3.

Parameter name: Maximum MCS of 64QAM low SE MCS table for DL of HR for RANK4
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed MCS for DL transmission when the UE works in high reliability mode and uses the 64QAM low SE MCS table for RANK4.

Parameter name: Maximum MCS of 64QAM MCS table for DL of HR for RANK1
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed MCS for DL transmission when the UE works in high reliability mode and uses the 64QAM MCS table for RANK1.

Parameter name: Maximum MCS of 64QAM MCS table for DL of HR for RANK2
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed MCS for DL transmission when the UE works in high reliability mode and uses the 64QAM MCS table for RANK2.

Parameter name: Maximum MCS of 64QAM MCS table for DL of HR for RANK3
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed MCS for DL transmission when the UE works in high reliability mode and uses the 64QAM MCS table for RANK3.

Parameter name: Maximum MCS of 64QAM MCS table for DL of HR for RANK4
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed MCS for DL transmission when the UE works in high reliability mode and uses the 64QAM MCS table for RANK4.

Parameter name: PDU session release during handover due to unsupported slice in the target
Description: This parameter indicates if PDU sessions are allowed to be released during intra-RAT handover due to not supported slice in the target cell.

Parameter name: Percentage reduction in SE for VoNR RAT1
Description: This parameter indicates the percentage of reduction of the spectral efficiency (SE) for initial transmission VoNR UEs (with 5QI-1 bearers) in downlink, hence reducing the corresponding proposed MCS index by link adaptation (MCS index tables in 3GPP TS38.214).  gNB-DU shall allocate more PRBs to downlink initial transmission of VoNR traffic in order to drain out the buffer of the UEs and reduce the BLER, when the resource allocation type 1 (RAT1) is configured for PRB allocations to PDSCH.
This parameter gathers the settings for the CSI-RS/PUCCH configuration of periodic CSI Acquisition.
This parameter indicates the CSI reporting periodicity

Parameter name: Number of CSI-RS resource period in one CSI report period
Description: This parameter indicates the number of cell specific CSI-RS resource periods in one CSI report period.  More precisely, that number is equal to Max (40, integer value of NRCELL.periodicCsiAcquisition.csiReportPeriodicity/(2^(integer value of NRCELL.periodicCsiAcquisition.csirsNumberWithinReportPeriod_Set1-1))) slots.    When NRCELL.dlMimoMode is equal to '8x4 Closed Loop Spatial Multiplexing', different randomization methods based on PCI for slots of CSI-RS and CSI-IM is supported via setting NRCELL.actPciBasedCsiImRandomization to FALSE or TRUE. For both methods, the possibility of UE drop due to measurement gap might be impacted in some PCI configurations because the slots for CSI-RS/CSI-IM resource sets in one CSI-RS resource period might be close to each other or if only one specific CSI-RS set can be used for the UE. For both methods, the number of supported DRX UEs might be impacted in some PCI configurations because the slots for CSI-RS/CSI-IM resource sets in one CSI-RS resource period might be close to each other and the PUCCH resources are limited in the DRX on duration period. Shortening the periodicity of CSI-RS/CSI-IM will improve the problem of DRX and measurement gap but peak throughput of PDSCH will be impacted.    If a short CSI-RS period like 40, 80 slots are actually preferred and CSI-RS cannot be arranged in the same slot with system information, then it is better to set NRSYSINFO_PROFILE.systemInformationTargetRate to 157, so that less SIB transmission slots are needed.    If NRCELL.actCellCsiRsImTddNonBf is equal to TRUE or NRCELL.actCellCsirsTddOnSsbBf is equal to TRUE, then only CSI-RS resource period 40 slot is supported. If drx-onDurationTimer (specified in 3GPP TS38.331) is not larger than half of periodicity of cell specific CSI-RS, then the number of UEs configured with DRX for the cell will be impacted because the gNB will make sure UE have at least one cell specific CSI-RS is in DRX ON for PCells.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter indicates the power of the cell-specific CS-RS for CSI acquisition in terms of EPRE.  It shall be set properly to make sure both CSI-RS and SSB do not exceed the maximum transmission power of the RU that is connected to the cell. Otherwise actual transmission power cannot match the setting.    The setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for Power parameters.

This parameter defines the maximum number of cell-specific CSI-RS for channel acquisition per UE.  Note that, for each UE, the number of CSI-RS actually configured is also limited by the capability of the UE, the RU that is connected to the cell, interworking with DRX, CA and so on.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter indicates the step of ScramblingId (see 3GPP TS 38.331) for the second CSI-RS. The second CSI-RS that will be multiplexed together will have ScramblingId equal to (NRCELL.physCellId plus NRCELL.periodicCsiAcquisition.scramblingIdStep) mod the maximum value of ScramblingId.    If NRCELL.actCsirsMultiplexing is equal to TRUE, the neighbor cell with overlapped coverage should not have the NRCELL.physCellId as (NRCELL.physCellId of current cell plus NRCELL.periodicCsiAcquisition.scramblingIdStep) mod the maximum value of ScramblingId, otherwise, NRCELL.periodicCsiAcquisition.scramblingIdStep should be adjusted to a different value.    This parameter is ignored if NRCELL.actCsirsMultiplexing is equal to FALSE.

This parameter defines a cell uniquely.  It consists of two parts; physical layer cell identity group and physical layer identity, and is calculated with the following formula:  physical layer cell identity = 3 x physical layer cell identity group + physical layer identity    Note: If NRCELL.actCsirsMultiplexing is equal to TRUE and the neighbor cell with overlapped coverage has the same physical layer cell identity group, the NRCELL.periodicCsiAcquisition.scramblingIdStep may need to be adjusted, for detail refer to NRCELL.periodicCsiAcquisition.scramblingIdStep.

Parameter name: Individual PLMN selection assistance info list of UE category 1
Description: This parameter indicates the list of individual PLMN assistance information for the UE to determine whether Access Category 1 applies to the UE.  This parameter must be configured for SIB1 to broadcast uac-AccessCategory1-SelectionAssistanceInfo for individual PLMNs.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the NRPLMN instance for which NRCELL.plmnIndvSelAssisInfoList.plmnIndvSelAssisInfo is defined. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1

Parameter name: Individual PLMN selection assistance info of UE category 1
Description: This parameter indicates the individual PLMN assistance information for the UE to determine whether Access Category 1 applies to the UE.
This parameter defines the power ramping factor

Parameter name: Power ramping step high priority CBRA
Description: This parameter indicates the power ramping step for high priority users in case of Contention Based Random Access (CBRA).    The parameter is broadcasted in SIB 1 as part of RACH-ConfigCommon.

Parameter name: Power Ramping Step High Priority CFRA
Description: This parameter defines the power ramping step in case of Contention Free Random access
This parameter defines the PRACH Configuration Index
This parameter indicates the system value of PRACH configuration index.
This parameter defines the PRACH root sequence index.  For the short PRACH format (L=139), the maximum value is 137.  For the long PRACH format (L=839), the maximum value is 837.
This parameter indicates the PRACH sequence Type
This parameter defines the maximum number of preamble transmission

This parameter indicates if DRB and UE preemption algorithms shall honor ARP of NSA UE/DRBs or treat NSA resources as lowest priority and preemption vulnerable regardless of ARP assigned to them.    In cells, where this parameter is set to FALSE, NSA preemption candidates shall not be preferred and shall not be provided as preferred to preemption algorithms triggered by other cells (refers to preemption candidate selection at cell group/pool level).
This parameter indicates the preferred scheduling request periodicity for voice over NR (VoNR)

Parameter name: Max queuing delay for primary path
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum DL data queuing that is allowed for the primary path of carrier aggregation configured UE when primary and secondary cells are configured.    If this parameter is set to 0, the DL DRB data will not be sent over the primary path.    This parameter shall not be set to 0 if buffer based secondary cell activation is used.    A small value could be configured for this parameter, just enough to trigger secondary cell activation, if, for the primary cell of the FDD carrier aggregation, NRCELL.lteNrDssMode is equal to 2 or 3 (corresponding respectively to DL_CRS_TDM_UL_FDM, DSS_Phase_3)    The recommended value for this parameter is 15ms if enhanced flow control based throughput estimation is activated, i.e. NRCELL.actEnhancedFlowControlETh is equal to TRUE.

Parameter name: Timer for strategy based on priority without mobility profile
Description: This parameter indicates the time during which the handover preparation will be delayed for strategy based on priority.
This parameter defines the procedural status of the NR Cell.  It shows configuration phase of the resource.
Range and step: not initialized (0), initialization required (1), initializing (2), validated (3), configured (4)

Description: This structure defines the PUCCH configuration that is computed by the gNB.

This parameter indicates the total amount of PUCCH PRB resources for long PUCCH that is computed by the gNB.  The total amount of PRBs for long PUCCH includes the maximum amount of PRBs used by long PUCCH for scheduling requests (SR), HARQ ACK/NACK and periodic channel state information (pCSI).

Parameter name: Number of PUCCH data samples for DTX detection
Description: This parameter indicates the number of PUCCH data samples used in DTX ratio calculation in radio link problem detection.

Parameter name: Number of PUCCH F1 OCC for HARQ and SR PRBs
Description: This parameter indicates the number of PUCCH Format 1 orthogonal cover codes (OCCs) to be supported for HARQ feedback and scheduling request (SR) PRBs.  - '1-1-0_OCCs' means 1 OCC values used for PUCCH Format 1 SR and 1 OCC values used for PUCCH Format 1 HARQ resources  - '2-2-0_OCCs' means 2 OCC values used for PUCCH Format 1 SR and 2 OCC values used for PUCCH Format 1 HARQ resources  - '3-2-0_OCCs' means 3 OCC values used for PUCCH Format 1 SR and 2 OCC values used for PUCCH Format 1 HARQ resources  - '2-2-1_OCCs' means 2 OCC values used for PUCCH Format 1 SR, 2 OCC values used for PUCCH Format 1 HARQ resources in HARQ area and 1 OCC for PUCCH Format 1 HARQ resources in shared SR/HARQ area    Note:  If NRCELL.reqMinNumPuschPrb is equal to 0 and NRCELL.actLongPucchResourceOpt is equal to TRUE, then the value of this parameter will be ignored.
This parameter indicates the code rate that can be used for PUCCH format 3
Range and step: zeroDot08 (8), zeroDot15 (15), zeroDot25 (25), zeroDot35 (35), zeroDot45 (45), zeroDot60 (60), zeroDot80 (80)

Description: This parameter indicates the modulation scheme for PUCCH format 3

Parameter name: Always on PUCCH F3 Rel-16 DMRS and Pi2-BPSK enabled
Description: This parameter indicates if configuration of the modulation and low-PAPR DMRS sequence type 2 for PUCCH F3 is always on, or if it depends on configuration of DFT-s-OFDM for PUSCH as follows:  - If NRCELL.actRel16DmrsForPucchF3 is equal to TRUE, and this parameter is equal to TRUE, then low-PAPR DMRS sequence type 2 as per Rel-16 3GPP TS38.211 is used for PUCCH F3 modulated with use of Pi/2-BPSK, regardless of whether DFT-s-OFDM is on or off for PUSCH.  - If NRCELL.actRel16DmrsForPucchF3 is equal to TRUE, and this parameter is equal to FALSE, then low-PAPR DMRS sequence type 2 as per Rel-16 3GPP TS38.211 is used for PUCCH F3 modulated with use of Pi/2-BPSK, only if DFT-s-OFDM is on for PUSCH.

This parameter indicates the PUCCH mode that is selected for the NR cell. This mode can be either short PUCCH or long PUCCH but short PUCCH is not allowed if the FR1 TDD NR cell has been mapped to FR1 RF7.1 radios. There is no restriction for FR2 (mmW).  This parameter is always equal to 'longPucch' for supplemental DL cells (FDD).    Note 1: If a heterogeneous configuration of short PUCCH and long PUCCH shall be configured in a gNB-DU, the short PUCCH and the long PUCCH need to be assigned to separate base band modules (e.g. ABIL) - at least 2 base band modules are required for the heterogeneous configuration.    Note 2: The feature can be activated for FPGA based BB modules like e.g. ABIL and DSP based BB modules like e.g. ABIO and ABIP and RINLINE2.

Parameter name: Number of long PUCCH PRBs used for HARQ ACK/NACK
Description: This parameter indicates the number of long PUCCH PRBs used for HARQ ACK/NACK for both PUCCH Format 1 and Format 3 resources when NRCELL.actLongPucchResourceOpt is set to TRUE. The value 'Set_by_system' means the number of long PUCCH PRBs is set by the gNB as follows:  - 4 PRBs if NRCELL.chBw is equal to '10MHz'  - 6 PRBs if NRCELL.chBw is equal to '15MHz' or '20MHz' or to '30MHz'  - 12 PRBs if NRCELL.chBw is equal to '40MHz'  - 16 PRBs if NRCELL.chBw is equal to '50MHz'or to '60MHz' or to '70 MHz' or to '80MHz' or to '90MHz' or to '100MHz'    Note:  If NRCELL.reqMinNumPuschPrb is equal to 0 and NRCELL.actLongPucchResourceOpt is equal to TRUE, then the value of this parameter will be ignored.

Parameter name: Number of PUSCH data samples for DTX detection
Description: This parameter indicates the number of PUSCH data samples used in DTX ratio calculation in radio link problem detection.

Parameter name: PUSCH configuration for high reliability link adaptation
Description: This structure gathers the PUSCH configuration for high reliability link adaptation.

Parameter name: Initial Delta SINR of UL OLLA for high reliability
Description: This parameter indicates the initial delta SINR of UL OLLA for high reliability.

Parameter name: Delta SINR maximum of UL OLLA for high reliability
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum value of the SINR offset of high reliability.

Parameter name: Delta SINR minimum of UL OLLA for high reliability
Description: This parameter indicates the minimum value of the SINR offset of high reliability.

Parameter name: Delta SINR Stepdown of UL OLLA for high reliability
Description: This parameter indicates the size of the delta SINR step down in OLLA for a NACK of high reliability.

Parameter name: Initial MCS for UL transmission of high reliability
Description: This parameter defines the default MCS for UL transmission of high reliability.  The default MCS is applied as long as SINR reports are missing or when the SINR reports are outdated.

Parameter name: Maximum MCS of 64QAM low SE MCS table for UL of HR for RANK1
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed MCS for UL transmission when the UE works in high reliability mode and uses the 64QAM low SE MCS table for RANK1.

Parameter name: Maximum MCS of 64QAM low SE MCS table for UL of HR for RANK2
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed MCS for UL transmission when the UE works in high reliability mode and uses the 64QAM low SE MCS table for RANK2.

Parameter name: Maximum MCS of 64QAM MCS table for UL of HR for RANK1
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed MCS for UL transmission when the UE works in high reliability mode and uses the 64QAM MCS table for RANK1.

Parameter name: Maximum MCS of 64QAM MCS table for UL of HR for RANK2
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed MCS for UL transmission when the UE works in high reliability mode and uses the 64QAM MCS table for RANK2.

Parameter name: SINR offset to corrected SINR calculation of ILLA for high reliability
Description: This parameter indicates the SINR offset to corrected SINR calculation of ILLA for high reliability.
This parameter indicates the mapping type for PUSCH.

Parameter name: Minimum required quality level in the cell
Description: This parameter indicates the minimum required quality level in the cell.
This parameter indicates the offset to the signaled qQualMin taken into account in the 'SrxLev' evaluation by the UE.

Parameter name: Minimum required RX level in the cell (dBm)
Description: This parameter indicates the minimum required RX level in the cell.  Actual qRxLevMin value = field value * 2 (dBm).
This parameter indicates the offset to the signaled qRxLevMin taken into account in the 'SrxLev' evaluation by the UE.  Actual value qRxLevMinOffset = field value * 2 (dB)
This parameter defines the timer for contention resolution

This parameter indicates the RAR Msg2 target rate for Link Adaptation (LA).  If this parameter is not equal to 'dciRaMsg2AggregationLevel', the target rate for LA is the one corresponding to the selected value.  Otherwise, the target rate for LA is the one associated with the Aggregation Level (AL) selected for RA Msg2 with MCS and scaling factor derived as follows:  - MCS7 and scaling factor=0.25, if AL4 is used for PDCCH  - MCS3 and scaling factor=0.25, if AL8 is used for PDCCH  - MCS0 and scaling factor=0.25, if AL16 is used for PDCCH    Note:  SF2 corresponds to scaling factor 0.25  SF1 corresponds to scaling factor 0.5  SF0 corresponds to scaling factor 1
Range and step: dciRaMsg2AggregationLevel (0), MCS0_SF2 (1), MCS1_SF2 (2), MCS2_SF2 (3), MCS0_SF1 (4), MCS3_SF2 (5), MCS4_SF2 (6), MCS1_SF1 (7), MCS5_SF2 (8), MCS2_SF1 (9), MCS6_SF2 (10), MCS0_SF0 (11), MCS3_SF1 (12), MCS7_SF2 (13), MCS8_SF2 (14), MCS4_SF1 (15), MCS1_SF0 (16), MCS9_SF2 (17), MCS5_SF1 (18), MCS2_SF0 (19), MCS6_SF1 (20), MCS3_SF0 (21), MCS7_SF1 (22), MCS8_SF1 (23), MCS4_SF0 (24), MCS9_SF1 (25), MCS5_SF0 (26), MCS6_SF0 (27), MCS7_SF0 (28), MCS8_SF0 (29), MCS9_SF0 (30)

Parameter name: Random access prioritization for access identities
Description: This parameter indicates whether the field ra-Prioritization-r16 applies for Access Identities 1 (Multimedia Priority Service) or 2 (Mission Critical Service) or both in Random Access (RA) procedure.    The parameter is broadcasted in SIB 1 as part of RACH-ConfigCommon.

Parameter name: Duration of random access response window
Description: This parameter defines the duration of random access response window.  Default Value for the parameter depends on whether the New Radio cell gets its HW resources from radio module(s) supported in analog beamforming (carrier frequencies above 6GHz) or digital beamforming (carrier frequencies below 6GHz).  1) In case of analog beamforming, default value for this parameter should be equal to 'sl80', i.e. 80 slots  2) In case of digital beamforming, default value for this parameter should be equal to 'sl20', i.e. 20 slots  According to 3GPP 38.331, the network configures a value lower than or equal to 10ms in licensed spectrum.  1) For FDD FR1, the applicable value compliant with 3GPP is 'sl10', i.e. 10 slots.  2) For TDD FR1, the applicable value compliant with 3GPP is 'sl20', i.e. 20 slots.  3) For TDD FR2, the applicable value compliant with 3GPP is 'sl20', 'sl40' or 'sl80', i.e. 20 slots, 40 slots or 80 slots.  4) It is known there are 2 UE behaviors,  a) if this parameter is larger than 10ms, the UE applies 10ms (3GPP compliance UE);  b) the UE applies the parameter setting even if the value is larger than 10ms (3GPP non-compliant UE).  If the parameter is adjusted from a value larger than 10ms to a 3GPP compliant value, RACH setup attempts may increase and RACH setup success ratio may decrease due to 3GPP non-compliant UE that may initiate more RACH attempts.

This parameter indicates the RAN Area Code for the NR cell. It is used in RRC Inactive state and is transmitted to the UE in SIB1.    If both NRCELL.ranAC and NRPLMNSET_SA.ranAC are not configured, then RRC Inactive state is not supported in this cell.

This parameter indicates the extension of the cell range.  If it is equal to 10 (corresponding to 1x_range), then regular range is applied.  Values other than 10 (corresponding to 1x_range) are allowed only to FR2 cells.

Parameter name: Rate matched CSI-IM in msg2 slot
Description: This parameter indicates if the CSI-IM position is kept in the msg2 slot or if an additionally reserved data slot different from the msg2 slot is used.  More precisely:  - If this parameter is equal to FALSE and NRDSSLTE.actRateMatchedCsiIm is equal to TRUE, then the CSI-IM position is in an additionally reserved data slot different from the msg2 slot.  - If this parameter is equal to TRUE and NRDSSLTE.actRateMatchedCsiIm is equal to TRUE, then the CSI-IM position is kept in the msg2 slot.  - If NRDSSLTE.actRateMatchedCsiIm is equal to FALSE, then this parameter is ignored.

This parameter indicates the reduced frequency offset from carrier center frequency to sub-block edge at both downlink and uplink direction.  Note: uplink direction is not applicable for supplemental downlink carrier.

This parameter indicates the number of measurement reports the UE is requested to send in NSA mode.  If NRCELL.reportAmountSA is not configured, this parameter also indicates the number of measurement reports the UE is requested to send in SA mode.

Parameter name: Report amount for A6 measurement for SCell swap
Description: This parameter indicates the number of measurement reports the UE is requested to send for carrier aggregation related A6 measurement for secondary cell swap.  This parameter is configured on the secondary cell.

Parameter name: Report amount for carrier aggregation related measurements
Description: This parameter indicates the number of measurement reports the UE is requested to send for carrier aggregation related measurements.

Parameter name: Report amount for A1 measurements for steering UE to preferred NR layer for NSA
Description: This parameter indicates the number of A1 measurement reports the UE is requested to send for steering UE to preferred NR layer for NSA.

Parameter name: Report amount for A1 measurements for steering UE to preferred NR layer for SA
Description: This parameter indicates the number of A1 measurement reports the UE is requested to send for steering UE to preferred NR layer for SA.

Parameter name: Report amount for NR-DC related measurements
Description: This parameter indicates the number of measurement reports the UE is requested to send for a given NR-DC related measurement.

This parameter indicates the number of measurement reports the UE is requested to send in SA mode.  If both NRCELL.reportAmount and NRCELL.reportAmountSA are configured in SA mode, then the value of NRCELL.reportAmountSA is the priority and taken into use.

This parameter indicates the interval between consecutive reports when NRCELL.reportAmount is greater than 'r1' in NSA mode.  If NRCELL.reportIntervalSA is not configured, this parameter also indicates the interval between consecutive reports in SA mode.

Parameter name: Report interval for A6 measurement for SCell swap
Description: This parameter indicates the interval between consecutive reports when the value of NRCELL.reportAmountA6MeasSCellSwap is greater than 1 (including infinity) for carrier aggregation related A6 measurement for secondary cell swap.  This parameter is configured on the secondary cell.

Parameter name: Report interval for carrier aggregation related measurements
Description: This parameter indicates the interval between consecutive reports when NRCELL.reportAmount is greater than 1 (corresponding to r1) for carrier aggregation related measurements.

Parameter name: Report interval for A1 measurements for steering UE to preferred NR layer for NSA
Description: This parameter indicates the interval between consecutive reports when NRCELL.reportAmountHoPrefNRLayer is greater than 1 for A1 measurements for steering UE to preferred NR layer for NSA

Parameter name: Report interval for A1 measurements for steering UE to preferred NR layer for SA
Description: This parameter indicates the interval between consecutive reports when NRCELL.reportAmountHoPrefNRLayerSA is greater than 1 for A1 measurements for steering UE to preferred NR layer for SA

Parameter name: Report interval for NR-DC related measurements
Description: This parameter indicates the interval between consecutive reports for a given NR-DC related measurement when NRCELL.reportAmountNrDc is greater than 1 (corresponding to r1).    Value ms120 corresponds to 120 ms, value ms240 corresponds to 240 ms and so on, while value min1 corresponds to 1 min, min6 corresponds to 6 min and so on.

This parameter indicates the interval between consecutive reports when NRCELL.reportAmountSA (or NRCELL.reportAmount if NRCELL.reportAmountSA is not configured) is greater than 'r1' in SA mode.    If both NRCELL.reportInterval and NRCELL.reportIntervalSA are configured in SA mode, then the value of NRCELL.reportIntervalSA is the priority and taken into use.
This parameter indicates whether or not the UE shall initiate the measurement reporting procedure when the leaving condition is met for a cell in Cells Triggered List in UE

Parameter name: Requested minimum number of PUSCH PRBs
Description: This parameter indicates the requested minimum number of PUSCH PRBs in the UL spectrum and allows to increase the PUSCH capacity to the cost of RRC Connected UEs. The increase of the PUSCH capacity is carried out in variable step sizes depending on the gNB configuration and, as a consequence, on the resources spent for PUCCH Format 1 and PUCCH Format 3.    If this parameter is equal to 0, then it is allowed to extend the PUSCH capacity to its maximum with a PUCCH configuration of minimal PUCCH resources for TDD FR1.  This parameter is ignored if NRCELL.pucchModeSelect is not equal to 'longPucch'.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PUCCH parameters.

Parameter name: Min quota limitation info for radio admission control
Description: This parameter provides information about gNB adjustment applied to the cell specific slice aware admission control minimum quota in respect to resources shared across multiple cells.  The gNB scales down the minimum quota values so that the sum of all resource group adjusted minimum quotas for all cells in the pool is not bigger than the shared multicell level resource pool (e.g gNB-DU or baseband pool resources). The minimum quota reservation at cell level is not impacted by the adjustment. This parameter provides information on the biggest adjustment together with the actual scaling factor applied and additional information on related multicell group type and resource type. The value is empty string if no adjustment is needed, otherwise [Scaling factor], [Multicell group type] and [Resource type] are provided as part of the string.
This parameter indicates the RL resume backoff timer duration.  UL RL outage and UL RL resume are separated by at least the time given by this parameter.

Parameter name: Radio link resume path loss threshold
Description: This parameter indicates the UL RL resume threshold for the path loss in radio link problem detection.
This parameter indicates the UL RL resume threshold for the average SINR in radio link problem detection.
This parameter indicates the threshold value for measurement quantity RSRP in Measurement Results in SCG-Failure Info to be used to trigger PSCell change.

Parameter name: Radio link outage consecutive DTX threshold
Description: This parameter indicates the UL RL outage threshold for the consecutive DTX ratio calculations indicating DTX in radio link problem detection.

Parameter name: Radio link outage DTX ratio threshold
Description: This parameter indicates the UL RL outage threshold for declaring PUSCH DTX in the DTX ratio calculation in radio link problem detection.

Parameter name: Radio link outage path loss threshold
Description: This parameter indicates the UL RL outage threshold for the path loss in radio link problem detection.
This parameter indicates the UL RL outage threshold for the average SINR in radio link problem detection.

Parameter name: Threshold for consecutive DTX for CSI/BSI reports to detect radio link problems
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for consecutive DTX for CSI/BSI reports to detect radio link problems.  RLF detection based on CSI reports is disabled if this parameter is equal to 0.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Threshold for consecutive DTX for DL HARQ feedback to detect radio link problems.
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for consecutive DTX for DL HARQ feedback to detect radio link problems.  RLF detection based on DL HARQ reports is disabled if this parameter is equal to 0.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Threshold for consecutive nonDTX for CSI/BSI reports to detect recovery of radio link.
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for consecutive nonDTX for CSI/BSI reports to detect recovery of radio link.  If this parameter is equal to 0, the first recovered CSI report will be considered for RLF cancellation.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Threshold for consecutive nonDTX for DL HARQ feedback to detect recovery of radio link.
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for consecutive nonDTX for DL HARQ feedback to detect recovery of radio link.  If this parameter is equal to 0, the first recovered DL HARQ report will be considered for RLF cancellation.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: RSRP threshold for SSB block selection
Description: This parameter defines the RSRP threshold for SSB block selection. Using this parameter, the UE can select the SS block and corresponding PRACH resource for path loss estimation and (re)transmission based on SS blocks that satisfy the SSB threshold.  Default Value for the parameter depends on whether the New Radio cell gets its HW resources from radio module(s) supported in analog beamforming (carrier frequencies above 6GHz) or digital beamforming (carrier frequencies below 6GHz).  1) In case of analog beamforming, this parameter should have Default Value equal to 53 (corresponding to -103dBm)  2) In case of digital beamforming, this parameter should have Default Value equal to 37 (corresponding to -119 dBm)

Parameter name: Conservative level of secondary cell activation
Description: The parameter indicates the aggressiveness/conservativeness level of secondary cell activation for FR1 CA in downlink direction.  The higher the value of the parameter, the more conservative the secondary cell activation is.  If configured to value X, the meaning is as follows: if it is estimated that the current UE data in the buffer is more than what can be drained on the primary cell and the currently active secondary cell during the next X slots, then one secondary cell or one additional secondary cell will be activated when NRBTS.sCellActivationMethod corresponds to bufferBased or bufferAndRLQualityBased and one secondary cell is configured for a UE.    Note: This parameter has no effect if NRBTS.sCellActivationMethod corresponds to blind.  Note: This parameter is used for FR1 DL CA.

Parameter name: Conservative level of secondary cell activation in uplink
Description: The parameter indicates the aggressiveness/conservativeness level of secondary cell activation for FR1 CA in uplink direction.  The higher the value of the parameter, the more conservative the secondary cell activation is.  If configured to value X, the meaning is as follows: if it is estimated that the current UE data in the buffer is more than what can be drained on the primary cell during the next X slots, then one secondary cell will be activated when NRBTS.sCellActivationMethod corresponds to bufferBased or bufferAndRLQualityBased and one secondary cell is configured for a UE.    Note: This parameter has no effect if NRBTS.sCellActivationMethod corresponds to blind.  Note: This parameter is used for FR1 UL CA.

Parameter name: Minimum data threshold for secondary cell activation
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for the minimum data in the buffer which is needed to activate a secondary cell.  The lower value provides to more aggressive behavior but may lead to inefficient resource utilization when small amount of data are sent via the secondary cell.  The higher value represents conservative approach assuring that there is high enough amount of data to be sent via the secondary cell.  Note: Secondary cell activation condition depends also on the value of NRCELL.sCellActivationLevel. The secondary cell activation algorithm also uses the value of NRCELL.sCellActivationMinDataThreshold for the NRCELL instance representing the primary cell.    Note: This parameter is used for all types of FR1 CA (NSA and SA)

Parameter name: MCS threshold for secondary cell bad channel quality in uplink
Description: This parameter indicates the MCS threshold below which the secondary cell is considered to have a bad radio link quality in uplink.  The gNB considers that the secondary cell is perceived by the UE to have a bad radio link quality if the MCS applied by this cell for data transmission to the UE is below this threshold.

Parameter name: MCS threshold for secondary cell bad channel quality
Description: This parameter indicates the MCS threshold below which the secondary cell is considered to have a bad radio link quality in downlink.  The gNB considers that the secondary cell is perceived by the UE to have a bad radio link quality if the MCS applied by this cell for data transmission to the UE is below this threshold.

Parameter name: Period for secondary cell channel quality estimation
Description: This parameter indicates the period during which the gNB calculates the percentage of good radio link quality and bad radio link quality based on NRCELL.sCellGoodChannelQualityThreshold and NRCELL.sCellBadChannelQualityThreshold.  After this period expires, the gNB will estimate whether the UE secondary cell is in good or bad radio link quality.    If NRBTS.actSCellReleaseBadSCellRlq is equal to enabled_Fr1 and if CQI=0 for the SCell is consecutively received for a period defined by: (NRBTS.sCellDeactivationBadRlqCount * NRCELL.sCellChannelEstimationPeriod), the SCell is released due to bad SCell radio link quality (RLQ).

Parameter name: Evaluation period for secondary cell deprioritization
Description: This parameter indicates the period for which the data buffered at DU is less than NRCELL.bufferThesholdSCellDePrioritize,to trigger the secondary cell deprioritization

Parameter name: Activate CA disable in poor RF
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates disabling of all SCells when UE is in poor RF conditions.    The value 'None' means that SCells are not deactivated when gNB enters PUSCH slot aggregation mode for a UE with VoNR DRB.  The value 'Deact_Scells_VoNr_SAg' means that SCells are deactivated when gNB enters PUSCH slot aggregation mode for a UE with VoNR DRB.    Note: When NRCELL.actUlSlotAgg is set to 'Enabled_VoNr', it is recommended to set NRCELL.sCellDeactInPoorRf to 'Deact_Scells_VoNr_SAg'.

This timer controls the deactivation of secondary cells for carrier aggregation configured UEs.    It behaves in the same way as the secondary cell deactivation timer defined in TS 38.213, but the result is an explicit secondary cell deactivation by the MAC CE instead of the implicit secondary cell deactivation in order to avoid the misalignment of the gNB and UE due to ambiguous HARQ feedback.    In case SCell with uplink is activated, inactivity timers are running independently in downlink and uplink, and this value is used in both downlink and uplink. Only when both downlink and uplink inactivity timers are expired, SCell is deactivated.    The value corresponding to 0 (infinity) means that no secondary cell deactivation will be triggered due to empty UE buffer.

Parameter name: MCS threshold for secondary cell good channel quality
Description: This parameter indicates the MCS threshold above which the secondary cell is considered to have a good radio link quality in downlink.  The gNB considers that the secondary cell is perceived by the UE to have a good radio link quality if the MCS applied by this cell for data transmission to the UE is above the threshold.

This parameter indicates the time during which a SCell has no data activity or is deactivated due to UE overheating before triggering an SCell release. This parameter applies when this cell is configured as a SCell.  If this parameter is set to 0, SCell inactivity release timer is disabled for the SCell. Currently, this parameter is applicable for FR1 only.    Note: If NRCELL.sCellDeactivationTimerGNB is not equal to 'infinity', then when there is no data activity, NRCELL.sCellInactivityReleaseTimer is not started until NRCELL.sCellDeactivationTimerGNB expires.  If NRBTS.actSCellReleaseBadSCellRlq is equal to 'disabled' and NRBTS.sCellDeactivationBadRlqCount is greater than 0, then this timer is also started when an SCell is deactivated due to bad SCell RLQ.

Parameter name: SCell only for FR2 SA cell
Description: This parameter is used to control whether the FR2 SA cell acts as SCell only or not.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE, then this cell shall only act as SCell for FR2 SA.  If this parameter is equal to FALSE, then this cell can act as PCell or SCell for FR2 SA.

This parameter defines the threshold for PCell or PSCell (when UE is in EN-DC) measurement controlling when the UE is required to perform measurements associated to neighbouring cells for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP.

Parameter name: Scaling stepdown and stepup according to HARQ used in data initial transmission for high reliability DRB in downlink enabled
Description: This parameter enables/disables the functionality of scaling stepdown and stepup according to the amount of HARQ which is used in data initial transmission for high reliability DRB in downlink.

Parameter name: Load level for SCell addition blocking
Description: This parameter indicates the cell load level in % starting from which, the setup of SCells in carrier aggregation will be blocked, from SCell perspective.    Setting the value to X% means that SCell addition blocking will start when less than (100-X)% of cell capacity related to UE contexts (5G parameter NRCELL.maxNumOfUsersPerNRCell) or CSI-RS resources is left for UE context establishment. Note that emergency reserved pool is not part of the above defined cell capacity. Setting the value to 100% shall disable the SCell addition blocking.    The parameter is not applicable to cells operating at frequency range 2 (FR2).

Parameter name: Time for blocking carrier aggregation setup and SCell addition
Description: This parameter indicates how long gNB-CU shall block SCell addition in carrier aggregation for a given P(S)Cell-SCell pair for which carrier aggregation setup or SCell addition was blocked due to cell load level reached NRCELL.caBlockingLoadLevel or NRCELL.scellBlockingLoadLevel values.    If scellBlockingLoadLevel or caBlockingLoadLevel are defined and set to values < 100%, then scellBlockingTime has to be defined.

Parameter name: Max queuing delay for secondary path
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum DL data queuing that is allowed for the secondary path of carrier aggregation configured UE when primary and secondary cells are configured.    If this parameter is set to 0, the DL DRB data subject to carrier aggregation will not be sent over the secondary path.    The recommended value for this parameter is 15ms if enhanced flow control based throughput estimation is activated, i.e. NRCELL.actEnhancedFlowControlETh is equal to TRUE.

This parameter indicates the SFN offset for the NR Cell.  The defined offset is observed as a shift of the frame number at the air interface with the reference to the BTS clock (as best represented by its 1PPS output).    This parameter is ignored if FEATCADM.actCellTimingOffset is equal to FALSE, for eCPRI cells.  This parameter is ignored if FEATCADM.actCellTimingOffsetCpriN is equal to FALSE, for CPRI-N cells.

Parameter name: Paging broadcast duration for SI change indication
Description: This parameter indicates the number of DRX cycles required for Paging broadcast to indicate SI change within a modification period.  This parameter shall be used only when lesser number of DRX cycles are needed in a Modification Period for Paging broadcast to increase the Cell Throughput.  Value 0 means that the whole modification period is used for Paging broadcast for SI change indication.

Parameter name: Start PRB of SIB randomization disabled
Description: This parameter, when equal to TRUE, will disable Start PRB randomization and set it to start PRB of CORESET(0). When equal to FALSE, start PRB of SIB will be randomly selected within the CORESET(0) bandwidth.

The parameter defines the description of the site template that is assigned for the base station. Site template description can be used for searching the Site template name, which is needed when generating the complete BTS configuration.
The parameter defines the name of the site template assigned for the base station. Site template can be used for generating the complete BTS configuration during the planning phase.

Parameter name: Skip band check in uplink power control
Description: This parameter maps the UE power class to p-Max in RRC reconfiguration message without checking if the power class is allowed for a particular band as per the table in 3GPP TS 38.101.  The table in TS 38.101 enumerates the power class values allowed per band.

This parameter indicates if the SSB-To-Measure IE in SIB2, SIB4 and RRC RECONFIGURATION for intra or inter frequency measurements is skipped.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE, then the SSB-To-Measure IE is skipped in SIB2, SIB4 and RRC RECONFIGURATION, else the SSB-To-Measure IE is included in SIB2, SIB4 and RRC RECONFIGURATION.
This parameter enables/disables the slice aware admission control in the NRCELL.

Parameter name: Slim carrier RF filter in downlink
Description: This parameter indicates the dedicated RF filter for slim carrier in downlink.  Only the dedicated RF filter bandwidths in the set defined by Range and Step are supported in addition to value 'Nominal' meaning the dedicated RF filter bandwidth is equal to the NRCELL.chBw (TDD) or NRCELL_FDD.chBwDl (FDD) value (nominal RF filter bandwidth).    In case the RF unit does not support the configured dedicated downlink filter bandwidth, the nominal RF filter bandwidth is used.

Parameter name: Slim carrier RF filter in uplink
Description: This parameter indicates the dedicated RF filter for slim carrier in uplink.  Only the dedicated RF filter bandwidths in the set defined by Range and Step are supported in addition to value 'Nominal' meaning the dedicated RF filter bandwidth is equal to the NRCELL.chBw (TDD) or NRCELL_FDD.chBwDl (FDD) value (nominal RF filter bandwidth).    In case the RF unit does not support the configured dedicated downlink filter bandwidth, the nominal RF filter bandwidth is used.

Parameter name: High BLER LA slots correction factor
Description: This parameter indicates the correction factor to be applied to high BLER slots in terms of CQI units for the slot specific LA algorithm

This parameter indicates to DL OLLA the slots within the 20 slot periodicity which are potentially high BLER slots and need correction from the slot specific LA algorithm.  It is a bit mask with Bit 0 (LSB) corresponding to slot 0, Bit 19 corresponding to slot 19 in the 20 slot periodicity.  If Bit x is equal to 0, slot x is not a high BLER slot.  If Bit x is equal to 1, slot x is a high BLER slot.
Range and step: bits mask: Slot 0 (0), Slot 1 (1), Slot 2 (2), Slot 3 (3), Slot 4 (4), Slot 5 (5), Slot 6 (6), Slot 7 (7), Slot 8 (8), Slot 9 (9), Slot 10 (10), Slot 11 (11), Slot 12 (12), Slot 13 (13), Slot 14 (14), Slot 15 (15), Slot 16 (16), Slot 17 (17), Slot 18 (18), Slot 19 (19)

Parameter name: Low BLER LA slots correction factor
Description: This parameter indicates the correction factor to be applied to low BLER slots in terms of CQI units for the slot specific LA algorithm.

This parameter indicates to DL OLLA the slots within the 20 slot periodicity which are potentially low BLER slots and need correction from the slot specific LA algorithm.  It is a bit mask with Bit 0 (LSB) corresponding to slot 0, Bit 19 corresponding to slot 19 in the 20 slot periodicity.  If Bit x is equal to 0, slot x is not a low BLER slot.  If Bit x is equal to 1, slot x is a low BLER slot.
Range and step: bits mask: Slot 0 (0), Slot 1 (1), Slot 2 (2), Slot 3 (3), Slot 4 (4), Slot 5 (5), Slot 6 (6), Slot 7 (7), Slot 8 (8), Slot 9 (9), Slot 10 (10), Slot 11 (11), Slot 12 (12), Slot 13 (13), Slot 14 (14), Slot 15 (15), Slot 16 (16), Slot 17 (17), Slot 18 (18), Slot 19 (19)

Parameter name: High LA BLER slots Use ACK NACK
Description: This parameter indicates whether the ACK NACK feedback from high BLER slots is to be used as input to the OLLA algorithm

Parameter name: Low LA BLER slots Use ACK NACK
Description: This parameter indicates whether the ACK NACK feedback from low BLER slots is to be used as input to the OLLA algorithm
This parameter indicates the scheduling request periodicity.  This parameter is ignored if (NRCELL.pucchModeSelect is equal to 0 (corresponding to shortPucch) and NRBTS.actLteNrDss is equal to FALSE.
This parameter indicates the scheduling request periodicity for the shortest SR (scheduling request) pool.
Range and step: slots5 (5), slots10 (10), slots20 (20), slots40 (40), slots80 (80), slots160 (160)

Description: This structure gathers parameters for SRS based beam management.

This parameter indicates the SRS subband configuration (corresponding to BSRS in table 6.4.1.4.3-1 of 3GPP TS38.211).    Together with NRCELL.srsForBeamMgmt.cSRS, it defines the subband bandwidth of periodic SRS which is configured for a UE for both codebook SRS and antenna switching SRS.    Please refer to table 6.4.1.4.3-1 in 3GPP TS38.211 for different system bandwidth.    When downlink SRS based sub-band beam management is enabled (NRCELL.actDlSrsSubbandBm is equal to TRUE), the gNB will decide whether a UE is configured with SRS for sub-band beamforming and thus this parameter will not be used.

This parameter indicates the SRS bandwidth configuration (corresponding to CSRS in table 6.4.1.4.3-1 of 3GPP TS38.211).  Together with NRCELL.srsForBeamMgmt.bSRS, it defines the subband bandwidth of the periodic SRS which is configured for a UE for both codebook SRS and antenna switching SRS.    Please refer to table 6.4.1.4.3-1 in 3GPP TS38.211 for different system bandwidth.    When downlink SRS based sub-band beam management is enabled (NRCELL.actDlSrsSubbandBm is equal to TRUE), the gNB will decide whether a UE is configured with SRS for sub-band beamforming and thus this parameter will not be used.
This parameter indicates the SRS comb configuration (corresponding to comb in table 6.4.1.4 of 3GPP TS38.211).

Parameter name: SRS power threshold for DL SRS based beamforming
Description: The parameter indicates the power threshold of SRS covariance matrix DTX for DL SRS based beamforming.  The configuration will impact sub-band BM (NRCELL.actDlSrsSubbandBm) because only UEs with valid SRS based wideband BF for DL is possible to be selected as sub-band BF candidates.

Parameter name: SRS power threshold for UL SRS based beamforming
Description: The parameter indicates the power threshold of SRS covariance matrix DTX for UL SRS based beamforming.

Parameter name: SRS type allocation for DL SRS-based beamforming
Description: This parameter indicates which type of SRS is used for SRS based DL beamforming.  The value 'codebook' means that only codebook SRS is used for DL beam management.  The value 'antenna switching' means that only antenna switching SRS is used for DL beam management.  The value 'antenna switching or codebook' means that, if UE is capable of antenna switching SRS, then antenna switching SRS is used for DL beam management; otherwise codebook SRS is used for DL beam management.    When downlink SRS based sub-band beam management is enabled (NRCELL.actDlSrsSubbandBm is equal to TRUE), the gNB will decide whether a UE is configured with TAS SRS for sub-band beamforming and thus this parameter will not be used.    Note: This parameter is applied only if both SRS based DL beamforming and SRS based UL beamforming are activated. If SRS based UL beamforming is deactivated, then no codebook SRS is allocated no matter which parameter value is set.
Range and step: antenna switching (0), codebook (1), antenna switching or codebook (2)

Description: This parameter indicates the UE periodicity for periodic SRS used by the UE to send SRS to the gNB for both codebook SRS and antenna switching SRS.    When downlink SRS based sub-band beam management is enabled (NRCELL.actDlSrsSubbandBm is equal to TRUE), the gNB will decide whether a UE is configured with SRS for sub-band beamforming and thus this parameter will be not used.
This structure gathers SRS parameters for high precision positioning.

This parameter indicates the SRS bandwidth configuration used for positioning (corresponding to CSRS in table 6.4.1.4.3-1 of 3GPP TS38.211).  With bSRS hardcoded to 0, it defines the bandwidth of the periodic SRS which is configured for a UE for codebook SRS used for positioning.  Please refer to table 6.4.1.4.3-1 in 3GPP TS38.211 for different system bandwidth.
This parameter indicates the SRS comb configuration.
This parameter indicates the number of cycle shifts reserved for a comb in the cell.
This parameter indicates the UE periodicity for periodic SRS used by the UE to send SRS to the gNB for positioning.
This structure gathers parameters for SRS based sub-band beam management.

Parameter name: Activate intra-Freq HO with SubBand BF
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates that when a UE enters the cell via intra-frequency HO, UEs can have SRS for SB BF be configured directly in the cell(target cell) if some criteria are met.    It may happen the configured SRS resource for SB BF is overlapped with measurement gap so actually UE can not works under SB BF.

Parameter name: Activate TAS SRS for critical band combination
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates TAS SRS for CA carriers that are critical band combination. Critical band combination means the TAS SRS transmission on one carrier will impact the other carriers due to UE's limitation.    If this parameter is equal to TRUE, TAS SRS for sub-band beamforming may be configured to CA carriers that belong to critical band combination so other carries will be impacted by the TAS SRS transmission. The gNB may mute impacted symbols/slots of the impacted carrier for UEs with this kind of CA relations.    If the parameter is equal to FALSE, TAS SRS for sub-band beamforming will NOT be configured to CA carriers that belong to critical band combination.

This parameter indicates the beamforming sub-band size as the number of PRBs that the operator prefers for sub-band BF.  If the beamforming sub-band size is larger than the cell bandwidth, then the largest SRS bandwidth (see table 6.4.1.4.3-1 of 3GPP TS 38.211) within the cell bandwidth would be selected automatically by the gNB. The last beamforming sub-band size may be adjusted to the cell bandwidth.  If NRCELL.actDlSrsSubbandBm is equal to TRUE and NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm.bfSubbandSize is equal to '4PRBs', then NRCELL.srsForBeamMgmt.cSRS and NRCELL.srsForBeamMgmt.bSRS may be adjusted to values that maps to smaller SRS subband size for wideband BF, this is to avoid too less wideband BF UEs
Range and step: cell bandwidth (0), 2 PRBs (2), 4 PRBs (4), 8 PRBs (8), 16 PRBs (16), 32 PRBs (32), 64 PRBs (64), 128 PRBs (128)

Description: This parameter indicates the TAS SRS configuration policy for CBC.  The possible values are:  - 'CBC first': when there is CBC for CA carriers, TAS SRS will avoid FDD signals and if it cannot avoid, then TAS SRS for sub-band BF will not be configured.  - 'TAS SRS first': when there is CBC for CA carriers, TAS SRS for sub-band BF will be configured without considering impact to other carriers so other carriers may be impacted.

This parameter indicates the comb reservation policy for subband beam management. The gNB will decide available comb IDs for each cell first and then select the comb ID for subband BF according to the configured value.    The possible values are:  - [Avoid SRS for subband BF] Comb ID that are selected for subband BF will try to avoid the comb ID for subband BF in neighbor cells.  - [Avoid SRS for wideband BF] Comb ID that are selected for subband BF will try to avoid the comb ID for wideband BF in neighbor cells.
Range and step: Avoid SRS for subband BF (0), Avoid SRS for wideband BF (1)

Description: If this parameter is not equal to 'mode0', the gNB will enable dynamic SRS resource management based on the number of UEs within the cell that require SRS resources, so that the maximum number of UEs that can be configured with sub-band BF may be less than the value of NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm.maxNumUeSrs due to lack of SRS resource. For eCPRI 7-2e platform, only mode0 is supported.  The meaning of the allowed values are as follows:  - 'mode0': The SRS resources for sub-band BF will always be reserved so that the wide band BF UEs cannot use them.  - 'mode1': For all the SRS resources that are reserved for sub-band BF, minimal 4 symbols within SRS periodicity will be reserved for sub-band BF while the other modes can be used for wide band BF if the latter's load is high.  - 'mode2': All the SRS resources that are reserved for sub-band BF will be available for wide band BF UEs if the latter's load is high.

Parameter name: Maximum number of UEs with reserved SRS
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of UEs that have SRS resource reserved for DL sub-band beamforming.  The actual supported sub-band BF UE number of a cell can be less than the configured value due to limitations from RU, DU and reserved SRS resources.    Note:  For Max 6 cells/half ABIP or 12 cells/ABIP configuration,  If allowSlowPrbPoolingStatNdmSrs is equal to FALSE and below conditions are fulfilled:    - MRBTS/NRBTS/NRCELL/tddFrameStructure.frameStructureType is equal to 'semiStatic'  - MRBTS/NRBTS/NRCELL/tddFrameStructure.ulDlDataSlotRatio is equal to '1/4' or MRBTS/NRBTS/NRCELL/tddFrameStructure.ulDlDataSlotRatio is equal to '3/7'  - NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm.srsUePeriodicityInput is set to 20(slots20)  - NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm-maxNumUeSrs is equal to 1    then NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm-srsUePeriodicityOutput will be set by system to 20(slots20)  Otherwise, NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm-srsUePeriodicityOutput will be set by system to greater than 20(slots20).

This parameter indicates user proposed number of SRS sub-bands in the cell. The gNB will calculate the effective number of SRS sub-bands with this parameter as input. The effective number of SRS sub-band is shown in the parameter NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm.numOfSrsSubbandOutput.    This parameter is only supported under eCPRI 7-2e.

Parameter name: Number of SRS sub-bands selected by system
Description: This parameter indicates the system value of number of SRS subbands in the cell.    This parameter is only supported under eCPRI 7-2e.

This parameter indicates the threshold of SRS signal power for enabling DL SRS sub-band beamforming. SINR will also be used for SRS validation if NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm.srsSinrThreshold is not equal to -40 (dB).  The value of this parameter is recommended to be higher than NRCELL.srsForBeamMgmt.srsPowerThresholdForDlBm because wide band beam that adopt NRCELL.srsForBeamMgmt.srsPowerThresholdForDlBm may have additional combination gain.

This parameter indicates the threshold of SRS SINR for enabling DL SRS sub-band beamforming together with NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm.srsPowerThreshold.
