Simple SINR estimation based on wide band SRS will be enabled if this parameter is not equal to -40 (dB).  Simple SINR measurement may not be effective enough if the received signal quality of SRS is significantly unbalanced between the two polarizations of RU. This is because the gNB only selects one TRX of one polarization of RU to apply SINR estimation.  This parameter is not recommended to be configured to values higher than -6 (dB) to avoid frequent fallback after sub-band BF is enabled for one UE.

This parameter indicates the periodicity of TAS SRS that operator prefers for sub-band BF.  For eCPRI 7-2a platform, the gNB may extend the periodicity if this parameter cannot meet the requirement considering the number of SRS symbols within the periodicity.  For eCPRI 7-2e platform, the gNB will not extend value of this parameter. NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm.srsUePeriodicityOutput is always same as NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm.srsUePeriodicityInput.
Range and step: slots10 (10), slots20 (20), slots40 (40), slots80 (80), slots160 (160), slots320 (320)

Description: This parameter indicates the periodicity of TAS SRS that the gNB applies for subband BF.  For eCPRI 7-2a platform,The gNB will adopt NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm.srsUePeriodicityInput as input and may extend the periodicity if it cannot meet the requirement considering the number of SRS symbols within the periodicity.  For eCPRI 7-2e platform,NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm.srsUePeriodicityOutput is always same as NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm.srsUePeriodicityInput.
Range and step: slots10 (10), slots20 (20), slots40 (40), slots80 (80), slots160 (160), slots320 (320)

Description: This parameter defines the SS and PBCH powers in terms of EPRE, where  - For beamforming type of radio (NRCELL.actBeamforming equal to TRUE), NRCELL.ssPbchBlockPower is defined as SS/PBCH block power per RE for 1 polarization, with number of TRX(s) per polarization.  - For non-beamforming type of radio (NRCELL.actBeamforming equal to FALSE), NRCELL.ssPbchBlockPower is defined as SS/PBCH block power per RE for 1 MIMO stream/layer, with 1TRX per MIMO stream/layer.    Its value shall be configured taking into account the constraints between this parameter and the maximum power configured through NRCELL.pMax, where  - In general, NRCELL.ssPbchBlockPower <= NRCELL.pMax + 10log10(Num. of TRXs per polarization) - 10log10(Num. of REs), where Num. of REs = max(ssbPbchBlock_REs, CSI-RS_REs) and CSI-RS_REs includes CSI-RS for tracking, CSI-RS for beam refinement, and CSI-RS for measurements in SSB slot.  - If NRCELL.dlMimoMode is 70, (corresponding to 8x4 Closed Loop Spatial Multiplexing), cell- specific CSI-RS for measurements shall take power adjustment into consideration so CSI-RS_REs for measurements = (actual CSI-RS RE number)*x, with x=10^( powerControlOffsetSS/10) and has values [0.5,1,2,4]. For cell-specific CSI-RS measurement with is extended precoding, x = 4*10^( powerControlOffsetSS/10) and has values [2,4,8,16]. powerControlOffsetSS=NRCELL.csirsPower -(NRCELL.ssPbchBlockPower+3dB). Only SSB transmit via both polarizations is supported here.  - If CSI-RS signals for refined beams are transmitted in the same slot as SS PBCH, then NRCELL.ssPbchBlockPower <= NRCELL.pMax + 10log10(Num. of TRXs per polarization) - 10log10(Num. of REs), where Num. of REs = max(ssbPbchBlock_REs, CSI-RS_REs) and CSI-RS_REs includes CSI-RS for tracking, CSI-RS for beam refinement+240, and CSI-RS for measurements in SSB slot.    These constraints depends on the RU configuration with examples as shown in below:  1- TDD CPRI cmWave RUs (e.g. AEQA): NRCELL.ssPbchBlockPower <= NRCELL.pMax + 10*log10(number of TRX per polarization) - 10*log10(20*12) (e.g. for AEQA: number of TRX per polarization = 32 and it is assumed that Num. of REs = ssbPbchBlock_REs with 240REs=20 PRB*12 REs/RB)  2- TDD CPRI mmWave RUs (e.g. AEUA): NRCELL.ssPbchBlockPower <= NRCELL.pMax - 10*log10(20*12) (e.g. for AEUA: number of TRX per polarization = 1 and it is assumed that Num. of REs = ssbPbchBlock_REs with 240REs=20 PRB*12 REs/RB)  3- FDD CPRI below 3GHz (cmWave) RUs (e.g. AHLOA): NRCELL.ssPbchBlockPower <= NRCELL.pMax- 10*log10(20*12) (it is assumed that Num. of REs = ssbPbchBlock_REs with 240REs=20 PRB*12 REs/RB).    The actual range of values supported by NRCELL.ssPbchBlockPower also depends on the dBFS range supported by CPRI/eCPRI RUs. The range of NRCELL.ssPbchBlockPower supported is:  For CPRI: The range is [max(-60, -66.1+NRCELL.pMax+10*log10(number of TRX per polarization)), min(50, NRCELL.pMax+10*log10(number of TRX per polarization))]  For eCPRI: The range is [max(-60, -90.3+NRCELL.pMax+10*log10(number of TRX per polarization)), min(50, NRCELL.pMax+10*log10(number of TRX per polarization))]    In order to avoid Alarm-4090, the lowest boundary value of NRCELL.ssPbchBlockPower should be set based on  - NRCELL.pMax  - the OAM configured InputPowerLowThreshold (defined in the BFP) and  - an offset Delta value in dB  with NRCELL.ssPbchBlockPower >= NRCELL.pMax + InputPowerLowThreshold  Delta(dB).  The default value for Delta(dB) is 3 (dB) and the default value for InputPowerLowThreshold is -30 (dB).    The setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for Power parameters.    When NRCELL.actCsirsMultiplexing is set to FALSE , updating this parameter will not provoke cell restart, the modification can be done on line.  When NRCELL.actCsirsMultiplexing is set to TRUE, updating this parameter will provoke cell restart.

Parameter name: SSB group for SSB based beamforming
Description: This structure defines the SSB groups which contains 4 SSB beams used to send over 8-port CSI-RS resource.  It takes effect only if NRCELL.actCellCsirsTddOnSsbBf is equal to TRUE and NRCELLGRP.numberOfTransmittedSsBlocks is greater than 4 (corresponding to 4 beams).

Parameter name: First SSB beam configuration group for SSB based beamforming
Description: This parameter defines the first SSB beams index allocation group. SSB beams in group are sent over 8-port CSI-RS for channel acquisition. This parameter is a 6 bits mask with Bit 0 (LSB) corresponding to the SSB beam index 0, each bit refers to one SSB beam, if Bit x is equal to 1, SSB beam with index x is used.    For example, if NRCELLGRP.numberOfTransmittedSsBlocks is equal to 6 (corresponding to 6 beams),  - NRCELL.ssbGroupForSsbBasedBF.firstSsbGroup can be configured as 0b00001111, which means the first SSB beam group contains SSB beam ID 0, SSB beam ID 1, SSB beam ID 2 and SSB beam ID 3.  - NRCELL.ssbGroupForSsbBasedBF.secondSsbGroup can be configured as 0b00111100 (not list all possible value here, just an example, such as 0b00110101 also works), but shall not be 0b00011110 which will result SSB beam ID 5 not covered by the first two groups. (The first two groups shall cover all the six SSB beams by setting the corresponding bits to 1)  - NRCELL.ssbGroupForSsbBasedBF.thirdSsbGroup can be configured as 0b00011110  - NRCELL.ssbGroupForSsbBasedBF.fourthSsbGroup can be configured as 0b00101101
Range and step: bits mask: SSB beam ID 0 (0), SSB beam ID 1 (1), SSB beam ID 2 (2), SSB beam ID 3 (3), SSB beam ID 4 (4), SSB beam ID 5 (5)

Parameter name: Fourth SSB beam configuration group for SSB based beamforming
Description: This parameter defines the fourth SSB beams index allocation group. SSB beams in group are sent over 8-port CSI-RS for channel acquisition. This parameter is a 6 bits mask with Bit 0 (LSB) corresponding to the SSB beam index 0, each bit refers to one SSB beam, if Bit x is equal to 1, SSB beam with index x is used.
Range and step: bits mask: SSB beam ID 0 (0), SSB beam ID 1 (1), SSB beam ID 2 (2), SSB beam ID 3 (3), SSB beam ID 4 (4), SSB beam ID 5 (5)

Parameter name: Second SSB beam configuration group for SSB based beamforming
Description: This parameter defines the second SSB beams index allocation group. SSB beams in group are sent over 8-port CSI-RS for channel acquisition. This parameter is a 6 bits mask with Bit 0 (LSB) corresponding to the SSB beam index 0, each bit refers to one SSB beam, if Bit x is equal to 1, SSB beam with index x is used.
Range and step: bits mask: SSB beam ID 0 (0), SSB beam ID 1 (1), SSB beam ID 2 (2), SSB beam ID 3 (3), SSB beam ID 4 (4), SSB beam ID 5 (5)

Parameter name: Third SSB beam configuration group for SSB based beamforming
Description: This parameter defines the third SSB beams index allocation group. SSB beams in group are sent over 8-port CSI-RS for channel acquisition. This parameter is a 6 bits mask with Bit 0 (LSB) corresponding to the SSB beam index 0, each bit refers to one SSB beam, if Bit x is equal to 1, SSB beam with index x is used.
Range and step: bits mask: SSB beam ID 0 (0), SSB beam ID 1 (1), SSB beam ID 2 (2), SSB beam ID 3 (3), SSB beam ID 4 (4), SSB beam ID 5 (5)

Description: This parameter indicates the PRACH occasion(s) associated with an SSB in which the MAC entity may transmit a Random Access Preamble.  It corresponds to the explicitly signaled PRACH mask index for RA Resource selection in TS 38.321 [3].  The mask is valid for all SSB resources.

This parameter indicates the SSB positions in burst set for TDD FR1 cells (see 3GPP TS38.331), when the cells have NRCELLGRP.numberOfTransmittedSsBlocks equal to '1 beam'.  It is a bit mask with Bit 0 (LSB) corresponding to SS/PBCH Index 0, Bit 1 corresponding to SS/PBCH Index 1, ... Bit 7 corresponding to SS/PBCH Index 7.  If Bit x is equal to 1, SS/PBCH Index x is active with the corresponding SS/PBCH configured (indicated by RRC IE: ssb-PositionsInBurst).  If Bit x is equal to 0, SS/PBCH Index x is inactive with the corresponding SS/PBCH not configured (indicated by RRC IE: ssb-PositionsInBurst).
Range and step: bits mask: SS/PBCH Index 0 (0), SS/PBCH Index 1 (1), SS/PBCH Index 2 (2), SS/PBCH Index 3 (3), SS/PBCH Index 4 (4), SS/PBCH Index 5 (5), SS/PBCH Index 6 (6), SS/PBCH Index 7 (7)

Description: This parameter indicates the subcarrier spacing value for SSB.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter defines the duration of the measurement window for intra-frequency A3/A5 measurements in which to receive SS/PBCH blocks. It is given in number of subframes.
This parameter defines the offset of the measurement window for intra-frequency A3/A5 measurements in which to receive SS/PBCH blocks. It is given in number of subframes.
This parameter defines the periodicity of the measurement window for intra-frequency A3/A5 measurements in which to receive SS/PBCH blocks. It is given in number of subframes.

Parameter name: Multiplier to increase the allocated PRB for VoNR UEs
Description: This parameter indicates the multiplier factor by which the allocated PRB will be increased for the VoNR UEs.  This will results in the increase of the coding gain for the VoNR UEs (with 5Q1 bearer(s))
This parameter indicates the system information area that the cell belongs to.

This timer is used to supervise the RRC connection establishment procedure.  Start: Transmission of RRCConnectionRequest  Stop: Reception of RRCConnectionSetup or RRCConnectionReject message, cell reselection and upon abortion of connection establishment by upper layers    At expiry: Perform the actions as specified in 38.331, 5.3.3.x

This timer is used to supervise the RRC connection reestablishment procedure.  Start: Transmission of RRCConnectionReestabilshmentRequest  Stop: Reception of RRCConnectionReestablishment or RRCConnectionReestablishmentReject message as well as when the selected cell becomes unsuitable    At expiry: Go to RRC_IDLE
This timer is used to supervise the recovery from physical layer problems.
This timer is used for Voice over NR to supervise the recovery from physical layer problems.
This timer is used to supervise the RRC connection reestablishment.

This timer is used to supervise the RRC resume procedure.  Start: Transmission of RRCResumeRequest or RRCResumeRequest1  Stop: RRCResume, RRCSetup, RRCRelease, RRCRelease with suspendConfig or RRCReject message, cell re-selection and upon abortion of connection establishment by upper layers
This timer indicates the validity time of dedicated priorities provided in CellReselectionPriorities IE.

Parameter name: Timer T320 for EN-DC idle mode traffic steering
Description: This parameter indicates the validity time of dedicated priorities during reselection to E-UTRA.    This parameter is specifically used in EN-DC aware idle mode traffic steering.

Parameter name: Maximum time interval for correlation during paging
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum time interval during which the gNB keeps track of 5G-S-TMSIs paged with Paging Priority IE. It is used to prioritize radio resource allocation for mt-Access calls paged with priority and determines the maximum time between the NGAP:PAGING and RRCSetupRequest that allows the gNB to correlate the above messages via 5G-S-TMSI. 5G-S-TMSI correlation is considered successful when ng-5G-S-TMSI-Part1 IE from RRCSetupRequest message corresponds to 5G-S-TMSI from NGAP: PAGING message, i.e. ng-5G-S-TMSI-Part2 IE from RRCSetupComplete is not used.    Note: If this parameter is equal to 0, then Prioritization of Emergency and Priority Access Callbacks are disabled.

Parameter name: Number of TA units for TA-based threshold
Description: This parameter defines a threshold in Timing Advance (TA) units for disconnecting UE (RRC connection release) or preventing RACH access based on Timing Advance (TA) limit.    1 TA unit equals to 16 times slots, which corresponds roughly to a distance of:  - 78 m for 15 kHz Sub Carrier Spacing (SCS)  - 39 m for 30 kHz Sub Carrier Spacing (SCS)
This parameter defines a time duration for monitored Timing Advance (TA) to continuously exceeding the threshold limit (NRCELL.taDiscThr) to initiate UE disconnection (RRC connection release).
The parameter defines a multiplier value for NRCELL.dllaBlerTarget, used by the users with used MCS less than NRCELL.boostSwitchBoundaryOfMcs.
The parameter defines a multiplier value for NRCELL.dllaBlerTarget, used by the users with used MCS higher than or equal to the NRCELL.boostSwitchBoundaryOfMcs.

Parameter name: Target percentage of resources for reserved MCS DL
Description: This parameter indicates the target amount of physical channel bits in percentage requested for an adaptive retransmission based on reserved MCS on PDSCH with reference to the physical channel bits allocated by the initial transmission.

Parameter name: Target percentage of resources for reserved MCS UL
Description: This parameter indicates the target amount of physical channel bits in percentage requested for an adaptive retransmission based on reserved MCS on PUSCH with reference to the physical channel bits allocated by the initial transmission.

Parameter name: List of target release parameter values
Description: This structure contains the list of target parameters to be created or modified with a target parameter value after migration towards a release greater than or equal to the target release.  The configuration in this structure has no effect if FEATCADM.actTargetConfigPrep is equal to FALSE.
This is a free text parameter for storing the additional explanation notes by the End User.

This parameter indicates the target parameter to be created or modified at migration towards a release greater than or equal to the target release.    If the target parameter has a single value (multiplicity = 1) it shall contain the Abbreviated Name of the target parameter.  Example1 : actSpecificBwpSize    If the target parameter is a list (multiplicity > 1) it shall contain the Abbreviated Name of the target parameter suffixed by '()'.  Example2 : sNSSAIDNList()    If the target parameter is equal to '#MOI#' it indicates that either the target managed object instance is created during migration with ID equal to the target value, or the target managed object instance is removed during migration if the target value is configured to '#DEL#'.  Example3 : #MOI#

This parameter indicates the target parent parameter (structure) to be created or modified at migration towards a release greater than or equal to the target release.    If the target structure has a single value (multiplicity = 1) it shall contain the Abbreviated Name of the target structure.  Example1 : pdcchAutoConfig    If the target structure is a list (multiplicity > 1) it shall contain the Abbreviated Name of the target structure suffixed by '()' and the target value must contain a comma-separated list of all entries of the target parameter on the structure list.  Example2 : cellBwpList()

This parameter indicates the target release for the migration of the parameters indicated by NRCELL.targetReleaseParamValueList.    When this parameter is not configured, changes will apply at the next migration (including also migration to newer software build using the same object model version).    When this parameter is in the format yyRq (e.g. '23R4'), the changes will apply at the next migration towards the new software build of the indicated commercial release.  Example1 : 23R4    When this parameter is in the format yyRq_ffbb_xyz (e.g. '23R3_2309_100'), the changes will apply at the next migration towards the new software build with the indicated object model package version.  Example2 : 23R3_2309_100

This parameter indicates the value of the target parameter to be set at migration towards a release greater than or equal to the target release.    If the target parameter or target parent parameter is a list (multiplicity > 1), then this parameter shall contain a list of comma-separated values, else it shall contain only one value.  Example1 : true  Example2 : 7,14,21,28    If this parameter is set to the special value of '#DEL#', then after migration the target parameter or object will be removed.  Example3: #DEL#

Parameter name: Target total load with artificial load
Description: This parameter indicates the target total load (artificial load) for creating artificial PDSCH load in the cell. When there are UEs scheduled in the slot, no artificial PDSCH load is added. However, when there are no UEs scheduled in the slot, artificial PDSCH load needs to be generated. Only empty slots will be used for generating artificial load.  If equal to 0, no artificial PDSCH load in the cell can be created.

Parameter name: Target total load with artificial load using sector beam
Description: This parameter indicates the target total load (normal + artificial load) for creating artificial load in the cell. The artificial load is created using the sector beam and covers the whole cell.    When normal load is below the target load, the artificial load is added up to the target load.  When normal load is greater than or equal to the target load, no artificial load is added.  If this parameter is equal to 0, then no artificial load shall be created.

This structure defines the parameters to configure the TDD frame structure.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter defines the type of the frame structure.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter defines the length in the OFDM symbols of the guard period.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition might provoke gNB reset (the gNB takes the decision whether gNB reset is needed or not).  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion might provoke gNB reset (the gNB takes the decision whether gNB reset is needed or not).    When additional external delay compensation is activated (NRCELL.addExtDelayCompensation is greater than 0.0), this parameter is automatically calculated by the gNB. The previously configured value will be overwritten according to the resulting value set by the gNB.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter defines the LTE to NR frame shift in ms.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.    Note: If NRCELL.tddFrameStructure.frameStructureType is equal to 3 (corresponding to tdLte) and NRCELL.tddFrameStructure.lteToNrFrameShift is equal to 3 (corresponding to 3ms), additional adjustment shall be performed to synchronize NR SFN 0 with LTE SFN 0 + 3ms. This adjustment can be performed either in case of actCellTimingOffset is set to true with frameStartOffset and sfnOffset. Otherwise (actCellTimingOffset is set to false) this adjustment can be set with manualFrameTimingAdjustment.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter indicates the TD LTE uplink and downlink configuration. Refer to TS 36.211 section 4.2 for information.    When NRCELL.tddFrameStructure.frameStructureType corresponds to tdLte, the system can further decide the NR frame structure with this parameter.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: UL to DL logical data slot ratio
Description: This parameter defines the ratio of the UL / DL logical data slots used in the dynamic slot selection algorithm by the 5G-L2-PS.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Threshold RSRP for source SCell for SCell swap
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantity RSRP to be used for checking whether current secondary cell has degraded below this threshold to allow a secondary cell swap. The parameter is used by gNB when A6 measurement report is received to perform additional criteria check before triggering a secondary cell swap.  This parameter is configured on the secondary cell.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 38.133:  * -156 dBm means a threshold lower than -156 dBm  * values between -155 dBm and -30 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -29 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -30 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold RSRQ for source SCell for SCell swap
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantity RSRQ to be used for checking whether current secondary cell has degraded below this threshold to allow a secondary cell swap. The parameter is used by gNB when A6 measurement report is received to perform additional criteria check before triggering a secondary cell swap.  This parameter is configured on the secondary cell.    The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 38.133:  - -43.5 dB means a threshold lower than -43 dB  - values between -43 dB and 19.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  - 20 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to 20 dB
This parameter indicates if the time restriction for interference measurements for a NR Cell is configured or not.

This parameter indicates the timing offset between the start of UL and DL frames on UE side.  It corresponds to the 3GPP parameter n-TimingAdvanceOffset which is specified in 38.211 section 4.3.1; 38.133 Table 7.1.2-2 and 38.331 in ServingCellConfigCommon and ServingCellConfigCommonSIB RRC structures when it is applicable.  It shall be set according to the frequency range and the duplex mode.  For FR1 TDD, the value shall be n39936 if LTE-NR shared Radio Unit, else the value shall be n25600 (without LTE-NR coexistence) or n39936 (with LTE-NR coexistence).  For FR2, the value shall be n13792.  NR FDD - NR TDD UL CA w/o LTE co-existence: n25600 applies for both FDD and TDD carriers in the UL CA group with 1 TAG  NR FDD - NR TDD UL CA w/ TDD LTE only co-existence: n39936 applies for both FDD and TDD carriers in the UL CA group with 1 TAG  NR FDD - NR TDD UL CA w/ FDD LTE only co-existence: n25600 applies for both FDD and TDD carriers in the UL CA group with 1 TAG  NR FDD - NR TDD UL CA w/ TDD LTE co-existence and FDD LTE co-existence: n39936 applies for both FDD and TDD carriers in the UL CA group with 1 TAG  NR FDD - NR FDD UL CA w/o FDD LTE co-existence: n25600 applies for FDD carriers in the UL CA group with 1 TAG.  NR FDD - NR FDD UL CA w/ FDD LTE co-existence: n0 applies for FDD carriers in the UL CA group with 1 TAG.  NR TDD FR1 - NR TDD FR1 UL CA w/o TDD LTE coexistence: n25600 applies for TDD carriers in the UL CA group with 1 TAG.  NR TDD FR1 - NR TDD FR1 UL CA w/ TDD LTE coexistence: n39936 applies for TDD carriers in the UL CA group with 1 TAG.  In case NR FDD - NR TDD UL CA rules conflict with NR FDD - NR FDD UL CA rules (for example: NR FDD PCell has UL CA relationship with NR FDD cell and NR TDD cell), NR FDD - NR TDD UL CA rules override NR FDD - NR FDD UL CA rules.    The value of this parameter shall be equal for all NRCELL instances of the same duplexing within the same BBMOD/SMOD instance.  - With ABIL: only one value of this parameter is allowed for the entire BBMOD instance  - With ABIN: only one value of this parameter is allowed for the entire BBMOD instance  - With ABIO/ASOE: only one value of this parameter is allowed per duplexing mode if there is (NR FR1 TDD, NR FR1 FDD) in the same BBMOD/SMOD instance  In case a mix of NR cells with LTE co-existence and NR cells without LTE co-existence in the same cell set, then the co-existence case shall take precedence when configuring this parameter  In case of mix of UL CA cells with non UL CA cells, then the UL CA rules shall take precedence.    When cell mapping per BBMOD instance cannot be known, the value of this parameter shall be equal for all NRCELL instances on the same BTS of the same duplexing mode and frequency range.    To limit the risk of misconfiguration, the value of this parameter shall be equal for all NRCELL instances  - on the same BTS of the same duplexing mode and frequency range.  - with TDD FR1 on the same network.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter indicates the total number of preambles used for contention based and contention free random access in the RACH resources

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the TRACKINGAREA instance. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/TRACKINGAREA-1  TRACKINGAREA-1

Parameter name: TRS muting in blanked PRBs enabled
Description: This parameter enables/disables the TRS muting function while the PRB blanking function is activated in the NR cell.

This parameter indicates the control resource set zero (CORESET(0)) configuration.  This CORESET is used at least by the UE for the System Information block type 1 (SIB1) acquisition.    With the index, the operator selects the CORESET size, duration and its position from the lower boundary of the Synchronization Signals and Physical Broadcast Channel (SS/PBCH) bandwidth defined by the Global Synchronization Channel Number (GSCN) and the subcarrier spacing used for these signals and channels in the cell.    The CORESET size and duration are 24 RBs over 2 symbols or 48 RBs over 1 or 2 symbols or 96 RBs over 1 or 2 symbols. The 3 symbols duration does not allow to optimize the PDCCH in time domain and its usage could be restricted by the UE capability. That is the reason it is not supported.    Its selection must be done carefully according to the expected configuration as it may have an impact on the whole PDCCH configuration, on the number of SS/PBCH allowed in the cell, on the Dynamic Spectrum Sharing constraints on LTE side.    When it is possible to use a CORESET(0) duration on 1 symbol, it will increase the possible combinations to manage the PDCCH size in order to optimize the dedicated traffic.    The CORESET(0) is available in all Bandwidth Parts fully overlapping it.    In SA, if another CORESET is configured and used for the Type0A or/and Type1 or/and Type2, this additional CORESET must fit within the CORESET(0) bandwidth.    When the Dynamic Spectrum Sharing (DSS) is activated, the number of Cell-Reference Signals (Cell-RS) configured on the LTE cell must be taken into account to select the right CORESET(0) duration on top of the NR constraints.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for GSCN parameters.
This parameter defines the periodicity and position of the potential Downlink Control Information (DCI) of the SIB1.
This parameter defines the unified access control access category list
This parameter defines the access category (3GPP 22.261)

Parameter name: Unified access control barring Info set index
Description: This parameter indicates the index of the entry in the field 'SIB1.uac-barringInfo.uac-BarringInfoSetList'.

Parameter name: UAC access control parameter set list
Description: This parameter defines the unified access control parameter set list
This parameter indicates the probability that access attempt would be allowed during access barring check

Parameter name: Unified access control barring for access identity
Description: This parameter indicates whether the access attempt is allowed for each Access Identity (AC ID).  In the bit string  - Bit 0 (Least significant bit - right-most bit) corresponds to Access Identity 15  - Bit 1 corresponds to Access Identity 14  - Bit 2 corresponds to Access Identity 13  - Bit 3 corresponds to Access Identity 12  - Bit 4 corresponds to Access Identity 11  - Bit 5 corresponds to Access Identity 2  - Bit 6 corresponds to Access Identity 1  Value 0 for a given Bit means that the access attempt is allowed for the corresponding Access Identity.
Range and step: bits mask: AC ID 15 (0), AC ID 14 (1), AC ID 13 (2), AC ID 12 (3), AC ID 11 (4), AC ID 2 (5), AC ID 1 (6)

Description: This parameter indicates the minimum time before a new access attempt is to be performed after an access attempt was barred at access barring check for the same access category.

This parameter indicates the usage of the associated BWP profile when the UE establishes a RRC connection in SA mode.    The possible values are:  - 'useDedicatedBwp': when the UE establishes a RRC connection in SA mode, the smallest supported dedicated BWP is used to configure UE in the RRC establishment procedure.  - 'useInitialBwp': when the UE establishes a RRC connection in SA mode, the initial BWP with dedicated configuration is used to configure UE in the RRC establishment procedure.    If smallest RRCSetup is deactivated (NRCELL.actSmallestRRCSetup is equal to FALSE), then this parameter controls whether Initial BWP or Dedicated BWP is used in the RRCSetup message. If smallest RRCSetup is activated, then this parameter controls whether Initial BWP or Dedicated BWP is used in the first RRCReconfiguration message which immediately follows RRCSetupComplete.

UE power is split on PCell and SCell in uplink overlapping slots for a UE configured with FR1 uplink CA, and the UE split power is adjusted step by step on PCell and SCell.  This parameter defines the maximum UE split power adjustment value for a step.    The higher the value of the parameter, the bigger UE split power adjustment step.  If configured to value X, the meaning is that the UE split power adjustment step is equal to X dBm.
This parameter indicates the monitoring time window to determine the UL Angle of Arrival (UL AoA).
This structure contains parameters related to UL BLER.

Parameter name: UL BLER threshold for data redirection
Description: This parameter indicates the percentage above which gNB considers that UL BLER observed for the UE is 'high' for data only calls.

Parameter name: UL BLER threshold for VoNR redirection
Description: This parameter indicates the percentage above which gNB considers that UL BLER observed for the UE is 'high' for VoNR calls.

Parameter name: Serving carrier weight for UL CA aware IMM steering
Description: This parameter indicates the serving carrier weight for UL CA aware IMM steering.
This parameter indicates the minimum PCell UL SINR for a UE with no established 5QI1 bearer to be considered a candidate for adding a SCell.

Parameter name: Uplink CA minimum PCell SINR for 5QI1
Description: This parameter indicates the minimum PCell UL SINR for a UE with an established 5QI1 bearer to be considered a candidate for adding a SCell.

This parameter indicates the minimum time a UE must meet the SINR threshold defined by NRCELL.ulCaMinPCellSinr or NRCELL.ulCaMinPCellSinr5qi1 on PCell before it can be considered a candidate for adding a SCell.

Parameter name: UL Configured Grant Type 2 Set Up
Description: This structure gathers parameters relating to UL configured grants type 2

Parameter name: Maximum GBR and configured grant type 2 traffic limit
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum percentage of radio resources that can used for GBR and configured grant type 2 in uplink from total available radio resources available for both non-GBR and GBR.  It corresponds to the percentage of radio resources that are available for GBR transmissions from the PUSCH resources. PUCCH and PRACH resources are not controlled by this parameter.

Parameter name: Maximum number of PRBs for configured grant type 2
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of PRBs for configured grant type 2 for the cell

Parameter name: Maximum number of CG scheduled users per slot
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of uplink configured grants scheduled users per slot for the cell
This parameter indicates the CG PRB pool start offset for the cell

This parameter indicates the DMRS additional position for PUSCH.    The supported values are:  - 0 (No additional DMRS) meaning the PUSCH DMRS additional position equals to 0 whether the UE has the UL PTRS capability or not,  - 1 (One additional DMRS) meaning the PUSCH DMRS additional position equals to 1 whether the UE has the UL PTRS capability or not,  - 2 (Two additional DMRS) meaning the PUSCH DMRS additional position equals to 2 whether the UE has the UL PTRS capability or not,  - 255 (Automatic) meaning the PUSCH DMRS additional position is controlled by the gNB based on the UE capability:  ** If NRCELL.actHighSpeedCell is equal to FALSE, then the PUSCH DMRS additional position is equal to 0 if the UE has the UL PTRS capability, otherwise it is equal to 1.  ** If NRCELL.actHighSpeedCell is equal to TRUE, then the PUSCH DMRS additional position is equal to 1 if the UE has the UL PTRS capability, otherwise it is equal to 2.    Note: Setting PUSCH DMRS additional position to 0 (No additional DMRS) might highly decrease the performance for high frequency offset scenario for UE without PTRS capability. Higher frequency offset is expected with higher UE clock error, and/or higher UE mobility velocity.
Range and step: No additional DMRS (0), One additional DMRS (1), Two additional DMRS (2), Automatic (255)

Description: This parameter gathers parameters for uplink data and DMRS FDM (frequency domain multiplexing).

Parameter name: Activate uplink data and DMRS FDM
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates uplink data and DMRS FDM.

Parameter name: Uplink data and DMRS FDM threshold 256QAM MCS
Description: This parameter indicates the MCS threshold for 256QAM MCS table to enable uplink data and DMRS FDM in runtime packet scheduling.  Uplink data and DMRS FDM could be enabled for CP-OFDM if the MCS used in PUSCH is higher or equal to this parameter. If DFT-s-OFDM is used, then FDM for uplink data and DMRS is disabled for all MCS indices.    Note: The threshold is only a precondition to use data and DMRS FDM. It just makes sure no data and DMRS FDM for MCS lower than this parameter. It does not mean data and DMRS FDM must be used when MCS is higher or equal to the threshold.  The gNB has the flexibility to decide whether data and DMRS FDM need to be used when MCS is higher or equal to the threshold.

Parameter name: Uplink data and DMRS FDM MCS threshold for 64QAM low SE MCS table
Description: This parameter indicates the MCS threshold for 64QAM low SE MCS table to enable uplink data and DMRS FDM in runtime packet scheduling.

Parameter name: Uplink data and DMRS FDM threshold 64QAM MCS
Description: This parameter indicates the MCS threshold for 64QAM MCS table to enable uplink data and DMRS FDM in runtime packet scheduling.  Uplink data and DMRS FDM could be enabled for CP-OFDM if the MCS used in PUSCH is higher or equal to this parameter. If DFT-s-OFDM is used, then FDM for uplink data and DMRS is disabled for all MCS indices.    Note: The threshold is only a precondition to use data and DMRS FDM. It just makes sure no data and DMRS FDM for MCS lower than this parameter. It does not mean data and DMRS FDM must be used when MCS is higher or equal to the threshold.  The gNB has the flexibility to decide whether data and DMRS FDM need to be used when MCS is higher or equal to the threshold.

Parameter name: Uplink limited MCS step up size BLER
Description: This parameter indicates the target BLER used in the computation of the step up size when ACKs are received for limited uplink MCS downgrade.

Parameter name: Enable UL buffer based MCS and PRB reduction or enhanced UL LA for buffer based MCS downgrade for high reliability
Description: This parameter enables/disables UL buffer based MCS and PRB reduction or enhanced UL link adaptation for buffer based MCS downgrade for high reliability.    The possible values are:  - 'disabled' meaning the UL buffer based MCS and PRB reduction for high reliability is disabled.  - 'enabled' meaning the UL buffer based MCS and PRB reduction for high reliability is enabled.  - 'enhanced' meaning the UL buffer based MCS and PRB reduction and the enhanced UL link adaptation for buffer based MCS downgrade for high reliability are enabled.
This parameter indicates the maximum MCS reduction allowed when performing an uplink MCS downgrade.
This parameter selects the UL MIMO mode for the PUSCH.
Range and step: Closed loop Spatial Multiplexing (2x2) (20), Closed loop Spatial Multiplexing (4x4) (40)

Parameter name: UL minimum TBS size for VoNR UEs
Description: This parameter indicates the UL minimum TBS size for voice packets of VoNR UEs with 5QI1 DRB configured.  This minimum TBS size, especially for cell-edge VoNR UEs, is to avoid end-to-end packet loss due to too much of segmentation. Segmentation involves lesser SINR requirements due to smaller TB sizes, but also causes additional overhead while transmission which corresponds to a considerable percentage of the TBS considering the usually small data packets in VoNR UEs. More HARQs used would mean more transmissions, and if there are segment losses in between, the entire packet is lost as there is no RLC level retransmissions.    The recommended values with respect to NRCELL.cellTechnology:  - If NRCELL.cellTechnology is equal to 'TDD': 168 and 208  - If NRCELL.cellTechnology is equal to 'FDD': 168, 176, 184, 208 and 224
This parameter defines the profile for uplink power control

Parameter name: Activate UL open loop power control
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates UL open loop power control for the cell

This parameter defines alpha. Alpha defines possible values of the pathloss compensation coefficient for uplink power control. al0 corresponds to 0, al04 corresponds to value 0.4, al05 to 0.5, al06 to 0.6, al07 to 0.7, al08 to 0.8, al09 to 0.9 and al1 corresponds to 1.    The recommended configuration is to have NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.p0NominalPusch equal to NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.p0NominalSrs and NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.alpha equal to NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.alphaSrs to ensure the same power level and target similar interference level on both channels. Configuration of those parameters has an impact on rank 1 throughput for 2Tx capable UEs. Refer to NRCELL.ulSinrSourceForRank1SUMimo.

This parameter defines alpha SRS. alpha0 corresponds to 0, alpha04 corresponds to value 0.4, alpha05 to 0.5, alpha06 to 0.6, alpha07 to 0.7, alpha08 to 0.8, alpha09 to 0.9 and alpha1 corresponds to 1.    The recommended configuration is to have NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.p0NominalPusch equal to NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.p0NominalSrs and NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.alpha equal to NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.alphaSrs to ensure the same power level and target similar interference level on both channels. Configuration of those parameters has an impact on rank 1 throughput for 2Tx capable UEs. Refer to NRCELL.ulSinrSourceForRank1SUMimo.
Range and step: alpha0 (0), alpha04 (1), alpha05 (2), alpha06 (3), alpha07 (4), alpha08 (5), alpha09 (6), alpha1 (7)

Description: This parameter indicates the nominal UL UE transmit power for transmission on PUCCH.

This parameter indicates the nominal UL UE transmit power for transmission on PUCCH format 1 and format 3.  It corresponds to the 3GPP parameter p0-NominalPUCCH in 38.213 chapter 7.2.1, which defines the UE's transmission power. It replaces NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.p0NominalPucch if NRCELL.pucchModeSelect is equal to 1 (corresponding to longPucch)

This parameter indicates the P0 value for PUSCH with grant (except msg3).    The recommended configuration is to have NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.p0NominalPusch equal to NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.p0NominalSrs and NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.alpha equal to NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.alphaSrs to ensure the same power level and target similar interference level on both channels. Configuration of those parameters has an impact on rank 1 throughput for 2Tx capable UEs. Refer to NRCELL.ulSinrSourceForRank1SUMimo.

This parameter defines the value of P0NominalSrs.  It is used for SRS power control.    The recommended configuration is to have NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.p0NominalPusch equal to NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.p0NominalSrs and NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.alpha equal to NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.alphaSrs to ensure the same power level and target similar interference level on both channels. Configuration of those parameters has an impact on rank 1 throughput for 2Tx capable UEs. Refer to NRCELL.ulSinrSourceForRank1SUMimo.
This parameter indicates the P0 value for PUSCH with grant (except msg3) for the UE.  Note: This parameter applies only to FR1 FDD-TDD UL CA.

This parameter indicates the transmit power offset for PUCCH format 1.  It corresponds to the 3GPP parameter deltaF-PUCCH in 38.213 chapter 7.2.1, which defines the UE's transmission power.  The UE applies this parameter whenever PUCCH format 1 is transferred.

This parameter indicates the transmit power offset for PUCCH format 3.  It corresponds to the 3GPP parameter deltaF-PUCCH in 38.213 chapter 7.2.1, which defines the UE's transmission power.  The UE applies this parameter whenever PUCCH format 3 is transferred.

This parameter indicates the duration time for uplink proactive grants.  It is only applicable for UEs that are configured for DRX.    The gNB stops uplink proactive grants after expiry of this duration time.    If this parameter is not configured, then the behavior is the same as if this parameter were configured with its Default Value.    If this parameter is equal to 0, then UL proactive scheduling is not stopped for DRX UEs at all, and UL proactive payload size is taken from NRCELL.payloadSizeProactiveNonDrx (as if it was non DRX UE).

Parameter name: UL proactive grant timer for skippable UL transmission
Description: This parameter indicates the duration time for uplink proactive grants sent to UEs configured for skipping UL transmission. Additionally, those UEs are required to be also configured for DRX.    The gNB stops skippable uplink proactive grants after expiry of this timer.    This parameter is the equivalent version of NRCELL.ulProGrantTimer, which is used for UEs configured for DRX but are not configured for skipping UL transmission.    If the value of that timer is equal to 0, then UL proactive scheduling is not stopped for DRX UEs configured for skipping UL transmission at all.
This parameter gathers parameters for uplink PTRS.

This parameter activates/deactivates uplink PTRS for both CP-OFDM and DFT-s-OFDM.  When this parameter is equal to FALSE, uplink PTRS is not configured to the UE.  When this parameter is equal to TRUE, uplink PTRS is configured to the UE which has uplink PTRS capability.

Parameter name: Uplink PTRS frequency density threshold NRB0
Description: This parameter indicates the uplink PTRS frequency density threshold NRB0 (see 3GPP TS 38.214 chapter 6.2.3 and 3GPP TS 38.331) in order to set the value for the frequency density Kpt-rs.  - Values in the range 1...276 correspond to the configured number of PRBs for NRB0.  - 277 means frequency density Kpt-rs is not configured in PTRS-UplinkConfig.  - 278 means the gNB selected uplink PTRS frequency density values (both NRB0 and NBR1) are used for uplink PTRS frequency density configuration.  - 279 means the UE recommended uplink PTRS frequency density values (both NRB0 and NRB1) included in UE capability report are used for uplink PTRS frequency density configuration. If the UE does not report selected uplink PTRS frequency density values, then the gNB recommended uplink PTRS frequency density values are used instead, i.e. as behavior as if this parameter is equal to 278.

Parameter name: Uplink PTRS frequency density threshold NRB1
Description: This parameter indicates the uplink PTRS frequency density threshold NRB1 (see 3GPP TS 38.214 chap 6.2.3 and 3GPP TS 38.331) in order to set the value for the frequency density Kpt-rs.  Values in the range 1...276 correspond to the configured number of PRBs for NRB1.
This structure gathers parameters for uplink PTRS with transform precoding (when enabled for a UE)

Parameter name: Uplink PTRS sample density threshold NRB0 for transform precoding
Description: This parameter indicates the uplink PTRS sample density threshold NRB0 (see 3GPP TS 38.214 chapter 6.2.3.2 and 3GPP TS 38.331) in order to set the value for the sample density when UL PTRS for transform precoding is configured for a UE.    The following values are supported:  - Values in the range 1...276 corresponding to the configured number of PRBs for NRB0. In that case, the sample density thresholds are set based on this parameter, NRCELL.ulPtrsForTransPrecoding.ulPtrsSampleDensityThresNrb1, NRCELL.ulPtrsForTransPrecoding.ulPtrsSampleDensityThresNrb2, NRCELL.ulPtrsForTransPrecoding.ulPtrsSampleDensityThresNrb3 and NRCELL.ulPtrsForTransPrecoding.ulPtrsSampleDensityThresNrb4.  - 277 means the gNB selects sample density thresholds  - 278 means the sample density thresholds are derived from the UE capabilities if provided, else gNB selects them

Parameter name: Uplink PTRS sample density threshold NRB1 for transform precoding
Description: This parameter indicates the uplink PTRS sample density threshold NRB1 (see 3GPP TS 38.214 chapter 6.2.3.2 and 3GPP TS 38.331) in order to set the value for the sample density when UL PTRS for transform precoding is configured for a UE.  Values in the range 1...276 correspond to the configured number of PRBs for NRB1.

Parameter name: Uplink PTRS sample density threshold NRB2 for transform precoding
Description: This parameter indicates the uplink PTRS sample density threshold NRB2 (see 3GPP TS 38.214 chapter 6.2.3.2 and 3GPP TS 38.331) in order to set the value for the sample density when UL PTRS for transform precoding is configured for a UE.  Values in the range 1...276 correspond to the configured number of PRBs for NRB2.

Parameter name: Uplink PTRS sample density threshold NRB3 for transform precoding
Description: This parameter indicates the uplink PTRS sample density threshold NRB3 (see 3GPP TS 38.214 chapter 6.2.3.2 and 3GPP TS 38.331) in order to set the value for the sample density when UL PTRS for transform precoding is configured for a UE.  Values in the range 1...276 correspond to the configured number of PRBs for NRB3.

Parameter name: Uplink PTRS sample density threshold NRB4 for transform precoding
Description: This parameter indicates the uplink PTRS sample density threshold NRB4 (see 3GPP TS 38.214 chapter 6.2.3.2 and 3GPP TS 38.331) in order to set the value for the sample density when UL PTRS for transform precoding is configured for a UE.  Values in the range 1...276 correspond to the configured number of PRBs for NRB4.

Parameter name: UL rank1 to rank2 switch threshold for average rank
Description: This parameter indicates the UL average rank value over which the UL rank1 to rank2 change occurs for the next initial transmission.    Notes:  - If NRCELL.actUlDftSOfdm is equal to FALSE, then this parameter is ignored and the system applies the SW default behavior.  - NRCELL.ulRank1to2Thresh shall be greater than NRCELL.ulRank2to1Thresh to ensure some hysteresis in order to avoid ping-pong switching.

Parameter name: UL rank2 to rank1 switch threshold for average rank
Description: This parameter indicates the UL average rank value over which the UL rank2 to rank1 change occurs for the next initial transmission.    Notes:  - If NRCELL.actUlDftSOfdm is equal to FALSE, then this parameter is ignored and the system applies the SW default behavior.  - NRCELL.ulRank1to2Thresh shall be greater than NRCELL.ulRank2to1Thresh to ensure some hysteresis in order to avoid ping-pong switching.
This parameter indicates the targeted time interval for proactive UL resource assignment for each connected user.

Parameter name: UL scheduling interval for skippable UL transmission
Description: This parameter indicates the targeted time interval for proactive UL resource assignment for each connected user that are configured for skipping UL transmission.    This timer is the equivalent version of NRCELL.ulSchedTimeInterval, which is used for UEs that are not configured for skipping UL transmission.

Parameter name: UL SINR source in link adaptation for rank1 SU MIMO
Description: This parameter indicates the UL SINR source in link adaptation for rank1 SU MIMO transmission.    For 2Tx capable UEs, this parameter provides the SINR source to select MCS for the next initial transmission in rank1 for uplink single user MIMO . The SINR source for link adaptation is either SRS (predicted SINR with best PMI for next transmission) or PUSCH (received SINR for PMI scheduled in current transmission).    This parameter has an impact on the UL features with UL SU MIMO such as those listed in Related Features.  The recommended configuration is to have NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.p0NominalPusch equal to NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.p0NominalSrs and NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.alpha equal to NRCELL.ulPowerControlCommon.alphaSrs to ensure the same power level and target similar interference level on both channels. Configuration of those parameters has an impact on rank 1 throughput for 2Tx capable UEs.    For 1Tx capable UEs (as per UE capabilities check), this parameter is not used, SINR source for link adaptation is always PUSCH.
This structure gathers parameters to control uplink transform precoder and PUSCH slot aggregation (when enabled for a UE).

Parameter name: Uplink threshold for disabling transform precoder and PUSCH slot aggregation for a UE
Description: If  - the UE is currently configured for DFT-s-OFDM and  - the total power of the UE is greater than or equal to the value in this parameter,  then the UE is configured with PUSCH transform precoding disabled (CP OFDM) and is no longer eligible for PUSCH slot aggregation.    Total power of the UE refers to the SINR of UE over all PRBs allocated to the UE.

Parameter name: Uplink threshold for enabling transform precoder and PUSCH slot aggregation for a UE
Description: If  - the UE is currently configured for CP OFDM and  - the total power of the UE is below the value in this parameter,  then the UE is configured with PUSCH transform precoding enabled (DFT-s-OFDM) and is eligible for repetitions greater than 1 for PUSCH slot aggregation.    Total power of the UE refers to the SINR of UE over all PRBs allocated to the UE.

Parameter name: Use of power boost for pi/2-BPSK with uplink transform precoding
Description: This parameter indicates if the use of power boost with pi/2-BPSK is enabled for UEs which support it.  If it is equal to TRUE and NRCELL.ulTransPrecodeCtl.ulTransPrecodePi2Bpsk is equal to TRUE and the UE capabilities, then this indicates the support of pi/2-BPSK power boost and TDD with power boost bands per 3GPP (use power boost for pi/2-BPSK), else power boost for pi/2-BPSK is not used.

Parameter name: Uplink threshold for disabling transform precoder for RedCap UEs
Description: This parameter is used to set up SINR threshold when gNB switches from DFT-s-OFDM to CP-OFDM modulation on PUSCH for RedCap UEs.

Parameter name: Uplink threshold for disabling transform precoder for a UE
Description: If  - DFT-s-OFDM for PUSCH is activated (i.e. if NRCELL.actUlDftSOfdm is equal to TRUE) and  - the UE is currently configured for DFT-s-OFDM and  - the measured SINR of the UE is greater than or equal to the value in this parameter,  then the UE is configured with PUSCH transform precoding disabled (CP OFDM)

Parameter name: Uplink threshold for disabling PUSCH transform precoder for a UE
Description: If  - DFT-s-OFDM for PUSCH is activated (i.e. if NRCELL.actUlDftSOfdm is equal to TRUE) and NRBTS.actUlTransPreEnhSinrMetric is equal to true and  - the UE is currently configured for DFT-s-OFDM and  - the total power of the UE is greater than or equal to the value in this parameter,then the UE is configured with PUSCH transformprecoding disabled (CP OFDM)

Parameter name: Uplink threshold for disabling PUSCH transform precoder for a RedCap UE
Description: If  - DFT-s-OFDM for PUSCH is activated (i.e. if NRCELL.actUlDftSOfdm is equal to TRUE) and NRBTS- actUlTransPreEnhSinrMetric is equal to true and  - the RedCap UE is currently configured for DFT-s-OFDM and  - the total power of the RedCap UE is greater than or equal to the value in this parameter,then the RedCap UE is configured with PUSCH transformprecoding disabled (CP OFDM)

Parameter name: Uplink threshold for enabling transform precoder for RedCap UEs
Description: This parameter is used to set up SINR threshold when gNB switches from CP-OFDM to DFT-s-OFDM modulation on PUSCH for RedCap UEs.

Parameter name: Uplink threshold for enabling transform precoder for a UE
Description: If  - DFT-s-OFDM for PUSCH is activated (i.e. if NRCELL.actUlDftSOfdm is equal to TRUE) and  - the UE is currently configured for CP OFDM and  - the measured SINR of the UE is below the value in this parameter,  then the UE is configured with PUSCH transform precoding enabled (DFT-s-OFDM)

Parameter name: Uplink threshold for enabling PUSCH transform precoder for a UE
Description: If  - DFT-s-OFDM for PUSCH is activated (i.e. if NRCELL.actUlDftSOfdm is equal to TRUE) and and NRBTS- actUlTransPreEnhSinrMetric is equal to true and  - the UE is currently configured for DFT-s-OFDM and  - the total power of the UE is below the value in this parameter,then the UE is configured with PUSCH transform precoder denabled (DFT-s-OFDM)

Parameter name: Uplink threshold for enabling PUSCH transform precoder for a RedCap UE
Description: If  - DFT-s-OFDM for PUSCH is activated (i.e. if NRCELL.actUlDftSOfdm is equal to TRUE) and and NRBTS- actUlTransPreEnhSinrMetric is equal to true and  - the RedCap UE is currently configured for DFT-s-OFDM and  - the total power of the RedCap UE is below the value in this parameter,then the RedCap UE is configured with PUSCH transform precoder denabled (DFT-s-OFDM)

Parameter name: Use of pi/2-BPSK for MCS0 and 1 with uplink transform precoder enabled
Description: This parameter indicates if the use of pi/2-BPSK for MCS0 and 1 with uplink transform precoder is enabled for UEs which support it.  If it is equal to TRUE and the UE capabilities indicates the support of pi/2-BPSK (use pi/2-BPSK), then 'q'=1 for transform precoder MCS range 0...1, else use 'q'=2 (QPSK).
This parameter indicates the target Block Error Ratio (BLER) of initial uplink transmissions for UL Outer Loop Link Adaptation in percent

Parameter name: Delta SINR maximum of UL OLLA
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum value of the SINR offset

Parameter name: Delta SINR minimum of UL OLLA
Description: This parameter indicates the minimum value of the SINR offset

Parameter name: Delta SINR Stepdown of UL OLLA
Description: This parameter indicates the size of the delta SINR step down in OLLA for a NACK.
This parameter indicates the default MCS for UL transmissions  The default MCS is applied as long as SINR reports are missing or when the SINR reports are outdated.

Parameter name: Specific initial UL BLER target for VoNR DRBs
Description: This parameter indicates the specific initial UL BLER target value for VoNR DRBs.

Parameter name: Upper MCS threshold for power backoff
Description: The parameter indicates the upper threshold of MCS for the power back-off algorithm.

Parameter name: Voice over New Radio Discontinuous Reception Transmission distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the associated NRDRX instance for VoNR DRB. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRDRX-2  NRDRX-2
This parameter indicates which fallback mode is used for the normal voice call

This parameter indicates the amount of SR resource to be reserved in the SR pool set as the preferred one for voice over NR (VoNR).    Reservation is done as a percentage of the total capacity of the preferred SR pool.    Those resources, even reserved for VoNR, can be used also by other services as a last resort.
This structure gathers parameters for wideband/sub-band beamforming switch measurement configuration.

This parameter indicates the hysteresis based on NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.channelStabilityThreshold for the evaluation of release sub-band beamforming.  The evaluation sample with channel stability factor lower than (NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.channelStabilityThreshold - this parameter) can be seen as a bad sample and contributing to release of sub-band beamforming.  Values close to 0 are not recommended.  If this parameter is greater than or equal to NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.channelStabilityThreshold, channel stability factor will not trigger the sub-band beamforming release.

This parameter indicates the threshold for channel stability for the evaluation of sub-band beamforming configuration.  The evaluation sample with channel stability factor greater than or equal to this parameter can be seen as a good sample and contributing to sub-band beamforming configuration.

This parameter indicates whether volatility metric is used for the evaluation of sub-band beamforming configuration.  The UE can experience a RRC reconfiguration back to wide band beamforming mode a short time after being configured with SRS for sub-band beamforming as the accuracy of volatility measure in sub-band beamforming mode is much more reliable.

Parameter name: Maximum wideband and sub-band SRS switch
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum wideband (WB) and SB SRS switch times for a UE within 30 seconds before the UE be constrained from having WB SRS configured again.  If a UE has WB and SB SRS switch more than NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.maxWbSbSwitch times within 30 seconds, the UE will be constrained from configuring WB SRS for a long time. The gNB also has WB and SB SRS toggle detection and internal protection that will also lead to a UE be constrained. This functionality will not block WB SRS to be released but only to be configured with WB SRS again.

Parameter name: Number of samples for sub-band beamforming configuration
Description: This parameter indicates how many times the radio quality buffer is checked for the evaluation of sub-band beamforming configuration.

Parameter name: Number of sub-band beamforming release samples
Description: This parameter indicates how many times the radio quality buffer is checked for the evaluation of releasing sub-band beamforming configuration.

This parameter indicates the hysteresis based on NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.prbRatioThreshold for the evaluation of releasing sub-band beamforming configuration.  The evaluation sample with PRB ratio lower than (NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.prbRatioThreshold - this parameter) is seen as a low PRB ratio sample and contribute for the evaluation sub-band beamforming release.  Values close to 1 are not recommended.  If this parameter is greater than or equal to NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.prbRatioThreshold, the PRB ratio will not trigger the sub-band beamforming release.

This parameter indicates the minimum ratio of scheduled PRB versus the number of valid PRB for the evaluation of sub-band beamforming configuration.  Its value will impact the maximum number of subband BF UEs in parallel in static traffic mode.  Note: in multi BWP, RAT0/RAT1 co-exist and in some scenarios, the PRB ratio of all UEs in the same slot may not reach 100%.

Parameter name: PRB sample high or low percentage
Description: This parameter indicates the percentage of PRB ratio samples that meet the high PRB ratio threshold within NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.numWbSrsConfigSample or low PRB ratio threshold within NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.numWbSrsReleaseSample.    It is best to avoid values around 50 because both sub-band beamforming configuration and release adopt this percentage threshold; in this case, values around 50 may trigger ping-pong switch if the high/low PRB ratio threshold hysteresis (NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.prbRatioHysteresis) is configured with a small enough value.

This parameter indicates the hysteresis based on NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.rankThreshold for the evaluation of release sub-band beamforming configuration.  The evaluation sample with DL rank lower than (NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.rankThreshold - this parameter) can be seen as a bad sample and contribute for release wideband SRS.  If it is greater than or equal to (NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.rankThreshold - 1), rank factor will not trigger sub-band beamforming release.

This parameter indicates the threshold for rank for the evaluation of sub-band beamforming configuration.  The evaluation sample with DL rank greater than or equal to this parameter can be seen as a good sample and contribute for sub-band beamforming configuration.

This parameter indicates the percentage of bad radio link quality samples after NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.numWbSrsReleaseSample.  Values close to 100 - NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.rlqGoodPercentage are not recommended to avoid ping-pong switch.
This parameter indicates the percentage of good radio link quality samples after NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.numWbSrsConfigSample.

This parameter indicates the hysteresis based on NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.seThreshold for the evaluation of release sub-band beamforming configuration.  The evaluation sample with DL spectral efficiency lower than (NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.seThreshold - this parameter) can be seen as a bad sample and contribute for releasing sub-band beamforming configuration.  Values close to 0 are not recommended.  If this parameter is greater than or equal to NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.seThreshold, the DL spectral efficiency factor will not trigger the sub-band beamforming release. Note: The DL spectral efficiency factor may also not trigger the sub-band beamforming releasing if (NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.seThreshold - this parameter) is equal to a very small positive value.

This parameter indicates the threshold for spectral efficiency for the evaluation of sub-band beamforming configuration.  If this parameter is greater than the maximum possible DL spectral efficiency (29.625), the UEs will not be selected for sub-band beamforming. Note: The UEs may also not be selected for wideband SRS, if (the maximum possible DL spectral efficiency - this parameter) is equal to a very small positive value or 0.
This parameter indicates which metric will be used for the priority of achieving sub-band beamforming.
Range and step: DL Spectral Efficiency (0), WB SRS power (1)

Description: This parameter indicates the timer for the gNB to prohibit configuring sub-band beamforming immediately after wide band beamforming is configured.

Parameter name: SRS for sub-band beamforming quality hysteresis
Description: This parameter indicates the hysteresis for SRS power based on NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.wbSrsPowerThreshold for the evaluation of releasing sub-band beamforming configuration.  UEs with the SRS power factor lower than (NRCELL.wbSbSrsSwitch.wbSrsPowerThreshold - this parameter) in dB can be selected for releasing sub-band beamforming configuration.  The smaller the value is, the greater possibility of having ping-pong switch occur.

Parameter name: SRS for sub-band beamforming power threshold
Description: This parameter indicates the power threshold for the evaluation of sub-band beamforming configuration.  The SRS power is estimated based on SB SRS covariance matrix so that its value has some gap with real SRS power. To avoid real SRS power being lower than sub-band BF validation threshold (NRCELL.srsForSubbandBm.srsPowerThreshold) after sub-band beamforming is configured based on covariance matrix power, a protection gap shall be added.

Parameter name: SRS for sub-band beamforming release prohibiting timer
Description: This parameter indicates the timer for the gNB to prohibit releasing SRS immediately after sub-band beamforming is configured.

Parameter name: Weight factor of the cell for secondary cell selection
Description: This parameter indicates the weight factor of the cell for secondary cell selection.  The higher value of the parameter means the higher probability for the cell to be selected as secondary cell.
This parameter indicates the weight factor of the PS cell for SgNB addition.  The higher value of the parameter means the higher probability for the cell to be selected.

Parameter name: Weight ratio of UE split power on SCell versus PCell
Description: This parameter defines a weight ratio of UE split power in uplink overlapping slots on SCell versus on PCell for a UE configured with FR1 uplink CA in over power state.    If configured to value X, the meaning is that the weight ratio of UE split power in uplink overlapping slots on SCell versus on PCell for a UE configured with FR1 uplink CA in over power state is X.  In case more UE power is expected to be allocated to PCell, a smaller value below 1 need be set, and in case more UE power is expected to be allocated to SCell, a bigger value above 1 need be set.
Range and step: WeightRatio 0.01 (1), WeightRatio 0.02 (2), WeightRatio 0.05 (5), WeightRatio 0.1 (10), WeightRatio 0.2 (20), WeightRatio 0.5 (50), WeightRatio 1 (100), WeightRatio 2 (200), WeightRatio 5 (500), WeightRatio 10 (1000), WeightRatio 20 (2000), WeightRatio 50 (5000), WeightRatio 100 (10000)

Description: This parameter defines the zero correlation zone configuration.

Parameter name: New Radio Cell Group instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Cell Group (NRCELLGRP) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.

Parameter name: Activate the higher amount of RRC connections in FR2
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the high amount of RRC connections in FR2 cell.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE, then it will allow more number of UEs to be connected on the cell.
This parameter activates/deactivates the load based CSI reporting periodicity in the NR CellGroup.    Note: This parameter is frozen; it can only be set to FALSE.
This parameter activates/deactivates NACK/DTX flood detection.    The recommended value for this parameter is  - FALSE if NRCELL.nrarfcn <= 800000 (FR1),  - TRUE if NRCELL.nrarfcn >= 2016667 (FR2)

Parameter name: Activate the beam constraint per PUCCH symbol in FR2
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the analog beam constraint per PUCCH symbol in FR2.  If this parameter is enabled for analog beamforming, the constraint of single beam per PUCCH symbol shall be enforced in FR2.

Parameter name: Additional number of user capacity for handovers
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for the additional number of UEs in addition to maxNumOfUsers in the DU for handovers for NSA operation. This parameter is used by the radio admission control in the CU and the DU.

Parameter name: Additional number of non-GBR data radio bearers in a New Radio Cell Group for SA handovers
Description: This parameter indicates the additional number of non-GBR data radio bearers of active UEs in the New Radio Cell Group for SA handovers.  This parameter is used by the radio admission control in the gNB-CU and the gNB-DU.

Parameter name: Additional number of non-GBR capacity for handovers
Description: This parameter indicates the additional number of non-GBR data radio bearers of active UEs operating in NSA mode 3x per 5G cell group for handovers. This parameter is used by the radio admission control in the CU and the DU.

Parameter name: Additional number of RRC connected users in a New Radio cell for SA handover
Description: This parameter indicates the additional number of RRC connected UEs in the New Radio Cell Group for SA handovers.  This parameter is used by the radio admission control in the gNB-CU and the gNB-DU.

Parameter name: Beam index list for artificial load
Description: This parameter defines which beams are used for the artificial PDSCH load. Beams are identified by beam index.    If this parameter is not configured, then all beams are considered.    Artificial load is always transmitted on one beam at a time. If multiple beams are considered, the beam is selected randomly in each slot.

This parameter is used to select the grid of beams used in beamforming. Supported values are the following:  - ABFG90 : ABF Grid width 90 degrees  - ABFG90DT : ABF Grid width 90 degrees, grid downtilted,  - ABFG120 : ABF Grid width 120 degrees,  - ABFG120DT : ABF Grid width 120 degrees, downtilted  in which ABF stands for 'Analog beamforming'. These values only effect analog beamforming.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Load Based Csi Periodicity increase Threshold
Description: This parameter indicates the amount of PUCCH F2 available resources to be allocated with the operator configured CSI periodicity (NRCELL.periodicCsiAcquisition.csiReportPeriodicity). The remaining resources will be allocated with the highest supported CSI periodicity.

Parameter name: Maximum number of DL HARQ transmissions
Description: This parameter defines the maximum number of DL Transmission. This number contains the initial transmission + n-1 retransmissions.
This parameter defines the maximum number of RACH Msg3 (UL, contains i.e. RRC Connection Request message) transmissions. The number contains the initial transmission + n-1 retransmissions.

Parameter name: Maximum number of non-GBR data radio bearers
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of non-GBR data radio bearers of active UEs operating in NSA mode 3x in the NR Cell Group.

Parameter name: Maximum number of non-GBR data radio bearers in New Radio Cell Group for SA
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of non-GBR data radio bearers of active UEs operating in the New Radio Cell Group for SA.  This parameter is used by the radio admission control in the gNB-CU and the gNB-DU.

Parameter name: Maximum number of non-GBR data radio bearers in an NR cell group for NR-DC-SN operation
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of non-GBR data radio bearers of active UEs operating in NR-DC-SN in the NR cell group.  This parameter is used by the radio admission control in the gNB-CU and the gNB-DU. It is applicable only for PSCell users.

Parameter name: Maximum number of users in an NR cell group for NR-DC-SN operation
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of users in the New Radio cell group which may establish SCG connection for NR-DC operation.  The number of users is the sum of the NR-DC-SN PSCell allocations and the NR-DC-SN DL SCell allocations.  This parameter is used by the radio admission control in the CU.

Parameter name: Maximum number of RRC connected users in a New Radio Cell Group for SA
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for the maximum number of RRC connected UEs in the New Radio Cell Group for SA.  This parameter is used by the radio admission control in the gNB-CU and the gNB-DU.

Parameter name: Maximum number of users in a NR Cell Group for NSA operation
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for the maximum number of users in the NR Cell Group which may establish SCG connection for NSA operation.  The number of users is the sum of the NSA PsCell allocations and the DL secondary cell allocations.  This parameter is used by the radio admission control in the CU and the DU.

Parameter name: Maximum number of UL HARQ transmissions
Description: This parameter defines the maximum number of UL Transmission. This number contains the initial transmission + n-1 retransmissions.

Parameter name: NACK and DTX flood detection algorithm configuration table
Description: This parameter gathers NACK and DTX flood detection algorithm configuration parameters for FR1 and FR2

Parameter name: Data flow resume threshold on FR1
Description: This parameter indicates the data flow resume threshold on FR1.    If NRCELLGRP.actNackDtxFloodControlDetection is equal to 0 (corresponding to FALSE), this parameter is ignored.

Parameter name: Data flow resume threshold on FR2
Description: This parameter indicates the data flow resume threshold on FR2.    If NRCELLGRP.actNackDtxFloodControlDetection is equal to FALSE, this parameter is ignored.

Parameter name: NACK and DTX flood forgetting ratio on FR1
Description: This parameter indicates the NACK and DTX flood forgetting ratio on FR1.    If NRCELLGRP.actNackDtxFloodControlDetection is equal to FALSE, this parameter is ignored.

Parameter name: NACK and DTX flood forgetting ratio on FR2
Description: This parameter indicates the NACK and DTX flood forgetting ratio on FR2.    If NRCELLGRP.actNackDtxFloodControlDetection is equal to FALSE, this parameter is ignored.

Parameter name: Maximum NACK and DTX flood burst size on FR1
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum burst size of NACK and DTX on FR1.    If NRCELLGRP.actNackDtxFloodControlDetection is equal to FALSE, this parameter is ignored.

Parameter name: Maximum NACK and DTX flood burst size on FR2
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum burst size of NACK and DTX on FR2.    If NRCELLGRP.actNackDtxFloodControlDetection is equal to FALSE, this parameter is ignored.

Parameter name: Threshold for the number of active component carriers
Description: This parameter is the maximum threshold for the number of active component carriers per slot.  It will help to limit the number of active component carriers and allows to use new algorithms in case of gNB load to improve the number of RRC connections.

Parameter name: List of NR cells assigned to cell group
Description: This parameter defines the list of New Radio cells uniquely assigned to a cell group.  Cells in this list are assigned to a cell group and shall have the same frequency range for duplex mode and subcarrier spacing, and have the same geographical coverage area that is also called a sector.  For the FR2 frequency range, the analog beamforming is supported between cells in the same cell group.

Parameter name: Number of transmitted Synchronization Signal Blocks
Description: This parameter defines the number of transmitted Synchronization Signal Blocks.  It is set by the system automatically to the correct value if NRCELL.actSuperCell is equal to TRUE.
Range and step: 1 beam (1), 2 beams (2), 3 beams (3), 4 beams (4), 5 beams (5), 6 beams (6), 8 beams (8), 9 beams (9), 12 beams (12), 15 beams (15), 18 beams (18), 21 beams (21), 24 beams (24), 32 beams (32), 56 beams (56)

Description: The parameter specifies the old distinguished name of the managed object before a configuration change like rehosting. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter defines the code rate that can be used for PUCCH F2

This parameter indicates the subcarrier spacing value.    The configuration of this parameter during NRCELL and NRCELLGRP instance addition will not provoke a gNB reset.  The modification of this parameter will provoke a gNB reset.  The removal of this parameter during NRCELL and NRCELLGRP instance deletion will not provoke a gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter enables or disables SP-Cell change in the gNB-DU and in the gNB-CU in case the gNB-CU selected PS-Cell cannot be allocated by gNB-DU. In this case, the gNB-DU selects a new PS-Cell from the list predefined by the gNB-CU.    This parameter is not applicable for NR-DC.
This parameter indicates the synchronization signal burst set transmission period.

Parameter name: New Radio Cell FDD instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Cell FDD (NRCELL_FDD) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRCELL instance.
This parameter activates/deactivates guardband for asymmetric 20/10 MHz and 30/10MHz on n66 channel with inner guardband.

This parameter activates/deactivates  - O-RAN with O-RU for FDD in SRAN.  - O-RAN with O-RU for FDD in vDU RINLINE2.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition might provoke gNB reset - gNB takes decision of reset necessity.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.

Parameter name: Activate periodic CSI report bundling for FDD
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the periodic CSI report bundling for FDD

This parameter defines the downlink bandwidth for the gNB transmission in a cell. It is used (together with NRCELLGRP.scs) to compute the maximum number of Physical Resource Blocks according to 3GPP specification in 38.104.
