This parameter affects real center frequency and channel bandwidth which is not validated against radio module capabilities and misconfiguration can cause cell setup failures with fault '1900: RF Module configuring failed' raised.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition might provoke gNB reset - gNB takes decision of reset necessity.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter defines the uplink bandwidth for the gNB transmission in a cell. It is used (together with NRCELLGRP.scs) to compute the maximum number of Physical Resource Blocks according to 3GPP specification in 38.104.    Supplemental DL cells shall always have this parameter equal to '0MHz'.    This parameter affects real center frequency and channel bandwidth which is not validated against radio module capabilities and misconfiguration can cause cell setup failures with fault '1900: RF Module configuring failed' raised.    Configuring this parameter during cell addition might provoke gNB reset - gNB takes decision of reset necessity.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Massive MIMO horizontal sector beamforming profile
Description: This parameter indicates the massive MIMO horizontal sector beamforming profile

Parameter name: NR Absolute radio frequency channel number in downlink
Description: This parameter indicates the New Radio Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number in downlink.  The supported 5G NR Bands and related ARFCNs are those specified in 3GPP TS 38.104.    This parameter affects real center frequency and channel bandwidth which is not validated against radio module capabilities and misconfiguration can cause cell setup failures with fault '1900: RF Module configuring failed' raised.    Note: The frequency range supported by a particular Radio Unit shall be checked in the latest Customer Documentation file: 'Nokia AirScale Radio Units Description'    Configuring this parameter during cell addition might provoke gNB reset - gNB takes decision of reset necessity.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: NR Absolute radio frequency channel number in uplink
Description: This parameter indicates the New Radio Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number in uplink.  The supported 5G NR Bands and related ARFCNs are those specified in 3GPP TS 38.104.    This parameter affects real center frequency and channel bandwidth which is not validated against radio module capabilities and misconfiguration can cause cell setup failures with fault '1900: RF Module configuring failed' raised.    Note: The frequency range supported by a particular Radio Unit shall be checked in the latest Customer Documentation file: 'Nokia AirScale Radio Units Description'    Configuring this parameter during cell addition might provoke gNB reset - gNB takes decision of reset necessity.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: New Radio Connected Mode Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Connected Mode Profile (NRCONNECTMODE_PROFILE) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter indicates the list of alternative frequency band indicators NR.  When accessed from the current NR Cell for NSA, it can be used for finding an appropriate alternative band associated to the cell frequency during NSA call setup, if the native band cannot be used.  When accessed from current NR Cell for SA or NSA, it can be used for configuring the intra-frequency measurements with an appropriate alternative band associated with the frequency of the cell, when the native band cannot be used.  When accessed from a NRHOIF instance for SA or NSA, it is used for configuring the inter-frequency measurements with an appropriate alternative band associated with the NRHOIF.ssbFrequency, when the native band cannot be used.  When accessed from a NRADJNRCELL instance for SA or NSA, it is used to check the feasibility of a handover towards this adjacent cell with regard to the bands it supports.

Parameter name: New Radio Trace Control instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Trace Control (NRCTRLTS) instance within the same containing MRBTS/NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: New Radio CU-UP Trace Control instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio CU-UP Trace Control (NRCTRLTSCUUP) instance within the same containing MRBTS/NRBTS/NRCUUP instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: New Radio DU Trace Control instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio DU Trace Control (NRCTRLTSDU) instance within the same containing MRBTS/NRBTS/NRDU instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio CU-UP (NRCUUP) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter uniquely identifies the gNB-CU-UP. It is configured at the gNB-CU-UP. The parameter value is set in the E1AP: E1 Setup Request message sent by the gNB-CU-UP to the gNB-CU-CP over the E1 interface.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter defines a name for the gNB-CU-UP. It is configured at the gNB-CU-UP. The parameter value is set in the E1AP: E1 Setup Request message sent by the gNB-CU-UP to the gNB-CU-CP over the E1 interface.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter indicates the local CU-C IPv4/v6 address
This parameter defines the list of supported 5QIs by a particular gNB-CU-UP  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: List of QCI supported by CUUP
Description: This parameter defines the list of supported QCIs by a particular gNB-CU-UP  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter indicates the remote CU-U IPv4/v6 address

Parameter name: New Radio DL MU-MIMO instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio DL MU-MIMO (NRDLMUMIMO) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRCELL instance.

Parameter name: Activate exclusion of low DL buffer user from DL MU-MIMO pairing.
Description: This parameter activate/deactivate exclusion of low DL buffer user from DL MU-MIMO pairing.
This parameter activates/deactivates the MU aware TD scheduling feature.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates the correlation threshold for selecting MU candidates in the MU aware scheduling algorithm
This parameter indicates the PRB ratio for selecting MU candidates in the MU aware scheduling algorithm

Parameter name: DL MU maximum number of layers per PRB
Description: This parameter indicates the DL MU maximum number of layers per PRB when NRCELL.actRat1Alloc is equal to TRUE.

Parameter name: DL MU maximum number of layers per RBG
Description: This parameter indicates the DL MU maximum number of layers per RBG.

Parameter name: DL MU MIMO correlation threshold between paired UEs
Description: This parameter indicates the DL MU MIMO correlation threshold between paired UEs.

Parameter name: CQI threshold of DL MU MIMO eligible UEs
Description: This parameter indicates the CQI threshold of DL MU MIMO eligible UEs.

Parameter name: DL MU MIMO pairing rank adaptation
Description: This parameter indicates the DL MU MIMO pairing rank adaptation policy for pairing efficiency    The possible values are:  - disabled meaning rank adaption is disabled. The PDSCH rank of paired UEs are same as SU-MIMO.  - always meaning for each paired UE, rank adaption will always reduce UE's rank from 3 or 4 to rank 2.  - adaptive meaning for each paired UE, rank adaption will automatically reduce UE's rank from 3 or 4 to rank 2 based on downlink pairing status.

Parameter name: DL MU MIMO spectral efficiency threshold
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for the DL MU MIMO spectral efficiency ratio of pairing N+1 over pairing N.  When the threshold is set to 0, the DL MU-MIMO spectral efficiency checking is disabled.

Parameter name: DL MU MIMO horizontal tapering value
Description: This parameter indicates the horizontal DL MU MIMO beamforming tapering value in dB or NoTapering.

Parameter name: DL MU MIMO vertical tapering value
Description: This parameter indicates the vertical DL MU MIMO beamforming tapering value in dB or NoTapering.
This parameter indicates the PRB ratio for triggering the DL MU pairing algorithm

Parameter name: New Radio DRB Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the DRB Profile (NRDRB) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.  Instance with NRDRB.nrDrbId equal to 1 defines the default profile, which is applied when there is no matching NRDRB_5QI instance (for SA) or NRDRB_QCI instance (for NSA) for a non-GBR DRB.
This parameter activates/deactivates reduction of DDDS.    If NRCELLs with high loads are expected in configuration the recommended value for this parameter is TRUE.

Parameter name: Activate DL data transmission resume on reception of PDCP status report
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates resuming the transmission of DL data at the target only after the reception of the PDCP status report from the UE during PDCP Re-establishment and PDCP Data Recovery scenarios. This parameter is applicable for mobility, bearer type change, and bearer takeback scenarios.  This is to ensure minimal or no duplication of PDCP PDUs on resumption of DL transmission at target.

Parameter name: Activate fast retransmission for lost PDCP PDU
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates fast retransmission for lost PDCP PDU.

Parameter name: Activate optimized data flow rate estimate
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the optimized calculation of data flow rate estimation at RLC.    The recommended value for this parameter is TRUE if enhanced flow control based throughput estimation in corresponding cell is activated, i.e. NRCELL.actEnhancedFlowControlETh is equal to TRUE.

Parameter name: Allowed boosting ALs due to no available CCEs
Description: This parameter defines the allowed PDCCH power boosting aggregation level (AL) due to no available control channel elements (CCEs) for the expected AL.  This function takes effect when PDCCH power boost (actPdcchPowerBoost) is activated and PDCCH candidates with corresponding AL2 (numOfPdcchCandidatesinAl2) or AL4 (numOfPdcchCandidatesinAl4) configured.    e.g. if no available CCEs for AL8 and this parameter is configured to "AL4" or "AL2_AL4", then AL4 with 3dB PDCCH power boosting is applicable for the PDCCH allocation.    e.g. if no available CCEs for AL4 and this parameter is configured to "AL2" or "AL2 and AL4", then AL2 with 3dB PDCCH power boosting is applicable for the PDCCH allocation.

Parameter name: Allowed boosting ALs due to not configured
Description: This parameter defines the allowed PDCCH power boosting aggregation level (AL) due to the expected AL is not configured.  This function takes effect when PDCCH power boost (actPdcchPowerBoost) is activated and PDCCH candidates with corresponding AL2 (numOfPdcchCandidatesinAl2) or AL4 (numOfPdcchCandidatesinAl4) configured.    e.g. if AL8 is not configured (numOfPdcchCandidatesInAL8 is n0), and this parameter is configured to "AL4" or "AL2_AL4" and the allocated PDCCH is AL4, then 3dB PDCCH power boosting is possible to be applied if there is enough power on PDCCH symbol(s).

Parameter name: RLC PDU re-sending delay margin for carrier aggregation
Description: This parameter indicates the additional buffer margin on top of the configured max queuing delay (NRCELL.primaryPathMaxQueueingDelay or NRCELL.secondaryPathMaxQueueingDelay) for the cell, that is allowed when RLC PDUs are re-sent due to delay when carrier aggregation is configured.

Parameter name: DRB profile configuration for cell aggregation level
Description: This parameter indicates the DRB profile configuration for cell aggregation functionalities.  This parameter is applicable for FR1 SA calls only.
Range and step: FR1 CA eligible (0), Not FR1 CA eligible (1), FR1 CA incompatible (2)

Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter indicates the time period after which the SDUs that are not yet transmitted due to transmission delay are to be discarded. The time the SDU spends in the buffer when the UE is in the RRC Inactive state is not included in the transmission delay calculation.    If this parameter is equal to "infinity", it means the discard timer is off.  If NRDRB.discardTimerUl is configured and NRBTS.actServiceAwarePDCPConfig is equal to TRUE, then this parameter is just applied to downlink SDU, otherwise, this parameter is applied to both downlink and uplink SDU.    The discard timer could be extended from the recommended values hereafter according to the jitter allowed to transmit a PDCP packets when a bearer is activated at the same time as the UE configuration is resumed (inactive to connected state). During the UE reconfiguration, the capability to handle the DRB traffic is delayed to the RRC procedure completion. In addition, the delay to transmit the buffered PDCP packets could be increased according to UE radio conditions leading to request more time than the recommended setting to recover a Packet Delay Budget associated to the 5QI characteristics.    Recommended values for this parameter per NRDRB_5QI:  - "100ms" if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 1.  - "150ms" if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 2.  - "50ms" if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 3.  - "300ms" if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 4.  - "150ms" if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 71.  - "300ms" if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 72.  - "500ms" if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 76.  - "10ms" if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 80.

This parameter indicates to the UE the time period after which the SDUs that are not yet transmitted in uplink due to transmission delay are to be discarded.    If this parameter is equal to 'infinity', it means the discard timer is off  This parameter applies to uplink SDU only if NRBTS.actServiceAwarePDCPConfig is equal to TRUE.    Recommended values for this parameter per NRDRB_5QI:  - '100ms' if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 1.  - '150ms' if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 2.  - '50ms' if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 3.  - '300ms' if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 4.  - '150ms' if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 71.  - '300ms' if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 72.  - '500ms' if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 76.  - '30ms' if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 80.

Parameter name: Downlink allow minimum delay link usage during secondary link calibration
Description: The parameter indicates if sending DL data to the link with minimum delay is allowed, when the secondary link is under calibration.  The applicability of the secondary link is as follows:  - SCG F1-U of EN-DC Split bearer  - MCG Xn-U of SN Terminated Inter-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer  - SCG F1-U of MN Terminated Intra-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer
This parameter indicates DL flow control algorithm to use.

Parameter name: UE DRB inactivity timer per DRB profile for SA
Description: This timer indicates the time period for the indication of the DRB inactivity in both DL and UL directions for DRB in given DRB profile for SA.  If this parameter is equal to 0, then this timer is off.

Parameter name: RRC Inactive UE DRB inactivity timer per DRB profile for SA
Description: This timer defines the time period for the indication of the DRB inactivity in both DL and UL directions for DRB in given DRB profile for RRC Inactive capable SA UEs.  If this parameter is equal to 0, then this timer is off.

This parameter indicates the DSCP (Differentiated Services Code Point) value associated with the DRB.    For NSA mode, the DSCP value will be set in each IP packet sent for the related bearer to S-GW or target gNB.    For SA mode, the DSCP value will be set in each IP packet sent over NG-U towards UPF for a QoS Flow related with the DRB.    This parameter supports all the values in the defined range, although the list of IETF based DSCP values are only the following ones (numerical values in decimal):  BE (=0),  AF11 (=10),  AF12 (=12),  AF13 (=14),  AF21 (=18),  AF22 (=20),  AF23 (=22),  AF31 (=26),  AF32 (=28),  AF33 (=30),  AF41 (=34),  AF42 (=36),  AF43 (=38),  CS3 (=24),  CS5 (=40),  EF (=44)    Recommended values for this parameter per NRDRB_5QI:  - 44 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 1  - 34 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 2  - 46 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 3  - 28 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 4  - 40 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains an element whose value is equal to 5  - 28 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 71  - 30 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 72 or 76  - 24 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 80  - 34 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 128

Parameter name: Delay threshold since last scheduling for micro DTX optimized scheduler
Description: Whenever a UE could be put under DTX optimized scheduling and provided that the value of this parameter is greater than 0, the scheduler shall first check if the delay since the last scheduling of this UE, which emptied its associated buffers, is greater than or equal to the value of this parameter.    If the measured delay is greater than or equal to the value of this parameter, the UE is not eligible to DTX optimized scheduling. Thus, no retention delay will be applied to schedule the UE non-GBR (except 5QI5) DRB traffic.    Whenever this parameter is equal to 0, this check is bypassed.    This parameter, if configured, overwrites cell specific value in DRB differentiation in micro-DTX optimized scheduler.

Parameter name: Maximum retention delay for micro DTX optimized scheduler
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum duration in ms between the first received data (possibly gathering several packets received at a similar time) in a bundle and the last one.  This implies that this parameter represents the maximum delay introduced by the micro DTX optimized scheduler.    This parameter, if configured, overwrites cell specific value in DRB differentiation in micro-DTX optimized scheduler.    Note: Value 0 disables the maximum retention delay.

Parameter name: DL data duration threshold to discard the counting results
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold under which the counting results of the DL bursts are excluded from the PM counter data and PCMD throughput reports.  It is applicable to DL IP throughput PM counters per DRB and PCMD throughput reports.  If this parameter is equal to 0, counting results of the DL bursts will not be discarded for reasons of short duration.

Parameter name: Data duration threshold to discard the counting results for DL MAC SDU user throughput counters
Description: This parameter indicates the data duration threshold under which the counting results of the bursts are excluded from the PM counter data for DL MAC SDU user throughput counters.  If this parameter is equal to 0, counting results of the bursts will not be discarded for reasons of short duration.

Parameter name: Data duration threshold to discard the counting results for DL PDCP PDU user throughput counters on 5G leg
Description: This parameter indicates the data duration threshold under which the counting results of the bursts are excluded from the PM counter data for DL PDCP PDU user throughput counters on 5G leg.  If this parameter is equal to 0, counting results of the bursts will not be discarded for reasons of short duration.

Parameter name: Data duration threshold to discard the counting results for DL PDCP PDU user throughput counters on LTE leg
Description: This parameter indicates the data duration threshold under which the counting results of the bursts are excluded from the PM counter data for DL PDCP PDU user throughput counters on LTE leg.  If this parameter is equal to 0, counting results of the bursts will not be discarded for reasons of short duration.

Parameter name: UL data duration threshold to discard the counting results
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold under which the counting results of the UL bursts are excluded from the PM counter data and PCMD throughput reports.  It is applicable to UL IP throughput PM counters per DRB and PCMD throughput reports.  If this parameter is equal to 0, counting results of the UL bursts will not be discarded for reasons of short duration.

Parameter name: Guard timer for end marker reception
Description: This timer guards  - the target gNB against missing DL end marker from the source gNB during the Inter-gNB mobility procedure (SA).  - NR-DC SN gNB against missing DL end marker from the NR-DC MN gNB during PSCell Addition / SNode Addition procedure  - NR-DC MN gNB against missing DL end marker from the NR-DC SN gNB during Bearer Takeback / SNode Release (with data forwarding) procedure.    Recommended values for this parameter per NRDRB_5QI:  - 500 (corresponding to 500ms) if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 1.

This parameter indicates the overhead factor of the downlink GBR in layer 2.  The gNB increases the GBR in downlink direction for radio layer 2 by the product GBR in downlink direction and the L2 overhead factor GBR UL/100.  The gNB ignores this parameter for nonGBR DRB.

This parameter indicates the overhead factor of the uplink GBR in layer 2.  The gNB increases the GBR in uplink direction for radio layer 2 by the product GBR in uplink direction and the L2 Overhead Factor GBR UL/100.  The gNB ignores this parameter for nonGBR DRB.
This parameter indicates the maximum GFBR for a DRB in the downlink direction.  If the GFBR provided by the AMF exceeds the value of this parameter, then the DRB addition will be rejected.
This parameter indicates the maximum GFBR for a DRB in the uplink direction.  If the GFBR provided by the AMF exceeds the value of this parameter, then the DRB addition will be rejected.

Parameter name: Maximum periodicity of Downlink Data Delivery Status Indication message during CPU overload
Description: This parameter defines the maximum periodicity of the F1-U and X2-U Downlink Data Delivery Status Indication message during CPU overload

Parameter name: Maximum time limit for the DL forwarding over X2
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum time limit for the downlink data forwarding over X2-U
This parameter defines the value of max RLC queuing delay to be used for flow control algorithm for GBR DRB
This parameter defines the value of max queuing delay include to be used for flow control algorithm for GBR DRB

Parameter name: Minimum throughput for DL forwarding over X2-U
Description: This parameter indicates the minimum throughput rate to be considered for downlink data forwarding over X2-U

Parameter name: SA NR-DC specific set of DRB profile parameters
Description: This structure gathers the SA NR-DC specific set of DRB profile parameters

Parameter name: Activate secondary link prioritization after inactivity for NR-DC
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates secondary link prioritization after data inactivity.  The applicability of the secondary link is as follows:  - MCG Xn-U of SN Terminated Inter-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer  - SCG F1-U of MN Terminated Intra-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer

Parameter name: Activate duplicate PDCP PDU transmission for NR-DC split bearers
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates duplicate PDCP PDU transmission for NR-DC split bearer.

Parameter name: DL data split buffer buildup threshold for NR-DC split bearer
Description: This parameter indicates the PDCP buffer build-up threshold with respect to the current primary link throughput after which DL data split can be started.  The primary link in the context of NR DC bearer is:  - SCG F1-U of SN Terminated Inter-gNB NR DC Split Bearer  - MCG F1-U of MN Terminated Intra-gNB NR DC Split Bearer.

Parameter name: DL data split gain threshold for NR-DC split bearer
Description: This parameter indicates the gain threshold over which DL data can be split over MCG and SCG.

Parameter name: DL data split mode for NR-DC split bearer
Description: This parameter indicates on which interface(s) DL data is sent.

Parameter name: Number of consecutive downlink data split gain or primary link congestion period
Description: This parameter indicates the number of consecutive DDDS periods for which the downlink data split gain condition or the instantaneous primary link congestion should be satisfied after which the actions are taken to split the data over MCG and SCG.  The primary link is  - SCG F1-U for SN Terminated Inter-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer  - MCG F1-U for MN Terminated Intra-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer    The instantaneous NR congestion is based on the DBS=0 report on the primary link.

Parameter name: DL preferred path for NR-DC split bearer
Description: This parameter indicates the DL preferred path for the NR-DC split bearers.    The primary link (value 'Primary') is defined as follows:  - SCG F1-U for SN Terminated Inter-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer  - MCG F1-U for MN Terminated Intra-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer    The secondary link (value 'Secondary') is defined as follows:  - MCG Xn-U for SN Terminated Inter-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer  - SCG F1-U for MN Terminated Intra-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer

Parameter name: DL data split buffer buildup threshold during secondary link prioritization
Description: This parameter indicates the PDCP buffer build-up threshold with respect to the current secondary link throughput after which DL data split can be started when the secondary link prioritization trigger is active.  The applicability of the secondary link is as follows:  - MCG Xn-U of SN Terminated Inter-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer  - MCG F1-U of MN Terminated Intra-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer.    If NRDRB.nrDcDrbParam.actPrioXxAfterInactNrDc is equal to FALSE, this parameter is ignored.

Parameter name: Inactivity duration for PDCP duplication for NR-DC split bearers
Description: This parameter indicates the duration for which no data has been sent over Xn-U to allow PDCP PDU duplication.

Parameter name: Inactivity threshold for secondary link prioritization
Description: This parameter indicates the inactivity threshold after which the secondary link is prioritized.  The applicability of secondary link is as follows:  - MCG Xn-U of SN Terminated Inter-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer  - SCG F1-U of MN Terminated Intra-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer    If NRDRB.nrDcDrbParam.actPrioXxAfterInactNrDc is equal to FALSE, this parameter is ignored.

Parameter name: Inactivity threshold for restarting secondary link prioritization
Description: This parameter indicates the inactivity threshold for restarting secondary link prioritization again when the secondary link prioritization trigger is active.  The applicability of the secondary link is as follows:  - MCG Xn-U of SN Terminated Inter-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer  - SCG F1-U of MN Terminated Intra-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer    If NRDRB.nrDcDrbParam.actPrioXxAfterInactNrDc is equal to FALSE, this parameter is ignored.

Parameter name: Default DL traffic routing for NR-DC
Description: This parameter indicates in which path (MCG or SCG) DL traffic is routed when bearer is set up.

Parameter name: Time duration for the secondary link prioritization
Description: This parameter indicates the duration during which the secondary link prioritization is activated.  The applicability of the secondary link is as follows:  - MCG Xn-U of SN Terminated Inter-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer  - SCG F1-U of MN Terminated Intra-gNB NR-DC Split Bearer.    If NRDRB.nrDcDrbParam.actPrioXxAfterInactNrDc is equal to FALSE, this parameter is ignored.

Parameter name: Ul data path for NRDC bearer
Description: This parameter indicates if UL data path is via MCG, SCG or both.

Parameter name: UL data path for UE not capable of UL split bearer for NRDC
Description: This parameter indicates if UL data path is via MCG or SCG for UEs which are not capable of UL split bearer and with NRDRB.nrDcDrbParam.ulDataPathNrDc configured as split bearer (i.e. with values 'ulDataSplit_PrimaryPathMCG' or 'ulDataSplit_PrimaryPathSCG')

Parameter name: UL data split threshold for NRDC bearer
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold above which UE will split data from primary path to secondary path (MCG or SCG leg in case of NRDC).

Parameter name: New Radio DRB L4S profile distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the NRDRB_L4S instance that is part of the NRDRB profile. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration. Examples: MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRDRB_L4S-1  NRDRB_L4S-1

Parameter name: New Radio DRB MAC Profile distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the NRDRB_MAC instance. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRDRB_MAC-1  NRDRB_MAC-1

Parameter name: New Radio DRB PDCP Profile distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the NRDRB_PDCP instance. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRDRB_PDCP-1  NRDRB_PDCP-1

Parameter name: New Radio DRB RLC AM Profile distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the NRDRB_RLC_AM instance. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRDRB_RLC_AM-1  NRDRB_RLC_AM-1

Parameter name: New Radio DRB RLC UM Profile distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the NRDRB_RLC_UM instance. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRDRB_RLC_UM-1  NRDRB_RLC_UM-1

Parameter name: New Radio DRB TCP boost profile distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the NRDRB_TCP_BOOST instance that is part of the NRDRB profile. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration. Examples: MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRDRB_TCP_BOOST-1  NRDRB_TCP_BOOST-1    If NRDRB.nrDrbTcpBoostDN is not configured for a NRDRB profile, then the DRBs defined by that NRDRB profile will not have TCP boost applied to that DRB.

Parameter name: New Radio Uplink Configured Grant Profile distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the associated NRULCG_PROFILE instance. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples: MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRULCG_PROFILE-1  NRULCG_PROFILE-1

Parameter name: New Radio Discontinuous Reception Transmission distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the associated NRDRX instance. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRDRX-2  NRDRX-2

Parameter name: New Radio PDCCH Profile for High Reliability Link Adaptation distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the associated New Radio PDCCH Profile for High Reliability Link Adaptation (NRPDCCHHRLA) instance. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPDCCHHRLA-1  NRPDCCHHRLA-1

Parameter name: New Radio PDSCH Profile for Basic Reliability Link Adaptation distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the associated New Radio PDSCH Profile for Basic Reliability Link Adaptation (NRPDSCHBRLA) instance. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration. Examples: MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPDSCHBRLA-1 NRPDSCHBRLA-1    Point: NRBTS/NRDRB/nrPdschBRLaDN shall be configured only if the referenced NRPDSCHBRLA instance exists.

Parameter name: New Radio PDSCH Profile for High Reliability Link Adaptation distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the associated New Radio PDSCH Profile for High Reliability Link Adaptation (NRPDSCHHRLA) instance. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPDSCHHRLA-1  NRPDSCHHRLA-1

Parameter name: New Radio PUSCH Profile for Basic Reliability Link Adaptation distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the associated New Radio PUSCH Profile for Basic Reliability Link Adaptation (NRPUSCHBRLA) instance. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples: MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPDSCHBRLA-1 NRPDSCHBRLA-1  Point: NRBTS/NRDRB/nrPuschBRLaDN shall be configured only if the referenced NRPDSCHBRLA instance exists.

Parameter name: New Radio PUSCH Profile for High Reliability Link Adaptation distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the associated New Radio PUSCH Profile for High Reliability Link Adaptation (NRPUSCHHRLA) instance. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPUSCHHRLA-1  NRPUSCHHRLA-1

Parameter name: NSA 3x specific set of DRB profile parameters
Description: This parameter gathers the NSA 3x specific set of DRB profile parameters.
This parameter activates/deactivates X2-U is prioritized after data inactivity

Parameter name: Activate duplicate PDCP PDU transmission over X2-U for NSA 3x DRB
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates duplicate PDCP PDU transmission over X2-U for NSA 3x DRB.

Parameter name: DL Data Split buffer buildup threshold
Description: This parameter indicates the PDCP Buffer build up threshold with respect to the current NR Tput after which DL data split can be started

Parameter name: DL Data Split buffer buildup threshold during X2-U prioritization
Description: This parameter indicates the PDCP Buffer build up threshold with respect to the current LTE Tput after which DL data split can be started when X2-U prioritize trigger is active.  If NRDRB.nsaDrbParam.actPrioritizeX2AfterInactivity is equal to 0 (corresponding to FALSE), this parameter is ignored.
This parameter indicates the Gain threshold over which DL data can be split over F1-U and X2-U interface.
This parameter indicates on which interface(s) DL data is sent.

Parameter name: Number of consecutive downlink data split gain or NR congestion period
Description: This parameter indicates the number of consecutive DDDS period for which the downlink data split gain condition or the instantaneous NR congestion should be satisfied after which the actions are taken to split the data over F1-U and X2-U.  The instantaneous NR congestion is based on the DBS=0 report on F1-U

Parameter name: DL preferred path for NSA 3x split bearer
Description: This parameter indicates the DL preferred path (F1-U or X2-U) for NSA 3x split bearers.

Parameter name: Inactivity duration over X2-U for PDCP duplication
Description: This parameter indicates the duration for which no data has been sent over X2-U to allow PDCP PDU duplication.

This parameter indicates the inactivity threshold after which X2-U is prioritized.  If NRDRB.nsaDrbParam.actPrioritizeX2AfterInactivity is equal to 0 (corresponding to FALSE), this parameter is ignored.

Parameter name: Inactivity threshold for restarting X2-U prioritization
Description: This parameter indicates the inactivity threshold for restarting X2-U prioritization again when X2-U prioritize trigger is active.  If NRDRB.nsaDrbParam.actPrioritizeX2AfterInactivity is equal to 0 (corresponding to FALSE), this parameter is ignored.
This parameter indicates in which path (LTE or NR) DL traffic is routed when bearer is set up.
This parameter indicates whether NSA 3x bearer is allowed for the DRB profile.

This parameter indicates the duration during which X2-U prioritization is activated.  If NRDRB.nsaDrbParam.actPrioritizeX2AfterInactivity is equal to 0 (corresponding to FALSE), this parameter is ignored.
This parameter indicates if UL data path is via LTE, NR or both.

Parameter name: UL data path for UE not capable of UL Split bearer
Description: This parameter indicates if UL data path is via LTE or NR for UEs which are not capable of UL Split bearer and with NRDRB.nsaDrbParam.ulDataPath configured as Split Bearer (i.e. with values corresponding to ulOverLteNr_PrimaryPathOverLte or ulOverLteNr_PrimaryPathOverNr)
This parameter indicates the threshold above which UE will split data from primary path to secondary path (either LTE or NR Leg).
This parameter indicates the number of DL PDCP SDUs that can be discarded in one discard interval.
This parameter is used to determine which paging strategy shall be applied for DRB profile.  Example: MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPAGING_STRAT_RRCINACT-1

Parameter name: DRB specific scheduling request payload size
Description: This parameter indicates the payload size that is scheduled and granted in case of responding to a scheduling request (SR) for a specific DRB.    It is expected that the size of the grant includes the size of possible UL MAC CEs and higher-level protocol headers.    Note: The DRB specific SR payload does not apply to the VoNR(5QI-1) DRB profile

This parameter indicates the amount of time the gNB PDCP should wait until the DL PDCP status report is received from the UE at the target. This parameter is applicable for mobility, bearer type change, and bearer takeback scenarios.    If the DL PDCP status report is received within the timer expiration, the DL transmission is resumed at the target. This timer ensures the resumption of DL Data transmission in case of non-reception of PDCP status report from the UE

Parameter name: PDCP status report wait timer offset
Description: This parameter, in addition to NRDRB.pdcpStatRepWaitTimer, indicates the amount of time the gNB PDCP should wait until the DL PDCP status report is received from the UE, during PDCP Data Recovery. For PDCP Re-establishment scenarios, only NRDRB.pdcpStatRepWaitTimer is used.
This parameter indicates the queue delay target of the PI2 queue management.
This parameter indicates the queue size target of the PI2 queue management.
This parameter indicates the counter group for QoS group based PM counters. If configured, this parameter overrides the default mapping from QCI/5QI value to QoS group.

This parameter indicates the priority level of the associated 5QI flows which are mapped to this DRB profile according to TS 23.501.  Recommended values for NRDRB.priorityLevel per NRDRB_5QI/NRDRB_QCI:  - 20 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList equals 1;  - 40 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList equals 2;  - 30 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList equals 3;  - 50 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList equals 4;  - 10 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList/ NRDRB_QCI.qciValueList equals 5;  - 60 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList/ NRDRB_QCI.qciValueList equals 6;  - 70 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList/ NRDRB_QCI.qciValueList equals 7;  - 80 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList/ NRDRB_QCI.qciValueList equals 8;  - 90 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList/ NRDRB_QCI.qciValueList equals 9;  - 5 if NRDRB_QCI.qciValueList equals 69;  - 55 if NRDRB_QCI.qciValueList equals 70;  - 56 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList equals 71;  - 56 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList equals 72;  - 56 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList equals 76;  - 65 if NRDRB_QCI.qciValueList equals 79;  - 68 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList equals 80
This parameter indicates the time period after bearer setup when the PDCP SDU delay based on the discard mechanism is activated for the bearer.

Parameter name: Activate DL PDCP SDU delay based discarding
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates DL PDCP SDU delay based discarding.    The supported values are:  - 'Disabled' meaning the delay-based discarding is disabled.  - 'Controlled Delay (CoDel)' meaning the legacy delay-based discarding is enabled.  - 'PI2' meaning the delay-based discarding using delay probability function PI2 (PI square) is enabled.

This parameter indicates the queuing delay above which DL PDCP SDUs could be discarded. The time the SDU spends in the buffer when the UE is in the RRC Inactive state is not included in the queuing delay calculation.

This parameter indicates the option used to prioritize the link over which the retransmission should be done for the lost PDCP PDU.    The possible values are:  - 'retxPrioSameLink' meaning the first priority for retransmission is the same link over which the PDCP PDU is lost if allowed by flow control, else the flow control algorithm is applied.  - 'retxBasedOnFC' meaning the link selected by the flow control algorithm will be used for retransmission.    The recommended value is 'retxPrioSameLink'.

This parameter indicates whether the DRB profile is for a GBR or a non-GBR bearer.  It determines if dedicated network resources related to a service or bearer level Guaranteed Bit Rate (GBR) value are permanently allocated.
This parameter indicates the New Radio RLC mode for the DRB.

Parameter name: RLC PDU delay threshold for carrier aggregarion
Description: This parameter indicates the delay threshold in milliseconds between RLC PDUs which are sent on different cells when carrier aggregation is enabled.

This parameter indicates the scheduling weight for gNB schedulers used for MAC scheduling (UL and DL) and DRB multiplexing in DL.  Recommended values for NRDRB.schedulWeight per NRDRB_5QI/NRDRB_QCI:  - 40 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList/ NRDRB_QCI.qciValueList equals 5;  - 20 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList/ NRDRB_QCI.qciValueList equals 6;  - 10 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList/ NRDRB_QCI.qciValueList equals 7;  - 5 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList/ NRDRB_QCI.qciValueList equals 8;  - 1 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList/ NRDRB_QCI.qciValueList equals 9;  - 12 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList/ NRDRB_QCI.qciValueList equals 80
This parameter indicates the discard interval timer for checking if DL PDCP SDUs are to be discarded based on queuing delay.

This parameter indicates the scheduling request periodicity for a specific DRB profile.    Note: The DRB specific SR periodicity does not apply to the VoNR(5QI-1) DRB profile.  According to 3GPP 38.300, the same periodicity value may represent the different number of slots depending on the numerology:  - For FDD, the duration of the slot is 1ms  - For TDD FR1, the duration of the slot is 0.5ms

This parameter indicates whether static UE is supported or not. It should not be configured if the UE's position is not fixed.    Static UE is supported if this parameter is configured and equal to TRUE.    A UE is considered as static UE when this UE has at least one DRB profile configured with NRDRB.staticUE equal to TRUE and does not have:  - High reliability RB configured, or  - VoNR 5QI1 configured for VoNR if NRBTS/NRCELL.actDlVoNrLimMaxMcsAndLayer is equal to TRUE.    Note: default NRDRB profile (NRBTS/NRDRB-1) is not advised to be configured to support static UEs.  Note: DRB profile having NRDRB.staticUE equal to TRUE should not be configured for VoNR or high reliability.

Parameter name: DL data volume threshold to discard the counting results
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold of the total DL data volume under which the counting results of the DL bursts are excluded from the PM counter data and PCMD throughput reports.  It is applicable to DL IP throughput PM counters per DRB and PCMD throughput reports.  The point where statistics are collected for PM counters must be before segmentation and after re-assembly.  If this parameter is equal to 0, counting results of the bursts will not be discarded for reasons of small volume.

Parameter name: Data volume threshold to discard the counting results for DL MAC SDU user throughput counters
Description: This parameter indicates the data volume threshold under which the counting results of the bursts are excluded from the PM counter data for DL MAC SDU user throughput counters. The point where statistics are collected for PM counters must be before segmentation and after re-assembly.  If this parameter is equal to 0, counting results of the bursts will not be discarded for reasons of small volume.

Parameter name: Data volume threshold to discard the counting results for DL PDCP PDU user throughput counters on 5G leg
Description: This parameter indicates the data volume threshold under which the counting results of the bursts are excluded from the PM counter data for DL PDCP PDU user throughput counters on 5G leg. The point where statistics are collected for PM counters must be before segmentation and after re-assembly.  If this parameter is equal to 0, counting results of the bursts will not be discarded for reasons of small volume.

Parameter name: Data volume threshold to discard the counting results for DL PDCP PDU user throughput counters on LTE leg
Description: This parameter indicates the data volume threshold under which the counting results of the bursts are excluded from the PM counter data for DL PDCP PDU user throughput counters on LTE leg. The point where statistics are collected for PM counters must be before segmentation and after re-assembly.  If this parameter is equal to 0, counting results of the bursts will not be discarded for reasons of small volume.

Parameter name: UL data volume threshold to discard the counting results
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold of the total UL data volume under which the counting results of the UL bursts are excluded from the PM counter data and PCMD throughput reports.  It is applicable to UL IP throughput PM counters per DRB and PCMD throughput reports.  The point where statistics are collected for PM counters must be before segmentation and after re-assembly.  If this parameter is equal to 0, counting results of the UL bursts will not be discarded for reasons of small volume.

Parameter name: New Radio 5QI to DRB Profile Mapping instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the 5QI to DRB Profile Mapping (NRDRB_5QI) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates whether or not data forwarding will apply on the corresponding DRB profile.

This parameter gathers a list of NGAP parameter 5G QoS Identifier (5QI) values, which are mapped to same DRB profile.    An element of NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList equal to 128 is only used to map a 5QI-2 within the gNB if NRCELL.actNonVoNRGbrService is equal to FALSE.

Parameter name: New Radio DRB Profile distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the DRB Profile (NRDRB) instance to be used for the QoS flow associated DRB fulfilling the mapping criteria. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRDRB-2  NRDRB-2

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the New Radio PLMN (NRPLMN) instance to be used for PLMN ID-specific 5G QoS Identifier (5QI) to non-GBR profile mapping in a shared RAN. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  If this parameter is not defined, then the 5QI specific mapping (NRDRB_5QI) is common for all PLMNs.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1
This parameter contains a list of SNSSAIs for the NR 5QI to DRB Mapping profile.  If NRDRB_5QI.snssaiList is not defined, then the 5QI specific mapping (NRDRB_5QI) is common for all network slices

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the SNSSAI which shall be mapped to a QoS Identifier (5QI) to DRB profile mapping as follows:  - one SNSSAI DN value or  - the value of the first SNSSAI DN of a range and, in this case, the last SNSSAI DN value of the range shall be configured in NRDRB_5QI.snssaiList.snssaiDNLast.  This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Example:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/SNSSAI-10  SNSSAI-10

Parameter name: Last SNSSAI distinguished name of a range
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the last SNSSAI of a range if a range of SNSSAI DNs shall be mapped to a 5G QoS Identifier (5QI) to non-GBR profile mapping.  This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Example:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/SNSSAI-25  SNSSAI-25

Parameter name: New Radio DRB L4S Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio DRB L4S applications profile (NRDRB_L4S) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: L4S enabler and selector in UL
Description: This parameter enables/disables and selects L4S in UL.

Parameter name: L4S enabler and selector in DL
Description: This parameter enables/disables and selects L4S handling in DL support.  - disabled: The parameter is disabled.  - bestEffortBearers: L4S for best effort bearers.  - dualPI2Configuration: L4S in dualPI2 configuration.  - LowLatencyCommunication: L4S for Low Latency Communication.

Parameter name: Drop latency for Step Dropper of L4S traffic
Description: This parameter is used as the Drop latency for Step Dropper of L4S traffic

Parameter name: Bandwidth margin to ensure L4S queue-less transmission
Description: This parameter used as the Bandwidth margin to ensure L4S queue-less transmission

Parameter name: Desired radio between L4S and non-L4S traffic
Description: This parameter is used as the desired radio between L4S and non-L4S traffic

Parameter name: Latency threshold for Step Marker of L4S traffic
Description: This parameter used as the Marking latency threshold for Step Marker of L4S traffic.
This parameter is used as the L4S target delay in UL

Parameter name: Enable UL latency shielding of L4S traffic
Description: This parameter enables/disables the UL latency shielding by discarding excessive non-L4S traffic.
This parameter is used as the L4S systematic offset in UL

Parameter name: New Radio DRB MAC Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the DRB MAC Profile (NRDRB_MAC) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates the maximum packet delay value used by the gNB MAC scheduling algorithm for GBR bearers.  The gNB ignores this parameter for nonGBR DRB.
This parameter indicates the value of the ID of the logical channel group, as specified in 3GPP TS 38.321, to which the logical channel belongs.

Parameter name: Maximum number of DL HARQ transmissions for DRB profile
Description: This parameter defines the maximum number of DL transmissions for a specific DRB profile. This number contains the initial transmission + n-1 retransmissions

Parameter name: Maximum number of UL HARQ transmissions for DRB profile
Description: This parameter defines the maximum number of UL transmissions for a specific DRB profile. This number contains the initial transmission + n-1 retransmissions.

This parameter indicates the nominal bit rate in the downlink direction.  It is only applicable for non-GBR DRB. If it is not configured, nominal bit rate does not apply to this NRDRB profile in this direction.

This parameter indicates the nominal bit rate in the uplink direction.  It is only applicable for non-GBR DRB. If it is not configured, nominal bit rate does not apply to this NRDRB profile in this direction.
This parameter indicates the prioritized bit rate for non-GBR bearers  It is used by the UE for the UL scheduling algorithm, as specified in 3GPP TS 38.321

This parameter indicates the Bucket Size Duration (BSD) of the UL and DL scheduler for GBR and NBR nonGBR bearers. For nonGBR bearers (without NBR) the BSD is set to 50ms, i.e. this parameter is not used.  The BSD is sent to the UE according to [38.321], the UE calculates the bucket size of a logical channel by PBR * BSD.

This parameter indicates the value of the logical channel priority for the UL scheduler, as specified in TS 38.321.    Recommended values for this parameter per NRDRB_5QI (i.e. for the NRDRB_5QI instance such that NRDRB_5QI.nrDrbDN refers to the NRDRB instance with NRDRB.nrDrbMacDN referring to the current NRDRB_MAC instance):  - 5 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList is equal to 1  - 7 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList is equal to 2  - 6 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList is equal to 3  - 8 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList is equal to 4, 71, 72 or 76  - 4 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList is equal to 5  - 9 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList is equal to 6  - 10 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList is equal to 7 or 80  - 11 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList is equal to 8  - 12 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList is equal to 9

Parameter name: New Radio DRB PDCP Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the DRB PDCP Profile (NRDRB_PDCP) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates the CU Flow Control Profile Id which contains the CU Flow control parameter.
This parameter indicates the maximum robust header compression context identifier value that can be allocated per DRB

Parameter name: Out of order PDCP delivery on DL
Description: This parameter enables/disables PDCP out of order delivery on DL. See 3GPP TS 38.323 and TS 38.331.    It is recommended to set this parameter to FALSE for specific DRBs whose mapping to upper layer protocols (e.g TCP) guarantees in-order delivery;  It is recommended to set this parameter to TRUE for specific DRBs whose mapping to low latency service based on upper layer protocols (e.g. UDP, QUIC or RTP) does not guarantee in-order delivery.

Parameter name: Out of order PDCP delivery on UL
Description: This parameter enables/disables PDCP out of order delivery on UL. See 3GPP TS 38.323 and TS 38.331.    It is recommended to set this parameter to FALSE for specific DRBs whose mapping to upper layer protocols (e.g TCP) guarantees in-order delivery;  It is recommended to set this parameter to TRUE for specific DRBs whose mapping to low latency service based on upper layer protocols (e.g. UDP, QUIC or RTP) does not guarantee in-order delivery.
This parameter enables/disables PDCP Buffer based discarding.
This parameter indicates the number of buffered PDCP SDU's and the PDCP PDU's waiting for acknowledgement after which new incoming PDCP SDU's are discarded.

This parameter indicates the delay threshold 1 trigger type configured for retransmission of the PDCP PDU.    The possible values are:  - transmittedPdcpSnTrig meaning that the delay threshold 1 monitoring is triggered based on the highest transmitted PDCP SN in DDDS received over the other interface link;  - pdcpPduSendTrig meaning that the delay threshold 1 monitoring is triggered after sending the PDCP PDU.

Parameter name: PDCP delay threshold based PDU retransmission mode
Description: This parameter indicates the delay threshold based retransmission mode configured for the retransmission of the PDCP PDU, in order to prevent t-Reordering timer expiry at the UE.    The possible values are:  - disabled meaning the delay threshold based retransmission is disabled;  - delayThresh1Enabled meaning the delay threshold based retransmission with only the threshold 1 monitoring is enabled;  - delayThresh1and2Enabled meaning the delay threshold based retransmission with both the threshold 1 and threshold 2 monitoring is enabled.

Parameter name: Maximum number of PDCP PDUs allowed for retransmission
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of PDCP PDUs allowed to be retransmitted for the DRB that are not yet indicated as delivered to UE.

Parameter name: PDCP PDU retransmission based on delay threshold 1
Description: This parameter indicates the delay threshold 1 for the PDCP PDU retransmission.  It is used to monitor the transmission delay of the PDCP PDU. The transmission delay may occur due to the delay or loss of the PDCP PDU over the F1-U/X2-U/Xn-U interfaces leading to t-Reordering timer expiry at the UE.

Parameter name: PDCP PDU retransmission based on delay threshold 2
Description: This parameter indicates the delay threshold 2 for the PDCP PDU retransmission.  It is used to monitor the delivery delay of the PDCP PDU. The delivery delay may occur due to air link degradation/RLC retransmissions leading to t-Reordering timer expiry at the UE.

Parameter name: Maximum delay allowed for sending of the retransmission PDCP PDU
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum delay allowed for sending of the PDCP PDU marked for the retransmission.

This parameter indicates the length of the PDCP Sequence Number (SN) and provides flexibility to decide which PDCP SN length setting will be used as priority for non-RedCap UEs for GBR bearers.    If the received UE capability indicates the support for  - 12bits, then this parameter value is used for RLC AM mode GBR bearers and RLC UM mode GBR bearers.  - 18bits, then this parameter value is not used and gNB automatically uses 18bits.    If this parameter is not configured, then gNB automatically uses 18bits for RLC AM mode GBR bearers and RLC UM mode GBR bearers.

Parameter name: PDCP SN Length for RedCap UEs
Description: This parameter indicates the length of the PDCP sequence number, and this applies for RedCap (reduced capability) UEs only.    This parameter provides flexibility for the customers to decide which PDCP SN length setting will be used as priority.  - If the received RedCap UE capability indicates the support for both 12bits and 18bits, then this parameter is used for RLC AM mode DRBs and RLC UM mode DRBs with NRDRB.dlFlowControlAlgo equal to "3gppFlowControl".  - When the RedCap UE supports only 12bits, then this parameter is not used and gNB automatically uses 12bits only.    If this parameter is not configured, then it is the gNB which will evaluate according to the RedCap UE capability on which SN length setting to use, taking 18bits as priority (if supported by the RedCap UE) for RLC AM mode DRBs and RLC UM mode DRBs with NRDRB.dlFlowControlAlgo equal to "3gppFlowControl".

This parameter indicates the value of timer t-Reordering for DL.  This timer is used to detect loss of PDCP Data PDUs at UE. See 3GPP TS 38.323 and TS 38.331.    Recommended values for this parameter per NRDRB_5QI (i.e. for the NRDRB_5QI instance such that NRDRB_5QI.nrDrbDN refers to the NRDRB instance with NRDRB.nrDrbPdcpDN referring to the current NRDRB_PDCP instance):  - 80 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 1 or 128.

This parameter indicates the value of timer t-Reordering for UL. This timer is used to detect loss of PDCP Data PDUs at gNB. See 3GPP TS 38.323 and TS 38.331.    Recommended values for this parameter per NRDRB_5QI (i.e. for the NRDRB_5QI instance such that NRDRB_5QI.nrDrbDN refers to the NRDRB instance with NRDRB.nrDrbPdcpDN referring to the current NRDRB_PDCP instance):  - 80 if NRDRB_5QI.fiveqiValueList contains only one element whose value is equal to 1 or 128

Parameter name: Index of X2-U/Xn-U flow control profile for CU
Description: This parameter indicates the index of the NRBTS.xxFlowControlProfForCu structure which contains the profile of the CU flow control parameters for X2-U/Xn-U.

Parameter name: New Radio QCI to non-GBR DRB Profile Mapping instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the QCI to non-GBR DRB Profile Mapping (NRDRB_QCI) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: New Radio non-GBR DRB Profile distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the non-GBR DRB Profile (NRDRB) instance to be used for the E-RAB associated DRB fulfilling the mapping criteria. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRDRB-2  NRDRB-2

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the New Radio PLMN (NRPLMN) instance to be used for PLMN ID-specific X2AP QoS Class Identifier (QCI) to non-GBR profile mapping in a shared RAN. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  If this parameter is not defined, then the QCI specific mapping (NRDRB_QCI) is common for all PLMNs.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1
This parameter gathers a list of X2AP QoS Class Identifier (QCI) values, which are mapped to same non-GBR DRB profile.

Parameter name: New Radio DRB RLC AM Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio DRB RLC AM Profile (NRDRB_RLC_AM) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter indicates the maximum number of downlink ARQ retransmissions allowed on the downlink.  When the retransmission counter of a PDU exceeds this threshold, the gNB-DU user plane triggers a notification for radio failure towards the gNB-DU control plane.  This parameter is applicable to the DL transmitter side (gNB-DU).

This parameter indicates the downlink value of pollByte parameter as per 3GPP TS 38.322.  This parameter represents the interval between polls in terms of number of transmitted bytes. This parameter is applicable to the DL transmitter side (gNB-DU).

This parameter indicates the downlink value of pollPDU parameter as per 3GPP TS 38.322.  It represents the interval between polls, in PDU.  It applies only to the RLC Acknowledged Mode and to the DL transmitter side (gNB-DU).
This parameter indicates the downlink value of timer T-PollRetransmit as per 3GPP TS 38.322.  It applies only to the RLC Acknowledged Mode and to the DL transmitter side (gNB-DU).

This parameter indicates the downlink value of timer t-StatusProhibit. This timer is used to prohibit the receiving side of an AM RLC entity from sending consecutive acknowledgement status reports.  It applies only to the RLC Acknowledged Mode and to the DL receiver side (UE).
This parameter indicates the downlink value of timer for reassembly in TS 38.322, in milliseconds.  This parameter is applicable to the DL receiver side (UE).

Parameter name: Timer reassembly DL for interband CA
Description: This parameter indicates the downlink value of timer for reassembly in TS 38.322, in milliseconds, used for CA UE  This parameter is applicable to the DL receiver side (UE).
This parameter indicates the DU Flow Control Profile, which contain the DU Flow control parameters to be used for RLC AM.

Parameter name: RLC AM mode DRB SN length for RedCap UEs
Description: This parameter indicates the length of the RLC sequence number to be configured for RLC AM mode DRB, and this applies for RedCap (reduced capability) UEs only.    This parameter provides flexibility for the customers to decide which RLC AM SN length setting will be used as priority.  - If the received RedCap UE capability indicates the support for both 12bits and 18bits, then this parameter is used.  - When the RedCap UE supports only 12bits, then this parameter is not used and gNB automatically uses 12bits only.    If this parameter is not configured, then it is the gNB which will evaluate according to the RedCap UE capability on which SN length setting to use, taking 18bits as priority (if supported by the RedCap UE).

This parameter indicates the maximum number of uplink ARQ retransmissions allowed on the uplink.  When the retransmission counter of a PDU exceeds this threshold, the UE triggers a request for RLC reestablishment procedure, as per TS 38.322. This parameter is applicable to the UL transmitter side (UE).

This parameter indicates the uplink value of pollByte parameter as per 3GPP TS 38.322. This parameter represents the interval between polls in terms of number of transmitted bytes. Note that in the uplink this function cannot be disabled in the UE, as per 3GPP. This parameter is applicable to the UL transmitter side (UE).

This parameter indicates the uplink value of pollPDU parameter as per 3GPP TS 38.322.  It represents the interval between polls, in PDU.  It applies only to the RLC Acknowledged Mode and to the UL transmitter side (UE).
This parameter indicates the uplink value of timer T-PollRetransmit as per 3GPP TS 38.322.  It applies only to the RLC Acknowledged Mode and to the UL transmitter side (UE).

This parameter indicates the uplink value of timer t-StatusProhibit. This timer is used to prohibit the receiving side of an AM RLC entity from sending consecutive acknowledgement status reports.  It applies only to the RLC Acknowledged Mode and to the UL receiver side (gNB-DU).
This parameter indicates the uplink value of timer for reassembly in TS 38.322, in milliseconds.  This parameter is applicable to the UL receiver side (gNB-DU).

Parameter name: Timer reassembly UL for interband CA
Description: This parameter indicates the uplink value of timer for reassembly in TS 38.322, in milliseconds, used for CA UE  This parameter is applicable to the UL receiver side (gNB).

Parameter name: New Radio DRB RLC UM Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio DRB RLC UM Profile (NRDRB_RLC_UM) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates the downlink value of timer for reassembly in TS 38.322, in milliseconds.  This parameter is applicable to the DL receiver side for RLC UM DRB (UE).

Parameter name: RLC UM mode DRB SN length
Description: This parameter indicates the length of the RLC sequence number to be configured for RLC UM mode DRB.
This parameter indicates the uplink value of timer for reassembly in TS 38.322, in milliseconds.  This parameter is applicable to the UL receiver side for RLC UM DRB (gNB-DU).

Parameter name: New Radio DRB TCP Boost Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio DRB TCP Boost Profile (NRDRB_TCP_BOOST) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: TCP boost proactive uplink grant duration
Description: This parameter indicates the boost duration during which proactive uplink grants (PUGs) will be sent to the UE once a TCP data flow has been detected.    The boost duration is divided into two parts: ramp-up duration and stable duration. The ramp-up duration is defined by NRDRB_TCP_BOOST.tcpBoostPugRampUpDuration. The stable duration is equal to NRDRB_TCP_BOOST.tcpBoostPugDuration minus NRDRB_TCP_BOOST.tcpBoostPugRampUpDuration. If NRDRB_TCP_BOOST.tcpBoostPugRampUpDuration is equal to NRDRB_TCP_BOOST.tcpBoostPugDuration there will be no stable duration.    PUGs will be sent more frequently during the ramp-up duration to ensure that the TCP slow start procedure rapidly increases the data rate. PUGs are sent less frequently in the stable duration which occurs after the TCP slow start procedure.

Parameter name: TCP boost proactive uplink grant inactive time
Description: This parameter indicates the minimum amount of time during which the DL DRB buffer must be empty before new DL data will mean the start of a new TCP data flow and trigger a new TCP boost proactive uplink grants (PUGs) cycle. If there is no DL data for a period greater than this time during a TCP boost PUGs cycle, the TCP boost cycle will be exited.

Parameter name: TCP boost proactive uplink grant minimum data size
Description: This parameter indicates the minimum amount of DL data that must be received for a UE to trigger the TCP boost proactive uplink grants (PUGs).

Parameter name: TCP boost proactive uplink grant minimum scheduling request period
Description: This parameter indicates the minimum Scheduling Request (SR) period that will allow TCP boost proactive uplink grants (PUGs) to be used. For UEs that have an SR period less than this value TCP PUGs will not be sent.

Parameter name: TCP boost proactive uplink grant ramp up duration
Description: This parameter indicates the ramp-up duration which is the first part of the TCP boost proactive uplink grants (PUGs) duration as described in the Description of NRDRB_TCP_BOOST.tcpBoostPugDuration. The ramp-up duration starts when the TCP data flow is detected and the UE is in the DRX active state.

Parameter name: TCP boost proactive uplink grant ramp up interval
Description: This parameter indicates the interval between sending TCP boost proactive uplink grants (PUGs) in the TCP boost ramp-up duration.

Parameter name: TCP boost proactive uplink grant stable interval
Description: This parameter indicates the interval between sending TCP boost proactive uplink grants (PUGs) in the TCP boost stable duration.

Parameter name: TCP boost proactive uplink grant transport block size
Description: This parameter indicates the Transport Block Size (TBS) that will be used for the TCP boost proactive uplink grants (PUGs).

Parameter name: TCP boost proactive uplink grant minimum UL SINR threshold
Description: This parameter indicates for UEs that do not support skippable UL grants the SINR threshold that the UE's uplink SINR must be greater than for TCP boost proactive uplink grants (PUGs) to be sent to the UE. If the UE's uplink SINR is less than this parameter, TCP boost PUGs will not be sent to the UE.

Parameter name: New Radio Discontinuous Reception Transmission instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Discontinuous Reception Transmission (DRX) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.  The following instances shall always be present (cannot be deleted):  NRDRX-0 - "NoDRX" - identifies instance to be used when NO DRX is to be configured.  NRDRX-1 - "Default NonGbr" - Identifies the default instance to be used for NonGbr when a custom instance is not configured.  NRDRX-2 - "Default VoNR" - Identifies the default instance to be used for VoNR when a custom instance is not configured.  NRDRX-3 - "Default ANR" - Identifies the default instance to be used for ANR when a custom instance is not configured.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: DRX HARQ RTT Timer for downlink
Description: This parameter indicates the number of symbols before allowing a downlink DRX HARQ retransmission.  If the value of this parameter expires and received DL HARQ feedback for that HARQ process was NACK, then drxRetransTimerDl starts.

Parameter name: DRX HARQ RTT Timer for uplink
Description: This parameter indicates the number of symbols before allowing an uplink DRX HARQ retransmission.  If the value of this parameter expires and received PUSCH for that HARQ process was ACK or NACK, then drxRetransTimerUl starts.
This parameter defines the duration after the PDCCH occasion in which a PDCCH indicates an initial UL or DL user data transmission for the MAC entity.
This parameter defines the long DRX cycle.
This parameter defines the DRX on duration timer.

This parameter indicates the priority level of the NRDRX instance which will be used to determine the values to be used for DRX installation.  A lower number would indicate a higher priority. 0 is the highest priority. The priority will be used to determine the NRDRX profile to be used when multiple DRBs are active on the call. The priority will not be used in case of ANR as it will be associated with a specific ANR type (NRCELL.drxProfileNrAnr.drxControl).  It is recommended that drxPriority of GBR 5QI to be configured with higher priority (lower number) than non-GBR 5QI.
This parameter defines the DRX active time for the UE to receive potential DL retransmission data.
This parameter defines the DRX active time for the UE to receive potential UL retransmission data.
This parameter denotes a label that can be used for a user-friendly description of the usage of the NRDRX instance.

Parameter name: LTE-NR Dynamic Spectrum Sharing instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the LTE-NR Dynamic Spectrum Sharing (NRDSSLTE) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRCELL instance.
This parameter activates/deactivates LTE-NR DSS superfast coordination.

Parameter name: Activate in-band LTE Cat-M in DSS
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates in-band LTE Cat-M support in DSS

Parameter name: Activate LTE-NR DSS NR PDCCH load use for resource allocation
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates LTE-NR DSS NR PDCCH load use for resource allocation.
This parameter activates/deactivates rate matching for CSI-IM

Parameter name: Activate UL adaptive retransmission enhancement for DSS
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates UL adaptive retransmission enhancement for DSS.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Timer poll retransmit DL for DSS
Description: This parameter configures the downlink value of timer T-PollRetransmit as per 3GPP TS 38.322.  This parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode.
