It is applicable to the DL transmitter side (gNB-DU) in a cell sharing spectrum with LTE.    When this parameter is configured, its value is used instead of the value of NRDRB_RLC_AM.dlTPollRetr

Parameter name: Timer status prohibit DL for DSS
Description: This parameter configures the downlink value of timer t-StatusProhibit. This timer is used to prohibit the receiving side of an AM RLC entity from sending consecutive acknowledgement status reports.  This parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. It is applicable to the DL receiver side (UE) in a cell sharing spectrum with LTE.    When this parameter is configured, its value is used instead of the value of NRDRB_RLC_AM.dlTProhib

Parameter name: Maximum number of DL DCIs per slot
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of DL CCEs per slot. The number of DL CCEs corresponds to this parameter times the maximum value of PDCCH.dciDedicatedAggregationLevel and PDCCH.dciRaMsg2AggregationLevel.    If this DSS cell is a primary cell of a carrier aggregation, the recommended value for this parameter is 1 so that a major part of the CCE space is reserved for UL scheduling, to avoid starvation of PUSCH.

Parameter name: Timer poll retransmit UL for DSS
Description: This parameter configures the uplink value of timer T-PollRetransmit as per 3GPP TS 38.322.  This parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. It is applicable to the UL transmitter side (UE) in a cell sharing spectrum with LTE.    When this parameter is configured, its value is used instead of the value of NRDRB_RLC_AM.ulTPollRetr

Parameter name: Timer status prohibit UL for DSS
Description: This parameter configures the uplink value of timer t-StatusProhibit. This timer is used to prohibit the receiving side of an AM RLC entity from sending consecutive acknowledgement status reports.  This parameter applies only for RLC Acknowledged Mode. It is applicable to the UL receiver side (gNB-DU) in a cell sharing spectrum with LTE.    When this parameter is configured, its value is used instead of the value of NRDRB_RLC_AM.ulTProhib

This parameter indicates the eNB which holds the partner cell involved in dynamic spectrum sharing.  This parameter is part of the Global eNodeB-ID.  Global eNodeB-ID is used to identify eNBs globally which is composed of the concatenation of MCC, MNC and the eNodeB-ID (this parameter).  This parameter indicates the eNB whose cells overlap with the NR Cell.

Parameter name: PLMN of Global eNB Id of the partner cell
Description: This parameter indicates the PLMN of the Global eNB ID of the partner cell for dynamic spectrum sharing.  It is defined by the PLMN ID (mcc + mnc + mncLength) + eNB ID + LCR ID

Parameter name: MCC of PLMN ID in Global eNB ID
Description: This parameter indicates the MCC (Mobile Country Code) of the PLMN (Public Land Mobile Network) ID included in the Global eNB ID.  MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC of PLMN ID in Global eNB ID
Description: This parameter indicates the MNC (Mobile Network Code) of the PLMN (Public Land Mobile Network) ID included in the Global eNB ID.  MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC length of PLMN ID in Global eNB ID
Description: This parameter indicates the length of the MNC (Mobile Network Code) of the PLMN (Public Land Mobile Network) ID
This parameter indicates the ID of the local cell resource  Its value uniquely identifies the cell within the eNB.
This parameter defines the downlink sharing ratio for dynamic spectrum sharing between LTE and NR.

This parameter indicates the downlink resource sharing algorithm for LTE-NR DSS.    The following options are available:  - 'DL PRB load based': the DL PRB load reports are used to adjust the LTE-NR DL sharing  - 'DL buffer level based': both the DL PRB load reports and the aggregated DL buffer level of all UEs attached to the LTE/NR cells are used to adjust the LTE-NR DL sharing (not supported)
Range and step: DL PRB load based (0), DL buffer level based (1)

Description: This parameter indicates the maximum downlink sharing ratio for dynamic LTE-NR spectrum sharing. gNB can re-configure the DL sharing ratio used for dynamic spectrum sharing between NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssDlRatio.minNrDssRatio and NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssDlRatio.maxNrDssRatio.    If NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssDlRatio.minNrDssRatio is equal to NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssDlRatio.maxNrDssRatio, the sharing ratio is fixed to this value.

This parameter indicates the minimum downlink sharing ratio for dynamic LTE-NR spectrum sharing. gNB can re-configure the DL sharing ratio used for dynamic spectrum sharing between NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssDlRatio.minNrDssRatio and NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssDlRatio.maxNrDssRatio.    If NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssDlRatio.minNrDssRatio is equal to NRDSSLTE..lteNrDssDlRatio.maxNrDssRatio, the sharing ratio is fixed to this value.    It is not recommended to set NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssDlRatio.minNrDssRatio to a high value (especially above 70) since this may result in LTE-NR cell coordination procedure failure due to eNB or gNB system configuration (minimal needed resources required by a technology may not be enough to fulfill NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssDlRatio.minNrDssRatio)

Parameter name: LTE-NR DSS superfast allocation performance enhancement
Description: This parameter indicates the gNB performance optimization mode of LTE-NR DSS Superfast Coordination feature. It is recommended to ensure the optimization to lower system load by reducing DSS messaging for minor changes in load and allocations.

This parameter indicates the MBSFN sharing ratio on sub frame basis, i.e. how many subframes are available for dynamic spectrum sharing between LTE and NR.  Depending on the LTE configuration (enabled features etc.), 2 to 6 subframes can be used for spectrum sharing.    If NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssMbsfnRatio.minValue and NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssMbsfnRatio.maxValue are equal to the same value, this ratio will be used without any change of sharing capable subframes.

This parameter indicates the maximum MBSFN subframe sharing ratio for LTE-NR dynamic spectrum sharing. Between 2 and 6 MBSFN subframes are available for spectrum sharing.    If NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssMbsfnRatio.minValue and NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssMbsfnRatio.maxValue are equal to the same value, the sharing ratio is fixed to this value

This parameter indicates the minimum MBSFN subframe sharing ratio for LTE-NR dynamic spectrum sharing. Between 2 and 6 MBSFN subframes are available for spectrum sharing.    If NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssMbsfnRatio.minValue and NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssMbsfnRatio.maxValue are equal to the same value, the sharing ratio is fixed to this value
This parameter indicates the uplink sharing ratio for dynamic spectrum sharing between LTE and NR.

This parameter indicates the maximum uplink sharing ratio for dynamic LTE-NR spectrum sharing. gNB can re-configure the UL sharing ratio used for dynamic spectrum sharing between NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssUlRatio.minNrDssRatio and NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssUlRatio.maxNrDssRatio.    If NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssUlRatio.minNrDssRatio is equal to NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssUlRatio.maxNrDssRatio, the sharing ratio is fixed to this value.

This parameter indicates the minimum uplink sharing ratio for dynamic LTE-NR spectrum sharing. gNB can re-configure the UL sharing ratio used for dynamic spectrum sharing between NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssUlRatio.minNrDssRatio and NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssUlRatio.maxNrDssRatio.    If NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssUlRatio.minNrDssRatio is equal to NRDSSLTE.lteNrDssUlRatio.maxNrDssRatio, the sharing ratio is fixed to this value.

Parameter name: LTE physical cell identifier of the partner cell
Description: This parameter indicates the physical cell identifier of the LTE partner cell.  The value of the LTE partner cell identifier can be found in LNCEL.phyCellId under MRBTS/LNBTS.
This parameter indicates the position of the SSB.  The position must be defined that it does not collide with the SSB position used by the LTE partner cell.

Parameter name: New Radio Distributed Unit instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Distributed Unit (NRDU) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.

Parameter name: Activate mobility support for mixed carrier aggregation in connected mode
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the mobility support for mixed carrier aggregation mode including FDD-FR1 TDD 2CC CA, FDD-FDD 2CC/3CC CA, FR1 TDD-FR1 TDD 2CC CA and FR1 TDD-FDD CA in connected mode
This parameter activates/deactivates inter-gNB carrier aggregation features.

This parameter activates/deactivates enhanced carrier aggregation required by Inter Band Carrier Aggregation features in case aggregated carriers are with different numerology (SCS) or different duplex mode (FDD/TDD).  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter activates/deactivates AI/ML based 5G CA SCell activation feature.

Parameter name: Activate non beamforming and beamforming TDD FR1 CA
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates TDD FR1 non beamforming cell and TDD FR1 beamforming cell carrier aggregation.  Updating this parameter will provoke gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter activates/deactivates UL carrier aggregation with 3 TX layers.
This parameter defines the administrative state of the New Radio Distributed Unit.  It sets permission to use or prohibition against using the resource, imposed through the management services.
This parameter indicates the list of 5G carrier aggregation features that are supported, excluding the aggregation for Intra-band Carrier in FR2.
Range and step: none (0), ca_Fdd_Fdd (3), ca_Fdd_Fr1Tdd_Sa (200), ca_Fdd_Fr1Tdd_Nsa (201), ca_Fdd_Fr1Tdd_Sa_WithUl (210), ca_Fdd_Fdd_Sa_WithUl (310), ca_Fr1Tdd_Sa (400), ca_Fr1Tdd_Nsa (401), ca_Fr1Tdd_Fr1Tdd_Sa_WithUl (410), ca_Fr1Tdd_Fdd_Sa (500), ca_Fr1Tdd_Fdd_Nsa (501), ca_Fr1Tdd_Fdd_Sa_WithUl (510), ca_Fdd_Any_Sa (600), ca_Fr1Tdd_Any_Sa (700)

Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter indicates the maximum number of FR1 cells that are supported in one gNB-DU for C-RNTI allocation.    The 'max72cellsEnh' option introduces an optimized method for C-RNTI allocation, which must be activated in conjunction with the NRBTS.actAutoPrachConfigIndexFddEnh functionality.    Modifying the value of this parameter will provoke a gNB reset.

Parameter name: Contribution percentage of DL data rate
Description: This parameter indicates the contribution percentage of the DL data rate versus the contribution percentage of UL data rate to the overall data rate of a given band combination and corresponding feature set during the band combination and feature set selection process in FR1.  For example:  - Value 0 means that there is no contribution in DL and full contribution in UL.  - Value 50 means equal contribution in DL and in UL.  - Value 80 means 80% contribution in DL and 20% contribution in UL.  - Value 100 means that there is full contribution in DL and no contribution in UL.  - Value 101 is a special value which means the old algorithm is used which checks the DL bit rate is checked first and if DL bit rate is the same between several band combinations and the corresponding feature sets, the UL bit rate is checked.

This parameter indicates the flexible 5G FR1 carrier aggregation mode.    The supported values are:  - BasicCAMode meaning that carrier aggregation is not supported  - MixedCAMode meaning that the carrier aggregation for FDD-FR1 TDD, FDD-FDD, FR1 TDD-FDD and FR1 TDD-FR1 TDD are supported and they can be configured within the same gNB.  - ConfigurationIndependent meaning that, in addition to the MixedCAMode mode, the carrier aggregation for FDD-FDD can be configured within the same gNB with no SISO restriction.  - NumberCellAmount meaning that, in addition to the ConfigurationIndependent mode, FDD cell amount could increase for baseband modules with (DSP based, e.g. ABIO, ABIN and ASOE, maximum of 24 cells for ABIO, maximum of 12 cells for ABIN and maximum of 16 cells for ASOE and RINLINE2) and FDD-FDD carrier aggregation between the cells in the same core are supported.    Modifying the value of this parameter will provoke a gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: Preference for FR1 UL CA in gNB-DU
Description: This parameter indicates whether estimated DL and UL data rate or FR1 UL CA is preferred when doing band combination and feature set selection in the gNB-DU.  This parameter will take effect when NRBTS.actHighestEstNrTputBcSel is equal to TRUE.

This parameter uniquely identifies the gNB-DU at least within a gNB-CU. It is configured at the gNB-DU. The parameter value is set in the F1AP: F1 Setup Request message sent by the gNB-DU to the gNB-CU over the F1 interface.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter defines a name for the gNB-DU. It is configured at the gNB-DU. The parameter value is set in the F1AP: F1 Setup Request message sent by the gNB-DU to the gNB-CU over the F1 interface.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter indicates the RRC version for the gNB-DU.  It is configured at the gNB-DU. The parameter value is set in the F1AP: F1 Setup Request message sent by the gNB-DU to the gNB-CU over the F1 interface.
This parameter indicates the local CU IPv4/v6 address

Parameter name: Maximum number of RRC connected users in DU
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of RRC connected users for SA, NSA and NR-DC-SN users in DU.    Note: inter-gNB CA users are also counted in the DU(s) of the gNB(s) that hosts UE's SCell(s).

Parameter name: BTS level Parameter set for CA use case
Description: This parameter contains the parameter set of BTS level parameters for AI/ML based 5G CA SCell activation use case

Parameter name: Interval period for ML Data Collection
Description: This parameter is used to configure interval period for reporting data from data collection clients to ML data collection engine.
This parameter defines the operational state of ML training for CA secondary cell activation use case.

Parameter name: Number of DRB resources reserved for emergency calls
Description: This parameter indicates the number of DRB resources reserved for emergency calls at NR DU level.  Admission control shall reserve specific amount of DRB resources on DU for emergency calls.

Parameter name: Number of DRBs reserved for priority access
Description: This parameter indicates the number of DRBs reserved pool for Priority Access calls as defined by NRBTS-applyPriorityAccess at NRDU level.

Parameter name: Number of DRBs reserved for temporary use by regular UEs for proactive preemption
Description: This parameter indicates the number of DRB resources reserved at NR DU level for temporary use during preemption.
The parameter specifies the old distinguished name of the managed object before a configuration change like rehosting. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter defines the operational state of the NR Distributed Unit.  It shows if the resource is physically installed and working.

This parameter indicates the list of NRCELLGRP instances assigned to this NRDU instance.  Example: refNrCellGroup = 1 (refers to NRCELLGRP-1)    Note: NRCELLGRP.nrCellList provides the list of NRCELL (5G Cell) associated to the NRCELLGRP and therefore to this NRDU (gNB-DU).    The configuration of this parameter during NRCELL and NRCELLGRP instance addition will not provoke a gNB reset.  When modifying this parameter, the gNB takes the decision whether reset is needed or not.  The removal of this parameter during NRCELL and NRCELLGRP instance deletion will not provoke a gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter indicates the remote DU IPv4/v6 address    Note: If value is set by operator, it is ignored until actDynamicFirewall is true

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the target APEQM instance that is associated with this NRDU instance. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/EQM-1/APEQM-1  APEQM-1    Updating this parameter without changing the referenced instance will be performed on-line.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: List of supported UL TX switching features
Description: This parameter indicates the list of UL TX switching features that are supported.
This structure indicates the list of distinguished names representing the Xg User Plane IP addresses that are used for inter-gNB carrier aggregation.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV4 instance representing the primary IPv4 address of Xg User Plane for inter-gNB carrier aggregation. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV6 instance representing the primary IPv6 address of Xg User Plane for inter-gNB carrier aggregation. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the New Radio PLMN instance representing the Xg User Plane for inter-gNB carrier aggregation. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1

Parameter name: New Radio E2 link instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio E2 link instance within the same containing NRBTS instance  It represents the New Radio E2 link connection to Near RT RIC instance identifier.

This parameter defines the administrative state of the NR E2 link.  It allows the customer to lock/unlock the NR E2 link. Locking the NR E2 link means closing the SCTP association between the gNB and the NR Near_RT RIC. Unlocking the NR E2 link means triggering the SCTP association establishment and E2AP Setup procedures.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter indicates whether the E2 link for ORAN gNB is successfully established (active) or not (inactive).

Parameter name: New Radio E2 Node instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio E2 Node instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: New Radio Emergency ARP Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Emergency ARP Profile (NREMERGARP_PROFILE) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance  NREMERGARP_PROFILE-1 is the default profile to use in case no PLMN related Emergency ARP Profile is found for one UE irrespective of PLMN configured in NREMERGARP_PROFILE-1.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter indicates the list of allocation and retention priority levels used to prioritize an emergency call over a normal call when emergency call extensions is enabled.  The range of the ARP priority level is 1 to 15 with 1 as the highest level of priority. For emergency sessions, only ARP priority levels 1-8 may be applied (3GPP TS23.501).

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of a New Radio PLMN (NRPLMN) instance to be used for the New Radio Emergency ARP Profile. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1

Parameter name: NR forced switched off power group instance identifier
Description: This parameter indicates the identifier of the NRFSOPGRP instance within the NRBTS instance.

This parameter indicates the New Radio forced cell switch off type:  - 'TimeWindow' means that selected cells are to be switched off/on according to the defined time window.  - 'LowVoltage' means that selected cells are to be switched off/on according to the defined voltage thresholds.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Low voltage cell switch off/on thresholds
Description: This parameter gathers the low voltage cell switch off/on thresholds.

Parameter name: Low voltage cell switch off threshold
Description: This parameter defines the Radio Module (RMOD) input voltage threshold for cell switch off.    Note: The defined threshold value is valid for all RMODs mapped to selected cells in a given NRFSOPGRP instance, and should be configured within the range of nominal input voltage for RU/RUs.

Parameter name: Low voltage cell switch on threshold
Description: This parameter defines the Radio Module (RMOD) input voltage threshold for cell switch on.    Note: The defined threshold value is valid for all RMODs mapped to selected cells in a given NRFSOPGRP instance, and should be configured within the range of nominal input voltage for RU/RUs.
This parameter identifies the NRCELL instance(s) in the New Radio forced switch off power group using NRCELL.nrCellId value.

Parameter name: Time window cell switch off/on period list
Description: This parameter gathers the time window cell switch off/on period parameters.

Parameter name: Forced switch off day of week
Description: This parameter indicates the day of the week for which the power saving period is defined for a specific NR cell.
Range and step: Sun (0), Mon (1), Tue (2), Wed (3), Thu (4), Fri (5), Sat (6), everyDay (7)

Parameter name: Forced switched off power saving duration
Description: This parameter indicates the end time of the power saving period for a specific NR cell.    The power saving period for a specific NR cell begins at the load-based power saving start time for this specific NR cell (NRFSOPGRP.timeWindowCellSwitchOffList.fsoStartHour and NRFSOPGRP.timeWindowCellSwitchOffList.fsoStartMinute) and continues for a number of minutes in NRFSOPGRP.timeWindowCellSwitchOffList.fsoDuration.

Parameter name: Forced switched off start time hour
Description: This parameter indicates, along with NRFSOPGRP.timeWindowCellSwitchOffList.fsoStartMinute, the local time when the power saving period begins for a specific NR cell.

Parameter name: Forced switched off start time minute
Description: This parameter indicates, along with NRFSOPGRP.timeWindowCellSwitchOffList.fsoStartHour, the local time when the power saving period begins for a specific NR cell.

Parameter name: New Radio GPRS Tunnel Protocol User Plane instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio GPRS Tunnel Protocol User Plane (NRGTPU) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Maximum number of unanswered N3 requests
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of GTP-U: ECHO REQUEST messages transmitted without acknowledgement before the gNB will consider the path as failed.
This parameter indicates the time between the sending of two GTP-U: ECHO REQUEST.

Parameter name: T3 maximum waiting time for GTP-U responses
Description: This parameter indicates the T3 maximum time during which the gNB expects to receive GTP-U ECHO RESPONSE messages.
This parameter indicates the time the gNB waits for path recovery in case of failure.

Parameter name: New Radio Handover to Neighbouring Inter-frequency NR Cell instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Handover to Neighbouring Inter-frequency NR Cell (NRHOIF) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRCELL instance.    Note: The NRHOIF instances are also used for reasons other than handover (e.g. NR-DC establishment).

Parameter name: A1 measurement based primary cell switch enabled
Description: This parameter enables/disables primary cell switch (inter-frequency handover to configured secondary cell to prevent UL overload in the current primary cell) for carrier aggregation based on UE measurement.  Primary cell switch is triggered by event A1 measuring the secondary cell. It is applicable to DL carrier aggregation case, when the primary cell has limited UL capacity.

Parameter name: A2 measurement based primary cell switch enabled
Description: This parameter enables/disables primary cell switch (inter-frequency handover to configured secondary cell in the current primary cell) for carrier aggregation based on UE measurement  Primary cell switch is triggered by event A2 measuring the primary cell.

Parameter name: A2 based primary cell switch priority
Description: This parameter indicates the priority of the cell as secondary cell to be selected as target cell of A2 based primary cell switch (inter-frequency handover to configured secondary cell in the current primary cell).  The higher value of the parameter means the lower priority.
This parameter indicates the measurement configuration that is enabled on event A3.  This can be the RSRP measurement or the RSRQ measurement or both or a combined criteria.
Range and step: none (0), rsrp (1), rsrq (2), rsrpAndRsrq (3), rsrpCombined (4), rsrqCombined (5)

Description: This parameter gathers all the associated parameters used to characterize the set of A3 measurement for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP.
This parameter indicates the hysteresis value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3.

Parameter name: A3 hysteresis SSB RSRP for VoNr UEs
Description: This parameter indicates the hysteresis value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3 for VoNr UEs

This parameter defines the offset value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3.    The offset value configured in this parameter is not the actual value used in the measurement quantity RSRP applied at the UE side in NR measurement report triggering.    The UE derives the actual a3-Offset in dB to be applied as follows:  actual a3-Offset = value configured in this parameter * 0.5 dB.    Examples:  - If this parameter is equal to 3, then the actual a3-Offset derived by the UE is equal to 3 * 0.5 dB = 1.5 dB  - If this parameter is equal to 6, then the actual a3-Offset derived by the UE is equal to 6 * 0.5 dB = 3 dB

Parameter name: A3 offset SSB RSRP for VoNr UEs
Description: This parameter defines the offset value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3 for VoNr UEs.    The offset value configured in this parameter is not the actual value used in the measurement quantity RSRP applied at the UE side in NR measurement report triggering.    The UE derives the actual a3-Offset in dB to be applied as follows:  actual a3-Offset = value configured in this parameter * 0.5 dB.    Examples:  - If this parameter is equal to 3, then the actual a3-Offset derived by the UE is equal to 3 * 0.5 dB = 1.5 dB  - If this parameter is equal to 6, then the actual a3-Offset derived by the UE is equal to 6 * 0.5 dB = 3 dB

Parameter name: A3 time to trigger SSB RSRP
Description: This parameter defines the time during which specific criteria for the event needs to be met in order to trigger a measurement report for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3.

Parameter name: A3 time to trigger SSB RSRP for VoNr UEs
Description: This parameter defines the time during which specific criteria for the event needs to be met in order to trigger a measurement report for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3 for VoNr UEs
This parameter gathers all the associated parameters used to characterize the set of A3 measurement for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ.
This parameter indicates the hysteresis value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3.

Parameter name: A3 hysteresis SSB RSRQ for VoNr UEs
Description: This parameter indicates the hysteresis value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3 for VoNr UEs

This parameter defines the offset value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3.    The offset value configured in this parameter is not the actual value used in the measurement quantity RSRQ applied at the UE side in NR measurement report triggering.    The UE derives the actual a3-Offset in dB to be applied as follows:  actual a3-Offset = value configured in this parameter * 0.5 dB.    Examples:  - If this parameter is equal to 3, then the actual a3-Offset derived by the UE is equal to 3 * 0.5 dB = 1.5 dB  - If this parameter is equal to 6, then the actual a3-Offset derived by the UE is equal to 6 * 0.5 dB = 3 dB

Parameter name: A3 offset SSB RSRQ for VoNr UEs
Description: This parameter defines the offset value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3 for VoNr UEs    The offset value configured in this parameter is not the actual value used in the measurement quantity RSRQ applied at the UE side in NR measurement report triggering.    The UE derives the actual a3-Offset in dB to be applied as follows:  actual a3-Offset = value configured in this parameter * 0.5 dB.    Examples:  - If this parameter is equal to 3, then the actual a3-Offset derived by the UE is equal to 3 * 0.5 dB = 1.5 dB  - If this parameter is equal to 6, then the actual a3-Offset derived by the UE is equal to 6 * 0.5 dB = 3 dB

Parameter name: A3 time to trigger SSB RSRQ
Description: This parameter defines the time during which specific criteria for the event needs to be met in order to trigger a measurement report for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3.

Parameter name: A3 time to trigger SSB RSRQ for VoNr UEs
Description: This parameter defines the time during which specific criteria for the event needs to be met in order to trigger a measurement report for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3 for VoNr UEs

Parameter name: Priority for inter-frequency A3/A5 without mobility profile
Description: This parameter indicates the priority defined for inter-freq frequency defined for A3/A5 measurement in case of strategy based on priorities.  Value 1 means the highest priority, while value 100 means the lowest priority.

Parameter name: A4 measurement configuration enabled for EN-DC idle mode traffic steering
Description: This parameter indicates the measurement configuration that is enabled on event A4 for EN-DC aware idle mode traffic steering.  This can be the RSRP measurement or the RSRQ measurement or both or a combined criteria.
Range and step: none (0), rsrp (1), rsrq (2), rsrpAndRsrq (3), rsrpCombined (4), rsrqCombined (5)

Parameter name: A4 measurement SSB RSRP for EN-DC idle mode traffic steering
Description: This parameter gathers all the associated parameters used to characterize the set of A4 measurement for EN-DC aware idle mode traffic steering and measurement quantities RSRP.

Parameter name: A4 hysteresis SSB RSRP for EN-DC idle mode traffic steering
Description: This parameter indicates the hysteresis value in measurement quantities RSRP to be used in measurement report triggering condition on event A4 for EN-DC aware idle mode traffic steering.

Parameter name: A4 threshold SSB RSRP for EN-DC idle mode traffic steering
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold value in measurement quantities RSRP to be used in measurement report triggering condition on event A4 for EN-DC aware idle mode traffic steering.

Parameter name: A4 time to trigger SSB RSRP for EN-DC idle mode traffic steering
Description: This parameter indicates the time during which specific criteria for the event needs to be met in order to trigger a measurement report for EN-DC aware idle mode traffic steering and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in measurement report triggering condition on event A4.

Parameter name: A4 measurement SSB RSRQ for EN-DC idle mode traffic steering
Description: This parameter gathers all the associated parameters used to characterize the set of A4 measurement for EN-DC aware idle mode traffic steering and measurement quantities RSRQ.

Parameter name: A4 hysteresis SSB RSRQ for EN-DC idle mode traffic steering
Description: This parameter indicates the hysteresis value in measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in measurement report triggering condition on event A4 for EN-DC aware idle mode traffic steering.

Parameter name: A4 threshold SSB RSRQ for EN-DC idle mode traffic steering
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold value in measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in measurement report triggering condition on event A4 for EN-DC aware idle mode traffic steering.

Parameter name: A4 time to trigger SSB RSRQ for EN-DC idle mode traffic steering
Description: This parameter indicates the time during which specific criteria for the event needs to be met in order to trigger a measurement report for EN-DC aware idle mode traffic steering and measurement quantities RSRQ to be used in measurement report triggering condition on event A4.

Parameter name: A4 measurement configuration to higher priority NR frequency enabled
Description: This parameter indicates the measurement configuration to higher priority NR frequency that is enabled on event A4.  This can be the RSRP measurement or the RSRQ measurement or both or a combined criteria.
Range and step: none (0), rsrp (1), rsrq (2), rsrpAndRsrq (3), rsrpCombined (4), rsrqCombined (5)

Parameter name: A4 measurement configuration for NR-DC PSCell addition enabled
Description: This parameter indicates the measurement configuration that is enabled on event A4 for NR-DC PSCell addition.    Possible values for such measurement are the following:  - none: no measurement is activated on given frequency layer (such frequency cannot be used as target for NR-DC PSCell addition)  - rsrp: measurement with MeasTriggerQuantity configured to rsrp is used  - rsrq: measurement with MeasTriggerQuantity configured to rsrq is used  - rsrpAndRsrq: two measurements with MeasTriggerQuantity configured respectively to rsrp and rsrq are used  - rsrpCombined: measurement with MeasTriggerQuantity configured to rsrp is used, but NR-DC PSCell addition can be started only if also rsrq criterion is met  - rsrqCombined: measurement with MeasTriggerQuantity configured to rsrq is used, but NR-DC PSCell addition can be started only if also rsrp criterion is met
Range and step: none (0), rsrp (1), rsrq (2), rsrpAndRsrq (3), rsrpCombined (4), rsrqCombined (5)

Parameter name: A4 measurement SSB RSRP for NR-DC PSCell addition

Parameter name: A4 hysteresis SSB RSRP for NR-DC PSCell addition
Description: This parameter indicates the hysteresis value for A4 SSB RSRP NR-DC PSCell addition measurement.

Parameter name: A4 threshold SSB RSRP for NR-DC PSCell addition
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold value for A4 SSB RSRP NR-DC PSCell addition measurement.    The actual value is (a4ThresholdNrDcSsbRsrp - 156) dBm, except for the IE value 127, in which case the actual value is infinity.

Parameter name: A4 time to trigger SSB RSRP for NR-DC PSCell addition
Description: This parameter indicates the time during which specific criteria for the event needs to be met in order to trigger an A4 SSB RSRP NR-DC PSCell addition measurement.    Value ms0 corresponds to 0 ms, value ms40 corresponds to 40 ms, and so on.

Parameter name: A4 measurement SSB RSRQ for NR-DC PSCell addition

Parameter name: A4 threshold SSB RSRQ for NR-DC PSCell addition
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold value for A4 SSB RSRQ NR-DC PSCell addition measurement.    The actual value is (a4ThresholdNrDcSsbRsrq value - 87) / 2 dB.

Parameter name: A4 time to trigger SSB RSRQ for NR-DC PSCell addition
Description: This parameter indicates the time during which specific criteria for the event needs to be met in order to trigger an A4 SSB RSRQ NR-DC PSCell addition measurement.    Value ms0 corresponds to 0 ms, value ms40 corresponds to 40 ms, and so on.

Parameter name: A4 measurement configuration for secondary cell addition enabled
Description: This parameter indicates the measurement configuration on primary cell that is enabled on event A4 for secondary cell addition.  The following values are defined:  - 'none': A4 measurements for SCell addition are disabled for the frequency corresponding to this NRHOIF instance.  - 'rsrp': a single UE measurement is configured with RSRP event criteria. The A4-based SCell candidate is meant as in-coverage if the measurement contains its PCI.  - 'rsrq': a single UE measurement is configured with RSRQ event criteria. The A4-based SCell candidate is meant as in-coverage if the measurement contains its PCI.  - 'rsrpAndRsrq': two UE measurements are configured, one with RSRP and one with RSRQ event criteria. The A4-based SCell candidate is meant as in-coverage if any of those measurements contains its PCI.  - 'rsrpCombined': a single UE measurement is configured with RSRP event criteria. The A4-based SCell candidate is meant as in-coverage if additionally RSRQ criteria is also met (RSRQ criteria checked by the gNB) for its PCI.  - 'rsrqCombined': a single UE measurement is configured with RSRQ event criteria. The A4-based SCell candidate is meant as in-coverage if additionally RSRP criteria is also met (RSRP criteria checked by gNB) for its PCI
Range and step: none (0), rsrp (1), rsrq (2), rsrpAndRsrq (3), rsrpCombined (4), rsrqCombined (5)

This parameter indicates the SSB positions in burst set of the corresponding FR1 neighboring cells (see 3GPP TS38.331).  It is a bit mask with Bit 0 (LSB) corresponding to SS/PBCH Index 0, Bit 1 corresponding to SS/PBCH Index 1, ... Bit 7 corresponding to SS/PBCH Index 7.  If Bit x is equal to 1, SS/PBCH Index x is active with the corresponding SS/PBCH configured.  If Bit x is equal to 0, SS/PBCH Index x is inactive with the corresponding SS/PBCH not configured.
Range and step: bits mask: SS/PBCH Index 0 (0), SS/PBCH Index 1 (1), SS/PBCH Index 2 (2), SS/PBCH Index 3 (3), SS/PBCH Index 4 (4), SS/PBCH Index 5 (5), SS/PBCH Index 6 (6), SS/PBCH Index 7 (7)

Range and step: 1 beam (1), 2 beams (2), 4 beams (4), 6 beams (6), 8 beams (8), 9 beams (9), 12 beams (12), 15 beams (15), 18 beams (18), 21 beams (21), 24 beams (24), 32 beams (32)

Parameter name: P-Max for inter-frequency neighbouring NR cells
Description: This parameter indicates the p-Max for inter frequency neighbouring NR cell.

Parameter name: List of PCI values for excludelisted cells
Description: This structure gathers the list of PCI values that are excluded in each serving cell
This parameter indicates the first physical layer cell identity in a list of PCI values of neighbouring intra frequency cells to be statically excluded in the serving cell
This parameter indicates the number of physical cell identifiers in the range (including NRIRFIM.pciExcludeList.physCellId).

Parameter name: Frequency specific offset for equal priority NR frequencies
Description: This parameter indicates the frequency specific offset for equal priority NR frequencies.

Parameter name: Minimum required quality level in the inter freq cell
Description: This parameter indicates the minimum required quality level for the inter frequency neighbour cell( dB).  Actual qQualmin value = field value (dB)

Parameter name: Minimum required RX level in the inter frequency cell
Description: This parameter indicates the minimum required RX level for the inter frequency neighbouring cell (dBm).  Actual qRxLevMin value = field value * 2 (dBm).

Parameter name: RedCap access allowed for idle mode reselection
Description: This parameter indicates whether the RedCap UEs are allowed to access and perform idle mode reselection in this frequency (NRIRFIM.dlCarrierFreq).    If this parameter is configured and is equal to TRUE, then, for the cells with activated RedCap support (NRCELL.actRedCapUeSupport equal to TRUE), the gNB will include redCapAccessAllowed IE in SIB4.  If this parameter is configured and is equal to FALSE or is not configured, then, for the cells with activated RedCap support (NRCELL.actRedCapUeSupport equal to TRUE), the gNB will exclude redCapAccessAllowed IE in SIB4.    UEs with reduced capabilities are specified in clause 4.2.21 in TS 38.306.

Parameter name: Scaling factor for high mobility state
Description: This parameter indicates the scaling (multiplying) factor to be applied in high mobility state to the NRSYSINFO_PROFILE.qHyst value.  oDot25 corresponds to 0.25, oDot5 corresponds to 0.5, oDot75 corresponds to 0.75 and so on.

Parameter name: Scaling factor for medium mobility state
Description: This parameter indicates the scaling (multiplying) factor to be applied in medium mobility state to the NRSYSINFO_PROFILE.qHyst value.  oDot25 corresponds to 0.25, oDot5 corresponds to 0.5, oDot75 corresponds to 0.75 and so on.
This parameter indicates the duration of the measurement window in which to receive SS/PBCH blocks.  It is given in number of subframes.
This parameter indicates the offset of the measurement window in which to receive SS/PBCH blocks.  It is given in number of subframes.
This parameter indicates the periodicity of the measurement window in which to receive SS/PBCH blocks.  It is given in number of subframes.

This parameter indicates the SSB positions in burst set of the corresponding FR1 neighboring cells (see 3GPP TS38.331).  It is a bit mask with Bit 0 (LSB) corresponding to SS/PBCH Index 0, Bit 1 corresponding to SS/PBCH Index 1, ... Bit 7 corresponding to SS/PBCH Index 7.  If Bit x is equal to 1, SS/PBCH Index x is active with the corresponding SS/PBCH configured.  If Bit x is equal to 0, SS/PBCH Index x is inactive with the corresponding SS/PBCH not configured.
Range and step: bits mask: SS/PBCH Index 0 (0), SS/PBCH Index 1 (1), SS/PBCH Index 2 (2), SS/PBCH Index 3 (3), SS/PBCH Index 4 (4), SS/PBCH Index 5 (5), SS/PBCH Index 6 (6), SS/PBCH Index 7 (7)

Description: This parameter indicates the subcarrier spacing of SSB of neighbouring inter frequency carrier.
This parameter indicates the cell reselection timer for NR.  Value is in seconds

Parameter name: Threshold Srxlev for reselecting higher priroity RAT/Frequency
Description: This parameter indicates the SrxLev threshold (in dB) used by the UE when reselecting towards a higher priority RAT/ frequency than the current serving frequency.  Actual threshold value = field value * 2 (dB).

Parameter name: Threshold Squal for reselecting higher priroity RAT/Frequency
Description: This parameter indicates the Squal threshold (in dB) used by the UE when reselecting towards a higher priority RAT/ frequency than the current serving frequency.  Actual threshold value = field value (dB).

Parameter name: Threshold Srxlev for reselecting lower priroity RAT/Frequency

Parameter name: Threshold Squal for reselecting lower priroity RAT/Frequency
Description: This parameter indicates the Squal threshold (in dB) used by the UE when reselecting towards a lower priority RAT/ frequency than the current serving frequency.  Actual threshold value = field value (dB).
This parameter indicates the RSRP threshold for the consolidation of the L1 measurements.

This parameter indicates the hysteresis value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3.

This parameter defines the offset value for RS type SS/PBCH blocks and measurement quantities RSRP to be used in NR measurement report triggering condition on event A3.    The offset value configured in this parameter is not the actual value used in the measurement quantity RSRP applied at the UE side in NR measurement report triggering.    The UE derives the actual a3-Offset in dB to be applied as follows:  actual a3-Offset = value configured in this parameter * 0.5 dB.    Examples:  - If this parameter is equal to 3, then the actual a3-Offset derived by the UE is equal to 3 * 0.5 dB = 1.5 dB  - If this parameter is equal to 6, then the actual a3-Offset derived by the UE is equal to 6 * 0.5 dB = 3 dB

This parameter defines the distinguished name of the NRPLMN instance(s) defining each operator for NR RAN Sharing to be used as criterion for matching NRMEASPR_MA_NSA instance selection. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1

This parameter indicates the list of power class capabilities to be used as criterion for matching NRMEASPR_MA_NSA instance selection. NRMEASPR_MA_NSA.pcCapabilityList.freqBandIndicatorNR and NRMEASPR_MA_NSA.pcCapabilityList.uePowerClass are used to check if they match with the UE capabilities for this band. If, for a band, no matching NRMEASPR_MA_NSA.pcCapabilityList.freqBandIndicatorNR is configured in any of the NRMEASPR_MA_NSA.pcCapabilityList elements, then elements having only NRMEASPR_MA_NSA.pcCapabilityList.uePowerClass configured are used as criterion.    Example on how to configure power class capability criterion for an NR Cell in NR operating band N77 and UE supporting UE power class 1.5, and MFBI UE supporting band N78 but not supporting band N77:  NRMEASPR_MA_NSA.pcCapabilityList[1].freqBandIndicatorNR = 77  NRMEASPR_MA_NSA.pcCapabilityList[1].uePowerClass = ue-PowerClass1Dot5  NRMEASPR_MA_NSA.pcCapabilityList[2].freqBandIndicatorNR = 78  NRMEASPR_MA_NSA.pcCapabilityList[2].uePowerClass = ue-PowerClass1Dot5
This parameter indicates the target frequency band indicator NR to measure for checking the corresponding UE Power Class in the UE capabilities.

This parameter defines the UE power class as the maximum transmit power over NR channel bandwidth as per 3GPP TS38.101, TS38.306 and TS38.331 for the frequency band indicator NR defined in NRMEASPR_MA_NSA.pcCapabilityList.freqBandIndicatorNR within the same element of NRMEASPR_MA_NSA.pcCapabilityList.
Range and step: ue-PowerClass1 (10), ue-PowerClass1Dot5 (15), ue-PowerClass2 (20), ue-PowerClass3 (30), ue-PowerClass4 (40), ue-PowerClass5 (50), ue-PowerClass6 (60), ue-PowerClass7 (70)

Description: This parameter indicates the Subscriber Profile ID (SPID) to be used as criterion for matching NRMEASPR_MA_NSA instance selection, and mapped to a measurement profile as follows:  - one SPID value or  - the value of the first SPID of a range and, in this case, the last SPID value of the range shall be configured in NRMEASPR_MA_NSA.spidLast.    As per 3GPP the allowed SPID values are the following:  - Operator specific SPID values: 1...128  - Reference values: 129...256

Parameter name: Last subscriber profile ID of a range
Description: This parameter indicates the last Subscriber Profile ID (SPID) value of a range if a range of SPID values to be used as criterion for matching NRMEASPR_MA_NSA instance selection.  As per 3GPP the allowed SPID values are the following:  - Operator specific SPID values: 2...128  - Reference values: 129...256

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier list for idle mode mobility steering
Description: This structure gathers the list of EUTRAN parameters for idle mode mobility steering.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier frequency for idle mode mobility steering
Description: This parameter indicates the ARFCN applicable for a downlink or bi-directional (TDD) EUTRA carrier frequency for idle mode mobility steering.

Description: This parameter indicates the EUTRA carrier weight factor for idle mode mobility steering.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier weight factor for EN-DC aware idle mode mobility steering
Description: This parameter indicates the EUTRA carrier weight factor for EN-DC aware idle mode mobility steering.

Parameter name: NR carrier list for idle mode mobility steering
Description: This structure gathers the list of NR parameters for idle mode mobility steering.

Parameter name: NR carrier frequency for idle mode mobility steering
Description: This parameter indicates the center frequency of the SS block of the NR carrier used for idle mode mobility steering, where the frequency corresponds to a GSCN value as specified in TS 38.101.

Parameter name: NR carrier weight factor for idle mode mobility steering
Description: This parameter indicates the NR carrier weight factor for DL CA aware / non-CA aware idle mode mobility steering.

Parameter name: NR carrier weight for UL CA aware IMM steering
Description: This parameter indicates the NR carrier weight for UL CA aware idle mode mobility steering.

Parameter name: Percentage of UEs for idle mode mobility steering for EN-DC
Description: This parameter indicates the percentage of UEs to be selected for EN-DC aware idle mode mobility steering.

Parameter name: SSB Frequency for idle mode mobility steering for EN-DC
Description: This parameter indicates the target SSB frequency to be used in evaluating if a UE is a valid candidate for idle mode traffic steering.

Parameter name: Weighted round robin for idle mode mobility steering enabled for EN-DC
Description: This parameter enables/disables weighted round robin for primary target selection for EN-DC aware idle mode Mobility steering.
This parameter indicates the selected algorithm for idle mode mobility steering.  Note: CA aware means DL CA aware algorithm.
Range and step: non CA aware (0), CA aware (1), UL CA aware (2), UL and DL CA aware (3)

Parameter name: Percentage of UEs for idle mode mobility steering
Description: This parameter indicates the percentage of UEs to be selected for idle mode mobility steering.

Parameter name: Weighted round robin for idle mode mobility steering enabled
Description: This parameter enables/disables weighted round robin for primary target selection for idle mode mobility steering

Parameter name: WRR for CA eligible secondary targets in IMM steering
Description: This parameter enables/disables weighted round robin priority assignment for CA eligible secondary target frequencies in UL CA and/or DL CA aware idle mode Mobility steering
Range and step: Disabled (0), DL CA aware (1), UL CA aware (2), UL and DL CA aware (3)

This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Example:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/SNSSAI-25  SNSSAI-25

Description: This parameter indicates the measurement configuration that is enabled on event A1 for handover in NSA mode.  This can be the RSRP measurement or the RSRQ measurement or both or a combined criteria.
Range and step: none (0), rsrp (1), rsrq (2), rsrpAndRsrq (3), rsrpCombined (4), rsrqCombined (5)

This parameter indicates the E-UTRA carrier frequency for redirection used in RRC Release message containing redirectedCarrierInfo IE (TS 38.331).  The parameter value is based on the 3GPP absolute radio frequency channel number ARFCN-ValueEUTRA.
This parameter indicates the SSB frequency of the NR target carrier for redirection used in the RRC release message containing redirectedCarrierInfo IE (TS 38.331).

Parameter name: Redirection priority for RRC connection release
Description: This parameter indicates the priority for target RAT selection during RRC connection release with redirection procedure. If this parameter is not configured, then the NRMORED instance is not eligible for A2 based redirection.    The NRMORED instance having the highest priority supported by the UE is selected as the redirection target for A2 based redirection.  Value 1 means the highest priority, while value 6 means the lowest priority.

Parameter name: Redirection priority for bad UL radio
Description: This parameter indicates the priority for redirection due to bad uplink radio conditions. If this parameter is not configured, then the NRMORED instance is not eligible for redirection due to bad uplink radio conditions.    The NRMORED instance having the highest priority supported by the UE is selected as the redirection target for redirection due to bad uplink radio conditions.  Value 1 means the highest priority, while value 6 means the lowest priority.
This parameter indicates the Radio Access Technology (RAT) to which the UE is redirected via RRC connection release with redirection procedure.

This structure gathers parameters required to control the immediate MDT session.  It is applicable in case NRMTRACECU.jobType is equal to 'ImmediateMDTAndTrace' or 'ImmediateMDTOnly'.

Parameter name: Cell maximum immediate MDT UEs traced
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum simultaneous number of active UEs that can be traced by PCMD and/or cell trace within a cell on the gNB-CU, allowed to enable MDT UE measurements.

This parameter controls whether the gNB requests the UE to attempt to provide detailed location information.  The UE is requested to attempt to have valid detailed location information available whenever sending a measurement report for which it is configured to include available detailed location information.  The UE may not succeed e.g. because the user manually disabled the GPS hardware, due to no/poor satellite coverage. Further details, e.g. regarding when to activate GNSS, are up to UE implementation.  If this parameter is equal to FALSE, the gNB does not send the includeCommonLocationInfo-r16 field in RRC signaling to UE.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE, the gNB sends the includeCommonLocationInfo-r16 field in RRC signaling to UEs, which are GNSS capable and are 3GPP Release 16 (or higher).

This parameter indicates whether the GNSS positioning method is applied to the immediate MDT job or no positioning method is used.  If this parameter is equal to 'GNSS', the UE will provide the GPS location information, if available, in the measurement report.  Only GNSS is supported as a positioning method with immediate MDT.

This parameter is used to limit the immediate MDT to those UEs which are GNSS capable.  If this parameter is equal to FALSE, any UE (independently of GNSS capability) can be considered for immediate MDT.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE, only GNSS capable UEs will be configured for immediate MDT.

This structure gathers parameters required to configure MDT UE measurements for the purpose of trace.  It is applicable in case NRMTRACECU.jobType is equal to 'ImmediateMDTAndTrace' or 'ImmediateMDTOnly'.
This parameter indicates the measurement collection trigger for immediate MDT.
This parameter indicates the number of periodic ReportStrongestCells measurement reports configured at the UE
This parameter indicates the time interval between two consecutive periodic ReportStrongestCells measurement reports configured at the UE
This parameter enables/disables the event-triggered measurement collection for immediate MDT according to the existing RRM configuration.

This parameter indicates the type of trace session.  The possible values are the following:  - 'TraceOnly' meaning no M1 measurements are installed for the UEs selected for trace session. Cell trace or PCMD content is traced or both (recorded and sent to the Trace Collection Entity).  - 'ImmediateMDTAndTrace' meaning M1 measurements are installed for the UEs selected for trace session. M1 measurements are traced together with Cell trace and/or PCMD content.  - 'ImmediateMDTOnly' meaning only M1 measurements are traced for selected UEs.

Parameter name: New Radio Network Signaling Pmax List
Description: This parameter indicates the list of allowed additional Pmax and additional spectrum emission (ASE), together with a priority, associated with a band. Thus, in a first step, only a single pair will be allowed.

Description: This parameter defines the MCS threshold of fallback from high reliability to legacy default BLER management for UE with 64QAM MCS table. After fallback, the high reliability DRBs of the UE should be treated as basic reliability DRB using legacy link adaptation.

Description: This parameter indicates the MCS threshold of fallback from high reliability to legacy default BLER management for UE with 64QAM low SE MCS table. After fallback, the high reliability DRBs of the UE should be treated as basic reliability DRB using legacy link adaptation.

Parameter name: Scale factor for high reliability GBR DRB in DL
Description: This parameter defines the scale (multiplier) factor for high reliability GBR DRB in downlink radio admission control.  The scale factor represents the increased resource usage of GBR DRB caused by lower spectral efficiency when high reliability link adaptation is applied.
