Parameter name: Load-based power saving cSON control enabled
Description: This parameter indicates whether the cSON solution is enabled to control the power group's cell membership and Load-based power saving cell switch off order (NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsCellSOOrder).  If this parameter is set to TRUE, the cSON solution application can create, delete and modify the NR power group cell list entries as well as set NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsCellSOOrder of the NR power group and determine whether to enable the last NR cell resource to be switched off (including cell switched off or TX switched off).  If this parameter is set to false, the cSON solution  - cannot add NR cells to, or remove NR cells from the NR power group  - cannot change neither NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsCellSOOrder nor NRPGRP.lbpsLastCellSOEnabled of the power group.
This parameter indicates the list of NR cells that service the same coverage area or follow the same power saving schedule and are included in the NR Power Group.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving cell switch off order
Description: This parameter indicates the relative number within a sequence in which the NR cell identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.nrCellId has its resources switched off (including cell switched off or TX switched off) if the capacity of the enabled NR cells in the NR power group can support the current load.  NR Cells have their resources switched off according to the value of this parameter from the lowest value onwards.  Value 100 for this parameter has a special meaning:  - If NRPGRP.lbpsLastCellSOEnabled is equal to TRUE, the NR Cell is considered to have the lowest cell resource switch off order value.  - If NRPGRP.lbpsLastCellSOEnabled is equal to FALSE, the cell resources cannot be switched off.

Parameter name: Use load-based power saving extended configurations
Description: This parameter indicates if it is allowed to modify, at individual NR cell level, the power saving method to be applied and time windows under which switch off is allowed.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE for a NR cell but no entry is found for the corresponding NR cell under NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList, then the NR cell is not allowed to switch off at all any resource during the time window indicated by NRPGRP.lbpsPeriodList.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE for a NR cell and at least an entry is found for the corresponding NR cell under NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList, then the NR cell is allowed to switch off resources using the switch off method indicated by NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellSOMethod, and only during the time window indicated by the corresponding entry under NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.

This parameter identifies the NRCELL instance in the NR power group.  If NRBTS.actNrLBmMimoRTXPowerSaving is equal to TRUE and NRPGRP.lbpsSOMethod is equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off' and this parameter needs to be configured for a mMIMO RU cell, then configuring or updating this parameter will provoke cell reset of the target NRCELL instance.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving cell period list
Description: This parameter indicates the list of periods during which power saving may be initiated for the NR cell identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.nrCellId in the NR power group. Power saving for the NR cell does not occur in the cell level time window defined by NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList that is outside the NR power group level time window defined by NRPGRP.lbpsPeriodList.    The time window defined at NR power group level by NRPGRP.lbpsPeriodList creates an envelope outside of which energy saving actions are not allowed. This means that if NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsUseExtConfig is equal to TRUE for a NR cell (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.nrCellId) and a NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList entry is found for the corresponding NR cell (NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.nrCellId equal to NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.nrCellId) with a cell level time window period outside the time window indicated by NRPGRP.lbpsPeriodList, then the cell resources are not allowed to switch off outside the time window defined at NR power group level by NRPGRP.lbpsPeriodList.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving day of week for a specific NR cell
Description: This parameter indicates the day of the week for which the power saving period is defined for a specific NR cell.
Range and step: Sun (0), Mon (1), Tue (2), Wed (3), Thu (4), Fri (5), Sat (6)

Parameter name: Load-based power saving duration for a specific NR cell
Description: This parameter indicates the end time of the power saving period for a specific NR cell.  The power saving period for a specific NR cell begins at the load-based power saving start time for this specific NR cell (NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellStartTimeHour and NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellStartTimeMinute) and continues for a number of minutes in NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellDuration.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving switch off method for a specific NR cell
Description: This parameter indicates the load-based power saving switch off method used for a specific NR cell when cell level extended configuration for power saving applies to this specific NR cell.    If NRBTS.actNrLBmMimoRTXPowerSaving is equal to TRUE and this parameter needs to be updated for a mMIMO RU cell (NRCELL instance with NRCELL.nrCellId equal to NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.nrCellId for the current NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList element and served by a RMOD instance with PHYANT instance defined) and no element exists for this NR cell in NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList with NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellSOMethod equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off' and NRPGRP.lbpsSOMethod is equal to 'cell switch off', then updating this parameter from 'cell switch off' to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off' will provoke mMIMO RU cell reset.
Range and step: cell switch off (0), TX switch off (1), mixed switch off (2)

Parameter name: Load-based power saving start time hour for a specific NR cell
Description: This parameter indicates, along with NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellStartTimeMinute, the local time when the power saving period begins for a specific NR cell.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving start time minute for a specific NR cell
Description: This parameter indicates, along with NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellStartTimeHour, the local time when the power saving period begins for a specific NR cell.

This parameter identifies the NRCELL instance in the NR power group for cell level extended configuration for MIMO muting and cell switch off.    If NRBTS.actNrLBmMimoRTXPowerSaving is equal to TRUE and this parameter needs to be configured for a mMIMO RU cell (NRCELL instance with NRCELL.nrCellId equal to the target NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.nrCellId and served by a RMOD instance with PHYANT instance defined) and NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellSOMethod for the current NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList element is equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off' and no element exists for this NR cell in NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList with NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellSOMethod equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off' and NRPGRP.lbpsSOMethod is equal to 'cell switch off', then configuring or updating this parameter will provoke cell reset of the target NRCELL instance.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving last cell minimum load
Description: This parameter indicates the low watermark for the aggregate load of a NR power group.  The gNB will switch off a NR power group cell in cell switch off order if the aggregate power group load is less than the low watermark value in NRPGRP.lbpsMinLoad and the expected aggregate power group load for the reduced aggregate power group capacity is less than the high watermark value in NRPGRP.lbpsMaxLoad. NRPGRP.lbpsMinLoad is used except when determining whether the last enabled cell in the NR Power Group may be switched off; in that case, NRPGRP.lbpsLastCellMinLoad is used. It is recommended to set NRPGRP.lbpsMinLoad to a value strictly lower than NRPGRP.lbpsMaxLoad/2 to avoid a situation where a cell is switched off due to the power group load being below NRPGRP.lbpsMinLoad and within a few minutes is switched on due to the power group load increasing above NRPGRP.lbpsMaxLoad.    Note: This parameter is only used for NRPGRP instances with NRPGRP.lbpsSOMethod equal to 'cell switch off' or 'mixed switch off' and for NRPGRP instances with at least one NR cell (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.nrCellId) having NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsUseExtConfig equal to TRUE and one corresponding element in NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.nrCellId) has NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellSOMethod equal to 'cell switch off' or 'mixed switch off'.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving last cell reduced TX min load
Description: This parameter indicates the low-watermark for the load of the last enabled cell of a power group for reduced TX power saving.  If the aggregate power group load of the enabled power group last cells* is at or below the last cell low-water mark for reduced TX power saving (NRPGRP.lbpsLastCellRTXMinLoad) for a minimum duration (NRPGRP.lbpsRTXSOffTime), the gNB will switch off TX paths at the enabled power group last cells if the last cell switch off enabled flag (NRPGRP.lbpsLastCellSOEnabled) is TRUE.    All switched off TX paths will be switched on at all power group cells when not in a power saving period.    The NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMinLoad value is used for all but the last enabled cell in the power group in which case the NRPGRP.lbpsLastCellRTXMinLoad value is used.    * The power group last cells are either all power group cells with switch off order set to the last cell special value (NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsCellSOOrder = 100) or if no power group cell is assigned the last cell special value, then the single enabled power group cell full TX paths with the greatest NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsCellSOOrder value.    Note: This parameter is only used for NRPGRP instances with NRPGRP.lbpsSOMethod equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off' and for NRPGRP instances with at least one NR cell (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.nrCellId) having NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsUseExtConfig equal to TRUE and one corresponding element in NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.nrCellId) has NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellSOMethod equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off'.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving last cell switch off enabled
Description: This parameter indicates whether the last enabled power group cell may have resources switched off (including cell switched off or TX switched off) and whether power group cells with the special handling cell switch off order value (NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsCellSOOrder) may have resources switched off.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE, the last enabled cell and the cells with the special handling cell switch off order value may have resources switched off.  If this parameter is equal to FALSE, neither the last enabled cell nor the cells with the special handling cell switch off order value may have resources switched off.

This parameter defines the load quantity calculation method where  - G: load from normalized PRB usage for GBR  - C: load from normalized PRB usage for category based non-GBR  - G_N_combined: load from combined normalized PRB usage for GBR and non-GBR  - P: load from PDCCH CCE usage

This parameter indicates the high watermark for the aggregate load of a NR power group.    In case of two or more enabled power group cells:  (1) The gNB will not switch off a NR cell if the expected aggregate power group load of the remaining enabled power group cells will be above the high watermark value in this parameter  (2) If needed, the gNB will switch on power group cells in the reverse cell switch off order to increase the aggregate power group capacity until the expected power group load is below the high watermark in this parameter.    For the last enabled power group cell:  (1) If the power group load is below the last cell low watermark in NRPGRP.lbpsLastCellMinLoad, the gNB will switch off a cell if the last cell switch off enabled flag (NRPGRP.lbpsLastCellSOEnabled) is equal to TRUE. The high watermark is not considered as there is no expected aggregate power group load  (2) If there are no enabled power group cells, there is no power group load. All switched off power group cells will be switched on when not in a power saving period.  It is recommended to set NRPGRP.lbpsMaxLoad to a value strictly higher than 2*NRPGRP.lbpsMinLoad to avoid a situation where a cell is switched off due to the power group load being below NRPGRP.lbpsMinLoad and within a few minutes is switched on due to the power group load increasing above NRPGRP.lbpsMaxLoad.    Note: This parameter is only used for NRPGRP instances with NRPGRP.lbpsSOMethod equal to 'cell switch off' or 'mixed switch off' and for NRPGRP instances with at least one NR cell (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.nrCellId) having NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsUseExtConfig equal to TRUE and one corresponding element in NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.nrCellId) has NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellSOMethod equal to 'cell switch off' or 'mixed switch off'.

This parameter indicates the low watermark for the aggregate load of a NR power group.  The gNB will switch off a power group cell in cell switch off order if the aggregate power group load is less than or equal to the low watermark value in NRPGRP.lbpsMinLoad and the expected aggregate power group load for the reduced aggregate power group capacity is less than the high watermark value in NRPGRP.lbpsMaxLoad.  NRPGRP.lbpsMinLoad is used except when determining whether the last enabled cell in the NR Power Group may be switched off; in that case, NRPGRP.lbpsLastCellMinLoad.  It is recommended to set NRPGRP.lbpsMinLoad to a value strictly lower than NRPGRP.lbpsMaxLoad/2 to avoid a situation where a cell is switched off due to the power group load being below NRPGRP.lbpsMinLoad and within a few minutes is switched on due to the power group load increasing above NRPGRP.lbpsMaxLoad.    Note: This parameter is only used for NRPGRP instances with NRPGRP.lbpsSOMethod equal to 'cell switch off' or 'mixed switch off' and for NRPGRP instances with at least one NR cell (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.nrCellId) having NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsUseExtConfig equal to TRUE and one corresponding element in NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.nrCellId) has NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellSOMethod equal to 'cell switch off' or 'mixed switch off'.

Parameter name: Load-based PS monitoring window for cell switch off
Description: This parameter defines the cell switch off load window

Parameter name: Load-based PS monitoring window for cell switch on
Description: This parameter defines the cell switch on load window

Parameter name: Load-based power saving PDCCH load offset
Description: This parameter indicates the offset subtracted from the sum of normalized PDCCH load of each enabled power group cell.  The power group PDCCH load average may be greater than the power group GBR and non-GBR load averages. Load-based power saving PDCCH load offset (NRPGRP.lbpsPdcchLoadOffset) is applied to align the power group PDCCH load average with the power group GBR and non-GBR load averages.  If the power group PDCCH load average is less than NRPGRP.lbpsPdcchLoadOffset, then the power group PDCCH load average is set to 0%.

This parameter indicates the list of periods during which power saving may be initiated for the cells in the NR Power Group.  A period is defined as the time between a start time and an end time within a day of the week. There may be multiple periods defined during any single day of the week. The energy saving can be suspended for an overlapping time period.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving day of week
Description: This parameter indicates the day of the week for which the power saving period is defined.
Range and step: Sun (0), Mon (1), Tue (2), Wed (3), Thu (4), Fri (5), Sat (6)

Description: This parameter indicates the end time of the power saving period.  The power saving period begins at the load-based power saving start time (NRPGRP.lbpsStartTimeHour and NRPGRP.lbpsStartTimeMinute) and continues for a number of minutes in NRPGRP.lbpsDuration.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving start time hour
Description: This parameter indicates, along with NRPGRP.lbpsStartTimeMinute, the local time when the power saving period begins.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving start time minute
Description: This parameter indicates, along with NRPGRP.lbpsStartTimeHour, the local time when the power saving period begins.
This parameter indicates whether energy saving is suspended for the NR cells in the NR power group for the power saving period.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving reduced TX cell capacity offset
Description: This parameter indicates the percent cell throughput at a reduced TX path cell relative to the full TX path cell throughput expected due to reduction in cell TX paths.  The cell throughput is expected to be decreased by the cell with reduced TX paths.    For 8T8R beamforming case, due to loss one polarization for 8T8R MIMO muting, the percent DL cell throughput at a reduced TX path cell relative to full TX path expected to be lower than 4T4R. It is recommended to set to not exceed 70% for 8T8R MIMO muting.    Note: This parameter is only used for NRPGRP instances with NRPGRP.lbpsSOMethod equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off' and for NRPGRP instances with at least one NR cell (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.nrCellId) having NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsUseExtConfig equal to TRUE and one corresponding element in NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.nrCellId) has NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellSOMethod equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off'.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving reduced TX maximum load
Description: This parameter indicates the high-watermark for the aggregate load of a power group for reduced TX power saving.  One or more enabled power group cells with all TX paths enabled:  - The gNB will not switch off TX paths at a cell if the expected aggregate power group load of the enabled power group cells will be above the high-water mark for reduced TX value of NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMaxLoad.  - If the aggregate power group load is above the high-water mark for a minimum duration (NRPGRP.lbpsRTXSOnTime), the gNB will switch on TX paths of power group cells in the reverse cell switch off order (NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsCellSOOrder) to increase the aggregate power group capacity until the expected power group load is at or below the high-water mark for reduced TX value of NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMaxLoad.    All switched off TX paths will be switched on at all power group cells when not in a power saving period.    It is recommended to set NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMaxLoad to a value strictly higher than 2*NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMinLoad to avoid a situation where a cell has its TX paths switched off due to the power group load being at or below NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMinLoad and within a few minutes is switched on due to the power group load increasing above NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMaxLoad.    Note: This parameter is only used for NRPGRP instances with NRPGRP.lbpsSOMethod equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off' and for NRPGRP instances with at least one NR cell (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.nrCellId) having NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsUseExtConfig equal to TRUE and one corresponding element in NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.nrCellId) has NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellSOMethod equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off'.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving reduced TX minimum load
Description: This parameter indicates the low-watermark for the aggregate load of a power group for reduced TX power saving.  The gNB will switch off TX paths of a power group cell in cell switch off order (NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsCellSOOrder) if the aggregate power group load is less than or equal to the low-watermark for reduced TX power saving value of NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMinLoad for a minimum duration (NRPGRP.lbpsRTXSOffTime) and the expected aggregate power group load for the reduced aggregate power group capacity is less than or equal to the high-water mark for reduced TX power saving value of NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMaxLoad.    NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMinLoad is used except when determining whether the last enabled cell in the Power Group with all TX paths enabled may have its TX paths switched off (see NRPGRP.lbpsLastCellRTXMinLoad).    All switched off TX paths will be switched on at all power group cells when not in a power saving period.    It is recommended to set NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMinLoad to a value strictly lower than NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMaxLoad/2 to avoid a situation where a cell has its TX paths switched off due to the power group load being at or below NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMinLoad and within a few minutes is switched on due to the power group load increasing above NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMaxLoad.    Note: This parameter is only used for NRPGRP instances with NRPGRP.lbpsSOMethod equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off' and for NRPGRP instances with at least one NR cell (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.nrCellId) having NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsUseExtConfig equal to TRUE and one corresponding element in NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.nrCellId) has NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellSOMethod equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off'.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving reduced TX switch off time
Description: The gNB will switch off TX paths of a power group cell in cell switch off order (NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsCellSOOrder) if the aggregate power group load is less than or equal to the low-watermark for reduced TX power saving value of NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMinLoad (or NRPGRP.lbpsLastCellRTXMinLoad) for a minimum duration (NRPGRP.lbpsRTXSOffTime) and the expected aggregate power group load for the reduced aggregate power group capacity is less than or equal to the high-water mark for reduced TX power saving value of NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMaxLoad.    Note: This parameter is only used for NRPGRP instances with NRPGRP.lbpsSOMethod equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off' and for NRPGRP instances with at least one NR cell (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.nrCellId) having NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsUseExtConfig equal to TRUE and one corresponding element in NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.nrCellId) has NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellSOMethod equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off'.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving reduced TX switch on time
Description: If the aggregate power group load is above the high-water mark (NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMaxLoad) for a minimum duration (NRPGRP.lbpsRTXSOnTime), the gNB will switch on TX paths of power group cells in the reverse cell switch off order (NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsCellSOOrder) to increase the aggregate power group capacity until the expected power group load is at or below the high-water mark for reduced TX value of NRPGRP.lbpsRTXMaxLoad.    Note: This parameter is only used for NRPGRP instances with NRPGRP.lbpsSOMethod equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off' and for NRPGRP instances with at least one NR cell (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.nrCellId) having NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.lbpsUseExtConfig equal to TRUE and one corresponding element in NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList (identified by NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.nrCellId) has NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellSOMethod equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off'.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving switch off method
Description: This parameter indicates the load-based power saving switch off method used by the power saving group instance.  The possible values are:  - 'cell switch off' meaning the power saving group instance is used for load-based power saving with NR cells switch off.  - 'TX switch off' meaning the power saving group instance is used for load-based power saving with NR cells TX paths switch off.  - 'mixed switch off' meaning the power saving group instance is used for both load-based power saving methods.    If NRBTS.actNrLBmMimoRTXPowerSaving is equal to TRUE and there is at least one mMimo RU cell that is configured in this NRPGRP instance and the corresponding NRCELL instance (with NRCELL.nrCellId equal to NRPGRP.lbpsCellList.nrCellId) is served by a RMOD instance with PHYANT instance defined, then,  - If NRPGRP.lbpsSOMethod is equal to 'cell switch off' and no element exists in NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList for this NRCELL instance with NRPGRP.lbpsCellPeriodList.lbpsCellSOMethod equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off', then updating this parameter will provoke mMimo RU cell reset.  - If NRPGRP.lbpsSOMethod is equal to 'TX switch off' or 'mixed switch off', then updating this parameter will not provoke cell reset.
Range and step: cell switch off (0), TX switch off (1), mixed switch off (2)

Parameter name: Load-based PS switch off triggering rule
Description: This parameter defines the switch-off triggering rule.  - MaxValueMethod: (Max 10s load in switch_off_load_window <= min_thr) AND (LoadAftSwOff( latest 10s volume ) <= max_thr)  - SlidingAverageMethod: LoadAftSwOff(Average volume in switch_off_load_window ) <= min_thr

Parameter name: Load-based PS switch on triggering rule
Description: This parameter defines the switch-on triggering rule.  - MinValueMethod: Min 10s load in switch_on_load_window > max_thr  - SlidingAverageMethod: Load( Average volume in switch_on_load_window ) > max_thr
This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio PLMN (NRPLMN) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates the MCC (Mobile Country Code) in the PLMN (Public Land Mobile Network) ID.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter indicates the MNC (Mobile Network Code) in the PLMN (Public Land Mobile Network) ID.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter indicates the length of the MNC (Mobile Network Code) in the PLMN (Public Land Mobile Network) ID, in digits.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter denotes a label that can be used for a user-friendly name of the NR PLMN  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: New Radio PLMN Set for NSA instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio PLMN Set for NSA (NRPLMNSET_NSA) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRCELL instance.
This parameter indicates whether or not the cell is reserved for operator use per PLMN.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates the configured EPS tracking area code (TAC) for a given New Radio cell. It enables to apply Roaming and Access Restrictions for EN-DC.

This parameter defines the distinguished name of the NRPLMN instance(s) defining each operator for NR RAN sharing. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke a gNB reset.  Removing this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke a gNB reset.  Updating, configuring or removing this parameter without cell addition or deletion will provoke a gNB reset except that updating this parameter without changing the referenced instance will be performed on-line.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: New Radio PLMN Set for SA instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio PLMN Set for SA (NRPLMNSET_SA) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRCELL instance.
This parameter indicates whether or not the cell is reserved for operator use per PLMN.

Parameter name: Cell reserved for operator use during maximum auto UAC barring
Description: This parameter indicates whether or not the cell is reserved for operator use per PLMN when maximum automatic UAC barring is broadcasted in SIB1. The value 'reserved' overrides NRCELL.cellReservedForOperatorUse and NRPLMNSET_SA.cellReservedForOperatorUse settings.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter defines the distinguished name of the NRPLMN instance(s) defining each operator for NR RAN sharing. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke a gNB reset.  Removing this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke a gNB reset.  Updating, configuring or removing this parameter without cell addition or deletion will provoke a gNB reset except that updating this parameter without changing the referenced instance will be performed on-line.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

This parameter indicates the RAN Area Code for the NRPLMNSET_SA. It is used in RRC Inactive state and is transmitted to the UE in SIB1.    If both NRCELL.ranAC and NRPLMNSET_SA.ranAC are not configured, then RRC Inactive state is not supported in this cell.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the TRACKINGAREA instance. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/TRACKINGAREA-1  TRACKINGAREA-1    Configuring this parameter during cell addition will not provoke a gNB reset.  Removing this parameter during cell deletion will not provoke a gNB reset.  Updating, configuring or removing this parameter without cell addition or deletion will provoke a gNB reset except that updating this parameter without changing the referenced instance will be performed on-line.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
This parameter uniquely identifies the NRPLMN support (NRPLMN_SUPPORT) instance within the SERVEDAMF instance.
This parameter indicates the MCC (Mobile Country Code) in the PLMN (Public Land Mobile Network) ID of the NRPLMN support instance.
This parameter indicates the MNC (Mobile Network Code) in the PLMN (Public Land Mobile Network) ID of the NRPLMN support instance.

Parameter name: MNC length of the supported PLMN
Description: This parameter indicates the length of the MNC of the NRPLMN support instance.

Parameter name: List of SNSSAI supported by AMF
Description: This parameter indicates the list of the network slices supported by the AMF for the NRPLMN support instance.
This parameter indicates the slice differentiator.
This parameter indicates the slice service type which identifies the slice type.
This parameter indicates the number of all reported slices by the AMF.

Parameter name: UAC Barring Per NR PLMN instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the UAC Barring Per NR PLMN (NRPLMN_UACBAR) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRCELL instance.  At least one NRPLMN_UACBAR instance must be configured for SIB1 to broadcast uac-BarringPerPLMN-List
This parameter indicates whether UAC implicit or explicit AC Barring List is to be used in the associated NRPLMN instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the NRPLMN instance for which the access barring per PLMN is to be defined. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1
This parameter indicates the UAC explicit AC barring list for the associated NRPLMN instance
This parameter indicates the access category

Parameter name: Unified access control barring Info set index
Description: This parameter indicates the index of the entry in the field 'SIB1.uac-barringInfo.uac-BarringInfoSetList'.
This parameter indicates the UAC implicit AC barring list for the associated NRPLMN instance

Parameter name: New Radio Performance Monitoring Counter Configuration Parameters instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Performance Monitoring Counter Configuration Parameters (NRPMCCP) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRPMRNL instance

This parameter is used to select the bin range setting for the TA counters.    Note:  Sub carrier spacing (SCS) identified based on NRCELLGRP.scs  expected cell size is identified based on NRCELL.expectedCellSize
Range and step: Bin ranges based on SCS (0), Bin ranges based on expected cell size (1)

Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: New Radio Performance Monitoring QCI ARP Profiles instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Performance Monitoring QCI ARP Profiles (NRPMQAP) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRPMRNL instance
This parameter activates/deactivates the Control Plane counters for NRPMQAP instance.

Parameter name: Enable User Plane Group 1 NRPMQAP counters
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the User Plane Group 1 counters for NRPMQAP instance.

Parameter name: Enable User Plane Group 2 NRPMQAP counters
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the User Plane Group 2 counters for NRPMQAP instance.

This parameter indicates the 5QI values in each NR PM QCI ARP profile.  The allowed formats are:  - a single 5QI value. Example: 1 for 5QI1.  - a list of 5QI values and ranges of 5QIs specified by the lowest and highest values of the range with a hyphen delimiter. No white spaces or punctuation other than the comma and the hyphen range designator are allowed. Example: 1,5-7,130,140-151

This parameter indicates the ARP values in each NR PM QCI ARP profile.  The allowed formats are:  - a single ARP value. Example: 1 for ARP.  - a list of ARP values and ranges of ARPs specified by the lowest and highest values of the range with a hyphen delimiter. No white spaces or punctuation other than the comma and the hyphen range designator are allowed. Example: 1,3-5,12

This structure indicates the PLMN ID configuration of the associated with the NR PM QCI ARP profile.    In case of CB008828 enabled, this parameter is used as an additional filter on top of the PLMN value(s) configured in SNSSAI object(s) (NRBTS.SNSSAI.nrPlmnDNList) used in the given PMQAP profile.
This parameter indicates the MCC (Mobile Country Code) in the PLMN ID.
This parameter indicates the MNC (Mobile Network Code) in the PLMN ID.
This parameter indicates the length of the MNC (Mobile Network Code) in the PLMN ID, in digits.
This parameter indicates the type of the NR PM QCI ARP profile.

This parameter indicates the QCI values in each NR PM QCI ARP profile.  The allowed formats are:  - a single QCI value. Example: 5 for QCI5.  - a list of QCI values and ranges of QCIs specified by the lowest and highest values of the range with a hyphen delimiter. No white spaces or punctuation other than the comma and the hyphen range designator are allowed. Example: 5-9,69,70,79,98-100,128-254
This structure indicates the configuration for the slice ID associated with the NR PM QCI ARP profile
This parameter indicates the slice differentiator.
This parameter indicates the slice service type.

This parameter indicates the Subscriber Profile ID (SPID) values in each NR PM QCI ARP profile for NSA.  The allowed values are:  - Special value 'none' that can be used to create NRPMQAP profile for the UEs which do not have SPID.  Note1: Value 'none' cannot be defined together with other SPID values.  Note2: Value 'none' cannot be defined more than once per PLMN (defined by NRPMQAP.cfgPlmnId)  Example: none  - A single SPID value.  Example: 1  - A list of SPID values and ranges of SPID values specified by the lowest and highest values of the range with a hyphen delimiter. No white spaces or punctuation other than the comma and the hyphen range designator are allowed.  Example: 1,5-7,96,100-128    As per 3GPP the allowed SPID values are the following:  - Operator specific SPID values: 1...128  - Reference values: 129...256
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter indicates the threshold for the DL AM RLC SDUs at PMQAP level.  The PM counter DL_RLC_AM_DLY_AIR_IF_TH_PMQAP is incremented if the measured DL AM RLC SDU delay is higher than the configured threshold.
This parameter contains a list of SNSSAIs for the NR PM QCI ARP profile.  This list is used only if NRBTS.actSliceNumExt is equal to TRUE.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the SNSSAI which shall be mapped to a NR PM QCI ARP profile as follows:  - one SNSSAI DN value or  - the value of the first SNSSAI DN of a range and, in this case, the last SNSSAI DN value of the range shall be configured in NRPMQAP.snssaiList.snssaiDNLast.  This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Example:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/SNSSAI-25  SNSSAI-25

Parameter name: Last SNSSAI distinguished name of a range
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the last SNSSAI of a range if a range of SNSSAI DNs shall be mapped to a NR PM QCI ARP profile.  This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Example:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/SNSSAI-25  SNSSAI-25

This parameter indicates the range of the highest BIN for DL throughput distribution PM counters.  Its value is the estimated maximum value of the highest BIN, i.e. BIN 20 for DL throughput distribution.  Note: This is an estimated maximum, thus if during calculation, the DL throughput for a certain measurement period exceeds this value, it is still reported under the maximum BIN, i.e. BIN 20.    Its value is used to define the range of all BINs

This parameter indicates the range of the lowest BIN for DL throughput distribution PMQAP PM counters.  Its value is the highest value of the lowest BIN, i.e. BIN 01 for DL throughput.    Note: In case 0 is selected, value 1 is taken as parameter value to avoid division by 0 issue when calculating BIN ranges.

Parameter name: Throughput histogram scale type for both UL and DL throughput distribution counters
Description: This parameter indicates if the PMQAP histogram scale type is linear or logarithmic for both the DL PDCP and UL RLC throughput histogram.

This parameter indicates the range of the highest BIN for UL throughput distribution PMQAP PM counters.  Its value is the estimated maximum value of the highest BIN, i.e. BIN 20 for UL throughput distribution.  Note: This is an estimated maximum, thus if during calculation, the UL throughput for a certain measurement period exceeds this value, it is still reported under the maximum BIN i.e. BIN 20.

This parameter indicates the range of the lowest BIN for UL throughput distribution PMQAP PM counters.  Its value is the highest value of the lowest BIN, i.e. BIN 01 for the UL throughput.    Note: In case 0 is selected, value 1 is taken as parameter value to avoid division by 0 issue when calculating BIN ranges.

Parameter name: Method to estimate average UL UE throughput
Description: This parameter indicates the method to estimate the average UL UE throughput.    The possible values are:  - CountingUEsBSRGT0 for the average UL user throughput TP measurement method counting UEs with BSR > 0  - CountingUEsBSRGT0+UEsDRXUlGrant for the UL TP measurement method counting UEs with BSR > 0 and UEs configured with DRX with gNB indication for needed UL grant  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.

Parameter name: New Radio Position Cell instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Position Cell (NRPOSCELL) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
This parameter defines the administrative state of the New Radio Positioning Cell.    Notes:  - The value 'Shutting Down' is only taken into account in the DU functional entity.
This parameter defines the availability status of the NR positioning Cell.  It shows if any specific conditions are present for the resource.
Range and step: in test (0), failed (1), power off (2), off line (3), off duty (4), dependency (5), degraded (6), not installed (7), log full (8)

This parameter indicates the altitude value (N).
This parameter indicates the confidence by which the position of a target entity is known to be within the shape description.
This parameter indicates the latitude value (N) which is derived from the latitude in degrees with formula: N <= 2^23*X/90 < N+1, where X is the latitude in degrees (0 to 90 degrees).
This parameter indicates the longitude value (N) which is derived from the longitude in degrees with formula: N <= 2^24*X/360 < N+1, where X is the longitude in degrees (-180 to +180 degrees).
This parameter defines the direction of altitude
This parameter indicates the latitude sign as northward or southward.

This parameter allows the operator to specify the number of fronthaul streams of a New Radio Position Cell.
This parameter defines the operational state of the NR Positioning Cell.  It shows if the resource is physically installed and working.
This parameter defines the procedural status of the NR Positioning Cell.  It shows configuration phase of the resource.
Range and step: not initialized (0), initialization required (1), initializing (2), validated (3), configured (4)

Parameter name: New Radio Priority Access Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Priority Access Profile (NRPRIOACC_PROFILE) instance identifier within the same containing NRBTS instance.

Parameter name: Maximum ARP value for HPA access
Description: This parameter together with the parameter NRPRIOACC_PROFILE-arpPrioLevelHpaMin define the range of Allocation and Retention Priority (ARP) used to prioritize High Priority Access calls over normal or emergency calls. The UE context with serving PLMN indicated by NRPRIOACC_PROFILE-nrPlmnIdx and with at least one QoS flow with ARP priority level within the given range of ARP will be regarded as High Priority Access call which can use emergency or priority access reserved resources as defined by NRBTS-applyPriorityAccess.

Parameter name: Minimum ARP value for HPA access
Description: This parameter together with the parameter NRPRIOACC_PROFILE-arpPrioLevelHpaMax define the range of Allocation and Retention Priority (ARP) used to prioritize High Priority Access calls over normal or emergency calls. The UE context with serving PLMN indicated by NRPRIOACC_PROFILE-nrPlmnIdx and with at least one QoS flow with ARP priority level within the given range of ARP will be regarded as High Priority Access call which can use emergency or priority access reserved resources as defined by NRBTS-applyPriorityAccess.

Parameter name: Maximum ARP value for MPS access
Description: This parameter together with the parameter NRPRIOACC_PROFILE-arpPrioLevelMpsMin define the range of Allocation and Retention Priority (ARP) used to prioritize Multimedia Priority Session (MPS) calls over normal or emergency calls. The UE context with serving PLMN indicated by NRPRIOACC_PROFILE-nrPlmnIdx and with at least one QoS flow with ARP priority level lower the given range of ARP will be regarded as Multimedia Priority Session (MPS) call which can use emergency or priority access reserved resources as defined by NRBTS-applyPriorityAccess.

Parameter name: Minimum ARP value for MPS access
Description: This parameter together with the parameter NRPRIOACC_PROFILE-arpPrioLevelMpsMax define the range of Allocation and Retention Priority (ARP) used to prioritize Multimedia Priority Session (MPS) calls over normal or emergency calls. The UE context with serving PLMN indicated by NRPRIOACC_PROFILE-nrPlmnIdx and with at least one QoS flow with ARP priority level within the given range of ARP will be regarded as Multimedia Priority Session (MPS) call which can use emergency or priority access reserved resources as defined by NRBTS-applyPriorityAccess.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter indicates a reference to the associated NRPLMN instance.    The UE context with the serving PLMN indicated by NRPRIOACC_PROFILE-nrPlmnIdx and at least one QoS flow with ARP priority level within NRPRIOACC_PROFILE-arpPrioLevelHpaMin, NRPRIOACC_PROFILE-arpPrioLevelHpaMax or NRPRIOACC_PROFILE-arpPrioLevelMpsMin, NRPRIOACC_PROFILE-arpPrioLevelMpsMax range of ARP priorities will be regarded as High Priority Access (HPA) or Multimedia Priority Session (MPS) call which can use emergency or priority access reserved resources as defined by NRBTS-applyPriorityAccess.

Parameter name: New Radio Power Saving Group for Energy-Efficient Emergency Activation instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Power Saving Group for Energy-Efficient Emergency Activation (NRPSGRP_EEEA) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: External Alarm Control Input distinguished name
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the External Alarm Control Input (EAC_IN) instance identifier under SMOD.  This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  EQM-1/APEQM-1/CABINET-1/SMOD-1/EAC_IN-1  SMOD-1/EAC_IN-1

This parameter indicates the list of NR cells entitled to be switched on from power saving state in case of an external alarm.    In case of an external alarm (for example fire alarm), the NR cells in this list will be brought On-line from power saving state.

Parameter name: New radio PUSCH profile BR link adaptation instance ID
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio PUSCH Profile for Basic Reliability Link Adaptation (NRPUSCHBRLA) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Data Radio Bearer specific BLER target for Uplink transmission
Description: This parameter indicates the DRB specific target Block Error Ratio (BLER) of initial uplink transmissions for UL Outer Loop Link Adaptation for Basic reliability

Parameter name: DRB specific Delta SINR Stepdown of UL OLLA
Description: This parameter indicates DRB specific delta SINR step down size in OLLA for a NACK.

Parameter name: New Radio PUSCH Profile for High Reliability Link Adaptation instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio PUSCH Profile for High Reliability Link Adaptation (NRPUSCHHRLA) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Scale factor for high reliability DRB in UL
Description: This parameter defines the scale (multiplier) factor for high reliability non-GBR DRB associated to uplink configured grant and high reliability GBR DRB in uplink radio admission control.  The scale factor represents the increased resource usage of non-GBR DRB associated to uplink configured grant or GBR DRB caused by lower spectral efficiency when high reliability link adaptation is applied.

Parameter name: Percentage for samples of possible TB size for high reliability fallback to basic reliability
Description: This parameter indicates the percentage for bad samples of possible TB size for high reliability fallback to basic reliability

Parameter name: BLER target outage period for high reliability DRB in uplink
Description: This parameter indicates the monitoring period for fallback to default BLER management in uplink.

Parameter name: Radio link outage possible wideband TBS threshold for high reliability for 64QAM LowSE table
Description: This parameter indicates the possible wideband TB size threshold of fall back from high reliability to cell default BLER management for the 64QAM LowSE table. After fallback, the high reliability DRBs of the UE should be treated as basic reliability DRB and using legacy link adaptation.

Parameter name: Radio link outage possible wideband TBS threshold for high reliability for 64QAM table
Description: This parameter indicates the possible wideband TB size threshold of fall back from high reliability to cell default BLER management for the 64QAM table. After fallback, the high reliability DRBs of the UE should be treated as basic reliability DRB and using legacy link adaptation.

Parameter name: Percentage for samples of possible TB size for basic reliability recover to high reliability
Description: This parameter indicates the percentage for samples of possible TB size for basic reliability recover to high reliability.

Parameter name: BLER target recover period for high reliability in uplink
Description: This parameter indicates the monitoring period for recover of usage of high reliability BLER target in uplink.

Parameter name: Radio link recover possible TBS threshold for high reliability DRB for 64QAM LowSE table
Description: This parameter indicates the possible wideband TB size threshold of recovering to NRPUSCHHRLA.ullaBlerTarget usage for high reliability DRB for the 64QAM LowSE table.

Parameter name: Radio link recover possible wideband TBS threshold for high reliability DRB for 64QAM table
Description: This parameter indicates the possible wideband TB size threshold of recovering to NRPUSCHHRLA.ullaBlerTarget usage for high reliability DRB for the 64QAM table.

Parameter name: UL BLER target for UL transmission for high reliability DRB
Description: This parameter defines the UL Block Error Ratio (BLER) target for UL transmission for high reliability DRB.

Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio RAN Function instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRE2NODE instance.

This parameter indicates the short name of the RAN function.
This parameter indicates the state of the RAN function, i.e. whether the RAN function is added to Near-RT RIC or not.

Parameter name: New Radio Redirection Target instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Redirection Target (NRREDRT) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRCELL instance.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the NRPLMN instance(s) defining each operator for NR RAN sharing. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1

This parameter indicates the E-UTRA carrier frequency for redirection used in RRC Release message containing redirectedCarrierInfo IE (TS 38.331).  The parameter value is based on the 3GPP absolute radio frequency channel number ARFCN-ValueEUTRA.
This parameter indicates the SSB frequency of the NR target carrier for redirection used in the RRC release message containing redirectedCarrierInfo IE (TS 38.331).

Parameter name: Redirection priority for RRC Connection Release
Description: This parameter indicates the priority for target RAT selection during RRC Connection Release with redirection procedure. If this parameter is not configured, then the NRREDRT instance is not eligible for A2 based redirection.    The NRREDRT instance having the highest priority supported by the UE is selected as the redirection target for A2 based redirection.  Value 1 means the highest priority, while value 6 means the lowest priority.

Parameter name: Redirection priority for bad UL radio
Description: This parameter indicates the priority for redirection due to bad uplink radio conditions. If this parameter is not configured, then the NRREDRT instance is not eligible for redirection due to bad uplink radio conditions.    The NRREDRT instance having the highest priority supported by the UE is selected as the redirection target for redirection due to bad uplink radio conditions.  Value 1 means the highest priority, while value 6 means the lowest priority.
This parameter indicates the Radio Access Technology (RAT) to which the UE is redirected via RRC Connection Release with redirection procedure.
This parameter indicates the subcarrier spacing value for SSB in the redirected SSB frequency.

Parameter name: SSB Measurement Timing Duration for Redirection
Description: This parameter indicates the SSB duration configuration for the redirected SSB frequency. It is based on timing reference of PCell and is given in number of subframes.

Parameter name: SSB Measurement Timing Offset for Redirection
Description: This parameter indicates the SSB offset configuration for the redirected SSB frequency. It is based on timing reference of PCell and is given in number of subframes.

Parameter name: SSB Measurement Timing Periodicity for Redirection
Description: This parameter indicates the SSB periodicity configuration for the redirected SSB frequency. It is based on timing reference of PCell and is given in number of subframes.

Parameter name: New Radio Neighbor Relation instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Neighbor Relation (NRREL) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRCELL instance.    A NRREL instance can be created/updated by the gNB when Intra-NR ANR is activated (NRBTS.actNsaUeBasedAnrNr or NRBTS.actNsaUeBasedInterFreqAnrNr or NRBTS.actSaUeBasedAnrNr or NRBTS.actSaUeBasedInterFreqAnrNr is equal to TRUE). It may be deleted when NRANR.actAutoNrNbRemoval is equal to TRUE and the other criteria for autonomous removal of unused NR neighbor relations are met.

Parameter name: Activate A4 to A1 fallback for measurement based SCell addition
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the fallback to A1-based SCell addition per A4-based SCell candidate for NSA UE contexts in PCells with NRCELL.cellDepType equal to 'SA+NSA'.

Parameter name: Cell individual SSB RSRP offset of related neighbor cell
Description: This parameter defines the cell individual SSB RSRP offset applicable to the related neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Cell individual SSB RSRQ offset of related neighbor cell
Description: This parameter defines the cell individual SSB RSRQ offset applicable to the related neighbor cell.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: gNB identity of related neighbor cell
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies together with lcrId the related neighbor cell within one PLMN.  Updating this parameter for a given NRREL instance which has NRREL.sCellAdditionMethod configured will provoke a cell reset, otherwise modification will be on-line.

Parameter name: gNB Id length of related neighbor cell
Description: This parameter indicates the length chosen by the operator for NRBTS.nrBtsId of the related neighbor cell. It corresponds to the left most bits of NRCELL.nrCellIdentity.  Updating this parameter for a given NRREL instance which has NRREL.sCellAdditionMethod configured will provoke a cell reset, otherwise modification will be on-line.

Parameter name: PLMN ID in Global gNB ID of related neighbor cell
Description: This parameter identifies PLMN of the related neighbor cell.

Parameter name: MCC of PLMN ID in Global gNB ID
Description: This parameter defines the related neighbor cell Mobile Country Code of the PLMN identity.  Updating this parameter for a given NRREL instance which has NRREL.sCellAdditionMethod configured will provoke a cell reset, otherwise modification will be on-line.

Parameter name: MNC of PLMN ID in Global gNB ID
Description: This parameter defines the related neighbor cell Mobile Network Code of the PLMN identity.  Updating this parameter for a given NRREL instance which has NRREL.sCellAdditionMethod configured will provoke a cell reset, otherwise modification will be on-line.

Parameter name: MNC length of PLMN ID in Global gNB ID
Description: This parameter defines the length of the related neighbor cell Mobile Network Code of the PLMN identity.  Updating this parameter for a given NRREL instance which has NRREL.sCellAdditionMethod configured will provoke a cell reset, otherwise modification will be on-line.

This parameter indicates the handover types that are allowed for this neighbor relation in standalone mode.    The supported values are:  - forbidden meaning that no outgoing handover is allowed,  - allowed meaning that any outgoing handover is allowed,  - XnHoNotAllowed meaning that outgoing handover via NG and intra-gNB handover are allowed but Xn based handover is not allowed.    In case of supplemental DL cells, this parameter shall be equal to 'forbidden'.

Parameter name: Handover allowed in SA for RedCap UEs
Description: This parameter indicates whether handovers of RedCap UEs are allowed or forbidden for this neighbor relation in standalone mode.    The supported values are:  - 'forbidden' meaning that no outgoing handover is allowed,  - 'allowed' meaning that any outgoing handover is allowed.    The gNB will use this parameter as one of the criteria for evaluating a candidate target cell for handover of RedCap UEs.    In case of supplemental DL cells, this parameter shall be equal to 'forbidden'.

Parameter name: Is replacement cell for PS-Cell selection
Description: This parameter indicates whether the NRCELL instance having a matching Cell Global Identity with the current NRREL instance is a replacement cell for the parent NRCELL instance of the current NRREL instance or not.  It is used by the gNB (during NSA initial access) while selecting FR1 PS-Cell for the SgNB addition. The replacement cell may get selected in case the cell (represented by parent NRCELL instance of the current NRREL instance) reported in the SgNB addition request message is not found suitable.

Parameter name: Local cell resource identifier of related neighbor cell
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies together with gNbId the related neighbor cell within one PLMN.    Updating this parameter for a given NRREL instance which has NRREL.sCellAdditionMethod configured will provoke a cell reset, otherwise modification will be on-line.

Parameter name: Allows matching cell usage as NR-DC PSCell
Description: This parameter indicates if matching cell can be used as NR-DC PSCell.
This parameter indicates if autonomous removal of the current neighbor relation (NRREL instance) by the gNB is not allowed (value TRUE) or is allowed (value FALSE).

Parameter name: RSRP offset replace cell for PS-Cell selection
Description: This parameter indicates the RSRP offset value (relatively to the associated reported cell indicated by the parent NRCELL instance) for the FR1 replacement cell (NRCELL instance having a matching Cell Global Identity with the current NRREL instance).  It is used by the gNB (during NSA initial access) in manipulating the actual RSRP value of the FR1 replacement cell when that replacement cell is not reported in the SgNB addition request message.

Parameter name: RSRQ offset replace cell for PS-Cell selection
Description: This parameter indicates the RSRQ offset value (relatively to the associated reported cell indicated by the parent NRCELL instance) for the FR1 replacement cell (NRCELL instance having a matching Cell Global Identity with the current NRREL instance)  It is used by the gNB (during NSA initial access) in manipulating the actual RSRQ value of the FR1 replacement cell when that replacement cell is not reported in the SgNB addition request message.

This parameter indicates the method of secondary cell addition for carrier aggregation.  If this parameter is configured, it defines the carrier aggregation relation between the NR cells.    Removing this parameter for a given NRREL instance will provoke a cell reset.  Removal of a NRREL instance that has this parameter configured will provoke a cell reset.
This parameter indicates the operational mode of the secondary cell for carrier aggregation.

This parameter indicates the priority of a secondary cell for a given secondary carrier.  It is used during secondary cell selection for a given secondary carrier.  Value 1 means highest priority, while higher value means lower priority.
