This parameter refers to the NRCELL instance at the gNB CU Level when NRRESOURCECU.typeNrCu indicates cell.    Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRCELL-1  NRCELL-1    This parameter refers to a NRBTS instance if NRRESOURCECU.typeNrCu indicates central.
This parameter indicates the resource type to be activated under NRRESOURCECU, which can be global (central) or a specific NR Cell.

Parameter name: New Radio Resource DU Trace Session instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Resource DU Trace Session (NRRESOURCEDU) instance within the same containing MRBTS/NRBTS/NRDU/NRCTRLTSDU/NRMTRACEDU instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the NRCELL or central resource instance to be used for this trace session. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.    This parameter refers to the NRCELL instance at the gNB DU Level when NRRESOURCEDU.typeNrDu indicates cell.    Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRCELL-1  NRCELL-1    This parameter refers to a NRDU instance if NRRESOURCEDU.typeNrDu indicates central.
This parameter indicates the resource type to be activated under NRRESOURCEDU, which can be global (central) or a specific NR Cell.

Parameter name: New Radio Resource Group instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Resource Group (NRRESOURCEGROUP) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRRESOURCEGROUP_PROFILE instance.    Slice aware scheduler supports up to 20 SA slices and 6 NSA Resource Groups, total 26 NRRESOURCEGROUP instances.    Subscriber Profile ID (SPID) based NSA slicing supports:  - for gNB with NSA only cells, up to 32 NRRESOURCEGROUP instances (either for a single PLMN or shared among multiple PLMNs in case of RAN sharing).  - for gNB with NSA and SA cells, up to 32 NRRESOURCEGROUP instances (either for a single PLMN or shared among multiple PLMNs in case of RAN sharing) with a limit of 20 SA slices.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter contains a list of New Radio resources for the New Radio Resource Group. The possible values are:  - SNSSAI instance(s) or a range of SNSSAI instances in case of parameterized slice(s) for SA resource(s) or  - NRPLMN instance in case of NSA resource or  - NRSPIDGRP instance in case of parameterized NSA resource per SPID value(s) or  - mixed SA (SNSSAI) and NSA (NRPLMN or NRSPIDGRP) resources.    If this parameter contains a distinguished name of a NSA resource group (NRPLMN) or a slice (SNSSAI) which is not assigned to the cell, then the system will ignore it; in this case, resource division might be not optimal.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of a SNSSAI instance or the first SNSSAI of a range of SNSSAI instances or a NRPLMN instance or a NRSPIDGRP instance for the New Radio resource list. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/SNSSAI-1  SNSSAI-1  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRSPIDGRP-1  NRSPIDGRP-1

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the last SNSSAI instance for the New Radio resource list. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/SNSSAI-25  SNSSAI-25
This structure gathers parameters related to the slice aware radio admission control

This parameter defines the upper limit of cell level radio admission controlled resources allocated to the Resource Group.    Note: The resources limited by this parameter are not reserved and could be used by users associated with all resource groups. Therefore, users from a given resource group may not always be able to utilise resources up to max quota.

This parameter defines the minimum amount of cell level radio admission controlled resources allocated to the Resource Group.  Note: The resources defined by this parameter are reserved and could be used only by users from the associated resource group, i.e. the minimum quota resources are not available for users from other resource groups. Therefore, the parameter may impact the total number of users served by the cell and should be set with caution.
This structure gathers parameters related to the slice aware scheduler

This parameter indicates the maximum quota (percentage) of PDSCH and/or PUSCH resources (PRBs) allocated to a NSA resource group or a SA slice.    If this parameter is not configured, then 100 would be assigned by the system to this NRRESOURCEGROUP instance.  If the sum of the maximum quota allocated to all NSA resource groups (NRPLMN instances if per PLMN or NRSPIDGRP instances if per SPID) or SA slices (SNSSAI instances) for all the NRRESOURCEGROUP instances under a same parent NRRESOURCEGROUP_PROFILE instance is less than 100%, then this may lead to waste of cell baseband resources.

This parameter indicates the minimum quota (percentage) of PDSCH and/or PUSCH resources (PRBs) allocated to a NSA resource group or a SA slice.  If this parameter is not configured, then 0 would be assigned by the system to this NRRESOURCEGROUP instance.
This parameter denotes a label that can be used for a user-friendly (and user assignable) name of the NRRESOURCEGROUP instance.

Parameter name: New Radio Resource Group Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Resource Group Profile (NRRESOURCEGROUP_PROFILE) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.

Parameter name: Apply cell radio access control for privileged UE
Description: This parameter indicates if Resource Group limits or cell level limits shall be applied for selected type of privileged UEs (Emergency, High Priority, Multimedia Priority Services). If the flag is TRUE, i.e. any bit 0, 1, or 2 (LSB) is set to 1, then the relevant privileged UEs may use all cell resources. Otherwise, only the resources limited by NRRESOURCEGROUP-racParams-maxQuota related to UE/DRB resource group and additionally dedicated reserved resources at cell level (e.g. NRCELL.numOfRadioResReservForEmergency, NRCELL.numOfRadioResReservForPa) can be used.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Default resource group list for NSA
Description: This parameter defines the list of default New Radio Resource Groups (NRRESOURCEGROUP) per NRPLMN for the New Radio Resource Group Profile (NRRESOURCEGROUP_PROFILE) referred by the cell to be used for NSA calls when there is no matching NRRESOURCEGROUP instance defined for the UE.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of a New Radio PLMN (NRPLMN) instance to be used for the default New Radio Resource Group list for NSA. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1

Parameter name: New Radio Resource Group instance identifier
Description: This parameter indicates the New Radio Resource Group instance identifier (NRRESOURCEGROUP.nrResourceGroupId) of the New Radio Resource Group (NRRESOURCEGROUP) instance within the same containing NRRESOURCEGROUP_PROFILE instance for the default resource group list for NSA.

Parameter name: Default resource group list for SA
Description: This parameter defines the list of default New Radio Resource Groups (NRRESOURCEGROUP) per NRPLMN for the New Radio Resource Group Profile (NRRESOURCEGROUP_PROFILE) referred by the cell to be used for SA calls when there is no matching NRRESOURCEGROUP instance defined for the UE.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of a New Radio PLMN (NRPLMN) instance to be used for the default New Radio Resource Group list for SA. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1

Parameter name: New Radio Resource Group instance identifier
Description: This parameter indicates the New Radio Resource Group instance identifier (NRRESOURCEGROUP.nrResourceGroupId) of the New Radio Resource Group (NRRESOURCEGROUP) instance within the same containing NRRESOURCEGROUP_PROFILE instance for the default resource group list for SA.

Parameter name: New Radio RFSP Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the RFSP Profile instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Index to RAT Frequency selection priority
Description: This parameter indicates the Index to RAT/Frequency selection priority (RFSP) as follows:  - one RFSP value or  - the value of the first RFSP of a range and, in this case, the last RFSP value of the range shall be configured in NRRFSP_PROFILE.rfspLast.    As per 3GPP the allowed RFSP values are the following:  - Operator specific RFSP values: 1...128  - Reference values: 129...256

Parameter name: RFSP based UE DRB inactivity timer
Description: This timer indicates the time period for the indication of the DRB inactivity in both DL and UL directions for DRB for given RFSP.  If this parameter is equal to 0, then this timer is off.

Parameter name: Last Index to RAT Frequency selection priority
Description: This parameter indicates the last Index to RAT/Frequency selection priority (RFSP) value of a range.  As per 3GPP the allowed RFSP values are the following:  - Operator specific RFSP values: 2...128  - Reference values: 129...256

Parameter name: RFSP based RRC Inactive UE DRB inactivity timer
Description: This timer defines the time period for the indication of the DRB inactivity in both DL and UL directions for DRB for a given RFSP for RRC Inactive capable SA UEs.  If this parameter is equal to 0, then this timer is off.

Parameter name: New Radio Remote Interference Management Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Remote Interference Management Profile (NRRIM_PROFILE) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRCELL instance

Parameter name: Activate DL mitigation Triggered by RI detection
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the downlink mitigation triggered by remote interference detection.
This parameter activates/deactivates RIM asymmetric indication for the NR cell.  If this parameter is equal to TRUE, the RIM asymmetric status can be indicated for the NR cell.
This parameter indicates the activation of RIM mitigation extension when remote interference is detected and related trigger conditions satisfy

Parameter name: Activate PDCCH muting on special slot for RIM
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the PDCCH muting on special slot during downlink mitigation.
This parameter activates/deactivates RIM soft muting. Meaning that RIM DL muting is applied based on current cell load level.

This parameter activates/deactivates RIM-RS enough indication (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 7.4.1.6.4.5).    Note:  To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.

Parameter name: Cell edge UE downlink pathloss threshold
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold of downlink path loss to determine cell edge UE

Parameter name: Cell load threshold for RIM mitigation
Description: This parameter defines the cell load threshold used when RIM soft muting (actRimSoftDlMuting) functionality is active. The average cell load over the last window defined by windowDurationForCellLoadAvg is compared to this threshold. Based on this comparison, different RIM DL mitigation methods are allowed:  - If the average cell load is below the threshold: RIM DL muting can be applied.  - If the average cell load is equal to or greater than the threshold: No RIM DL mitigation is applied.    Note: Setting a high threshold for this parameter may lead to persistent DL muting until other (non-cell load) conditions are met. This is because the cell load cannot exceed the threshold, preventing the CB013350 condition from being satisfied and releasing the muting. For more information, refer to CB013350 CuDo.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter indicates the multiplier factor for RIM-RS sequence initialization (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 7.4.1.6).    Note:  It is not recommended to configure this parameter to a value equal to 0.  This parameter is used for RIM-RS when NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-0'.  This parameter is used for RIM-RS type 1 when NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-1'.    To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.

This parameter indicates the multiplier factor for RIM-RS type 2 sequence initialization (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 7.4.1.6).    Note: It is not recommended to configure this parameter to a value equal to 0.    To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.

This parameter indicates the global ARFCN as a configured reference point in this network work band to map global F0 for RIM-RS (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 5.4 and NRRIM_PROFILE.startFreqOffsetForRs).    Note:  To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.

Parameter name: High priority RBs transmission muted slots
Description: This parameter indicates if the PDSCH data transmission is allowed in RIM DL muted slots for RBs with priority equal to or greater than GBR.

Parameter name: Maximum RIM-RS detection duration without RI
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum duration of the RIM-RS detection allowed after RI disappeared.    This parameter is ignored if NRCELL.actNrRim is not equal to 'framework-0' nor 'framework-1'.

Parameter name: Minimum DL mitigation duration without RI
Description: This parameter indicates the minimum duration of downlink mitigation sustained after RI disappeared.

Parameter name: Disable monitoring power of first symbol in uplink slot during RI sloping shape detection
Description: This parameter disables monitoring power level of first symbol in normal uplink slot during RI sloping shape detection, if it is equal to TRUE.

Parameter name: End symbol of monitoring downhill for NR remote interference detection
Description: This parameter indicates the end symbol of monitoring downhill for NR remote interference detection.  It indicates the symbol index in each uplink slot which is used as the end symbol of monitoring downhill pattern.

Parameter name: Start symbol of monitoring downhill for NR remote interference detection
Description: This parameter indicates the start symbol of monitoring downhill for NR remote interference detection.  It indicates the symbol index in each uplink slot which is used as the first symbol of monitoring downhill pattern.

Parameter name: Monitoring RI sloping in special slot enabled
Description: This parameter enables/disables monitoring RI sloping in the special slot.

Parameter name: Time window for monitoring remote interference
Description: This parameter indicates the time windows in which gNB monitors and detects the appearance and disappearance of remote interference

Parameter name: Base threshold for NR remote interference detection
Description: This parameter indicates the base threshold of interference power level per RB in uplink symbols for remote interference detection.

Parameter name: Drop height threshold for remote interference detection
Description: This parameter indicates the drop height (dB) threshold of downhill shape among uplink symbols in uplink slots for remote interference detection.

Parameter name: Drop height threshold for RI detection in special slot
Description: This parameter indicates the drop height (dB) threshold of downhill shape among uplink symbols in special slots for remote interference detection.

Parameter name: Ratio threshold of remote interference duration for detection
Description: This parameter indicates the ratio threshold of down hill event duration within a monitoring window which determines the appearance and disappearance of remote interference.
This parameter indicates the RIM mitigation scheme when RI or RIM-RS is detected.    This parameter is ignored if NRCELL.actNrRim is not equal to 'framework-0' nor 'framework-1'.
Range and step: no mitigation (0), UL mitigation only (1), DL mitigation only (2), UL and DL mitigation (3)

Parameter name: Remote interference specific power ramping step
Description: This parameter indicates the value of the power ramping step in system information block in case of remote interference mitigation (see 3GPP TS38.331).

Parameter name: Remote interference mitigation specific RAR TPC command
Description: This parameter indicates the value of the TPC command for PUSCH used in random access response (RAR) message in case of remote interference mitigation. (see 3GPP TS38.213 Table 8.2-1).

Parameter name: Number of detected setID for mitigation
Description: This parameter indicates the number of detected RIM-RS type 1 setIDs which could be configured to trigger DL mitigation.  If the number of detected RIM-RS type 1 setIDs is equal to or greater than this parameter, DL mitigation can be started. If the number of detected RIM-RS type 1 setIDs is strictly lower than this parameter, the detected RIM-RS type 1 setID will not trigger DL mitigation.

This parameter indicates the number of resource blocks for RIM-RS (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 7.4.1.6.4.3).    Note:  To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.

Parameter name: Total number of setIDs for RIM-RS type 1
Description: This parameter indicates the total number of setIDs used for RIM-RS type 1 configured in the network (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 7.4.1.6).    Note:  This parameter is used for RIM-RS when NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-0'.  This parameter is used for RIM-RS type 1 when NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-1'.    To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.

Parameter name: Total number of setIDs for RIM-RS type 2
Description: This parameter indicates the total number of setIDs used for RIM-RS type 2 configured in the network (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 7.4.1.6).    Note:  To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.

Parameter name: Number of windows with RI detected for DL mitigation
Description: This parameter indicates a threshold related to the number of consecutive RI monitor windows with RI detected. When the number of consecutive RI monitor windows with RI detected is equal to or greater than this threshold, the downlink mitigation could be triggered.

This parameter indicates the offset for RIM-RS sequence initialization (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 7.4.1.6).    Note:  It is not recommended to configure this parameter to a value equal to 0.  This parameter is used for RIM-RS when NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-0'.  This parameter is used for RIM-RS type 1 when NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-1'.    To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.

This parameter indicates the offset for RIM-RS type 2 sequence initialization (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 7.4.1.6).    Note: It is not recommended to configure this parameter to a value equal to 0.    To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.

This parameter indicates the number of consecutive uplink-downlink periods for RIM-RS type 1 (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 7.4.1.6.4.2).    Note:  This parameter is used for RIM-RS when NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-0'.  This parameter is used for RIM-RS type 1 when NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-1'.    To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.

This parameter indicates the number of consecutive uplink-downlink periods for RIM-RS type 2 (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 7.4.1.6.4.2).    Note:  To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.
This parameter indicates the asymmetric status detection window in unit of RIM-RS transmission period if NRRIM_PROFILE.actRimAsymmetricIndication is equal to TRUE.

This parameter indicates the method to manually trigger downlink muting in unit of slot.  The possible values are:  - 'disabled' meaning manually triggering downlink muting is disabled  - 'special slot muting' meaning PDSCH plus PDCCH (optional, if NRRIM_PROFILE.actRimPdcchMutingOnSpecialSlot is equal to TRUE) muting is manually triggered in the special slot  - 'DL+special slots muting' meaning PDSCH muting is manually triggered in the special slot and its preceding downlink slot, plus PDCCH (optional, if NRRIM_PROFILE.actRimPdcchMutingOnSpecialSlot is equal to TRUE) muting is manually triggered in the special slot.  - '2DL+special slots muting' meaning PDSCH muting is manually triggered in the special slot and its preceding 2 downlink slot, plus PDCCH (optional, if NRRIM_PROFILE.actRimPdcchMutingOnSpecialSlot is equal to TRUE) muting is manually triggered in the special slot.    Note:  Manually triggered downlink muting will override downlink muting triggered by RIM.
Range and step: disabled (0), special slot muting (1), DL+special slots muting (2), 2DL+special slots muting (3)

Description: This parameter indicates the maximum downlink muting range, when the downlink muting is triggered by RIM.    The possible values are:  - 'special slot' meaning the downlink muting can be triggered in the special slot.  - 'DL+special slots' meaning the downlink muting can be triggered in the special slot and its preceding downlink slot.  - '2DL+special slots' meaning the downlink muting can be triggered in the special slot and its preceding 2 downlink slots.

Parameter name: RIM dynamic SRS slot offset enabled
Description: This parameter enables/disables dynamic slot offset for aperiodic SRS according to the muting status of PDCCH on special slot.

Parameter name: Enabling monitoring all UL symbols during RI state 0
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates monitor RSSI on the configured UL symbol range during RI state 0.  When this parameter is equal to FALSE, monitor RSSI on the first UL symbol during RI state 0  When this parameter is equal to TRUE, monitor RSSI on the configured UL symbol range during RI state 0

Parameter name: RIM trigger stop uplink close loop power control
Description: This parameter indicates the RIM trigger stop uplink close loop power control during remote interference.

Parameter name: Threshold of detection times of RIM RS
Description: This parameter defines the threshold of detection times of remote interference management (RIM RS), which is used to confirm the detection of RIM RS. If NRCELL.actNrRim is set to either 'RI detection only', 'RI detection and mitigation' or 'disabled' value of NRCELL/NRRIM_PROFILE.rsDetectTimesThresFa will be ignored.

This parameter indicates the RIM-RS detection window in unit of slot during one uplink to downlink switching period, when NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-1'.  The possible values are:  - 'disable RS detection' meaning RIM-RS detection is disabled.  - 'sloping based' meaning the RIM-RS detection window is based on the RI sloping impacting range.  - 'special+UL slots' meaning the RIM-RS detection window corresponds to the special slot and the first following uplink slot.  - 'special+2UL slots' meaning the RIM-RS detection window corresponds to the special slot and the first 2 following uplink slots.
Range and step: disable RS detection (0), sloping based (1), special+UL slots (2), special+2UL slots (3)

Description: This parameter indicates a configurable RIM-RS distance threshold in unit of symbol to filter the setIDs. If the distance between Victim and Aggressor deduced from RIM-RS setIDs is less than (the number of guard symbols + NRRIM_PROFILE.rsDistanceThreshold) * 10.7 Kilometers, then these detected RIM-RS setIDs will not be handled by RIM.

This parameter indicates the time domain position used for RIM-RS transmission in one uplink-downlink switching period.  The possible values are:  - 'near only' meaning the last 2 downlink symbols in the special slot are used for RIM-RS transmission.  - 'near-far config1' meaning RIM-RS is transmitted on the last 2 downlink symbols in the special slot for the first half repetitions and on the last 2 symbols in the last DL slot before the special slot for the second half repetitions.  - 'near-far config2' meaning RIM-RS is transmitted on the last 2 downlink symbols in the special slot for the first half repetitions and on the last 2 symbols in the second last DL slot before the special slot for the second half repetitions.    Note:  To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.
Range and step: near only (0), near-far config1 (1), near-far config2 (2)

Description: This parameter indicates the uplink-downlink switching period for pattern 1 (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 7.4.1.6).    Note:  To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.

This parameter indicates the uplink-downlink switching period for pattern 2 (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 7.4.1.6).    Note:  To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.

This parameter indicates power offset for the RIM-RS transmission power.    Note:  This parameter is used for RIM-RS when NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-0'.  This parameter is used for RIM-RS type 1 and RIM-RS type 2 when NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-1'.

This parameter indicates the setID which is configured on the gNB for remote interference management (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 7.4.1.6).  It is encoded in the RIM-RS signal and it is used to inform other gNBs that this is a victim gNB under remote interference.

This parameter indicates the detected RIM-RS setIDs will be displayed in the fault 7527 or not when NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-0' or 'framework-1'.  If this parameter is equal to 'enabled', then the RIM-RS setIDs will be displayed. Otherwise, the detected RIM-RS setIDs will not be displayed.    Note:  - If NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-0', RIM-RS type 1 can be detected.  - If NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-1', both RIM-RS type 1 and RIM-RS type 2 can be detected.  - If NRRIM_PROFILE.rsSetIdDisplayInFault is equal to 'enabled', it will increase fault 7527 update frequency.

This parameter indicates the RIM-RS transmission trigger scheme.  The possible values are:  - 'constantly trigger' meaning RIM-RS is configured to transmit constantly. If NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-1', both RIM-RS type 1 and RIM-RS type 2 is configured to transmit constantly.  - 'RI trigger' meaning RIM-RS type 1 is triggered only when RI is detected. If NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-1', RIM-RS type 2 is triggered only when RIM-RS type 1 is detected.  - 'RS1 constantly' meaning RIM-RS type 1 is configured to transmit constantly and RIM-RS type 2 is triggered only when RIM-RS type 1 is detected, if NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-1'.  - 'RS2 constantly' meaning RIM-RS type 2 is configured to transmit constantly and RIM-RS type 1 is triggered only when RI is detected, if NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-1'.
Range and step: constantly trigger (1), RI trigger (2), RS1 constantly (3), RS2 constantly (4)

Description: This parameter indicates the list of seeds for RIM-RS Type 1 sequences generation (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 7.4.1.6).    Note:  The order and content of the elements in this list shall be same in the network.  This parameter is used for RIM-RS when NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-0'.  This parameter is used for RIM-RS Type 1 when NRCELL.actNrRim is equal to 'framework-1'.  To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.

This parameter indicates the list of seeds for RIM-RS Type 2 sequences generation (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 7.4.1.6).    Note:  The order and content of the elements in this list shall be same in the network.  To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.

This parameter indicates a list of the starting frequency offset relative to a configured reference point (NRRIM_PROFILE.globalF0ForRs) for RIM-RS and expressed in units of resource blocks (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 7.4.1.6).    Note:  The order and content of the elements in this list shall be same in the network.  To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.

This parameter indicates a list of RIM-RS starting RB for each frequency resource assigned to RIM-RS transmission (see 3GPP TS38.211 Chapter 7.4.1.6). The number of elements in this list indicates the number of candidate frequency resources configured for RIM-RS transmission in the network.    Note: The order of the elements in this list shall be same in the network.    Note:  The order and content of the elements in this list shall be same in the network.  To make sure RIM-RS can be detected successfully, this parameter shall be configured consistently on a network.

Parameter name: Window duration for cell load average
Description: Defines window duration for cell load averaging.

Parameter name: New Radio SAS User Group instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio SAS User Group (NRSASUSERGROUP) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates the SAS user group identifier.
This parameter indicates the SAS user group type.

Parameter name: New Radio Stream Control Transmission Protocol instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the instance of the New Radio Stream Control Transmission Protocol (SCTP) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines which SCTP profile is used for the E2 interface
The parameter defines which SCTP profile is used for the NG-C interface.
This parameter defines the SCTP protocol configuration for external connections over SCTP

This parameter defines the number of unanswered heartbeat messages or data acknowledgements (within a time defined by RTO/T3-rtx and calculated internally in SCTP), used for declaring the SCTP association failure.
This parameter defines whether SCTP chunk bundling is enabled or not.
This parameter defines the interval, counted in seconds, between two SCTP heartbeat messages.

Parameter name: Maximum number of packets can be sent
Description: The parameter defines the limit the number of packets sent when the time comes for the sender to transmit new DATA chunks.

This parameter defines the maximum number of octets in an SCTP packet available for chunks. The parameter sctpMaxPayloadSize should be aligned with the Ethernet MTU in order to avoid fragmentation of SCTP packets in the IP layer. The value for the parameter needs to take into account the overhead of the IP layer (IP header, and if used, IPSec overhead) and the SCTP header.

This parameter is used for the associations whose peer IP addresses are not configured by OAM but obtained from peer side. Once the SCTP reestablishment is triggered, the gNB will retry the reestablishment only before the timer. If the SCTP reestablishment is still failed after time out, the association is removed.

This parameter defines the number of unanswered heartbeat messages or data acknowledgements (within a time defined by RTO/T3-rtx and calculated internally in SCTP), used for declaring the SCTP path failure.
This parameter is the id of SCTP profile

Parameter name: Maximum randomized wait time before starting SCTP init after shutdown
Description: This parameter defines the maximum random time the gNB needs to wait until it tries to reinitialize the SCTP association.  It defines the upper bound of the random value in seconds. The random value shall be in units of 100ms.  This prevents the peer endpoint to be overflooded by having SCTP association being reinitialized from multiple local endpoints.    Note: The actual waiting time is the sum of NRSCTP.sctpProfile.sctpWaitTimeInitSeqRetry and a random value between 0 and the value in this parameter.
This parameter specifies the initial value, in ms, for the retransmission timer T3-rtx when the DATA or heartbeat was sent and no ACK has come back. This is used for the SCTP calculation range.
This parameter specifies the maximum value for the retransmission timer T3-rtx, in ms, when the DATA or heartbeat was sent and no ACK has come back. This is used for SCTP calculation range.
This parameter specifies the minimum value, in ms, for the retransmission timer T3-rtx when the DATA or heartbeat was sent and no ACK has come back. This is used for the SCTP calculation range.

This parameter specifies the maximum time period, in ms, the SCTP receiver waits before sending a Sack. The SCTP receiver sends a SACK before the timer expires if the number of received frames achieves the value of the parameter selective acknowledge frequency (sctpSackFreq).

This parameter specifies the number of SCTP frames that the SCTP receiver is allowed to receive before it sends a SACK. The SCTP receiver shall send a Sack if the waiting time (sctpSackDelay) for receiving this number of frames expires.
The parameter defines the lifespan of state cookie of the SCTP association.

Parameter name: Wait time before starting SCTP init after shutdown
Description: This parameter defines the wait time, in seconds, that the local endpoint waits until it tries to reinitialize the SCTP association.  Case A: After having tried unsuccessfully to establish an association to a peer with a SCTP sequence.  Case B: After reception of SCTP SHUTDOWN/ABORT.    The value defines a fixed time period. In addition, the local endpoint adds an equally distributed random time period between 0 and NRSCTP.sctpProfile.sctpRandomTimeInitSeqRetry to the configured value.  This prevents the peer endpoint to be overflooded by SCTP reinitialize from multiple local endpoints.
The parameter defines which SCTP profile is used for X2-C interface.
The parameter defines which SCTP profile is used for the Xn-C interface.

Parameter name: New Radio SPID Group instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio SPID Group (NRSPIDGRP) instance within NRBTS instance.  The NRSPIDGRP instance refers to a NSA Resource Group (NRG) that is partitioned by SPID value(s).
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the New Radio PLMN (NRPLMN) instance to be used for the NRSPIDGRP instance. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1

This parameter indicates the Subscriber Profile ID (SPID) as follows:  - one SPID value or  - the value of the first SPID of a range and, in this case, the last SPID value of the range shall be configured in NRSPIDGRP.spidLast.    As per 3GPP the allowed SPID values are the following:  - Operator specific SPID values: 1...128  - Reference values: 129...256

Parameter name: Last subscriber profile ID of a range
Description: This parameter indicates the last Subscriber Profile ID (SPID) value of a range.  As per 3GPP the allowed SPID values are the following:  - Operator specific SPID values: 2...128  - Reference values: 129...256
This parameter denotes a label that can be used for a user-friendly (and user assignable) name of the NRSPIDGRP instance.

Parameter name: New Radio SPID Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio SPID Profile instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter indicates the Subscriber Profile ID (SPID) as follows:  - one SPID value or  - the value of the first SPID of a range and, in this case, the last SPID value of the range shall be configured in NRSPID_PROFILE.spidLast.    As per 3GPP the allowed SPID values are the following:  - Operator specific SPID values: 1...128  - Reference values: 129...256

This timer defines the time period for the indication of the bearer inactivity in both DL and UL directions for NSA UE in mode 3x for given SPID.  It is ignored if NRBTS.actSpidRfspInactTimers is equal to FALSE.  If this parameter is equal to 0, then this timer is off.

Parameter name: Last subscriber profile ID of a range
Description: This parameter indicates the last Subscriber Profile ID (SPID) value of a range.  As per 3GPP the allowed SPID values are the following:  - Operator specific SPID values: 2...128  - Reference values: 129...256

Range and step: sibType2 (2), sibType3 (3), sibType4 (4), sibType5 (5), sibType6 (6), sibType7 (7), sibType8 (8), sibType9 (9)

Description: This structure gathers parameters related to the relaxed measurement condition for stationary mobility.

This parameter indicates the system information target rate.  - 0: LA according to the target rate associated to the Aggregation Level selected for the SI.  - 1: Full initial bandwidth allocation with MCS0 and no SIB1 retransmission during SI window.  - 2...1023: LA according to specified target rate for SI.    In some use cases (e.g. baseband pooling), if this parameter is equal to 1, not enough available resources will be provided to encode the SIB1. It is then needed to increase the value of this parameter to a value greater than or equal to 157 (at least MCS1).

Description: This parameter indicates the Squal threshold (in dB) used by the UE on the serving cell when reselecting towards a lower priority RAT/ frequency.  Actual threshold value = field value (dB).

Parameter name: New Radio Automatic Unified Access Control Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio Automatic Unified Access Control Profile (NRUAC_AUTO_PROFILE) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.

Parameter name: Cell reserved for operator use during maximum auto UAC barring
Description: This parameter indicates whether or not the cell is reserved for operator use per PLMN when maximum automatic UAC barring is broadcasted in SIB1. The value 'reserved' overrides NRCELL.cellReservedForOperatorUse settings.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates the PUCCH high load threshold.
This parameter indicates the RRC high load threshold.
This parameter indicates the PUCCH low load threshold.
This parameter indicates the RRC low load threshold.

This parameter indicates the multiplier that is applied to the load level of pooled resources, i.e. shared by multiple cells (e.g. L1 pool, L2 pool, DU), in order to calculate the cell level usage from the pool level resource usage.  Pool level resource load is expected to have greater inertia and thus the operator may apply multiplier to the pool level load to start automatic Unified Access Control (UAC) barring earlier or later. For example, when the pool load is reported as 80% and this parameter is set to 75(%), then the derived cell level load would be assumed to be 60% and this value would be checked against UAC barring start thresholds.  Value 0 means that load level of pooled resources cannot trigger automatic UAC barring.

This parameter can be used to indicate a unique name for the New Radio Automatic Unified Access Control profile. E.g. 'Common profile for NRCELLs 1..13', 'Profile for barring access category 5', 'Overload related barring only'.  This parameter has no operation impact on the system.

This parameter enables/disables rejecting EN-DC additions and blocking PSCell changes when UAC barring is broadcasted in SIB1 for access category 7 when automatic unified access control is active.    Note: UAC barring refers to both static UAC barring and automatic UAC barring.

This parameter indicates the time to wait before a cell RRC or PUCCH load trigger becomes active if its high load condition sustains, triggering cell level automatic UAC barring tightening during high load.

Parameter name: Start UAC barring timer for overload
Description: This parameter indicates the time to wait before the overload trigger becomes active if overload condition sustains, triggering cells level maximum automatic UAC barring.

This parameter indicates the time to wait before a cell RRC or PUCCH load trigger becomes inactive if its low condition sustains, triggering cell level automatic UAC barring softening if no other triggers are active.

Parameter name: Stop UAC barring timer for overload
Description: This parameter indicates the time to wait before the overload trigger becomes inactive if no overload condition sustains, triggering cells level automatic UAC barring softening if no other triggers are active.

This parameter indicates the triggers for automatic UAC barring.  The possible triggers are overload, high cell RRC load, and high cell PUCCH load. Each trigger is tracked independently. A trigger becomes active, triggering automatic UAC barring tightening, if its high load or overload condition sustains during start UAC barring timer period. A trigger becomes inactive, triggering automatic UAC barring softening if no other triggers are active, if its low load or no overload condition sustains during stop UAC barring timer period.
This structure gathers the unified access control access category list for automatic UAC barring.
This parameter indicates the access category (3GPP 22.261).

Parameter name: Max UAC barring step only flag
Description: This parameter indicates if the list entry is applicable to the maximum automatic UAC barring step only.

Parameter name: Unified access control barring Info set index
Description: This parameter indicates the index of the entry in the field 'SIB1.uac-barringInfo.uac-BarringInfoSetList'.

Parameter name: UAC access control parameter set list
Description: This structure gathers the unified access control parameter set list for automatic UAC barring.

Parameter name: Maximum unified access control barring factor
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum value used to compute the probability that access attempt would be allowed during access barring check

Parameter name: Minimum unified access control barring factor
Description: This parameter indicates the minimum value used to compute the probability that access attempt would be allowed during access barring check.

Parameter name: Unified access control barring for access identity
Description: This parameter indicates whether the access attempt is allowed for each Access Identity (AC ID). It does not apply for the maximum automatic UAC barring step.  In the bit string  - Bit 0 (Least significant bit - right-most bit) corresponds to Access Identity 15  - Bit 1 corresponds to Access Identity 14  - Bit 2 corresponds to Access Identity 13  - Bit 3 corresponds to Access Identity 12  - Bit 4 corresponds to Access Identity 11  - Bit 5 corresponds to Access Identity 2  - Bit 6 corresponds to Access Identity 1  Value 0 for a given Bit means that the access attempt is allowed for the corresponding Access Identity.
Range and step: bits mask: AC ID 15 (0), AC ID 14 (1), AC ID 13 (2), AC ID 12 (3), AC ID 11 (4), AC ID 2 (5), AC ID 1 (6)

Parameter name: Maximum unified access control barring for access identity
Description: This parameter indicates whether the access attempt is allowed for each Access Identity (AC ID). It applies only for the maximum automatic UAC barring step.  In the bit string  - Bit 0 (Least significant bit - right-most bit) corresponds to Access Identity 15  - Bit 1 corresponds to Access Identity 14  - Bit 2 corresponds to Access Identity 13  - Bit 3 corresponds to Access Identity 12  - Bit 4 corresponds to Access Identity 11  - Bit 5 corresponds to Access Identity 2  - Bit 6 corresponds to Access Identity 1  Value 0 for a given Bit means that the access attempt is allowed for the corresponding Access Identity.
Range and step: bits mask: AC ID 15 (0), AC ID 14 (1), AC ID 13 (2), AC ID 12 (3), AC ID 11 (4), AC ID 2 (5), AC ID 1 (6)

Parameter name: Maximum unified access control barring time
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum value used to compute the minimum time before a new access attempt is to be performed after an access attempt was barred at access barring check for the same access category.

Parameter name: Minimum unified access control barring time
Description: This parameter indicates the minimum value used to compute the minimum time before a new access attempt is to be performed after an access attempt was barred at access barring check for the same access category.

This parameter enables/disables the automatic UAC barring alarm informing about automatic UAC barring being broadcasted in SIB1. If this parameter is equal to TRUE then the fault 7533 will be enabled, otherwise the fault 7533 is not reported.    Note: The resulting alarm can be suppressed.

This parameter indicates the number of automatic UAC barring steps.  The steps are evaluated evenly from minimum to maximum. Value 1 means that there is only one step, the maximum automatic UAC barring step.
This parameter indicates the interval between automatic UAC barring step evaluations, when overload trigger is not active.

Parameter name: New Radio UE Bandwidth Limitation Profile instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio UE Bandwidth Limitation Profile (NRUEBWLIM_PROFILE) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: List of the masked IMEI-SV selectors
Description: This parameter indicates the list of the masked IMEI-SV selectors.  The masked IMEI-SV is a value of the IMEI-SV where the last four digits of the SNR shall have hex digit 'F' and only decimal digits or hex digit 'F' are allowed for the other digits.  IMEI-SV (International Mobile station Equipment Identity and Software Version number) is one of the four Permanent Equipment Identifiers (PEI) of a UE. The structure of IMEI-SV is defined in 3GPP 23.003 specification.

This parameter indicates the maximum channel bandwidth supported by the limitation profile.  The UEs may not support the bandwidth section in the bottom of the cell bandwidth or the top of the cell bandwidth. The BWPs may have to be configured accordingly aligned to the top or bottom of the cell bandwidth.

Parameter name: New Radio UL MU MIMO instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio UL MU MIMO (NRULMUMIMO) instance within the same containing NRBTS/NRCELL instance.

Parameter name: Activate uplink MU MIMO UE group pairing
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates uplink MU MIMO UE group pairing.    If NRCELL.actUlMuMimo is equal to FALSE, then this parameter is ignored.
This parameter activates/deactivates UL MU MIMO tapering
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Degree separation configuration between paired UEs
Description: This structure indicates the degree separation configuration between paired UEs

Parameter name: Horizontal degree separation at stage N
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for the UL MU MIMO absolute horizontal degree separation at stage N.

Parameter name: Horizontal degree separation at stage N+1
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for the UL MU MIMO absolute horizontal degree separation at stage N+1.

Parameter name: Vertical degree separation at stage N
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for the UL MU MIMO absolute vertical degree separation at stage N.

Parameter name: Vertical degree separation at stage N+1
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for the UL MU MIMO absolute vertical degree separation at stage N+1.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO candidate UE PRB ratio
Description: This parameter is used to control whether a UE is a UL MU MIMO candidate UE according to the number of required PRBs in UL MU MIMO  More precisely, if this required number of PRBs of a UE is higher than the value in this parameter, then that UE shall be selected as a UL MU MIMO candidate UE.    If NRCELL.actUlMuMimo is equal to FALSE, then this parameter is ignored.

Parameter name: UL MU maximum number of layers per PRB
Description: This parameter indicates UL MU maximum number of layers per PRB. The number of UE paired per PRB shall vary depending on the actual number of layers of each UE

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO root UE required PRB threshold
Description: This parameter indicates UL MU MIMO root UE required PRB threshold.    If required PRB number of the root UE is less than NRULMUMIMO.ulMinPrbThreshold, NRULMUMIMO.ulMuMimoPrbThresholdAbsolute will be used to decide whether a candidate UE shall be added to a UL MU MIMO pair or not.  If required PRB number of the root UE is equal to or greater than NRULMUMIMO.ulMinPrbThreshold, NRULMUMIMO.ulMuMimoPrbThresholdRatio will be used to decide whether a candidate UE shall be added to a UL MU MIMO pair or not.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO correlation threshold between paired UEs
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for the UL MU MIMO correlation ratio of pairing N+1 over pairing N.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO correlation threshold between paired UEs 2
Description: This parameter indicates the second threshold for the UL MU MIMO correlation ratio of pairing N+1 over pairing N.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO frequency offset threshold
Description: This structure indicates the threshold of absolute frequency offset for UL MU MIMO eligible UEs.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO frequency offset threshold for 256QAM
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold of absolute frequency offset for UL MU MIMO eligible UEs with 256QAM.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO frequency offset threshold for non 256 QAM
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold of absolute frequency offset for UL MU MIMO eligible UEs with non 256QAM.

Parameter name: Switching link adaption mode for UL MU MIMO
Description: This parameter indicates the link adaption mode for UL MU MIMO.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO MCS compensate offset group
Description: This parameter indicates UL MU MIMO offset for Link adaptation MCS compensation when NRULMUMIMO.ulMuMimoLinkAdaptionSwitch is set to MCS compensation. This structure defines the MCS offset to be applied for UE(i) for a given difference X between the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at current slot and the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at previous slot.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO MCS compensate offset for layer difference five
Description: This parameter indicates UL MU MIMO MCS compensate offset to be applied for UE(i) for a difference X=5 between the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at current slot and the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at previous slot.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO MCS compensate offset for layer difference four
Description: This parameter indicates UL MU MIMO MCS compensate offset to be applied for UE(i) for a difference X=4 between the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at current slot and the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at previous slot.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO MCS compensate offset for layer difference one
Description: This parameter indicates UL MU MIMO MCS compensate offset to be applied for UE(i) for a difference X=1 between the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at current slot and the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at previous slot.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO MCS compensate offset for layer difference seven
Description: This parameter indicates UL MU MIMO MCS compensate offset to be applied for UE(i) for a difference X=7 between the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at current slot and the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at previous slot.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO MCS compensate offset for layer difference six
Description: This parameter indicates UL MU MIMO MCS compensate offset to be applied for UE(i) for a difference X=6 between the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at current slot and the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at previous slot.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO MCS compensate offset for layer difference three
Description: This parameter indicates UL MU MIMO MCS compensate offset to be applied for UE(i) for a difference X=3 between the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at current slot and the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at previous slot.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO MCS compensate offset for layer difference two
Description: This parameter indicates UL MU MIMO MCS compensate offset to be applied for UE(i) for a difference X=2 between the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at current slot and the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at previous slot.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO MCS compensate offset for layer difference zero
Description: This parameter indicates UL MU MIMO MCS compensate offset to be applied for UE(i) for a difference X=0 between the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at current slot and the number of layers of paired UEs excluding the number of layers of UE(i) at previous slot.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO PRB differential absolute threshold
Description: This parameter indicates UL MU MIMO PRB differential absolute threshold between paired UEs when required PRB number of the root UE is less than NRULMUMIMO.ulMinPrbThreshold.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO PRB differential threshold
Description: This structure indicates UL MU MIMO PRB differential threshold. Three kinds of ranges are defined for UL MU MIMO root UE required PRB number, Range One: UL MU MIMO root UE required PRB number is in range NRULMUMIMO.ulMinPrbThreshold to 100; Range Two: UL MU MIMO root UE required PRB number is in range 101 to 200; Range Three: UL MU MIMO root UE required PRB number is in range 201 to 273.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO PRB differential threshold for range one
Description: If UL MU MIMO root UE required PRBs number is in range one (NRULMUMIMO.ulMinPrbThreshold to 100), this parameter will be used to decide whether a candidate UE can be added to a UL MU MIMO pair or not.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO PRB differential threshold for range three
Description: If UL MU MIMO root UE required PRBs number is in range three (201 to 273), this parameter will be used to decide whether a candidate UE can be added to a UL MU MIMO pair or not.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO PRB differential threshold for range two
Description: If UL MU MIMO root UE required PRBs number is in range two (101 to 200), this parameter will be used to decide whether a candidate UE can be added to a UL MU MIMO pair or not.

Parameter name: SINR threshold of UL MU MIMO eligible UEs
Description: This parameter indicates SINR threshold of UL MU MIMO eligible UEs.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO spectral efficiency threshold
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold for the UL MU MIMO spectral efficiency ratio of pairing N+1 over pairing N. The spectral efficiency should not decrease below this threshold when pairing N+1 compared to pairing N users.

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO horizontal tapering value
Description: This parameter indicates the horizontal UL MU MIMO beamforming tapering value in dB or no tapering ('0dB' means no tapering).

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO vertical tapering value
Description: This parameter indicates the vertical UL MU MIMO beamforming tapering value in dB or no tapering ('0dB' means no tapering).

Parameter name: UL MU MIMO SINR diff threshold
Description: This parameter indicates the UL MU MIMO SINR difference threshold between paired UEs.  Only the UEs with the similar channel quality can be paired if the correlation between the paired UEs is high. It is a combination of correlation and SINR difference.    If NRCELL.actUlMuMimo is equal to FALSE, then this parameter is ignored.

Parameter name: New Radio X2 Link Trust instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the New Radio X2 Link Trust (NRX2LINK_TRUST) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.    Notes:  Instances of NRX2LINK_TRUST (with x2LinkTrustCtrl equals 'gnbControlled') are created/updated by the gNB, when the gNB has exchanged X2 link information during EN-DC Configuration Transfer.  For the case NRBTS.actDynamicFirewall equals 'True', the operator can create/update instances of NRX2LINK_TRUST (with x2LinkTrustCtrl equals 'oamControlled')  For the case NRBTS.actDynamicFirewall equals 'False', the operator shall not add/update NRX2LINK_TRUST.ipV4Addr or NRX2LINK_TRUST.ipV6Addr parameters (with x2LinkTrustCtrl equals 'oamControlled'). I.e. creation/update of NRX2LINK_TRUST MOC is prohibited.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter indicates the transport network IPv4 address of the LTE eNB for X2-C interface.  Format: IPv4 address parameter in dotted decimals.    Note: Mainly, this parameter is updated by the operator, only for the responding/intermediate eNB. It can be updated either by the operator when NRX2LINK_TRUST.x2LinkTrustCtrl is equal to 'oamControlled', or automatically by the system (based on information provided by ANR procedures) when NRX2LINK_TRUST.x2LinkTrustCtrl is equal to 'gnbControlled'.

This parameter indicates the transport network IPv6 address of the LTE eNB for X2-C interface.  Format: IPv6 address parameter in dotted decimals.    Note: Mainly, this parameter is updated by the operator, only for the responding/intermediate eNB. It can be updated either by the operator when NRX2LINK_TRUST.x2LinkTrustCtrl is equal to 'oamControlled', or automatically by the system (based on information provided by ANR procedures) when NRX2LINK_TRUST.x2LinkTrustCtrl is equal to 'gnbControlled'.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the New Radio PLMN instance representing the gNB X2 Control Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1
This parameter denotes a label that can be used for a user-friendly name of the usage description of the NRX2LINK_TRUST instance.
This parameter indicates if NRX2LINK_TRUST.ipV4Addr and NRX2LINK_TRUST.ipV6Addr are controlled by the OAM or the gNB

When the cell is loaded, this parameter allows to downgrade the Aggregation Level 16 (AL16) to AL8 for any grant (except for the common channels). This behavior will shrink the PDCCH cell coverage.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.

Description: This parameter indicates if it is allowed to downgrade the Aggregation Level by one level for proactive scheduling if the PDCCH resource at expected Aggregation Level is not available.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.

Parameter name: Dynamic Aggregation Level settings for high reliability DRB
Description: This structure gathers the dynamic Aggregation Level parameters of the PDCCH for high reliability DRB.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.

Parameter name: Dynamic Aggregation Level allowed in the BWP for high reliability DRB
Description: This parameter indicates the list of Aggregation Level that are allowed in the BWP for high reliability DRB.    This list shall obey the following rules:  1) The number of PDCCH candidates (PDCCH_CONFIG_DEDICATED.searchSpaceDedicated.numOfPdcchCandidatesInAL1, PDCCH_CONFIG_DEDICATED.searchSpaceDedicated.numOfPdcchCandidatesInAL16, PDCCH_CONFIG_DEDICATED.searchSpaceDedicated.numOfPdcchCandidatesInAL2, PDCCH_CONFIG_DEDICATED.searchSpaceDedicated.numOfPdcchCandidatesInAL4, PDCCH_CONFIG_DEDICATED.searchSpaceDedicated.numOfPdcchCandidatesInAL8 of the PDCCH_CONFIG_DEDICATED instance referred by a given NRCELL instance via NRCELL.cellBwpList.bwpDN) corresponding to the aggregation level used in this list is not equal to 'n0'.  2) The corresponding cqiDciCssAlHR (PDCCH.dynamicAggregationLevelHRSet.cqiDciCssAl1HR, PDCCH.dynamicAggregationLevelHRSet.cqiDciCssAl16HR, PDCCH.dynamicAggregationLevelHRSet.cqiDciCssAl2HR, PDCCH.dynamicAggregationLevelHRSet.cqiDciCssAl4HR, PDCCH.dynamicAggregationLevelHRSet.cqiDciCssAl8HR) is not equal to 0.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.

Parameter name: Outer Loop Control CQI correction up for high reliability DRB
Description: This parameter indicates the correction up applied to select the Aggregation Level when the Downlink Control Information is decoded by the UE for high reliability DRB.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.

Parameter name: CQI threshold of Downlink Control Information with AL16 in a Common Search Space for high reliability
Description: This parameter indicates the reference threshold to use AL16 for a Downlink Control Indication (DCI) with a specific size (corresponding to DCI Format sent in the common search space) for high reliability.  The gNB uses the CQI reported by the UE, mitigates it with the PDCCH BLER Loop Control, the DCI size to be sent and potential missing CQI report(s) before comparing it with the value in this parameter.  If this parameter is equal to 0, the AL16 usage for any search space defined under the PDCCH_CONFIG_DEDICATED instance is deactivated.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.

This parameter indicates the size of the REG bundle interleaver of the common CORESET.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.

Parameter name: Resource Element Group bundle size of the common CORESET
Description: This parameter indicates the size of the REG bundle used within the interleaver of the common CORESET.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.

Parameter name: Common Resource Block size of the common CORESET
Description: This parameter indicates the size in the frequency domain of the common CORESET.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.

Parameter name: Search space configuration for common PDCCH
Description: This parameter gathers the search space parameters of the common PDCCH.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.

This parameter indicates the Control resource set (CORESET) identifier associated with the common search space.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.
This parameter indicates the type of DCI format allowed in the common search space.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.
This parameter indicates the number of consecutive slots within the common search space.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH and paging parameters.
This parameter indicates the symbol(s) within the slot where the common CORESET is starting.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.
Range and step: symbol_0 (0), symbol_0_1 (1), symbol_0_2 (2), symbol_0_1_2 (3), symbol_1 (10), symbol_1_2 (12), symbol_2 (20)

Parameter name: Number of PDCCH candidates in AL16
Description: This parameter indicates the number of PDCCH candidates the UE attempts to decode a DCI with the Aggregation Level 16.    Setting of this parameter needs to follow the Configuration Guide for PDCCH parameters.    Notes:  1) This parameter can be set to values other than 0 (corresponding to n0) only if there are enough CCEs in the CORESET referred to by PDCCH_CONFIG_COMMON.coresetCommon.coresetId for this aggregation level.  2) For a common CORESET (PDCCH_CONFIG_COMMON.coresetCommon), the number of CCEs is equal to (PDCCH_CONFIG_COMMON.coresetCommon.size x PDCCH_CONFIG_COMMON.coresetCommon.duration)/6.  3) For CORESET0 (defined via NRCELL.type0CoresetConfigurationIndex), the size and duration depend on NRCELL.type0CoresetConfigurationIndex. Refer to the Table 13-1 serious in 3GPP 38.213 for details.
