Parameter name: Physical Downlink Shared Channel instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the Physical Downlink Shared Channel (PDSCH) instance within the same containing NRBTS/BWP_PROFILE instance
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates which configuration is used for PDSCH Rat0 RBG size

Parameter name: Served Access and Mobility Management Function instance identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the Served Access and Mobility Management Function (SERVEDAMF) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.  The served AMF is the AMF with which the gNB has an NG-C connection.  The SERVEDAMF with SERVEDAMF.servedAmfId equal to 1 corresponds to the main served AMF.

This parameter defines the administrative state of SERVEDAMF NG-C link.  It allows the customer to lock/unlock the NG-C link. When NG-C link is locked (SERVEDAMF.administrativeState= 'Locked') or removed (SERVEDAMF instance deleted), the SCTP association shall be gracefully terminated (SCTP SHUTDOWN). Unlocking the SERVEDAMF NG-C link means triggering the SCTP association establishment and NGAP Setup procedures.

This parameter indicates the IPv4 or IPv6 address of the AMF that the gNB shall setup an SCTP association with upon bring up.  It will be configured by the operator on the gNB-CU-CP.    Configuring this parameter when a SERVEDAMF instance is created will not provoke a gNB reset.  Updating this parameter will provoke a gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter when a SERVEDAMF instance is deleted will not provoke a gNB reset.

Parameter name: Primary IPv4/v6 address resolved from FQDN
Description: This parameter indicates the resolved transport network IPv4 or IPv6 address of the AMF primary interface in case the Fully Qualified Domain Name (FQDN) is used for the primary AMF IP address (SERVEDAMF.amfIPAddress).

This parameter indicates the IPv4 or IPv6 address of the AMF received in INIT ACK by gNB.  This is read only parameter. It is updated whenever a secondary IP address is received from the AMF in multihoming (symmetric/asymmetric) case.

This parameter indicates the time to request the Fully Qualified Domain Name (FQDN).  This parameter will be used as TTL (Time to Live) timer when the TTL of the FQDN could not be retrieved from the DNS server.
This parameter is a human readable name for the AMF instance that the gNB is connected to
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

This parameter indicates whether the AMF can be considered as a default AMF.  Several AMF(s) may be defined as default AMF(s)). A default AMF is selected by the gNB when it cannot select a suitable AMF based on Requested SNSSAI, GUAMI or 5G-S-TMSI provided by the UE.
The AMF provides its own GUAMI(s) when it connects to the gNB as part of NG Setup procedure. This parameter is used by the gNB to store the GUAMI(s).
This parameter uniquely identifies an AMF within a given AMF set.
The entire PLMN is divided into AMF regions, each of which is uniquely identified by an AMF Region ID.
This parameter uniquely identifies an AMF Set within a given AMF Region
This parameter is a human readable name for the backup AMF provided by the AMF that the gNB is connected to. The backup AMF is defined per GUAMI.
This parameter indicates the status of the GUAMI.

This parameter identifies the type of the served GUAMI (Globally Unique AMF ID) as 'native' AMF (Access and Mobility management Function) or 'mapped' from the MME's (Mobility Management Entity) GUMMEI (Globally Unique MME ID). If present, the value of this parameter is taken into account in the AMF selection procedure.

Parameter name: MCC of PLMN ID in GUAMI
Description: This parameter indicates the MCC part of the AMF's PLMN ID

Parameter name: MNC of PLMN ID in GUAMI
Description: This parameter indicates the MNC part of the AMF's PLMN ID

Parameter name: MNC Length of the Served AMF
Description: This parameter indicates the length of the MNC of the AMF's PLMN ID
This parameter indicates the local CU IPv4/v6 address
The parameter indicates whether the NG link is successfully established (Active) or not (Inactive).

Parameter name: NG Control Plane transport Network Layer identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the NG Control Plane transport network Layer    Configuring this parameter when a SERVEDAMF instance is created will not provoke a gNB reset.  Updating, adding or removing this optional parameter will provoke a gNB reset.  Removal of this parameter when a SERVEDAMF instance is deleted will not provoke a gNB reset.  Note: In SBTS, changing this parameter will require only a 5G RAT restart.
The AMF provides its own relative AMF capacity when it connects to the gNB as part of NG Setup procedure. This parameter is used by the gNB to store this relative AMF capacity.
This parameter uniquely identifies the Network Slicing (SNSSAI) instance within the same containing MRBTS/NRBTS instance.
This parameter defines the administrative state of Network Slicing.  It sets permission to use or prohibition against using the resource, imposed through the management services.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: UE DRB inactivity timer per slice for SA
Description: This timer indicates the time period for the indication of the DRB inactivity in both DL and UL directions for DRB in given slice for SA.  If this parameter is equal to 0, then this timer is off.

Parameter name: RRC Inactive UE DRB inactivity timer per slice for SA
Description: This timer defines the time period for the indication of the DRB inactivity in both DL and UL directions for DRB in given slice for RRC Inactive capable SA UEs.  If this parameter is equal to 0, then this timer is off.
This parameter indicates the list of distinguished names representing the gNB NG User Plane IP addresses.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV4 instance representing the primary IPv4 address of the gNB NG User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV4 instance representing the secondary IPv4 address of the gNB NG User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV6 instance representing the primary IPv6 address of the gNB NG User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV6 instance representing the secondary IPv6 address of the gNB NG User Plane. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1

This parameter defines the distinguished name of the NRPLMN instance(s) defining each operator for NR RAN Sharing to which the slice is assigned. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRPLMN-1  NRPLMN-1    Updating this parameter without changing the referenced instance will be performed on-line.
This parameter defines the operational state of the Network Slice instance.  It shows if the resource is physically installed and working.
This parameter indicates the slice differentiator.
This parameter indicates the slice service type which identifies the slice type.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the profile-based IP configuration for network slice (NG-U and Xg-U IP addresses). This parameter is alternatively used with SNSSAI specific addresses (SNSSAI.ngUplane, SNSSAI.xgUplane) only if NRBTS.actSliceNumExt is equal to TRUE.  If network slice specific IP addresses are not set then global addresses are used for a given slice (relevant NRBTS.ngUplane, NRBTS.xgUplane for a given PLMN).  This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration. Example: MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/NRTRS_PROFILE-1  NRTRS_PROFILE-1
This parameter denotes a label that can be used for a user-friendly name of the slice instance
This structure indicates the list of distinguished names representing the Xg User Plane IP addresses that are used for inter-gNB carrier aggregation.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV4 instance representing the primary IPv4 address of Xg User Plane for inter-gNB carrier aggregation. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV4-1

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the IPADDRESSV6 instance representing the primary IPv6 address of Xg User Plane for inter-gNB carrier aggregation. This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNLSVC or TNL.  Examples:  MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1  TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-1/IPADDRESSV6-1
This parameter uniquely identifies the Tracking Area (TRACKINGAREA) instance within the same containing MRBTS/NRBTS instance.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates the NR extended Tracking Area Code (TAC). TAC is extended from 2 octets to 3 octets.
This parameter contains a list of SNSSAIs for the TRACKINGAREA instance.

This parameter indicates the distinguished name of a SNSSAI instance representing a network slice for the TRACKINGAREA instance. It can be:  - one SNSSAI DN value or  - the value of the first SNSSAI DN of a range and, in this case, the last SNSSAI DN value of the range shall be configured in TRACKINGAREA.snssaiList.snssaiDNLast.  This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Example:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/SNSSAI-10  SNSSAI-10

Parameter name: Last SNSSAI distinguished name of a range
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the last SNSSAI of a range if a range of SNSSAI DNs is specified for the TRACKINGAREA instance.  This distinguished name can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Example:  MRBTS-1/NRBTS-1/SNSSAI-25  SNSSAI-25

This parameter uniquely identifies the Xn Link (XNLINK) instance within the same containing NRBTS instance.    A XNLINK instance can be created/updated by the gNB during XN setup or XN link resolution (via ANR) or in other XN link management procedures.

This parameter holds the C-Plane IPv4 or IPv6 address of the adjacent gNB.  Both IP address formats can be used.  Format: IPv4 address parameter in dotted decimals or IPv6 address parameter according to RFC 4291.    IPv4 address ranges:  It is not allowed to configure the address 0.0.0.0, the broadcast address 255.255.255.255 or an address within the range of multicast addresses  (224.0.0.0-239.255.255.255) or loopback addresses (127.0.0.0-127.255.255.255).    IPv6 address ranges:  It is recommended to configure only an address within the range of Unique Local Unicast addresses (FC00::/7) or Global Unicast addresses (2000::/3).
This parameter indicates if the XNLINK.cPlaneIpAddr parameter is controlled by the OAM or the remote gNB.
The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.
This parameter indicates the local CU IPv4/v6 address
The parameter provides information whether the Xn link is successfully established.

Parameter name: Xn Control Plane transport Network Layer identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies the Xn Control Plane transport network Layer
